window.IDW_ITEMS_TR=window.IDW_ITEMS_TR||{};window.IDW_ITEMS_TR["en"]={"ICON-0001":{"nm":"Footprint","on":"footprint","de":"A single earth-toned mark left on the floorboards. Someone paced for a long while, then finally took one more step forward. What a footprint records isn't the time spent lingering, but the very moment one resolved to leave."},"ICON-0002":{"nm":"Lantern","on":"lantern","de":"When flame touches the wick, the darkness quietly retreats inch by inch. With the small warmth that heats the fingertips, people of old once wrote their wishes and set them adrift. A lantern is lit not to give light, but to keep you company."},"ICON-0003":{"nm":"Ribbon","on":"ribbon","de":"With a single knot, the heart is wrapped up prettily. Easy to untie for the giving hand, yet slow to undo for the receiving one. What a ribbon binds isn't the box, but the flutter of nerves right before it's handed over."},"ICON-0004":{"nm":"Mailbox","on":"mailbox","de":"It stands at the mouth of the alley with its red mouth open wide. Even in an age when handwritten letters have grown rare, this little box waits to the very end for someone's news. A kindly vessel that shines brightest the moment it empties."},"ICON-0005":{"nm":"Private Island Mini-Map","on":"mini-map","de":"A single sheet of paper: a pocketful when folded, sea and ridgeline lying side by side when spread. To one arriving for the first time, every corner is a promise not yet opened. The moment it unfolds, even a small island becomes a wide world."},"ICON-0006":{"nm":"Microphone","on":"microphone","de":"That half-beat of catching your breath just before the first note. Knowing the eyes of the audience await your single word makes the fingertips tremble. A microphone doesn't amplify sound; it carries that tremor all the way through."},"ICON-0007":{"nm":"Clock","on":"clock","de":"The second hand never rests, but no one is rushing you. So many nights until debut, so many minutes until the stage—on the dial, waiting and excitement turn at the same speed. To read the time is to soothe the heart."},"ICON-0008":{"nm":"Notebook","on":"notebook","de":"The thing with the most blank space of all. Choreography paths, dawn resolutions, words never quite sent—they all pile up here. The moment you open it, yesterday's self gently speaks to today's self."},"ICON-0009":{"nm":"Seal","on":"seal","de":"Soaked in red ink paste and pressed down firmly, a promise is etched clear. A mark heavier than writing, plainer than words. At the end of every document, people entrusted their hearts to this little seal in place of a name."},"ICON-0010":{"nm":"Stand","on":"stand","de":"It lowers itself as far as it can to hold up something else. Down at the very bottom, bearing the weight in silence so what rests above won't waver. It never shines, yet here is the kindness that keeps things from collapsing."},"ICON-0011":{"nm":"Stamp","on":"stamp","de":"A tiny picture you'd lick a corner of and press down. The most honest price set on a heart sent far away. A single square of scenery takes the letter's hand and carries it across the sea."},"ICON-0012":{"nm":"Flag Pin","on":"pin","de":"Stick it into the map and it says, 'I made it this far.' Not a conquest but a record, and a cheer for whoever comes next. A marker that wordlessly nudges your back—seeing this flag, take just one more step."},"ICON-0013":{"nm":"Branch","on":"branch","de":"A branch that has bent once forgets how to break. Where it bowed before the wind, a knot sets in firm and hard, and true strength comes from the marks of having endured—so the old forest tells you on the breeze."},"ICON-0014":{"nm":"Button","on":"button","de":"Undone and fastened again and again, it draws the collar closed. One small circle quietly fends off the dawn chill and a sudden flush of shyness alike. Only when it pops off do you realize how big its little place was."},"ICON-0015":{"nm":"Envelope","on":"envelope","de":"The moment its mouth is sealed, it finally becomes a secret. Only the recipient knows what's tucked inside. A single layer of paper set between the heart and the world—the thinnest, kindest door of all."},"ICON-0016":{"nm":"Box","on":"box","de":"Its four corners are square, so it embraces anything generously. Memories in moving season, gifts at holidays, odds and ends the rest of the time. Inside the closed lid, it's always full of someone's 'later.'"},"ICON-0017":{"nm":"Handle","on":"handle","de":"Between a door and a person, it's the first to reach out a hand. Only when pulled once do inside and outside finally connect. Every decision to enter or leave grips this cold hand once on the way through."},"ICON-0018":{"nm":"Spoon","on":"spoon","de":"With its hollow mouth, it quietly lifts warm broth. A tool that remembers the warmth of the first spoonful Mother blew cool and offered first. At the table, it's the gentlest hand—the one that touches your lips most often."},"ICON-0019":{"nm":"Slippers","on":"slippers","de":"The moment you cross the threshold, your feet breathe a sigh first. The sound of evening, shuffling softly after shedding a day of brisk clatter. A pair set neatly at the entrance tells you, 'You're home now.'"},"ICON-0020":{"nm":"Key","on":"key","de":"You learn how to open before you learn how to lock. A small piece of metal that warms in the palm, then one day stops quietly before an unfamiliar new door. The thing that holds a departing person's warmth the longest."},"ICON-0021":{"nm":"Cup","on":"cup","de":"Tidy when empty, warmer than anything when filled. In the clear ring of two cups raised face to face and clinked, a wordless promise is held. A vessel born to shine with two rather than one."},"ICON-0022":{"nm":"Plate","on":"plate","de":"Within its round rim, a day's worth of care is fully laid out. Emptied, wiped, and refilled for a lifetime—the most often gleaming, most often forgotten of household things. The table's stage is always set upon it."},"ICON-0023":{"nm":"Light","on":"light","de":"One switch and the room's expression changes. Bright, it's the everyday; soft, it's comfort. A single point of light left on to the end for someone who came home late becomes the warmest welcome in the world."},"ICON-0024":{"nm":"Teaspoon","on":"teaspoon","de":"Stir it slowly once around the tea, and leaf and water seep into each other. An unhurried motion, a small wait until the aroma spreads. One silver hand gently slows the pace of the afternoon."},"ICON-0025":{"nm":"Bookmark","on":"bookmark","de":"A promise quietly tucked into the spot where reading stopped. The vow 'I stopped here, so I'll be sure to come back' sleeps between the pages. The story may close, but the heart is marked clearly on that one line."},"ICON-0026":{"nm":"Cushion","on":"cushion","de":"It wordlessly receives the back and knees that need somewhere to lean. Sinking deep then slowly swelling, it soaks up the day's fatigue. The thing that most generously allows the laziest of postures."},"ICON-0027":{"nm":"Frame","on":"frame","de":"A square border binds a single scene into forever. For just the moment it captured, time will not fade no matter how much passes. A kind choice less about what to hold than about what one decided to keep."},"ICON-0028":{"nm":"Map","on":"map","de":"In every crease lingers the trace of getting lost and finding the way again. Spread it open and you can walk even unvisited places with your fingertips first. Every adventure begins with the small courage of unfolding this one sheet."},"ICON-0029":{"nm":"Postcard","on":"postcard","de":"Half the back is a photo, half a blank. One gone far away sends 'I'm doing well' in a few words, with the scenery of that place alongside. The most honest sheet of paper, where news needs no envelope to feel unashamed."},"ICON-0030":{"nm":"Entry Badge","on":"entry badge","de":"The moment you hang it around your neck, you finally step into the inner world. Your name on the small card quietly grants, 'Here, this is your place.' Not a qualification to pass through, but proof that you belong somewhere."},"ICON-0031":{"nm":"Letter B","on":"letter B","de":"The letter called up most often in the middle of a word. You have to close your lips once and pop them open for the sound to come. Neither beginning nor end, but a dependable second place that keeps the beat."},"ICON-0032":{"nm":"Business Card","on":"business card","de":"Handed over with both hands, received while meeting the eyes. A person's day and pride are quietly compressed into a single sheet of paper. In the narrow margin between name and title, that day's first impression gently settles."},"ICON-0033":{"nm":"Cover","on":"cover","de":"At the very outside of the story, it meets the wind and rain first. Protecting the letters within, it wears down from its own corners. The brief flutter of anticipation just before opening always begins with this one page."},"ICON-0034":{"nm":"Textbook","on":"textbook","de":"One person's struggle is written densely with underlines and highlighter. Daunting when new, it becomes the most dependable friend once finished. The traces of coming to know what was once unknown are folded neatly on every page."},"ICON-0035":{"nm":"Dance Pass","on":"dance pass","de":"This single sheet flings open the practice room door. A mirror-filled room, the sound of stamping feet, the first eight counts ever learned. It's okay if your dancing is still clumsy—a small slip of paper gently pushes a trembling back forward."},"ICON-0036":{"nm":"Document Binder","on":"document binder","de":"Loose pages that drifted about are threaded neatly onto one spine, finally gaining an order. With order comes a story, and the thicker it grows, the kinder the proof that someone lived through that much, page by page."},"ICON-0037":{"nm":"Exam Paper","on":"exam paper","de":"Fingertips trembling for a moment above the blank lines. Scarier than a wrong answer is facing head-on the thing you don't know. When the grading is done, at every mistaken spot, a margin for growing next time quietly remains."},"ICON-0038":{"nm":"Letter A","on":"letter A","de":"The first sound that comes only when you open your mouth wide. It often stands at the head of a line, at the very start of a name. Whenever you begin anything, you start with this letter—so it's always just a little braver."},"ICON-0039":{"nm":"Letter D","on":"letter D","de":"With its softly curved back, it gently props up a word. Its round side hangs neatly at the end of someone's name. Not flashy, yet sorely missed when gone—a quiet companion among the letters."},"ICON-0040":{"nm":"Practice Sheet","on":"practice sheet","de":"The one paper in the world where mistakes are fine. It lets you write the same move, the same sentence, dozens of times over. For every crumpled page thrown away, someone was surely getting a little better."},"ICON-0041":{"nm":"Composition Sheet","on":"composition sheet","de":"Two in the morning, a single hum wakes you from sleep. The pencil hesitates over the staff because the melody is faster than the hand. In every erased-and-rewritten mark, a still-nameless song is slowly growing."},"ICON-0042":{"nm":"Access Pass","on":"access pass","de":"The moment you hang it around your neck, an ordinary corridor turns into another world. Cables snake across the dark like serpents, and beyond the stage an unheard countdown begins. The right to step in here, this single sheet speaks on your behalf."},"ICON-0043":{"nm":"Contact Sheet","on":"sheet","de":"In each little frame, a different expression stands frozen. Laughing, glancing back, eyes closed. Point to one shot at a time and the flutter of that day's shutter returns to your fingertips. Even choosing a single frame is already a record."},"ICON-0044":{"nm":"Call Sheet","on":"sheet","de":"Tomorrow, what time, where, and what. A single sheet sketches out a day's route in advance. Among the minute-by-minute cells, someone follows the order written here, walking one step at a time toward a dream."},"ICON-0045":{"nm":"Tag","on":"tag","de":"Behind the price hangs the quiet time of the one who made it. Only with that brief snip does the little paper finally become yours. What lingers at the cut is the scent of something new and a handful of excitement."},"ICON-0046":{"nm":"Portfolio","on":"portfolio","de":"Turn the cover and the path you've walked spreads out all at once. Beside a page you're proud of, a first clumsy attempt sits shyly side by side. When you first hand yourself to someone, there's no introduction more honest than this."},"ICON-0047":{"nm":"Planner","on":"planner","de":"Write today, sketch next week, and now and then black out a single box. Even when nothing goes to plan, the hand filling the boxes never stops. It's a little ritual of living the future once in advance."},"ICON-0048":{"nm":"Playlist","on":"playlist","de":"Between slow songs and quick beats, you line up music to match the day's mood like weather. Imagine someone's whole day flowing exactly in this order, and even the silence between tracks turns kind."},"ICON-0049":{"nm":"Student ID","on":"student ID","de":"A name, a photo, and a few numbers. A single card proving the days of going back and forth between classroom and practice room. In the card worn at the corners from pocket trips, a fresh-faced everyday that can't come again is etched."},"ICON-0050":{"nm":"Wristband","on":"wristband","de":"Remember tying that day's color around your wrist? The chant cried out together, the concert night soaked through side by side. Even as the band frays and the color fades, you don't untie it—you want that summer to keep living on your wrist."},"ICON-0051":{"nm":"Armband","on":"armband","de":"The moment you wrap it around your arm, the weight called responsibility quietly adds itself on. The mark of the one who stands at the head of the line and leaves their post last. A single strip of cloth makes someone grow a little taller."},"ICON-0052":{"nm":"Ring","on":"ring","de":"A single line looped round with no break. Because its start and end touch, people see in it the shape of forever. Gently join two hands and, before words, a promise remains as a form."},"ICON-0053":{"nm":"Medal","on":"medal","de":"On the little piece of metal pinned to the chest, the days endured are engraved. What shines isn't the metal but the countless nights of practice hidden behind it. What wells up before pride is, somehow, gratitude."},"ICON-0054":{"nm":"Apron","on":"apron","de":"Tie the strings at your neck and both hands are freed. A signal that you're ready to dive headlong into something—flour or paint alike. The more stains add up one by one, the deeper the care poured into that day grows."},"ICON-0055":{"nm":"Ear Hood","on":"ear hood","de":"Wrap your ears snugly and the outside sounds step back a pace. On the knife-wind walk to school, a small refuge to slip into the soft inside. Winter's warmth sometimes begins, just like this, at the tips of the ears."},"ICON-0056":{"nm":"Costume","on":"costume","de":"Before the curtain rises, a single outfit hangs on the rack, holding its breath. Choreography is folded into every seam. The moment an arm slips through, a person becomes a role, and the stage becomes the outfit's second skin."},"ICON-0057":{"nm":"Crown","on":"crown","de":"The moment it rests on the head, a bowed back straightens on its own. Its golden gleam whispers of responsibility before power. The cool weight at the brow says it all: the more radiant the place, the heavier it is."},"ICON-0058":{"nm":"Cape","on":"cape","de":"Drape it over your shoulders and the wind flutters at your back. That feeling of one swath of fabric chasing after you with every run. Less a hero's emblem than a child's heart that simply wanted to look cool."},"ICON-0059":{"nm":"Mask","on":"mask","de":"Hide the face and, oddly, you grow more honest. Like the old courtyard plays where one laughed and wept freely behind the mask. Beyond the concealed expression, the real voice usually swallowed leaks out all the louder."},"ICON-0060":{"nm":"Lipstick","on":"lipstick","de":"Twist off the cap, draw one stroke, and a small resolve sets at the lips. A last check before the mirror, a red line painted over hesitation. In that brief moment the color goes on, fear quietly slips aside."},"ICON-0061":{"nm":"Jacket","on":"jacket","de":"When the shoulder line falls just right, a person grows a little firmer. Roll the sleeves for a working mind, pop the collar for a mind set to step out. A single outfit quietly sets the day's bearing."},"ICON-0062":{"nm":"Taekwondo Belt","on":"belt","de":"Each time the color shifts up a rank, the sweat stacked beneath it changes too. The dojang morning of cinching the knot tight and bowing low. Through the fingertips tying the belt, a scattered spirit gathers again."},"ICON-0063":{"nm":"Goggles","on":"goggles","de":"Put them on and the world sharpens a tone. Beyond the round shield that blocks wind and dust alike, even the ordinary path you always walk somehow glitters like a starting line."},"ICON-0064":{"nm":"Glove","on":"glove","de":"Slip it on and the courage to grip anything firmly wells up. Fingers that flinched, afraid to drop things, finally spread wide open. The hand is what's protected, but what's truly kept safe is the challenge that comes next."},"ICON-0065":{"nm":"Mask","on":"mask","de":"Cover the lower face and the eyes speak all the more. On a bustling street, a small freedom of anonymity enjoyed behind a slight cover. So the smile left where it's all taken off spreads all the brighter."},"ICON-0066":{"nm":"Hat","on":"hat","de":"Tip the brim down a touch and both sun and stares veer off by a hand's width. Under the little roof set on your head, today at least you may walk with an easy face. The lightest transformation always begins here."},"ICON-0067":{"nm":"Shirt","on":"shirt","de":"Crisp—the freshly ironed collar smells of morning. As you fasten the buttons in order from the top, a rumpled heart grows tidy one notch at a time. A single white sheet opens the day's first sentence."},"ICON-0068":{"nm":"Scarf","on":"scarf","de":"Wrap it once around the neck and the wind's passage is blocked. While the ends sway gently at the shoulder, the cold can no longer reach inside. One swath set somewhere between style and warmth."},"ICON-0069":{"nm":"Gloves","on":"gloves","de":"Wrapped snug to the fingertips, even cold things hold no fear. Winter's small luxury, as hands you once blew warm grow quietly cozy. One glove slipped off and handed over can warm another's hand too."},"ICON-0070":{"nm":"Dog Tags","on":"tags","de":"Two thin plates face each other quietly. Three syllables of a name and a few numbers—that's what keeps someone remembered to the end. Cold metal, yet somehow it resembles the warmest promise."},"ICON-0071":{"nm":"Grip Ring","on":"ring","de":"Slip a finger through and the worry of dropping it slides away. A small reassurance, enough to hold and wave even with one hand. When you stretch your arm far to leave one photo behind, it quietly supports your palm."},"ICON-0072":{"nm":"Flower Crown","on":"flower crown","de":"Set it on your head and an armful of spring follows. Flowers picked from the field and woven into a ring softly circle the brow. Above the bright smile in the photo, a faint scent of grass lingers long."},"ICON-0073":{"nm":"Eye Mask","on":"eye mask","de":"Cover the eyes and light and noise recede all at once. Unable to see, all you hear is your own breath. Switch off the world for a while and step into the inner stillness, and a small door closes gently behind you."},"ICON-0074":{"nm":"Muffler","on":"muffler","de":"One loop, two loops—each turn around the neck softens winter a little. Somewhere among the yarn, perhaps, is mixed a heart someone knitted in. Bury yourself up to the nose and the world feels that much cozier."},"ICON-0075":{"nm":"Half-Mask","on":"half-mask","de":"Covering only half the face, the night of the masquerade begins. The bared lips smile, the hidden eyes hold a secret. That narrow gap of almost-knowing-who sets the midnight air aflutter."},"ICON-0076":{"nm":"Beret","on":"beret","de":"Tilt it on at an angle and an ordinary day quietly gains some flair. One round, flat swath of cloth gently dresses your shoulders in an artist's air. Even the brief moment of choosing the angle before the mirror is a delight."},"ICON-0077":{"nm":"Choker","on":"choker","de":"Fit it snug around the neck and the gaze naturally gathers upward. A single thin band changes the whole mood. Small but distinct, like a clasp that fills today's confidence."},"ICON-0078":{"nm":"Parka","on":"parka","de":"Zip it all the way up and even the blizzard steps back a pace. Push your hands deep into the thick inside, and all the world's clamor falls quiet. A small house that stays warm to the end even amid the rough wind."},"ICON-0079":{"nm":"Pants","on":"pants","de":"Slide your feet through, fasten the waist, and at last you're ready to head out. With every step, the fabric moves smoothly along its grain. Somewhere between comfort and neatness, the day begins."},"ICON-0080":{"nm":"Piercing","on":"piercing","de":"Even adding one small point takes a little courage. A single gleam of metal sets a clear period at an ordinary ear. Very small, yet a light reflecting a today that has surely changed."},"ICON-0081":{"nm":"Waveform","on":"waveform","de":"To an engineer, a song isn't heard—it's seen. From the ridgeline rising and falling on the screen, they read where the breath trembled that day. A voice once invisible lies down like a mountain range, unfolding the terrain of a single track."},"ICON-0082":{"nm":"Tuner","on":"tuner","de":"Just before the show, you stroke the six strings one by one, settling stray notes back in place. Off by even half a degree and the audience catches it like ghosts. Tuning it so precisely no one could tell—that's a kindness toward the stage."},"ICON-0083":{"nm":"Strap","on":"strap","de":"Loop it once around the wrist and the fear of dropping things unravels. On stage, the most frightening thing is losing your grip on something, so this one small strap finally puts the heart at ease."},"ICON-0084":{"nm":"Cymbal","on":"cymbal","de":"In the single instant of one clash, a clear period is set on the song's final sentence. The golden disc knows how to ring shortest and leave the longest echo. An ending should close as brightly as this."},"ICON-0085":{"nm":"Guitar","on":"guitar","de":"When fingers slide over the six strings, a small room turns wholly into a stage. Someone's first melody, the muttered words of a sleepless dawn—within this round wooden body, they first drew breath."},"ICON-0086":{"nm":"Sound Cloud","on":"sound cloud","de":"On one side of the sky, notes bunch up like cotton and drift along. They say when the wind sweeps by once, melodies fall instead of raindrops—so the island's children go out to meet it without even an umbrella."},"ICON-0087":{"nm":"Step","on":"step","de":"Stage blocking is arithmetic solved with the toes. A step here, a half-beat there—mistakes are fine, so take it slow. The cells trodden hundreds of times and etched into the body gather to complete the map of a single song."},"ICON-0088":{"nm":"Amp","on":"amp","de":"A box that turns a whisper into a roar. Even so, before nudging the volume up one notch, the hand always pauses. That a more accurate sound, not a louder one, reaches the very back row—this box knows."},"ICON-0089":{"nm":"Note Fluff","on":"note fluff","de":"When the round-headed notes gather into a fluffy ball, it's as soft as a pillow. Lie down and rest your head on it, and a barely-there lullaby comes flowing out—the island's kindest little rumor."},"ICON-0090":{"nm":"Cassette","on":"cassette","de":"Press rewind and—creak—the tape winds slowly back to that summer's first song. Within the little box where a whole era is wound, time you can never touch again sleeps fully intact."},"ICON-0091":{"nm":"Tuning Fork","on":"tuning fork","de":"Tap the two-pronged metal lightly and a single reference note is born in midair. To this small tremor, every instrument quietly bows its head in tune. The start of anything comes from a vibration this faint."},"ICON-0092":{"nm":"Waveform Chip","on":"chip","de":"A fragment of sound is gently trapped inside a chip the size of a fingernail. An ad-lib never meant to be recorded, the laughter of someone you thought was gone—within this, they still live and breathe, warm as ever."},"ICON-0093":{"nm":"LP","on":"LP","de":"When the needle takes its first step along the groove, a faint crackling breath is heard before anything else. Loving even that little noise, some can never, to the very end, let this black disc go."},"ICON-0094":{"nm":"Pocket","on":"pocket","de":"What you treasure most, you always keep closest to the chest. One palm-sized cloth pouch becomes a hand-warmer one day, a talisman another, and yet another day a keeper of secrets."},"ICON-0095":{"nm":"Bandage","on":"bandage","de":"On nights when practice runs long, a small medal sticks to each heel. A strip applied to swallow the word 'it hurts'—a quiet promise no one knows, to dance again tomorrow no matter what."},"ICON-0096":{"nm":"Pillow","on":"pillow","de":"The place where you finally set down a whole day's stage is, after all, this one soft square. Lay your head down gently and the applause that lingered at your ears slowly fades, and at last night falls over the island too."},"ICON-0097":{"nm":"Bell","on":"bell","de":"With one short jingle, someone pushes the door open and steps in. A signal that a guest has come, a greeting that the day has opened. One small piece of metal rings out nothing but welcome all day long."},"ICON-0098":{"nm":"Case","on":"case","de":"The more precious a thing, the more you build it a sturdy house of its own. The hands that open and close it grow careful each time, because what's held inside isn't merely an object but a heart you can't bear to lose."},"ICON-0099":{"nm":"Brush","on":"brush","de":"Sweep along the grain down to the last bristle, and dust clinging in the corners quietly retreats. Thanks to a touch that doesn't shy even from unseen places, the room greets a new morning every day."},"ICON-0100":{"nm":"Sketch","on":"sketch","de":"Lines before completion don't bother hiding their hesitation. In every mark erased and drawn again, what it wished to become remains without a lie. The clumsier the start, the most honest it is."},"ICON-0101":{"nm":"Doll","on":"doll","de":"There are beings that comfort you simply by being held in your arms without a word. The cotton-stuffed friend that trembled beside your pillow on nights your hands shook backstage—everyone keeps one like it somewhere in the heart."},"ICON-0102":{"nm":"Bell","on":"bell","de":"The mountain temple bell rings once and crosses a whole valley. It's the metal's heart, longing to reach far and farther still, crying out long—so the sound settles slowly in the listener's chest."},"ICON-0103":{"nm":"Umbrella","on":"umbrella","de":"Share one and one shoulder is bound to get wet. Under the umbrella tilted ever so slightly, the soaked shoulder is the clearest proof of kindness. The short walk of sharing one roof lingers long in the heart."},"ICON-0104":{"nm":"Mat","on":"mat","de":"Spread one over the bare floor and that spot becomes a practice room at once. A place that wordlessly catches you when you roll and fall—countless moves first broke themselves in on the body upon this."},"ICON-0105":{"nm":"Jingle Bell","on":"jingle bell","de":"Shake it gently and a clear, tinkling sound rolls out in your hand. The small, round joy that children of old once dangled from the hems of their rainbow-striped jackets and ran about the yard with awakens again upon your palm."},"ICON-0106":{"nm":"Toy Snake","on":"toy snake","de":"Its long, dangling shape mischievously gives people a fright. Scared, fleeing, then bursting into giggles in the end—a prank like this, too, is one branch of kindness toward each other."},"ICON-0107":{"nm":"Toy","on":"toy","de":"Everyone has one box they can't quite bring themselves to throw away, even grown up. Inside it, the laughter of the brightest days is still wound tight like an unsprung spring."},"ICON-0108":{"nm":"Dining Table","on":"dining table","de":"Unfold its folded legs and anywhere soon becomes the family's place. The sound of spoons clinking as everyone gathers round—that humble ensemble rings the warmest of all the day's songs."},"ICON-0109":{"nm":"Soap","on":"soap","de":"Growing smaller bit by bit in the hand, it quietly makes someone clean. Wearing itself down to wash another—only long after the bubbles have all faded does that quiet heart finally show."},"ICON-0110":{"nm":"Comb","on":"comb","de":"Just as it loosens tangled hair strand by strand, a rumpled day gradually grows tidy too. One brief touch offered before the mirror quietly mends, beyond the hair, even the bearing of the heart."},"ICON-0111":{"nm":"Birdcage","on":"birdcage","de":"There's a bird that sings without leaving, even with the door flung wide open. A heart that stays not because it's caged but because it wishes to remain—that subtle difference, this cage senses before anyone."},"ICON-0112":{"nm":"Hand Warmer","on":"hand warmer","de":"In the winter wait line outside the venue, a small warmth in the pocket gently thaws stiffened fingers. A palm-sized kindness someone shook warm in advance, thinking of you trembling in the cold."},"ICON-0113":{"nm":"Handkerchief","on":"handkerchief","de":"A single cloth that takes in tears and sweat without complaint. The small embroidery in its corner lingers there prettily, like a last farewell left by one who departed first, saying don't forget."},"ICON-0114":{"nm":"Spray","on":"spray","de":"One spritz and the texture of the air changes in an instant. The mist drifting over the stage, the plant by the morning window—within these fine droplets, for a moment they become another world and glisten."},"ICON-0115":{"nm":"Scent Strip","on":"scent strip","de":"Choosing a scent is, somehow, very much like choosing a memory. One faint thread of fragrance touched to the tip of a slender paper gently brings a season you thought forgotten back to the nose."},"ICON-0116":{"nm":"Table","on":"table","de":"In every worn grain of wood, the number of meals shared together is quietly etched. The boisterous dinners, the late nights faced alone—this square took them all in without a word and grew lustrous."},"ICON-0117":{"nm":"Skein of Thread","on":"skein","de":"Pull one end gently and it unwinds smoothly; one stitch and it joins again. Mending what's broken always begins quietly, just like this, from a single thin strand of thread."},"ICON-0118":{"nm":"Raincoat","on":"raincoat","de":"Even on pouring days, it's this one garment that gets you out the door at last. Only those who know the joy of splashing through the rain refuse to use the rain as an excuse to stay home."},"ICON-0119":{"nm":"Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Cinch the mouth into a circle and what's inside is at last kept safe. In one small, well-worn sack, coins, a memory of some day, and words never quite said all sway together."},"ICON-0120":{"nm":"Bookshelf","on":"bookshelf","de":"Run your finger slowly along the spines lined up and the seasons you've passed through can be felt at your fingertips. Why you can't bear to throw out a finished book is that the you of back then still lives there."},"ICON-0121":{"nm":"Stack of Books","on":"stack of books","de":"Books read lie down on their sides; books unread stack up on top. Even as the promise to read them all someday sways a little near the ceiling, you love even that swaying, so today you add one more volume."},"ICON-0122":{"nm":"Running Wheel","on":"running wheel","de":"It may feel like staying in place no matter how hard you run, but the little feet are learning the rhythm of the toes first. The yesterdays that never stopped gather and, one day, shine bright on a real road."},"ICON-0123":{"nm":"Cover","on":"cover","de":"So dust won't settle, so it won't fade in the sun—even the act of covering takes the care of one's fingertips. The more you treasure something, the more kindly it's protected in places unseen."},"ICON-0124":{"nm":"Yarn","on":"yarn","de":"A single strand that unwound, tumbling, from Grandmother's lap. It may look tangled, but find the end and tug gently and it follows without fail. That's how winter nights grew long, one stitch at a time."},"ICON-0125":{"nm":"Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Lip balm, a hair tie, a neatly folded letter—small as it looks, a day's worth of heart is held inside. With the sound of the zipper closing, all the precious odds and ends are kept safe at once."},"ICON-0126":{"nm":"Armrest","on":"armrest","de":"An afternoon dozed off mid-read, an evening paced through during a call. In the spot that deepens with use the longer you sit, every rest the elbow remembers pools quietly by a hand's width."},"ICON-0127":{"nm":"Pack","on":"pack","de":"Until it's torn open, it belongs to no one yet. A sealed packet brims with unopened anticipation, so the fingertips gripping its corner tremble lightly. That's the thrill of opening."},"ICON-0128":{"nm":"Wrapping Paper","on":"wrapping paper","de":"A heart that arrives one step ahead of the gift. While you fold the corners to align and tie it with a ribbon, the smiling face of the one who'll receive it unfolds brightly in advance within your hands."},"ICON-0129":{"nm":"Game Pad","on":"pad","de":"Buttons the thumbs remember before the head does. Lost, but just one more round—and that one round ends up keeping you up all night. The weight that fits the hand just right gently lifts tonight's adventure."},"ICON-0130":{"nm":"Signal","on":"signal","de":"Red means stop for a while, green means you may go now. With one simple promise, countless roads flow without tangling. That even waiting has its turn, the blinking light kindly tells you."},"ICON-0131":{"nm":"Arrow","on":"arrow","de":"The kindest shape to one who has lost the way. When it's hard to know where to go, one direction someone drew first makes the halted footsteps firm again."},"ICON-0132":{"nm":"Coordinates","on":"coordinates","de":"With just two numbers, you can pinpoint anywhere in the world. The spot where you agreed to meet, the sandy beach where treasure was buried. So a promise won't lose its way, one small dot holds it fast to the end."},"ICON-0133":{"nm":"Tile","on":"tile","de":"Alone, it's just one square piece. The moment they lie side by side, shoulders touching, they become a floor and a wall. Small things gather to make a place where someone can set foot at ease."},"ICON-0134":{"nm":"Hourglass","on":"hourglass","de":"As the upper chamber empties, the lower one slowly fills. Watching the sand trickle softly down, we believe time is flowing. Flip it and it's the start again—that's the sand's kindly little lie."},"ICON-0135":{"nm":"Ball","on":"ball","de":"Throw it and it comes back; kick it and it rolls away. Being round, never knowing where it'll bounce, is its greatest charm. In the middle of the playground, laughter always began roundly from this little sphere."},"ICON-0136":{"nm":"Switch","on":"switch","de":"Click—on with one press, off with one press. That small sound made stepping into a dark room divides the scattered start and end of a day into one clear line."},"ICON-0137":{"nm":"Question Mark","on":"question mark","de":"Not knowing the answer is nothing to be ashamed of. It's the welcome proof that curiosity is still alive. When this little hook taps at your mind, learning finally takes its first step."},"ICON-0138":{"nm":"Match","on":"match","de":"A single stick that strikes its own body to pass on fire. It burns briefly and vanishes quietly, but in that brief moment a candle is lit and a hearth is warmed. A small offering becomes the first button of warmth."},"ICON-0139":{"nm":"Step Stool","on":"stool","de":"Step up onto it and your hand reaches even the shelf you couldn't touch. The work of stretching someone's height for a moment. Here is a kind place that crouches low to gently lift us higher."},"ICON-0140":{"nm":"Watch","on":"watch","de":"The first thing strapped to the wrist the day you resolved to exercise. A small coach that counts your heartbeats and steps taps to tell you that today you walked a little more than yesterday."},"ICON-0141":{"nm":"Alarm","on":"alarm","de":"The most faithful friend, resented every morning. Thanks to it fighting the lure of five more minutes under the covers in your place each time, neither promises nor dreams run late. That spitefully ringing sound is, in truth, a cheer."},"ICON-0142":{"nm":"Core","on":"core","de":"The innermost part that remains to the end once everything outside is peeled away. An apple's seed, the heart's true feeling—whatever it is, the very center holds the firmest thing. The one point that remains in the end, even when shaken."},"ICON-0143":{"nm":"Pen","on":"pen","de":"The smudge that brushed onto the side of your hand before the ink dried. Write well or not, the first stroke drawn before a white page always takes a little courage. It's the bridge by which thought crosses to the fingertips."},"ICON-0144":{"nm":"Brush","on":"brush","de":"When it holds ink and passes over the hanji, even a single hesitant tremor remains fully intact. Get greedy and rush to write, and it's exposed at once. The brush is the first to know the honesty dwelling in the fingertips."},"ICON-0145":{"nm":"Speech Bubble","on":"speech bubble","de":"The spot that surfaces round above the head before the words quite make it out of the mouth. The one thing you want to say is held here. When it's empty, it's in the midst of choosing what to fill it with."},"ICON-0146":{"nm":"Checkbox","on":"checkbox","de":"Draw two strokes in the empty square and the heart grows that much lighter. A small medal you award yourself for a finished task. At the end of the day, looking at the filled boxes, we reassure ourselves we lived well today too."},"ICON-0147":{"nm":"Tablet","on":"tablet","de":"Pictures spread and letters flow wherever the fingers touch. Set it gently on your lap and a whole world lights up bright. Light it is, but the possibility held within is by no means thin."},"ICON-0148":{"nm":"Remote","on":"remote","de":"It has a natural-born talent for hiding in the cracks of the sofa. The power to change channels always belongs to whoever holds it. The smallest, most endearing squabble among family plays out over this one hand's span."},"ICON-0149":{"nm":"Counterweight","on":"counterweight","de":"A weight that lowered itself to the very bottom to hold steady what sways. However the top lurches, if the bottom is heavy it won't fall in the end. Balance always holds firm in places unseen."},"ICON-0150":{"nm":"Puzzle","on":"puzzle","de":"The night you groped even under the sofa for the last missing piece. That soundless thrill of the moment it slots in just right. When scattered things find their places, the picture is at last complete."},"ICON-0151":{"nm":"Ruler","on":"ruler","de":"Measuring length is also a way of keeping a promise. So that one span is the same for everyone, the marks line up honestly. A single straight line can even smooth out a crooked heart."},"ICON-0152":{"nm":"Canvas","on":"canvas","de":"An empty white surface is the most frightening, and the most thrilling. Until the first dot is placed, it could become anything. Emptiness isn't an ending, but another name for a beginning."},"ICON-0153":{"nm":"Cube","on":"cube","de":"More than a few people have stayed up all night trying to align all six faces. The dogged fingertips that twist it again and again. The moment the jumbled colors find their places, a tiny universe falls neatly into order."},"ICON-0154":{"nm":"Handheld Console","on":"handheld console","de":"A little screen that cousins would huddle over during school breaks. A world of adventure that fits snugly in your palm. Just one bar of the power-on melody, and that whole summer comes flooding back."},"ICON-0155":{"nm":"Grip","on":"grip","de":"The sensation of it nestling into your hand when you clench tight quietly hands you confidence. So you won't slip, so you won't lose your hold. In the most crucial moment, it's the link that binds hand and tool into one solid whole."},"ICON-0156":{"nm":"Fountain Pen","on":"fountain pen","de":"While you write with refilled ink, even your handwriting grows a little tidier. Steadying your heart to the scratch of the nib, it quietly resembles the care of slowly beginning the first line of a handwritten letter."},"ICON-0157":{"nm":"Palette","on":"board","de":"Blue beside red, green over yellow. On this little board where colors lie neatly side by side, a picture finally gains its expression. Every adventure of mixing and layering takes its first step right here."},"ICON-0158":{"nm":"Set","on":"set","de":"Each piece may be plain, but lined up together they become a single story. That reassurance when nothing is missing and all is in place. Gathering scattered things into one spot carries a small joy of completion."},"ICON-0159":{"nm":"Shuttlecock","on":"shuttlecock","de":"The soft rush of wind the feathers make as it soars up off the racket. It seems too light to go far, but hit with intent, it flies straight to the far end of the court. Lightness, too, is a fine kind of power."},"ICON-0160":{"nm":"Antenna","on":"antenna","de":"It stands quietly toward the sky, trying to catch invisible signals. The patience to draw in even distant voices in the end. On days when reception is poor, just tilt the angle a touch and it grows clear again."},"ICON-0161":{"nm":"Stethoscope","on":"stethoscope","de":"The round tip cold against the chest, and a breath held for a moment. Gather your ear to a single small drumbeat, and the oldest rhythm of being alive travels to your fingertips. A tool where listening comes first."},"ICON-0162":{"nm":"Chess Pawn","on":"chess pawn","de":"A little pawn that walked only one slow square at a time. Yet the moment it reaches the far rank, it can become anything. The old chessboard quietly watches over that single move that flips the whole game with a clumsy step."},"ICON-0163":{"nm":"Controller","on":"controller","de":"Remember the nights you roamed the universe with two thumbs? The worn grip you flung down in defeat, then sheepishly picked back up. The longest, warmest conversation you shared wordlessly with someone across the screen."},"ICON-0164":{"nm":"Console","on":"console","de":"Turn on the power and a little boot chime rings out like a greeting. The square box you switched on and off under the covers all break long; childhood's first adventure always began in the glow of this screen."},"ICON-0165":{"nm":"Timeline","on":"timeline","de":"The left end is the beginning, the right end a day yet to come. Drag a single dot anywhere in between, and a moment you thought forgotten unfolds again. A place where time is laid down in a single line."},"ICON-0166":{"nm":"Prism","on":"prism","de":"To think that light, so seemingly clear, held seven colors all along. The secret that unravels into a rainbow the moment it passes through a sliver of glass. The tidier a thing looks, the more colors hide within."},"ICON-0167":{"nm":"Golf Tee","on":"golf tee","de":"One little stand to set the ball gently upon. The farther you want to send something, the more you first need something to brace it firmly. This tiny peg on the grass props up the first step."},"ICON-0168":{"nm":"Knitting Needle","on":"needle","de":"One stitch, then another. Drop a single one and you have to unravel it all and go back to the start. The scarf that lengthened slowly on your lap through a winter, the place where fingertip patience was knit into warmth."},"ICON-0169":{"nm":"Line","on":"line","de":"A single bar that leaked from your lips in a hum before the lyrics were laid on top. Within that hazy tune, still bare of words, lies a song's most honest first face."},"ICON-0170":{"nm":"Radar","on":"radar","de":"It fires a signal into the darkness it cannot see, and quietly waits for a single returning dot. The patience of round green light that believes something is there, even when nothing is visible."},"ICON-0171":{"nm":"Rhythm Pad","on":"pad","de":"Tap, tap, give it a light knock and light and sound spring up at once. A place that makes your hands memorize the beat before your head does. The smallest, kindest stage, spread across your palm."},"ICON-0172":{"nm":"Paint","on":"paint","de":"Old artisans ground stone and earth to obtain color. Indigo from grass, red from soil. In this single drop squeezed out at your fingertips now, too, flows the ancient care of carefully transferring nature into a vessel."},"ICON-0173":{"nm":"Line","on":"line","de":"The thing born only the moment you resolve to connect dot to dot. Short or long, curved or straight, it's the simplest trace left by the wish to go somewhere. The start of every picture."},"ICON-0174":{"nm":"Shutter","on":"shutter","de":"Click, that one brief flash of darkness holds a scene forever. Even an expression you'd almost let slip in the blink of an eye, it slices off a little light and hardens it into a memory. A small blade."},"ICON-0175":{"nm":"Safety Rope","on":"rope","de":"The rope that's tied down firmly one step ahead of the person climbing high. It holds in your place the heart that frets over falling, guarding your side unseen, a cord of promise. It's always at your back."},"ICON-0176":{"nm":"Padlock","on":"padlock","de":"The heavy iron padlock fastened on the storehouse. It wasn't to imprison something, but a wish to leave the precious safe at ease. Even the hand that locked it held care, the sturdy comfort of an old home."},"ICON-0177":{"nm":"Scale","on":"scale","de":"When one side grows heavier, the other lightens on its own. In that moment of wavering over what to place and how much, a person learns fairness. Two arms that teach balance by tipping back and forth."},"ICON-0178":{"nm":"Splitter","on":"splitter","de":"Even what's firmly joined will, if you follow the grain, finally split apart. A little tool to divide anything in two and peer inside. Curious fingertips that long to take apart what's been put together and look again."},"ICON-0179":{"nm":"Counter","on":"counter","de":"One, two, three. A little friend that silently counts the numbers in place of your fingers. A gentle companion of tallying that turns the heart fretting over a missed count, click by click, into ease."},"ICON-0180":{"nm":"Cursor","on":"cursor","de":"A little arrow that blinks somewhere on the screen, waiting for the next command. Even while you hesitate, it never leaves its spot, the tip of light quietly beckoning, let's begin now."},"ICON-0181":{"nm":"Hold","on":"hold","de":"The one point you grab last, just before the strength drains from your fingertips. There are moments you endure on a single will not to let go, the little knob on the wall quietly tells you so."},"ICON-0182":{"nm":"Pebble","on":"pebble","de":"A stone that rolled long in the brook, giving up all its corners. To grow round is another name for the time worn away. Hold it gently in your palm, and you can feel the patience of the flowing river."},"ICON-0183":{"nm":"Crest","on":"crest","de":"Old houses carved beasts and stars onto a single banner to make themselves known. A picture that conveyed the heart before words could. An ancient mark, carefully compressing one person's pride into a small frame."},"ICON-0184":{"nm":"Shield","on":"shield","de":"To stand in the way was always for the sake of the one behind your back. Taking incoming arrows in their stead, it guarded someone's ordinary day, a heavy yet tender wall."},"ICON-0185":{"nm":"Revival","on":"revival","de":"There's a heart that goes out and lights up again. Only after falling once do you finally learn how to rise again. A second breath that quietly wells up in the very place you thought was the end."},"ICON-0186":{"nm":"Bow","on":"bow","de":"The hand that means to send far first draws the string back all the way. To let go, you must first hold that close, the taut, bent bow quietly tells you so without a word."},"ICON-0187":{"nm":"Heart","on":"heart","de":"The words 'I like you' keep shrinking into a little shape. This form sketched slyly at the tip of a lightstick, or between two touching fingers. The most common and honest shorthand of the heart."},"ICON-0188":{"nm":"Cloud","on":"cloud","de":"Drifting slowly toward the wind, it becomes a different face each time. A rabbit, then cotton, holding nothing for long and letting all things pass, the sky's lightest heart."},"ICON-0189":{"nm":"Maze","on":"maze","de":"A place where you learn how to turn back from a dead-end wall. Even while you wander, your steps grow little by little toward the exit. You have to lose your way once to get your bearings."},"ICON-0190":{"nm":"Tooth","on":"tooth","de":"There was a custom of tossing a lost tooth onto the roof. A small prayer for the new tooth to grow in straight. A childhood's tender promise that you must lose something once, growing up, to gain something stronger."},"ICON-0191":{"nm":"Planet","on":"planet","de":"A round body that orbits a star without ever once leaving its path. It looks lonely, yet its gravity always keeps something turning beside it. Quietly holding its place becomes a world in itself."},"ICON-0192":{"nm":"Star","on":"star","de":"On nights when they lost their way, people looked up at the brightest point. A light too far to reach, yet clear enough to point the direction. A promise made all the firmer for being far away."},"ICON-0193":{"nm":"Silhouette","on":"silhouette","de":"Stand with your back to the light and only your outline remains. A single black shape, its name and expression erased. An unfilled space that makes you imagine all the more for being empty."},"ICON-0194":{"nm":"Ear","on":"ear","de":"To sing well, you must first listen well. Both rhythm and heart, in the end, begin with listening. A small door, opened round, where all the sounds of the world arrive first and linger."},"ICON-0195":{"nm":"Fallen Leaf","on":"fallen leaf","de":"There are leaves that shine most beautifully in the very moment they fall. The lightness of burning a season's green all away into red and gently letting go. Autumn shows us that an ending, too, can be this lovely."},"ICON-0196":{"nm":"Moon","on":"moon","de":"There were nights of clasping hands and making wishes under the round harvest light. A face that, waxing and waning over and over, was never once the same. A lantern that changes yet always lights that same spot."},"ICON-0197":{"nm":"Heart","on":"heart","de":"Even on stage, the most honest thing is this heartbeat in the end. It doesn't stop though it trembles, and pounds all the harder when it swells. A small red drum that throbs in your stead the cheers words could never finish."},"ICON-0198":{"nm":"Shadow","on":"shadow","de":"A companion that never falls away as long as there is light. Darkening the brighter it gets and fading the dimmer it grows, another me that has followed me longest. One person standing by my side even on lonely days."},"ICON-0199":{"nm":"Tail","on":"tail","de":"It wags on its own when happy, and curls under when afraid. The honest little tip that, though the mouth stays clamped shut, can never quite hide the heart. The inner feeling the body leaks out first."},"ICON-0200":{"nm":"Tail Tie","on":"tie","de":"A little cord tied at the end to finish off, like a ribbon. The heart that knotted it once more, tight, so it wouldn't come loose. A tender fastening that gathers and soothes together the things apt to scatter."},"ICON-0201":{"nm":"Pupil","on":"pupil","de":"You can choose your words, but you can't hide the look in your eyes. The spot where a caught heart leaks out first, inside that black circle. Even if you swallow the words 'I like you,' your pupils are already trembling toward you."},"ICON-0202":{"nm":"Horseshoe","on":"horseshoe","de":"A piece of iron that grew sturdier the more its tip wore down from running long roads. Hung upside down over the door, they said the luck coming and going would pool inside it. It quietly upholds someone's safe return home."},"ICON-0203":{"nm":"Crest Stone","on":"crest stone","de":"Even as wind and rain grind the letters faint, trace it with your fingertips and the carved grain comes vividly alive. The weight of some heart that did not want to be forgotten. So a stone holds a single name for long."},"ICON-0204":{"nm":"Webbed Foot","on":"webbed foot","de":"With one thin membrane joining the toes, it learns to push the water. A little oar nature slips into the hand of a poor swimmer. A tender design that, slow though it is, gets you across the river in the end."},"ICON-0205":{"nm":"Glitter","on":"glitter","de":"Everyone grumbles that it follows you around for days once it gets on your hands, yet on a festival day they reach for these grains of light first. Scatter a handful of stardust and even plain paper sparkles, and today turns special."},"ICON-0206":{"nm":"Claw","on":"claw","de":"The beasts of the forest scratch the soil with their claws to leave their trail. Not a threat but a trace, a quiet signature that they passed through here. A sharp tip can become, to someone, a tender signpost."},"ICON-0207":{"nm":"Lightning","on":"lightning","de":"In the instant the sky briefly spreads open its palm-lines, the light arrives ahead of the thunder. As if telling you to catch one breath before the great sound reaches you. Fear and awe are always born together from the same flash."},"ICON-0208":{"nm":"Talisman","on":"talisman","de":"A single line of wishing pressed firmly in ink onto red paper. They believed that, tucked under the pillow, it would steer bad dreams aside. A heart that prays for someone's safety is this warm even with a single thin sheet of paper."},"ICON-0209":{"nm":"Brush Wing","on":"brush wing","de":"There are moments when a brush tip becomes a wing. That lightness of gliding across the paper as you draw a single stroke. That writing is itself a kind of flying, the old hand grinding ink must have dimly known."},"ICON-0210":{"nm":"Bone","on":"bone","de":"The thing left only after all the flesh has crumbled away. The white frame that endured to the very last because it was hardest. A quiet piece of proof that remembers, at least, the form, though time carries all else off."},"ICON-0211":{"nm":"Nose","on":"nose","de":"Smell is the fastest shortcut to memory. The scent of oil in a holiday kitchen, the cold air of a morning after first snow, the tip of the nose catches it first and the heart follows a beat behind."},"ICON-0212":{"nm":"Toast","on":"toast","de":"A busy morning's quickest meal to grab in hand. Bite into the golden-toasted surface and a day's worth of courage crunches apart. Things that need not be grand but are filling get a person back on their feet."},"ICON-0213":{"nm":"Cookie","on":"cookie","de":"The one who waited longest before the oven earns the first bite. The warmth of a just-baked edge, a brief sweetness. The ones baked while thinking of someone are, strangely, all the sweeter."},"ICON-0214":{"nm":"Snack","on":"snack","de":"On an afternoon when practice runs long, a little bag pulled from deep in your backpack. Split it in half and the heartiness, oddly, doubles. A handful of tenderness that fills the heart before the hunger."},"ICON-0215":{"nm":"Capsule","on":"capsule","de":"No one can know until they twist it open. What's inside the round shell is always the same flutter of the heart. The most honest thrill in the world, where you buy and sell a small chance."},"ICON-0216":{"nm":"Doorknob","on":"knob","de":"The spot the countless hands opening and closing a door touch first. The home's first greeting, starting cold and warming in your palm. The more the handling builds up, the more that room slowly becomes someone's home."},"ICON-0217":{"nm":"Walk","on":"walk","de":"Even walking with no destination has its reason. A time to unravel tangled thoughts one strand at a time into your footsteps. Come back from a loop and the answer's the same, yet the heart alone is a good deal lighter."},"ICON-0218":{"nm":"Scooter","on":"scooter","de":"Two wheels cutting through narrow alleys. It isn't fast, but it takes the wind full on the body. There are days you just want to ride out refreshingly today, fine if you can't go far."},"ICON-0219":{"nm":"Safety Bar","on":"safety bar","de":"Before you board, a single crossbar that lowers firmly in front of your chest. A reassuring promise that endures the scary stretch with you to the end. It tells you, coldly and without a word, that it's okay to hold on tight."},"ICON-0220":{"nm":"Stairs","on":"stairs","de":"Climb one step at a time and before you know it the view has changed. The soles of your feet learn first that no height is reached in a single bound. The going up and down itself was, to someone, a day's worth of steps."},"ICON-0221":{"nm":"Terrarium","on":"terrarium","de":"It isn't trapping a forest in glass, but tending a whole world with care. A palm-sized universe where moss spreads and water droplets form. The longer you peer in, the more your heart slowly stains green."},"ICON-0222":{"nm":"Podium","on":"podium","de":"Climb to a spot a span higher and the view you see changes. A place where fear and pride meet at the same height. Depending on who stands there, that single tier becomes a different stage each time."},"ICON-0223":{"nm":"Airplane","on":"airplane","de":"The moment clouds spread beneath your feet, you finally come to miss the place you left. It isn't growing distant but the world growing wider. Even a dream raised on a small island crosses the sky like this."},"ICON-0224":{"nm":"Skateboard","on":"skateboard","de":"A thing you can only ride once you've first learned how to fall. Every time your knees get scraped, balance is carved a little more into your body. Honest four wheels that roll farther for every good fall taken."},"ICON-0225":{"nm":"Passport","on":"book","de":"Turn the cover and it's full of blank pages. Each stamp to be filled becomes proof of a life lived. A little book that holds not how far you've been but the possibility of going anywhere at all."},"ICON-0226":{"nm":"Hand-drawn Map","on":"map","de":"It has no exact distance or scale, but being a path drawn by hand there's no fear of getting lost. Paper where alleys and shop names tangle warmly. Guidance with heart in it is always warmer than the road itself."},"ICON-0227":{"nm":"Blocking Chart","on":"blocking chart","de":"Paper where each footstep on stage is drawn out as a line. Where to stop, where to turn, the arrows promise in advance. Even a dance that looks free actually begins from this single sheet."},"ICON-0228":{"nm":"Seating Guide","on":"seating guide","de":"In an unfamiliar space, the first thing you grope to find is your own seat. The one spot you reach at last, following row and number. A single sheet of paper settles thousands of flutters neatly, each into its place."},"ICON-0229":{"nm":"Alley Guide Card","on":"card","de":"Guidance someone wrote out by hand for those apt to lose their way in maze-like alleys. The kind handwriting telling you to turn at which corner. A neighborhood's warmth, written clearly into a single little card."},"ICON-0230":{"nm":"Security Pass","on":"card","de":"Only when you hang this card around your neck does the door to the inner world finally open. A small permission that grants entry, and a quiet token that you belong here. Only those who know the time it took to earn it know its weight."},"ICON-0231":{"nm":"Day Wristband","on":"band","de":"Fasten it once on your wrist and you're a member of that day until you peel it off. A single paper band divides inside from out and becomes a mark that you spent the same day together. Even after it's snapped off, the trace lingers a good while."},"ICON-0232":{"nm":"Guest Label","on":"label","de":"With one little name tag stuck to your chest, an unfamiliar place becomes your spot. When the word 'welcome' is carried over on a single sheet of paper, even a first-timer finally becomes a guest."},"ICON-0233":{"nm":"Poster Tube","on":"poster tube","de":"A sturdy cylinder that keeps a rolled-up poster safe without a single crease. Because the more precious the picture, the more it must be sent out straight. You can't see inside, but it sets off holding someone's care."},"ICON-0234":{"nm":"Folder Cover","on":"cover","de":"The first page wrapping a thick bundle of documents. The face your hand touches before the contents. When the cover is tidy, even the mindset within looks tidy, the tender start of a small formality."},"ICON-0235":{"nm":"Souvenir Postcard","on":"card","de":"You write a greeting on a scrap of distant scenery and send it off. By the time it arrives, the heart you sent has aged a little too, growing dearer. The slow warmth of a handwritten letter that a message on a screen can never quite chase down."},"ICON-0236":{"nm":"Gift Tag","on":"tag","de":"A little slip of paper tied onto a gift. With just the two words 'for you,' the wrapping is already complete. The shortest letter in the world, writing down not what you give but who you thought of."},"ICON-0237":{"nm":"Packaging Sticker Roll","on":"packaging sticker roll","de":"Every time you tear off a piece to use, the finish comes out a good deal neater. A little knot that tidily holds the end trying to come loose. The last move of carefully wrapped packaging always comes from this coiled band."},"ICON-0238":{"nm":"Clear Letter Sleeve","on":"clear letter sleeve","de":"A clear layer that wraps a handwritten letter so it won't fade with the years. The letters stay visible, but the smudge of handling won't reach. An unseen film quietly guards someone's cherishing heart."},"ICON-0239":{"nm":"Color Wax Seal","on":"color wax seal","de":"The last dot that closes an envelope, the more vivid its color, the less the heart leaks out. A promise that no hand touched it until it's torn open. Even a secret needs a knot this pretty."},"ICON-0240":{"nm":"Message Tag Book","on":"message tag book","de":"A little book binding short notes together. Each page is a word to hand to someone. Gather up, one by one, the words you couldn't quite say, and someday the courage to surely deliver them grows."},"ICON-0241":{"nm":"Folding Sign","on":"board","de":"Unfold and it says 'this way,' fold it and 'that's all for today.' Legs spread at the mouth of an alley, it stands a whole day for someone apt to lose their way. The evening it folds is, to me, the tenderest rest."},"ICON-0242":{"nm":"Mail Band","on":"band","de":"Wrap a heap of postcards around the waist and the greetings about to scatter finally become one bundle of heart. A single light band ties up neatly the words bound for distant places, and quietly sees off the back that's setting out."},"ICON-0243":{"nm":"Thank-You Note Bundle","on":"thank-you note bundle","de":"Because the word 'thank you' keeps slipping off the tongue, you write it on a palm-sized paper and quietly bind it up. The thicker the bundle grows, the thicker, side by side, grows the heart you owe to someone."},"ICON-0244":{"nm":"Cheer Chant Sample Sheet","on":"cheer chant sample sheet","de":"A sample sheet that reads 'shout it like this.' A cheer with no voice yet laid on it holds only a quiet flutter, like a blank score waiting for the first beat."},"ICON-0245":{"nm":"Pre-recording Request Memo","on":"memo","de":"A memo asking to book a pre-recording always lingers in the 5 a.m. slot. The little paper takes down in silence, as if it understands all of it, the heart that cuts its sleep short to save a spot."},"ICON-0246":{"nm":"Fansign Order Ticket","on":"ticket","de":"A single sheet that sets which turn you'll give your greeting. Lining up isn't waiting for your turn, it's briefly borrowing an order because you can't put a number on how much you care."},"ICON-0247":{"nm":"Queue Number Wristband","on":"queue number wristband","de":"A single number decides the order you'll line up in today. Front of the line or back, the people wearing this small, light band on their wrists are, in the end, comrades of one heart gathered to see the same stage."},"ICON-0248":{"nm":"Photocard Sorting Chart","on":"chart","de":"Same face, yet all different, you note them divided cell by cell. The fuller the chart, the tidier the heart, and the one cell left empty sets your chest aflutter with the thrill you want to fill today."},"ICON-0249":{"nm":"Album Checklist","on":"album checklist","de":"Version, photocard, even whether it's sealed, a list of affection written down in numbers. Picturing in advance the pride of the day it's all filled, today too you draw a neat little circle on one line."},"ICON-0250":{"nm":"Cheer Guide Note","on":"cheer guide note","de":"Hand shapes, the beat to shout on, even the spots to catch your breath. So that even a first-timer quickly blends into one voice, the little note becomes a kind guide passing from hand to hand."},"ICON-0251":{"nm":"Private Memo Pad","on":"pad","de":"You pick out only the sentences you'll show no one and write them here. That the never-opened page is the most honest, this pad guards in silence, its cover kept closed."},"ICON-0252":{"nm":"Anniversary Stamp Sheet","on":"anniversary stamp sheet","de":"Press it, and another day turns special. With one little stamp tapped onto an ordinary date, 'today' slyly enters its name onto the roster of days worth remembering."},"ICON-0253":{"nm":"Clipboard Cover","on":"cover","de":"Though the wind blows, though the rain drives in, it guards the clipped paper to the very end. I, who have taken it upon myself to be the board's armor, am the reliable bodyguard of the written letters."},"ICON-0254":{"nm":"File Index","on":"file index","de":"So you won't lose your way among thick documents, it pokes out a little tongue and signals 'here.' One colorful tab governs a hundred pages at a single glance."},"ICON-0255":{"nm":"Category Tab Label","on":"label","de":"This in this slot, that in that slot. My job is to tidy the world's clutter neatly, one line at a time. The moment a label goes on, the jumbled things finally find their places."},"ICON-0256":{"nm":"Mini Approval Board","on":"board","de":"The moment you tap a stamp down, somehow you feel like you've become a real grown-up. Small in size but with a spry authority, one approval stamp and the piled-up work wraps up briskly."},"ICON-0257":{"nm":"Clear Document Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Transparent through and through, with nothing to hide. Holding important paper, it wraps it in its own clear body lest it get soaked by rain or crumpled, and carries it all the way to the meeting place."},"ICON-0258":{"nm":"Attendance Band","on":"band","de":"Came, and another cell is filled. When each day's footprints pile up in a row along the band, an unseen diligence finally becomes a pattern visible at a glance."},"ICON-0259":{"nm":"Mistake Notebook","on":"mistake notebook","de":"Writing down what you got wrong isn't gathering up shame. So you won't trip twice in the same spot, it's rewriting yesterday's mistake into today's guide."},"ICON-0260":{"nm":"Schedule Stamp Board","on":"board","de":"Stamp once onto a blank planner and a 'plan' is born. The magic of a day decided with one snap of the wrist, that magic is actually just another name for the diligence of preparing well ahead."},"ICON-0261":{"nm":"Spine Label","on":"label","de":"The name tag of books standing with their spines turned toward the shelf. The short letters written on a narrow spine call out at once, with a beckon, the very book you were hunting among hundreds."},"ICON-0262":{"nm":"Photo Protector","on":"photo protector","de":"No bare hands allowed. Telling you not to leave even a single fingerprint, it gently lays its body over a precious shot. A cherishing heart lasts long and long through such careful handling."},"ICON-0263":{"nm":"Film Index Sheet","on":"film index sheet","de":"Put a number on each strip of film and the scattered moments regain their turn in the story. A little guide that tends the memories written in light so they won't get muddled."},"ICON-0264":{"nm":"Photo Sleeve Bag","on":"photo sleeve bag","de":"A clear home where square bits of happiness are enshrined one by one. With no worry of crushed corners, the most cherished face shines tidily in here through all four seasons."},"ICON-0265":{"nm":"Mini Photo Envelope","on":"envelope","de":"Before the warmth of a freshly printed photo has even cooled, a little envelope opens both arms to receive it. A single shot that goes in through the palm-sized mouth becomes, before you know it, a treasure in someone's bag."},"ICON-0266":{"nm":"Lenticular Cover","on":"cover","de":"My mission is to guard, without a single scratch, a finicky photo whose expression changes when you tilt it. Protecting every different face at every angle, I mustn't be anything short of diligent myself."},"ICON-0267":{"nm":"Cut Sorting Label","on":"label","de":"Of four cuts, the label points out for you which is the best. This small task of sorting the well-shot from the funny, side by side, is the secret to enjoying a memory twice."},"ICON-0268":{"nm":"Photo Strip Band","on":"band","de":"It wraps neatly around a narrow, long four-cut memory. Hugging that day's scattering laughter firmly into one bundle, it carries it safely to the depths of your bag."},"ICON-0269":{"nm":"Photo Corner Sticker","on":"photo corner sticker","de":"When you put a photo in an album, a little hand that gently holds its four corners. So it won't fall off without slathering on glue, delicacy begins, like this, from the corners."},"ICON-0270":{"nm":"Print Correction Chart","on":"chart","de":"A touch warmer, a shade less bright. A single chart where you fiddle with the numbers until the color you like comes out quietly turns a common shot into a work of art."},"ICON-0271":{"nm":"Receipt Clip","on":"clip","de":"It bites tidily onto the crumpled receipts and won't let go. With its little mouth it keeps a day's spending firmly in hand, so the end-of-month reckoning comes a good deal lighter."},"ICON-0272":{"nm":"Reservation Confirmation Slip","on":"slip","de":"At the single line 'your reservation is confirmed,' the heart slowly settles. One sheet of paper becomes proof of a promise, keeping the thrill stored up, bit by bit, until the awaited day."},"ICON-0273":{"nm":"Return Receipt","on":"return receipt","de":"A small but honorable proof that you've put what you borrowed back in its place. The moment this paper is in your hand, one debt that weighed on a corner of your heart is wiped lightly away."},"ICON-0274":{"nm":"Claim Ticket Holder","on":"holder","de":"So you won't lose the ticket to claim what you left behind, I'll hold onto it tight for you. The whereabouts of one little slip can sway the end of someone's day, after all."},"ICON-0275":{"nm":"Rental Tag Tail","on":"rental tag tail","de":"A little tag that flutters on each rented item. Follow this tail and at once it shows who took what, so even the mystery of a lost item is quickly solved."},"ICON-0276":{"nm":"Inspection Checklist","on":"inspection checklist","de":"You trace it over, one by one, with your eyes to see nothing's missing. When the check marks fill up in a row, an unseen thoroughness finally earns the name of trust."},"ICON-0277":{"nm":"Settlement Memo Envelope","on":"envelope","de":"Write the money that came in and went out on the envelope, and the cluttered numbers calmly fall into line. The end of the reckoning is always this little memo, quietly setting the final period."},"ICON-0278":{"nm":"Shipping Label","on":"shipping label","de":"It sets out with where it's going and who it'll reach written on its own body. The moment this label goes on, the box becomes a traveler with a destination and departs with a thrill."},"ICON-0279":{"nm":"Receipt Confirmation Band","on":"band","de":"It binds the words 'received well' into a single band and sends them back. The relief of the one who received and the ease of the one who sent quietly clasp hands on this little cord."},"ICON-0280":{"nm":"Word Card Ring","on":"ring","de":"The words that would get lost if they scattered as loose sheets, one little ring strings together and holds fast. Flip through them again and again, and the once-unfamiliar words become, before you know it, friends well-worn on the tongue."},"ICON-0281":{"nm":"Pronunciation Memo Band","on":"band","de":"You hang a little tag at the spot where your tongue keeps slipping. Even an unfamiliar sound that lost its way in your mouth finds its proper pronunciation, before you know it, by following this memo. The first page of taming a clumsy sound, little by little."},"ICON-0282":{"nm":"Translation Note Box","on":"translation note box","de":"Little bridges that cross between word and word lie folded neatly, one to a slot. Write down a hard-chosen phrase and slip it over, and even a heart that wouldn't get through grows closer with a single note between."},"ICON-0283":{"nm":"Quote Scrap Sheet","on":"quote scrap sheet","de":"A sentence that lands right on the heart only lasts if you copy it by hand. Stick a line clipped from the corner of a book in front of your desk, and those letters quietly prop up a day that was sinking."},"ICON-0284":{"nm":"Note Index","on":"note index","de":"Colorful little flags tucked in so you won't lose your way within a thick book. You can wander farther only when you know the spot to come back to, the tabs poking out quietly tell you so from between the pages."},"ICON-0285":{"nm":"Memorization Check Chip","on":"chip","de":"A single mark tapped down beside what you've memorized. Being a little anchor that holds onto things that drop by your head for a moment and try to vanish, each blacked-in cell quietly carries last night's spent effort."},"ICON-0286":{"nm":"Quiz Envelope Pack","on":"quiz envelope pack","de":"Until you tear the envelope open, no one knows what'll come out. Those few seconds of fiddling at the sealed spot with your fingertips, a bundle of thrill where a single question lies neatly folded, the flutter sealed in along with it."},"ICON-0287":{"nm":"Grammar Tab Notebook","on":"notebook","de":"Rules aren't memorized with the head but learned by hand. From the colored tab of the page you open most often to the softening, wearing notebook, that worn corner becomes the growth ring of the time you endured."},"ICON-0288":{"nm":"Speaking Practice Chart","on":"chart","de":"A single chart for the person to whom opening their mouth is the hardest thing in the world. Trace down the cells with your finger and even the first words that trembled in your throat find, before you know it, their own voice. Even courage has its turns."},"ICON-0289":{"nm":"Color Rough Sheet","on":"color rough sheet","de":"The colors lie roughly before they're finished, catching their breath. Not the right answer but still a possibility, on this less-than-polished sheet sways more tomorrow than anything else."},"ICON-0290":{"nm":"Mood Board Piece","on":"mood board piece","de":"Gather and paste in one place the impressions scattered piece by piece, and a mood that wouldn't quite come to hand dimly reveals its outline. A sense still without a name, the pieces lean on one another and quietly point to it."},"ICON-0291":{"nm":"Pattern Sample Book","on":"pattern sample book","de":"The lattice of a wrapping cloth and the weave of a window grille are neatly arranged, page by page, in one volume. Where the same pattern repeats to the very end dwells not laziness but a promise, the firm heart of holding to one grain."},"ICON-0292":{"nm":"Costume Swatch Sheet","on":"costume swatch sheet","de":"Though it's the same light, the texture and shadow settle differently on each scrap of cloth. Before choosing a stage costume, the night spent wavering, brushing it over and over with your fingertips, is preserved whole in a single little swatch."},"ICON-0293":{"nm":"Logo Don't-Use Guide Sheet","on":"logo don't-use guide sheet","de":"Paper that first writes out, clearly, the things you must not do. Within an outline struck through with a red X, freedom grows all the clearer, so a new path opens, of all places, where you thought it was a dead end."},"ICON-0294":{"nm":"Color Reference Chip","on":"chip","de":"A sample scrap made on its own because color simply can't be explained in words. It traps onto a small palm a certain instant when the sunset glowed reddest, so you can hand the next person, exactly, 'this very color.'"},"ICON-0295":{"nm":"Layout Rough Card","on":"card","de":"A first sketch lightly drawn of what to put where. Deciding the placement is itself deciding the heart, so among the clumsily scattered lines, the balance of the whole slowly opens its eyes."},"ICON-0296":{"nm":"Material Memo Board","on":"board","de":"Wood, earth, stone, the names of touchable things are written densely. A secret known only to those who begin by reading the grain with their hands first, what you build with already decides, half over, what it'll become."},"ICON-0297":{"nm":"Pattern Tracing Paper","on":"pattern tracing paper","de":"You lay thin paper over the underdrawing and quietly trace along the lines. While you briefly borrow another's path, your hand learns that path, and among the lines you copied, a line all your own slyly grows, before you know it."},"ICON-0298":{"nm":"Entry Path Band","on":"band","de":"People file in in a line, following the band stuck long along the floor. A single line that quietly guides so the excited steps won't tangle, an unseen tender hand that props up the thrill so it won't collapse."},"ICON-0299":{"nm":"Event Guide Picket","on":"event guide picket","de":"A sign standing in place of the words 'this way.' A small kindness set up at each junction so no one wanders, taking the hand of a first-timer's unfamiliar day and quietly walking it along."},"ICON-0300":{"nm":"Booth Number Label","on":"label","de":"A single number assigned to each booth clearly sets the owner of that one space. A small number, but being the promise that 'this is your spot,' it gives you a place to return to at an unfamiliar event."},"ICON-0301":{"nm":"Staff Agreement Form","on":"staff agreement form","de":"A single signature left where hearts agreed to work together. It's just one thin sheet of paper, yet it carries the weight of choosing to trust one another, and every helping hand at the event begins right here."},"ICON-0302":{"nm":"Trial Ticket Bundle","on":"trial ticket bundle","de":"A plump stack of trial passes bundled to sit snugly in one hand. The more you hand out, the less it shrinks and the more 'first times' it keeps giving to others, a bundle of goodwill that grows warmer the more you touch it."},"ICON-0303":{"nm":"Queue Marker Sheet","on":"queue marker sheet","de":"Please wait from here, the floor murmurs softly. When the hearts keeping their turn gather together, even a long line becomes a scene of its own, and one small marker turns impatience into calm."},"ICON-0304":{"nm":"On-Site Pickup Tag","on":"on-site pickup tag","de":"A small tag that catches lightly where you collect what you pre-ordered. The instant it's in your hand, that gentle relief slips from your shoulders, a knot where a long-waited heart finally takes shape."},"ICON-0305":{"nm":"Mystery Box Ticket","on":"ticket","de":"The joy of picking one without knowing what's inside. Shake it and your heart races first at the rattle within, and that brief moment just before opening becomes the most swollen-with-hope time of the day."},"ICON-0306":{"nm":"Trade-Complete Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"A small round stamp announcing the swap went off without a hitch. It's the smooth period left between the hands that gave and received, and once it's pressed on, the deal finally rounds out warmly."},"ICON-0307":{"nm":"Record Seal Band","on":"band","de":"A precious box wrapped once around with a band and quietly sealed. A request not to open it carelessly, and the quietest courtesy of treasuring what's inside that much, all held in a single band."},"ICON-0308":{"nm":"Secret Memo Capsule","on":"secret memo capsule","de":"A word you wanted to say, gently shut away inside a small canister. Seal it tight like burying a feeling you couldn't send, and a tiny vault in your palm keeps watch over time until the day you open it again."},"ICON-0309":{"nm":"Little Scrap Card","on":"card","de":"A clipped-and-pasted piece carries the faint mood of that day. Lighter than a diary and more handmade than a photo, a palm-sized sheet holds tight to a day that would otherwise slip through your fingers."},"ICON-0310":{"nm":"First Visit Record Sheet","on":"first visit record sheet","de":"The flutter of the day you first set foot on this island remains in a short line. Right before strangeness turned to fondness, the paper holds that purest first feeling in your place and keeps it long."},"ICON-0311":{"nm":"Memory Sorting Chart","on":"chart","de":"A chart where memories are sorted by grain and branch, written down one by one. Pile every memory into one drawer and even your most cherished day gets buried, so the more precious it is, the more gently it gets its own place."},"ICON-0312":{"nm":"Speech Bubble Memo Chip","on":"chip","de":"The words you wanted to say swell round like a balloon and float on the paper. Even a line you couldn't speak aloud quietly finds courage inside that round border, a small warm passage for a heart to slip out through."},"ICON-0313":{"nm":"Date Holder","on":"holder","de":"A little stand that sets today's date upright to face you. Pick a single day from those streaming past and seat it front and center, and even an ordinary date gains a warmth worth celebrating."},"ICON-0314":{"nm":"Collection Number Tag","on":"collection number tag","de":"A unique number assigned to each thing you cherish. To collect is to vow to call that one thing the only one of its kind in the world, so the number on the small tag bears the clear weight of the heart."},"ICON-0315":{"nm":"Archive Slip","on":"archive slip","de":"A thin inner sleeve you slide each long-kept thing into, one at a time. Setting something just one layer apart from light and time, to love something is, in the end, to keep it well."},"ICON-0316":{"nm":"Photocard Toploader Strap","on":"strap","de":"A slender strap that lets you hang a toploader around your neck. It's a way of fandom, walking through the day with your bias near your chest, and on this one thin line a whole day of tender company is tied."},"ICON-0317":{"nm":"Photocard Stand Pin","on":"pin","de":"With one little pin, a photocard stands upright on the desk. Lying flat it's just a sheet of paper, but stood up it becomes a face you meet eye to eye, quietly making a spot where your gaze can linger."},"ICON-0318":{"nm":"Holo Photocard Film","on":"holo photocard film","de":"A single thin film where rainbows stream down with every angle. A layer that catches a bit of light dresses an ordinary card in starshine, a small magic where a different expression sparkles awake each time you flick your wrist."},"ICON-0319":{"nm":"Photocard Protector Cap","on":"protector cap","de":"One press to a corner and it feels like the heart you cherish gets creased too. A clear armor that firmly hugs one precious sheet, this kind of care always comes with truly cherishing something."},"ICON-0320":{"nm":"Photocard Sorting Tray","on":"tray","de":"A shallow tray that lays dozens of photocards down neatly, grain by grain. Scattered, they're just a pile, but laid out in rows they become a collection, and the order of affection is etched with each tidying hand."},"ICON-0321":{"nm":"Photocard Trade Envelope","on":"envelope","de":"When you slip a photocard into an envelope to hand over, your fingertips hesitate for a moment. It isn't sending it away but asking it to become someone's bias. The instant you fold the flap, a small bond quietly changes hands."},"ICON-0322":{"nm":"Photocard Deco Pen","on":"pen","de":"What fills the blank space isn't writing but feeling. Wherever the nib passes, tiny hearts and stars sprout, and a plain sheet of paper wakes as a one-of-a-kind cheer. Decorating is just another name for confession."},"ICON-0323":{"nm":"Photocard Clip Ring","on":"ring","de":"Click, the sound of a clip biting shut. With that one small latch, cards that nearly scattered gather into a single row. Even jostled all day in a bag, not a single corner gets hurt. Sturdiness is this quiet."},"ICON-0324":{"nm":"Photocard Carry Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A habit has settled into the hand that zips it open and shut. Through a sudden shower, through a crush of crowds, only the inside stays dry. Keeping what you cherish most in the deepest place, that is the tender labor of carrying."},"ICON-0325":{"nm":"Fan Meeting Wristband Strap","on":"strap","de":"One fan long remembered how warm the staff's hands were tying the strap on their wrist. A single knot marks belonging here today. Wound twice so it won't come loose, that strap holds a day's worth of excitement in place."},"ICON-0326":{"nm":"Entry Wristband","on":"wristband","de":"The very moment you pass the entrance, inside and outside finally divide clearly. Worn all day it soon grows familiar against your skin, and by the time you take it off a thin mark remains, like proof of the place you stayed in."},"ICON-0327":{"nm":"Talk Corner Chip","on":"chip","de":"When the talk corner opens, a chip rolls along. Who speaks first, which question gets drawn, that small chance changes the whole mood. A single chip's whim is more lovable than any written script."},"ICON-0328":{"nm":"Signing Event Queue Ticket","on":"ticket","de":"You take your place in line clutching a numbered slip. Number 142. While you count the 141 ahead, your heart counts its turn first. The wait is long, but thanks to this one slip even that time becomes part of the thrill."},"ICON-0329":{"nm":"High-Touch Glove","on":"high-touch glove","de":"In the instant palms meet, the glove takes in that brief warmth in your place. A hand warmed all day for a 0.5-second touch. Even wearing cloth can't block that flutter, and everyone only realizes it then."},"ICON-0330":{"nm":"Commemorative Photo Pin","on":"pin","de":"One click and today is preserved just as it is. Inside the frame held fast by a pin, even an awkward smile becomes the most missed scene someday. A record is the most tender greed for holding onto a moment."},"ICON-0331":{"nm":"Seat Ribbon Tag","on":"seat ribbon tag","de":"A small ribbon hung on a seat back sways though there's no breeze. A marker someone tied, a trace that a person was here. Even in the empty seat after the show, only the ribbon seems to still remember the beat."},"ICON-0332":{"nm":"Gift Inspection Label","on":"label","de":"A label goes on each and every gift. Was it sent, was it checked, is anything missing. Even receiving someone's heart takes housekeeping, so this small sticker links care to care without a single gap."},"ICON-0333":{"nm":"Memorial Slip","on":"memorial slip","de":"A sheet of paper written to keep and revisit for a long time. The weather that day, the seat number, even the title of the last song. Memory fades, but only this slip won't. Even storing a memory needs a small form."},"ICON-0334":{"nm":"Cheer Towel Loop","on":"loop","de":"Slip a loop on the end of a towel and it won't slide off your shoulder. Between wiping sweat, whirling it overhead, and slinging it back around your neck, one small link keeps the gestures of cheering unbroken."},"ICON-0335":{"nm":"Slogan Clip","on":"clip","de":"Clips firmly grip both ends of a slogan. So even with both arms raised high, the letters don't fold or flutter away. Here is the most steadfast supporting actor, straightening the message out of sight."},"ICON-0336":{"nm":"Silencing Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"The zipper slides slowly, without a sound. A silence designed so not one noise escapes where quiet is promised. Consideration is sometimes making yourself unheard, this pouch quietly says."},"ICON-0337":{"nm":"Applause Rhythm Chip","on":"chip","de":"Each time palms meet, the chip counts the beat. Clap, clap, clap, and scattered claps suddenly gather into one rhythm. The magic of thousands of applauses becoming a single breath, a small chip quietly lends a hand to it."},"ICON-0338":{"nm":"Cheer Guide Folder","on":"cheer guide folder","de":"Open it and the cheer guide is written step by step. Which color to raise on which line, when to add a shout. Even a first-timer becomes one of the family with this one folder. A small guide for sharing a promise."},"ICON-0339":{"nm":"Seat Fan Strap","on":"strap","de":"Tie a strap to a hand fan's handle and it won't fall even if it slips from your grip. On a hot day, when both hands break free for cheering after fanning, it dangles from your wrist. One strap cools heat and excitement at once."},"ICON-0340":{"nm":"Glitter Film Piece","on":"glitter film piece","de":"Catch the light and each piece shatters it at a different angle. Rest it on your palm and a tiny rainbow shimmers, the colors coming alive with every shake. Maybe sparkling is just sharing light split into tiny pieces."},"ICON-0341":{"nm":"Mini Banner Pole","on":"pole","de":"Extend the small pole and the cloth pulls taut in the wind. Raise it high with both hands and the letters reach past the seats, fold it and it tucks into a corner of your bag. The size of a heart isn't measured by the length of a pole."},"ICON-0342":{"nm":"Cheer Sticker Pack","on":"cheer sticker pack","de":"Each sticker is stamped with a cheering phrase. On a planner, on a phone, on the corner of a laptop, wherever you stick them, daily life gets tinted with cheer. A fond heart leaves its traces everywhere like this."},"ICON-0343":{"nm":"Album Protector Cover","on":"cover","de":"The hand wrapping an album in a cover is careful. So the corners don't wear, so it doesn't fade in the sun. Music is heard by the ears, but this one sheet is remembered by the hands. An armor of the heart that keeps what you cherish near for long."},"ICON-0344":{"nm":"Disc Sleeve Ring","on":"ring","de":"Slip discs into sleeves and bind them with a ring and they become an album book. The rustle each time you turn a page is lovely. Gathering scattered music neatly into hand, that is a collector's quiet happiness."},"ICON-0345":{"nm":"Goods Storage Divider","on":"goods storage divider","de":"With one divider, goods that nearly mixed together find their places. Photocards here, keyrings there, light sticks beside them. To organize is to build homes for things. The moment the cells divide, clutter turns into order."},"ICON-0346":{"nm":"Random Pack Seal Cord","on":"cord","de":"Tie a random pack's mouth shut with a cord and no one's fate is decided yet. Until you untie it, everyone is the lead of their own hopes. The flutter of fingertips undoing the seal is the very joy this cord has guarded."},"ICON-0347":{"nm":"Perk Sorting Box","on":"perk sorting box","de":"Perks line up by type inside a box. Postcards with postcards, bookmarks with bookmarks. Look at the cells filling tighter as they grow, and all the time you've collected comes into view at a glance. To sort is to list memories."},"ICON-0348":{"nm":"Version Sorting Label","on":"label","de":"There are things that look the same but aren't. One label divides Version A from Version B, the first print from the reprint. Thanks to a small marker, confusion vanishes, and one clear name tag goes onto the world of collecting."},"ICON-0349":{"nm":"First-Week Sales Check Memo","on":"memo","de":"Release week, and a single number sets the heart swaying. Check marks neatly written on a notepad. Gather a few days' records and it becomes a small report card of support. A careful habit of translating a fond heart into numbers."},"ICON-0350":{"nm":"Poster Fixing Cap","on":"cap","de":"Slip a cap onto the end of a rolled poster and it stays calmly unfurled. So it won't crease while you wonder whether to hang it or frame it. A small stopper that keeps your favorite scene perfectly straight."},"ICON-0351":{"nm":"Standing Photo Stand","on":"stand","de":"A photo stands at a slant on the stand. In a corner of the desk, at just the right angle for eye level. An invention that makes your eyes meet every time you pass. The simplest way to bring a beloved face into your daily view."},"ICON-0352":{"nm":"Rehearsal Tape Roll","on":"rehearsal tape roll","de":"Tape is stuck on the floor to mark where you should stand. One mark, two marks, exactly here. Stepping on the same spots dozens of times, the blocking gets carved into the body. Beneath a dazzling stage lie these honest tape marks."},"ICON-0353":{"nm":"Stage Blocking Pin","on":"pin","de":"A single pin stuck into the stage floor tells the next step. Even in the dark, the toes find that spot first. An exact path you can't see, an invisible map drawn by countless rehearsals."},"ICON-0354":{"nm":"Staff Ear Cap","on":"cap","de":"Put in the ear cap and the crowd's roar dims one layer, while only the voice relaying cues stays clear. Backstage staff ears always hear two worlds at once. A small tool for picking out the signal amid the clamor."},"ICON-0355":{"nm":"Greenroom Hanger Tag","on":"tag","de":"A name tag hangs on each hanger. Outfit 1, outfit 2, encore outfit. Look at that chart listing the change order, and the day's stage is sketched out in advance by the order of clothes. A quiet order that tames the bustle."},"ICON-0356":{"nm":"Prop Inspection Tag","on":"tag","de":"Before going on stage, a tag is fastened to each and every prop. Is anything missing, is it all sound. The audience doesn't know, but this small check prevents accidents. Behind a seemingly flawless stage there is always a meticulous hand."},"ICON-0357":{"nm":"Cue Sign Chip","on":"chip","de":"A cue chip passes from hand to hand. Now, go in. A moment when timing is relayed without a single word. In the darkness beside the stage, this small signal keeps everyone from missing the beat."},"ICON-0358":{"nm":"Backstage Patch","on":"backstage patch","de":"There's a door only those wearing this patch may pass. Backstage, where cheers come through beyond the wall. One small scrap of cloth divides the dazzling front from the busy back. The mark of the people who hold up the stage."},"ICON-0359":{"nm":"Prompter Shade Board","on":"board","de":"A shade board keeps the prompter's light from leaking out to the seats. Only the person on stage sees it, the watchers none the wiser. A polite keeper of the stage's secret, quietly hiding help that mustn't be caught."},"ICON-0360":{"nm":"Greenroom Mirror Cover","on":"cover","de":"In the greenroom after the show, the mirror is draped with cloth. The glass that reflected countless expressions all day closes its eyes for a while. What a makeup-wiped bare face faces last isn't the mirror, but quiet darkness."},"ICON-0361":{"nm":"Pre-Recording Entry Wristband","on":"pre-recording entry wristband","de":"A small band that, once fastened, won't come off until it's cut. For the single qualification to enter the pre-recording seats, someone boarded the first train in the pitch-dark dawn. The weight on the wrist becomes a day's worth of excitement."},"ICON-0362":{"nm":"Recording Standby Label","on":"label","de":"Just before the red light comes on, binding everyone's breath into one row is my job. In the silence waiting for the cue, I hold out quietly to the very end. The moment I'm peeled off, the live broadcast's curtain finally rises."},"ICON-0363":{"nm":"Camera Position Chip","on":"chip","de":"One small mark stamped on the floor deftly sets the paths of six cameras. Where to be caught for the brightest look, the director knows even before rehearsal. A hand that sketches inside the frame from outside it in advance."},"ICON-0364":{"nm":"Sound Check Tag","on":"tag","de":"You tap, tap the mic toward the empty seats. If the echo runs long, one more layer of acoustic foam on the ceiling. The care of tuning the grain of sound while the audience never knows quietly begins from this small tag."},"ICON-0365":{"nm":"On-Site Stamp Book","on":"on-site stamp book","de":"Each time you pass a venue, you collect one more stamp in a cell. In every smudged mark of ink, that day's weather and heartbeat were stamped too. A fully filled page becomes a map of footprints no one can imitate, mine alone."},"ICON-0366":{"nm":"Broadcast Station Visitor Strap","on":"strap","de":"Without this strap the lobby gate won't open. Worn around the neck, walking the corridor step by step, the world you saw only on screen until yesterday slowly draws near enough to touch."},"ICON-0367":{"nm":"Studio Foot Cover Pack","on":"studio foot cover pack","de":"Studio floors are always cold and slippery. Take off your shoes, put on thin foot covers, and footsteps quietly vanish. The camera captures the dance, not the footsteps, so erasing sound is its own courtesy to the stage."},"ICON-0368":{"nm":"Greenroom Snack Tag","on":"greenroom snack tag","de":"Between rehearsal and the live show, hunger arrives most honestly. A small name tag on each greenroom snack saying whose it is. That tenderness of setting things aside is what carries you through the long, long day to the end."},"ICON-0369":{"nm":"Monitoring Memo Band","on":"band","de":"You watch the playback and write. A gaze here, half a beat there. The crowded handwriting is a secret letter to tomorrow's self. The band stuck on the end is a quiet promise to be a hand better than yesterday."},"ICON-0370":{"nm":"Showcase Invitation Slip","on":"showcase invitation slip","de":"A single sheet of paper can be a whole year's wait for someone. A short line inviting you to the showcase, born as the world's smallest invitation, holding even the flutter of fingertips opening the envelope."},"ICON-0371":{"nm":"Press Lanyard Strap","on":"strap","de":"Hung around a reporter's neck, it weaves through the heart of the shutter clatter. Footsteps rushing to find the best angle, and that very speed becomes the passage carrying the stage's heat out to the wider world."},"ICON-0372":{"nm":"Stage Greeting Order Chart","on":"chart","de":"So no one falters even in the moment applause pours down, who's first and who's next is written out in one row. The lineup of the final greeting is arranged just as carefully as the first entrance."},"ICON-0373":{"nm":"Photo Wall Floor Marker","on":"photo wall floor marker","de":"In front of the photo wall, the spot to place your toes is marked in advance. Step just one pace off and the backdrop logo gets cut. The secret of the position captured most brightly is quietly marked underfoot."},"ICON-0374":{"nm":"Premiere Wristband","on":"premiere wristband","de":"A small band fastened to the wrist right before the theater lights go out. When the curtain rises, everyone meets the same scene for the very first time in the same darkness. A small mark of having been there for that first moment."},"ICON-0375":{"nm":"Commemorative Curtain Piece","on":"commemorative curtain piece","de":"On the final show, the curtain slowly came down after the last bow. A piece cut from that span and set in a frame. The heat of the lights and the tremor of applause still linger lukewarm in the cloth, not yet cooled."},"ICON-0376":{"nm":"Debut Reveal Stamp","on":"debut reveal stamp","de":"A stamp carved for the single time you first show yourself to the world. There's no second first reveal, so even the brief moment of ink drying is a time that will never return."},"ICON-0377":{"nm":"Stage Moment Card","on":"card","de":"The most radiant single frame from a stage, clipped onto a card. The music and lights have stopped, but the instant it's in your hand, that day's cheers swell again at your ears. A small magic where a paused scene comes alive."},"ICON-0378":{"nm":"Ending Pose Memo","on":"memo","de":"A memo sketching the angle of fingertips and gaze that must freeze the instant the last note ends. Only those who know one ending frame can sway days keep this small drawing folded with care."},"ICON-0379":{"nm":"Tour City Pin","on":"pin","de":"On the map, a pin goes into each city you've visited. Busan's sea breeze and Gwangju's midday are both stuck on these small nail tips. Quietly connect the dots and you see the long line of a journey crossing a whole season."},"ICON-0380":{"nm":"Seating Section Clip","on":"clip","de":"It divides tens of thousands of seats into sections and guides the way. So you don't get lost, so you don't bump into anyone. Follow me and anyone reaches their place. Order is, in the end, a small kindness for everyone."},"ICON-0381":{"nm":"Entry Gate Tag","on":"entry gate tag","de":"At the gate, one person at a time passes a check in turn. The last gate that lets a ticket-clutching hand and a pounding heart inside. The moment you pass me, the long wait ends and today's stage begins."},"ICON-0382":{"nm":"Wristband Keepsake Capsule","on":"wristband keepsake capsule","de":"Though the color fades, that day's roar stays sealed just the same. Unable to throw away the band from your wrist, you roll it up neatly into a small capsule. Because even a precious memory deserves one little space to lay itself down."},"ICON-0383":{"nm":"On-Site Exchange Pole","on":"pole","de":"Between fan and stage, something passes from hand to hand. It could be a letter, it could be a small gift. I make a way for that heart to arrive safely, the busiest bridge on the scene."},"ICON-0384":{"nm":"Performance Date Seal","on":"performance date seal","de":"That day's date is stamped inside a round seal and stops forever. The calendar turns, but this small circle alone stays in that one day. When it's a day they don't want to forget, people always seal something away."},"ICON-0385":{"nm":"Tour Bag Patch","on":"tour bag patch","de":"A bag that toured along gains one more patch for each city. The place names sewn onto the cloth become a résumé before you know it. Even the worn, frayed corners remain as proof of having gone everywhere together."},"ICON-0386":{"nm":"Ticket Board Cord","on":"cord","de":"A board swaying at the end of the entry line, its tip tied firm by a single cord. Amid the scene of hands holding tickets high stretching long, I quietly mark the head of a procession where excitement stands in line."},"ICON-0387":{"nm":"Encore Ribbon Piece","on":"encore ribbon piece","de":"On the night the voices crying for an encore were loudest, a piece of the ribbon adorning the stage fell. Like a song sung longer because it was a shame to end, this piece too has a reluctance to leave knotted into it."},"ICON-0388":{"nm":"Message Capsule Bottle","on":"bottle","de":"A single word neatly folded inside a glass bottle. Like a small boat set adrift hoping to reach someone someday, I hold a heart and drift slowly over time. Until the day it's opened, the promise sleeps quietly inside."},"ICON-0389":{"nm":"Little Confession Tag","on":"little confession tag","de":"Words you couldn't bring yourself to say, written on a small tag and slipped in quietly. The handwriting trembled, but only the sincerity was clear. There are times when the smallest paper holds the greatest courage."},"ICON-0390":{"nm":"Anonymous Cheer Note Box","on":"anonymous cheer note box","de":"Even without writing a name, the heart gets across. With each note that enters the box, someone's cheer piles up one sheet at a time, anonymously. A collection of faceless tenderness, where only the warmth is clear though you don't know who wrote it."},"ICON-0391":{"nm":"Wish-Folding Paper","on":"wish-folding paper","de":"A square of paper becomes a crane, becomes a star, following your fingertips. With each fold, the wish folds over one layer too. In a carefully folded shape dwells a sincerity that lasts longer than words."},"ICON-0392":{"nm":"Seal Ribbon Wax","on":"seal ribbon wax","de":"Drip the wax and press the stamp down, and the letter is finally sealed. Just the old way of firming up a heart. Atop the cooling red wax, one secret quietly locks shut."},"ICON-0393":{"nm":"Gift Cushioning Paper","on":"gift cushioning paper","de":"Fearing the gift might get hurt, it softly wraps all around it. Into every crumpled fold seeps a plea not to break. A careful layer of heart in an unseen place that the receiver will likely pass by without noticing."},"ICON-0394":{"nm":"Colored Letter Cord","on":"cord","de":"Even the cord binding a letter has color. Yellow for cheer, blue for longing. Feelings words can't fully say are chosen by hue and knotted. Before you even untie it, the temperature of the heart reaches your fingertips first."},"ICON-0395":{"nm":"Handwriting Cover Band","on":"band","de":"A single band that hides the writing until the very moment of handing it over. It guards a confession anxious about being caught right up to the last second. The sincerity revealed when you lift it slightly, the weight of that flutter I know closest of all."},"ICON-0396":{"nm":"Cheer Phrase Chip","on":"chip","de":"On a night when light sticks ripple, a single phrase to shout in one voice is carved inside the chip. Words of promise that gather scattered hearts into one line. When sung all together, that phrase shines the brightest."},"ICON-0397":{"nm":"Worn Practice Room Keyring","on":"ring","de":"A keyring that opened and shut the practice room door hundreds of times. The paint has peeled and the loop has loosened, but in it the sweat of the clumsiest days remains as handworn patina. To be worn means to have stayed that long."},"ICON-0398":{"nm":"Stage Makeup Crayon Piece","on":"stage makeup crayon piece","de":"Stage makeup is only completed under the lights. A piece of that deep color. In the trace pressed on firmly so it wouldn't smudge with sweat lingers the care of carrying an expression all the way to the far seats."},"ICON-0399":{"nm":"Eartip Case","on":"case","de":"The small eartips that let you hear your own voice on stage. When the show ends, you lay them gently inside the case. The closer something carried the music to you, the more carefully you want to keep it."},"ICON-0400":{"nm":"Personal Locker Label","on":"label","de":"At the end of the dorm corridor, a name tag on each locker. Small writing telling whose spot it is turns an unfamiliar space into a home. Getting your own cell is a tender permission to stay here."},"ICON-0401":{"nm":"Portable Throat Care Bottle","on":"bottle","de":"Between rehearsals, you slowly swallow a sip of lukewarm water. The throat is an instrument a singer borrows, so this small bottle filled before it cools guards tomorrow's first note in advance. A cherishing heart is always this quiet."},"ICON-0402":{"nm":"Schedule Reminder Pin","on":"pin","de":"Over a day packed minute by minute, a pin points to the next cell. Among those dense rows, the most welcome thing is one empty cell. The time you may glance out the window is hiding there, tiny."},"ICON-0403":{"nm":"Greenroom Blanket Clip","on":"clip","de":"An afternoon dozing off against a chair with makeup all done, someone gently draped a blanket over your shoulders. This clip, biting it so it wouldn't slide off, quietly holds the warmth of that touch until it's time to go on stage."},"ICON-0404":{"nm":"Little Perfume Sample","on":"little perfume sample","de":"Dab it lightly on the inner wrist and the scent blooms only within a hand's span. It's fine if it doesn't drift far. A trace only those who've drawn near notice, more secret for it, and so more like me."},"ICON-0405":{"nm":"Practice Wear Laundry Tag","on":"practice wear laundry tag","de":"No matter how many times you wash it, the smell of sweat sunk deep into the cloth never fully comes out. Folding the practice wear hung in the sun and dried soft, you think, that mark that won't come out is actually the most honest trace."},"ICON-0406":{"nm":"Lighting Gel Film","on":"lighting gel film","de":"Slip in one thin colored film and white light bleeds into sunset, layer one more and dawn settles in. Behind the curtain, a hand holding its breath, dressing even the light in clothes, choosing which season to tint the stage."},"ICON-0407":{"nm":"Spotlight Lens Cap","on":"cap","de":"Even while the camera is off, someone opens this small cap to clean the lens. For the next scene not yet shot. Over time that isn't captured on screen, the busiest hand sets the focus in advance."},"ICON-0408":{"nm":"Stage Reflector Board","on":"board","de":"There's a board that, though it doesn't shine on its own, returns the light it received to a shadowed face. The center of the stage is so bright because at the edge there's someone's arm quietly setting the angle and casting it back."},"ICON-0409":{"nm":"Color Filter Sleeve","on":"color filter sleeve","de":"Slot blue light into the clear sleeve and the whole audience becomes a sea, switch to red and a sunset falls in its place. The magic of the same stage becoming a different season with one color begins in this thin single layer."},"ICON-0410":{"nm":"Light Number Pin","on":"pin","de":"Each of the many lights has a small number. Which turns on and which sleeps, tonight's show flow is arranged in advance by the order of these numbers. Behind a dazzling curtain there is always a meticulous list laid open."},"ICON-0411":{"nm":"Lighting Tape Marker","on":"lighting tape marker","de":"On the blacked-out stage floor, glowing tape quietly lights the spot where a foot should stop. Unseen from the seats, but the performer's toes grope for this faint light to find their place. Even in darkness there is a tender guide."},"ICON-0412":{"nm":"Shadow Blocking Board","on":"board","de":"A board that blocks leaking light to drop a shadow sharply. Handling darkness is, in the end, handling light, so what to show is decided first by what to quietly hide."},"ICON-0413":{"nm":"Illuminance Check Chip","on":"chip","de":"A small chip measuring a space's brightness reads numbers on your palm. Because too bright or too dark hurts the eyes. This chip quietly guards that invisible sweet spot where a person rests most comfortably."},"ICON-0414":{"nm":"Pin Spot Shade","on":"pin spot shade","de":"A shade fitted so a pin spot doesn't leak to the wrong place. Gathering light onto only one person is a tender focus. The instant you step into that round light, the world looks at just one person for a while."},"ICON-0415":{"nm":"Eartip Set","on":"eartip set","de":"A pair of eartips snug in the ears. Off by even a little in size and the sound leaks, and the moment it leaks you lose the beat. A song without a hair's wobble on stage sometimes begins from this small pair of rubber."},"ICON-0416":{"nm":"Cable Velcro","on":"cable velcro","de":"A velcro strap that binds tangled wires neatly into one strand. The less anyone sees, backstage, the more tidiness shines. The neatness of a single bundle of cables quietly holds up sound flowing unwavering out front."},"ICON-0417":{"nm":"Line Check Label","on":"label","de":"Name tags handwritten on dozens of wires telling which instrument is which. Only when every crooked bit of that writing keeps its place do sounds that played apart finally flow together into one song."},"ICON-0418":{"nm":"Silence Pad","on":"pad","de":"A single silence pad that quietly swallows footsteps and tremors alike. It's laid where stillness is truly needed. The clearest sound is sometimes born only on this quiet floor where no noise leaks out at all."},"ICON-0419":{"nm":"Sound Check Token","on":"token","de":"A token that warms in the hand while sound is tuned before the show. Each time a mic, a speaker is checked, it shifts to a new grip. The perfection of the main stage is shaped step by step within this quiet rehearsal."},"ICON-0420":{"nm":"Mic Cover Cap","on":"cap","de":"Because it's where so many voices have touched, you clean the cap wrapping the mic's tip more carefully. It's a vessel that holds a song, so to a singer it's like another hand. While cleaning it, you sketch tomorrow's first verse in advance."},"ICON-0421":{"nm":"Pop Filter Clip","on":"clip","de":"A thin mesh layer hung between lips and mic. Thanks to the small clip holding that screen, breaths that leaked rough soon get smoothed into a round, soft voice flowing out."},"ICON-0422":{"nm":"Sound Rack Tag","on":"tag","de":"A small tag hung so as not to get lost among shelves of stacked gear in the dark backstage. The source of the dazzling sound that fills the seats is always tidily arranged in such dim places, stacked up neatly."},"ICON-0423":{"nm":"Speaker Grille Pin","on":"pin","de":"A pin that firmly fixes the speaker mesh. The window where sound comes out is the first to meet dust, so a thin mesh layer guards the tone. Everything that reaches the ear has an unseen layer of protection laid over it."},"ICON-0424":{"nm":"Step Marker Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"Blocking stickers stuck dot by dot on the floor. The secret of a group dance landing like a blade is actually hidden underfoot. Atop countless promised marks where dozens step on the same dot, scatter, and gather again."},"ICON-0425":{"nm":"Turn Practice Disc","on":"disc","de":"A practice disc that spins round and round in place. To overcome dizziness, you first learn to fix your gaze on a single point. No matter how fast you spin, the balance is carved slowly into the body so you never let go of that one point."},"ICON-0426":{"nm":"Knee Tape Roll","on":"knee tape roll","de":"A roll of tape that firmly wraps the knee. Joints that have jumped and landed thousands of times stay silent in the end, but this one layer quietly bears up that silence. Behind a body that holds out to the last there is always someone's care."},"ICON-0427":{"nm":"Toe Alignment Board","on":"board","de":"A board that neatly sets the angle of the toes. They say dance is completed at the toes rather than the fingertips. Dozens of toes stretched in the same direction gather to weave the magic of many looking like one."},"ICON-0428":{"nm":"Practice Room Non-Slip Pad","on":"pad","de":"A non-slip pad laid on the practice room floor. To leap freely you must first be safe. Only on a floor where you can roll without fear of falling do the boldest, most fearless moves finally bloom."},"ICON-0429":{"nm":"Move Breakdown Card","on":"card","de":"A card that breaks choreography into tiny pieces, one beat at a time. However hard a move, split it cell by cell and you soon find yourself following along. The water-smooth flow on stage is made of these chopped-and-memorized drawings gathered together."},"ICON-0430":{"nm":"Mirror Cover Curtain Pin","on":"pin","de":"A pin holding up the curtain that briefly covers the practice room mirror. Time spent dancing by the body's sense alone, with no reflection, is needed too. The moment the mirror is covered, the music finally seeps into the very skin, you know."},"ICON-0431":{"nm":"Beat Count Bead","on":"beat count bead","de":"Tick, you push one bead with your fingertip for each beat, counting along. Tangible, like an old counting method. The beat, the backbone of music, only settles firmly into the body when learned through something you can touch like this."},"ICON-0432":{"nm":"Warmup Check Strap","on":"strap","de":"A check strap marking whether you've fully warmed up. Before real practice there always comes a calm preparation first. Rather than regretting after getting hurt, tying one strap and waking the body slowly lets you dance longer in the end."},"ICON-0433":{"nm":"Costume Number Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clip that bites a number onto each outfit so the many don't get mixed up. In a breathless quick-change, mixing up even one outfit is a disaster, so each one's turn is clearly marked. Even bustle is graceful when order holds it up."},"ICON-0434":{"nm":"Mending Room Pin Cushion","on":"mending room pin cushion","de":"A pin cushion set in a corner of the mending room. A hand that has silently filled burst seams and fallen buttons lingers here. Behind the flawless fit on stage hides the care of stitches that have never once seen the stage."},"ICON-0435":{"nm":"Fabric Scrap Ring","on":"ring","de":"A ring threading spare fabric scraps into one. The same cloth is set aside in advance for when the main outfit gets damaged. This small preparation kept while hoping nothing goes wrong saves the stage costume the very moment something big strikes."},"ICON-0436":{"nm":"Quick Button Pack","on":"quick button pack","de":"A pack of buttons you can attach right away in a hurry. Just before a show, when one button pops off, the whole dressing room stirs in an instant. A small but utterly dependable first-aid kit that quells that brief, dizzying emergency at a stroke."},"ICON-0437":{"nm":"Stage Belt Holder","on":"holder","de":"A holder that firmly grips the belt of a stage costume. So the outfit doesn't come undone however hard you jump and spin. The freedom you fully enjoy on stage comes, in the end, from tightly tucking away the parts no one sees."},"ICON-0438":{"nm":"Feather Duster","on":"feather duster","de":"Because under the lights even a tiny piece of lint stands out, you sweep softly over the costume with a feather duster. Right before stepping onto the stage, that tender touch of smoothing the clothes one last time always belongs to this soft feather."},"ICON-0439":{"nm":"Greenroom Slipper Tag","on":"greenroom slipper tag","de":"A name tag on each greenroom slipper. In one small tag saying whose it is rests the quiet relief that we're the same team. That room where you take off your shoes and stretch your feet becomes the coziest home backstage."},"ICON-0440":{"nm":"Styling Clip Board","on":"board","de":"A clip board that holds strands in place while doing the hair. Smoothing strand by strand, the fingers entrust the hair that wants to scatter to this clip for a while. Neatness, in the end, is made of such small pauses gathered together."},"ICON-0441":{"nm":"Safety Pin Organizer Capsule","on":"safety pin organizer capsule","de":"A dawn when a seam burst, open the capsule lid and small cold silver lies neatly. A hand that holds a costume firmest from the unseen inside, the safety pin always works quietly behind the stage."},"ICON-0442":{"nm":"Lens Cleaning Cloth","on":"lens cleaning cloth","de":"Huff once with your breath and wipe in circles, and the hazy world turns clear. You keep cleaning the lens because that brief instant feels so good. A small patch of spring sunlight that clears someone's view in their place."},"ICON-0443":{"nm":"Tripod Rubber Feet","on":"tripod rubber feet","de":"Slip rubber onto the three tips and the floor no longer screams. While the small points swallow the wobble, the scene on screen falls quiet as if by a lie. Stability always begins quietly underfoot."},"ICON-0444":{"nm":"Camera Rain Cover","on":"cover","de":"Even as raindrops trickle down, the lens captures the world dry. On a cloudy afternoon of outdoor shooting, a clear raincoat is gently fitted over the camera. Because what's precious is wrapped before it gets wet."},"ICON-0445":{"nm":"Filming Marker Tape","on":"filming marker tape","de":"Stand here, turn there, short marks in colors point out the way without a word. Even when peeled off without regret after the show ends, the toes grown used to it remember that spot long after."},"ICON-0446":{"nm":"Cut Divider Clip","on":"clip","de":"A small clip that bites scattering papers in one mouthful. With one crisp click, yesterday and today are neatly bound. To organize is a tender habit of gently holding onto what was nearly lost."},"ICON-0447":{"nm":"White Balance Board","on":"board","de":"Hold a white board up to the screen and the colors quietly find their places. The yellow sunset, the blue dawn, without lie. One board that knows true white makes the remaining colors speak honestly."},"ICON-0448":{"nm":"Memory Storage Can","on":"memory storage can","de":"Inside a small tin can, memory chips sleep soundly. Open the lid with a click and last season's scenes spill into your palm. Memory rests held lovingly in one sturdy can like this."},"ICON-0449":{"nm":"Monitor Hood Cap","on":"cap","de":"Wrap a black shade around the monitor and the glare stops cold. Even by a window flooded with sunlight, the screen doesn't lose its color. To see well you must first block the stray light, the hood quietly tells you."},"ICON-0450":{"nm":"Set Soundproof Pin","on":"pin","de":"A small pin wedged in the door gap quietly cuts off outside noise. The footsteps in the hall, the laughter next door, none reach this far. Because to capture clear sound you must first build silence."},"ICON-0451":{"nm":"Makeup Sponge Pack","on":"makeup sponge pack","de":"A neatly stacked bundle of soft, plush sponges. Dab on a little powder with your fingertips and your face brightens by a tone. Behind every radiant smile on stage hide these gentle little touches."},"ICON-0452":{"nm":"Hairpin Case","on":"case","de":"A tidy home for the tiny pins so easily lost. Open the lid and rows of silver line up to greet you. Scattered they vanish, but gathered they reassure. Even the smallest things need a home of their own."},"ICON-0453":{"nm":"Brush Sterilizing Box","on":"box","de":"Brushes that held color all day take a UV shower inside the box. As invisible light washes the old away, tomorrow's bristles come out fresh as new. Cleanliness is one fold of devotion too."},"ICON-0454":{"nm":"Powder Puff Mesh","on":"powder puff mesh","de":"Round puffs catch their breath inside the mesh bag. As air flows through the netting, their softness lasts longer. A well-dried puff holds tomorrow morning's glow in advance."},"ICON-0455":{"nm":"Hold-Spray Cap","on":"cap","de":"One quick spritz and not a strand stirs in the wind. A little cap to hold a carefully styled look through the night. Bright lights pour down and shatter over the firmly set hair."},"ICON-0456":{"nm":"Lip Brush Cover","on":"cover","de":"A small cap that gently wraps the slender bristle tip. Tossed about in a bag, the brush stays straight and clean. Caring for one tiny brush completes a single stroke of color on the lips."},"ICON-0457":{"nm":"Queue-Number Mirror","on":"mirror","de":"A little mirror sits quietly beside the number that calls your turn. Just before stepping onstage, it's the spot to smooth one last stray lock of hair. Even nerves grow a little lighter once you catch your reflection."},"ICON-0458":{"nm":"Wristband Towel","on":"wristband towel","de":"A soft band that wipes the sweat from your brow with one swipe of the wrist. The fiercer the choreography, the more often your hand reaches for it. A small comfort on the wrist, staying close through every breathless moment."},"ICON-0459":{"nm":"Prop Bag Label","on":"label","de":"Even with ten identical bags lined up in the dressing room, there's no mixing them up. Each name tag clearly tells whose is whose. Writing 'mine' on something is a small but tender mark."},"ICON-0460":{"nm":"Practice Room Booking Pin","on":"pin","de":"Who's using this practice room today? A little pin stuck on the board by the door silently divides up the time. The hearts waiting for the next turn line up quietly behind this one pin."},"ICON-0461":{"nm":"Wall Clock Cover Ring","on":"ring","de":"A clear cover settles gently over the wall clock to keep out dust. The ticking hands never blur and time flows on clear. Precious things always need an invisible layer of protection."},"ICON-0462":{"nm":"Floor Protector Pad","on":"pad","de":"A thin pad stuck under a chair leg keeps the wooden floor from getting scratched. Drag it and nothing scuffs, move it and no marks are left. Caring for the floor unseen is the secret to making it last."},"ICON-0463":{"nm":"No-Drinks Marker Chip","on":"chip","de":"Let's set our drinks aside for now, the little chip kindly asks. Sheet music and gear are in trouble if they get wet. Even a word like 'forbidden' becomes warm consideration when offered this way."},"ICON-0464":{"nm":"Ventilation Button Label","on":"label","de":"When you want to freshen the stuffy air, press here, says the little label beside the button. Catching your breath, surprisingly, quietly begins with one small marker like this."},"ICON-0465":{"nm":"Speaker Rubber Foot","on":"speaker rubber foot","de":"A rubber foot beneath the speaker softly swallows the dull rumble. With the bass no longer spreading through the floor, the sound rings far clearer. Good resonance only comes clean atop a solid footing."},"ICON-0466":{"nm":"Locker Number Magnet","on":"magnet","de":"A small number magnet that snaps onto a locker door. Which slot will my things sleep in today? Even if the spot changes daily, one magnet makes a locker mine in no time. Belonging comes from a mark this light."},"ICON-0467":{"nm":"Mirror Wiper","on":"mirror wiper","de":"One swipe across the mirror and the fog clears clean away. The moment my blurred face rises into focus. To truly see myself, I must first gently wipe away what clouds the view."},"ICON-0468":{"nm":"Door Cushion Pad","on":"pad","de":"A plush buffer wedged into a slamming door's gap. It softly catches both the bang and a pinched hand. A small safety that slips one tender layer between rough collisions."},"ICON-0469":{"nm":"Cable Cover Block","on":"cable cover block","de":"A sturdy cover bridges firmly over cables crossing the floor. No tripping feet, no trampled lines. One block's quiet steadiness, guarding the path without blocking it."},"ICON-0470":{"nm":"Caution Wet-Floor Cone","on":"caution wet-floor cone","de":"A yellow cone stands alone on the wet floor, warning in silence. Step carefully, slowly. Behind the bright stage stands this little sentinel, quietly guarding every footstep."},"ICON-0471":{"nm":"Emergency Light Stick","on":"stick","de":"A single beam flicks on in a blacked-out hallway. So you won't lose your way even in the dark, the emergency glow is placed in your hand. There are surely things in this world that shine brightest at the darkest moment."},"ICON-0472":{"nm":"Railing Guard Cap","on":"guard cap","de":"A rounded cap fitted on the end of a stair railing softly wraps the sharp corner. Even a careless brush of the hand won't hurt. Gently covering up what's sharp is a kindness toward someone too."},"ICON-0473":{"nm":"Stage Edge Cushion","on":"stage edge cushion","de":"A plush cushion wraps around the edge of the stage. So even a toe grazing it during fierce choreography won't bruise. Behind every dazzling move, unseen protection dances along."},"ICON-0474":{"nm":"Floor Marker Disc","on":"disc","de":"A round disc laid on the floor quietly says 'stand here.' Those lining up, those finding their place, all stop at this one point. Order grows from a small marker."},"ICON-0475":{"nm":"Flashlight Strap","on":"strap","de":"Loop the cord on a flashlight's end once around your wrist, and you won't lose the light even in the dark. No worry of dropping it, both hands free, a small but reliable loop."},"ICON-0476":{"nm":"Crowd-Control Rope","on":"rope","de":"Please don't come past here, a single rope gently draws the line. A kind boundary quietly parting the dangerous from the safe. Holding someone back is one way of keeping them safe."},"ICON-0477":{"nm":"Safety Check Pin","on":"pin","de":"At every spot the inspection clears, a little pin leaves its 'checked.' One point like a stamp of a mind that looked everywhere, missing nothing. Safety isn't grand; it's the sum of marks left point by point."},"ICON-0478":{"nm":"Mini Clapboard","on":"mini clapboard","de":"At the crisp snap that cuts the first beat, everyone on set finds their breath in a single instant. Small as it is, every scene's starting line is always this one beat. The thrilling start of filming opens here."},"ICON-0479":{"nm":"Desk Mic Cover","on":"cover","de":"A soft cover slips gently over the mic on the desk. Even a sharp burst of breath comes through cleanly, free of noise. The warmest thing wrapping a voice is this small, soft layer."},"ICON-0480":{"nm":"Acoustic Panel Piece","on":"acoustic panel piece","de":"A piece of sound-absorbing panel set in the wall quietly gathers up the echoes. With sound no longer bouncing and scattering, the song pools far clearer. Good resonance begins with carefully refining silence."},"ICON-0481":{"nm":"Headphone Hook Cap","on":"cap","de":"Hanging your headphones here is a small promise. Untangle the cord and lay it neat, so the next person can pick it up and go. One hook brings quiet order to a busy booth."},"ICON-0482":{"nm":"Recording Light","on":"recording light","de":"The moment the red light comes on, every breath in the booth holds still. A signal that stops even the footsteps beyond the door. Capturing sound begins with keeping this deep silence."},"ICON-0483":{"nm":"Pick Organizer Box","on":"box","de":"Picks slotted into compartments by color. Thickness and weight shape the habits of your fingertips. Just before the stage, the precision of grabbing the right one without looking grows from here."},"ICON-0484":{"nm":"Cable Labeler","on":"cable labeler","de":"To keep from getting lost among dozens of tangled strands on the floor, you have to write a name on each end. Only the one who marked where it comes from and where it goes won't fumble in the dark."},"ICON-0485":{"nm":"Mini Mixer Knob","on":"mini mixer knob","de":"Turn it a finger's width and the texture of a voice changes. Raise it and it grows harsh, lower it and it sinks, feeling for that single point between. The most delicate touch shapes the greatest change."},"ICON-0486":{"nm":"Stand Lock Washer","on":"washer","de":"What holds up the stage isn't the dazzling lights but this little ring. Holding the wobble firmly in place, it endures quietly at its post, unseen by anyone."},"ICON-0487":{"nm":"Set Strike Label","on":"label","de":"Even laying everything you built carefully back down follows a clear order. A single sheet noting where to loosen and where to move. The hands that take down are as sure as the hands that build."},"ICON-0488":{"nm":"Lost & Found Envelope Chip","on":"chip","de":"Every dropped item carries its own story. Tucking it in a small envelope to await its owner's name is a tenderness that briefly holds even the lost person's heart."},"ICON-0489":{"nm":"Cleaning Route Marker","on":"cleaning route marker","de":"Follow the arrows drawn on the floor and you'll clean without a gap. Even a broom needs a path so it won't spin in vain. The most gleaming spot lies at the end of the best-traced footsteps."},"ICON-0490":{"nm":"Exit Guide Wand","on":"wand","de":"When the last applause fades, this wand opens the way. A hand that slowly ushers out hearts still aflutter, without bruising them. Even guiding the ending carries warm care."},"ICON-0491":{"nm":"Leftover Tape Ball","on":"leftover tape ball","de":"Roll up the scraps left over and they find a use once more. Just as a tail end nearly thrown away gathers into a firm ball, a thrifty heart grows from small fingertips."},"ICON-0492":{"nm":"Seat Number Cap","on":"cap","de":"Every seat in the house needs a number so no one wanders lost. One little cap that assigns a spot turns a newcomer's flutter into easy relief."},"ICON-0493":{"nm":"Recycling Sorter Pin","on":"pin","de":"A little pin to sort and slot paper from plastic. Mixed, it's just trash; separated, it becomes a resource to use again. Sorting is a tender act that gives objects a second life."},"ICON-0494":{"nm":"Equipment Return Tag","on":"equipment return tag","de":"What's borrowed must always come back to its place. With every fingertip that returns it tagged, trust stacks up layer by layer. The one who returns well borrows with an easy heart next time too."},"ICON-0495":{"nm":"Green Room Checkout Key","on":"green room checkout key","de":"Shed all of today's makeup and costume, and last of all, return this key. Putting back on the way out what you received on the way in. A day's beginning and end held in the same hand."},"ICON-0496":{"nm":"Cushion Puff Case","on":"case","de":"A soft puff loses its grain when pressed. That's why it's laid gently to rest in one round home. To keep softness long, you must first handle it softly."},"ICON-0497":{"nm":"Eyeshadow Chip","on":"chip","de":"A single point of color laid on the lid changes the whole expression. The hue asleep in a little chip only wakes under the lights, adding depth to the gaze turned toward the stage."},"ICON-0498":{"nm":"Blush Brush Cap","on":"cap","de":"When the bristle tip is ruined, the color payoff crumbles too. Capping it to protect its grain is the quiet habit of someone who wants to keep good tools close for a long time."},"ICON-0499":{"nm":"Slim Lip Palette","on":"slim lip palette","de":"A bulky palette takes up the whole bag. A hand that knows one slim line is enough. The moment when paring down becomes the very act of packing well."},"ICON-0500":{"nm":"Mascara Guard","on":"mascara guard","de":"So the lashes set one by one won't smudge, a little guard gently protects their curve. What was lifted with care must be guarded with care, the time before the mirror reminds us."},"ICON-0501":{"nm":"Cotton Swab Case","on":"case","de":"A little home to keep white cotton swabs from scattering everywhere. A touch always kept close for one last touch-up. Tiny preparations fill the gaps of a great stage."},"ICON-0502":{"nm":"Eyelash Curler Rubber Pack","on":"eyelash curler rubber pack","de":"When the rubber hardens, curling the lashes pinches and stings. Keeping spare refills on hand comes from a tenderness that takes even small pains into account."},"ICON-0503":{"nm":"Concealer Brush","on":"brush","de":"A fine bristle tip gently erases the shadows. Bringing brightness to spots the light never reached. A hand that adds light rather than covering flaws finishes far more gracefully."},"ICON-0504":{"nm":"Powder Sifter","on":"powder sifter","de":"Sift the fine powder once and it lays on smooth, free of clumps. The trouble of passing it through the sieve one more time. Devotion, in the end, shows in the fingertip that takes one extra step."},"ICON-0505":{"nm":"Bangs Roll Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clip that rolls the bangs round and holds them a moment. As you wait, the shape settles calmly into place. Neatness blooms where you know how to wait without rushing."},"ICON-0506":{"nm":"Hair Wax Spoon","on":"spoon","de":"Scoop the wax with this little spoon before it ever touches your hands. The restraint of taking just exactly what you need. A hand that knows how to use without excess makes the most natural texture."},"ICON-0507":{"nm":"Curling Iron Rest Mat","on":"mat","de":"You can't just set a scorching curling iron down anywhere. One resting mat protects both the desk and your hands. A spot that handles heat always needs a safe place to rest."},"ICON-0508":{"nm":"Hair Oil Sample","on":"hair oil sample","de":"One drop is enough shine, so it's tucked neatly into a little sample bottle and slipped into a corner of the bag. A small bottle, rather than a big one, ends up in hand far more often."},"ICON-0509":{"nm":"Brush Cleaning Rake","on":"brush cleaning rake","de":"Comb the hair tangled in the bristles slowly out with the rake. Tending to your tools is a quiet ritual after the work is done. A well-groomed brush shapes tomorrow's texture beautifully."},"ICON-0510":{"nm":"Hair Tie Bobbin","on":"hair tie bobbin","de":"Just wound around a spool, they're all visible at a glance. This little bundle, coiled neatly, is a tender bit of ease offered to busy mornings when hair ties rolled away in every direction."},"ICON-0511":{"nm":"Dye Glove Pack","on":"dye glove pack","de":"Thin gloves worn so the hands applying color won't get stained. A wish to greet the next thing with clean hands even after the work is done. Protection is just another name for that kind of readiness."},"ICON-0512":{"nm":"Hairnet Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A small pouch to neatly fold and hold the net that keeps a hairstyle in place. The less bulk a thing has, the easier it's lost, so a thoughtful touch that gives it a home is a welcome thing."},"ICON-0513":{"nm":"Flyaway Fixer Pen","on":"pen","de":"A pen that taps stray flyaways back into place. The very last touch after all the big styling is done. Finishing is always the work of soothing the smallest spot."},"ICON-0514":{"nm":"Perfume Tester Cap","on":"cap","de":"When choosing a scent, don't hold it straight to your nose. Dab it on a little cap and let it drift through the air to reveal its true grain. A fragrance, too, is only honest when smelled a step away."},"ICON-0515":{"nm":"Roll-On Scent Bottle","on":"bottle","de":"A round bead rolls along, tracing scent across the wrist. Unlike the old dab-on bottles, a single line glides and spreads. Scent leaves a different story with every way it touches."},"ICON-0516":{"nm":"Body Mist Cap","on":"cap","de":"A small cap that holds in a scent spreading like mist. Closing and keeping what only scatters when opened. A little heart that saves some makes that fragrance linger longer by your side."},"ICON-0517":{"nm":"Hand Cream Keyring","on":"ring","de":"Attach a ring to the small cream you rub on your hands and it goes everywhere with you. A companion dangling and swaying outside the bag becomes a tender note of care for dry fingertips."},"ICON-0518":{"nm":"Shower Puff Hook","on":"shower puff hook","de":"After working up a frothy lather, it must be dried well. The mesh ball hung on a hook in the corner of the bathroom shakes off the water, awaiting a fresh tomorrow morning."},"ICON-0519":{"nm":"Massage Ball Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A small pouch to hold the firm ball that loosens knotted shoulders. A short rest behind the stage, a time to quietly soothe a stiff body. Care always begins with oneself."},"ICON-0520":{"nm":"Cooling Patch Tin","on":"tin","de":"A tin gathering patches that cool you down when applied. On the night a heated stage ends, a small comfort sleeps within, slowly settling a body and heart grown hot."},"ICON-0521":{"nm":"Nail Oil Pen","on":"pen","de":"Press, rub, sparkle. One drop is enough for dry fingertips. No need for any lavish remedy; a soft sheen spreading from the tip of a little pen winds gracefully over the nails. Care begins with one small drop like this."},"ICON-0522":{"nm":"Sachet Clip","on":"clip","de":"A small knot that ties scent onto paper. Every time you open the drawer, a faint handful greets you before your hand does. A tenderness that lingers near though unseen, one clip quietly holding a day's worth of comfort."},"ICON-0523":{"nm":"Nail Tip Tray","on":"tray","de":"A little stage to lay out the colors of all ten fingers in advance. Which tone suits today? A quiet audition opens on the tray. That brief moment of choosing is somehow thrilling, and a fingertip's day begins here."},"ICON-0524":{"nm":"Cuticle Pusher Cap","on":"cap","de":"There's tenderness even in pushing back. A single hangnail, gently with the rounded tip, never in a hurry. A rushing hand always misses something, so tidying is closer to a mind that looks slowly."},"ICON-0525":{"nm":"Mini File Buffer","on":"mini file buffer","de":"A coarse side and a fine side, two faces held in one hand. Gently filing the rough edges smooth is a small thing, but completion always comes from such small touches. The last word, in the end, belongs to softness."},"ICON-0526":{"nm":"Nail Sticker Sheet","on":"sheet","de":"Stars, flowers, hearts, just pick the one sheet that fits today's mood and tap it on. On a sheet lined with little pictures the size of nails, one sticker sparkles like a tender signature left on a fingertip."},"ICON-0527":{"nm":"Gel Lamp Shade Plate","on":"plate","de":"A thin screen that holds the light in for a while. As it cures, the eyes rest and only the fingertips quietly harden. Even waiting needs a strip of shade, and in unhurried time, today's fingertips are finished."},"ICON-0528":{"nm":"Nail Art Parts Tin","on":"tin","de":"Glittering pieces sleep in compartment after compartment. Rhinestones, pearls, stardust, you lift the lid with the thrill of opening an unlabeled jewelry box. Which light to lay on the nails? That moment of choosing sparkles most."},"ICON-0529":{"nm":"Hand Care Glove Pack","on":"hand care glove pack","de":"A short vacation the hands take while you sleep. Inside the gloves, dry skin slowly grows moist through the night. Care, in the end, is something that happens unseen, and by morning the fingertips are first to know that tenderness."},"ICON-0530":{"nm":"Remover Pump Bottle","on":"bottle","de":"One press, just exactly enough. A cool scent soaks into the cotton and wipes yesterday clean off the nails. There's a rhythm even to emptying, and one pump quietly clears a space to paint anew."},"ICON-0531":{"nm":"Rhinestone Tweezers","on":"tweezers","de":"To pick up a gem finer than a fingertip, you need an even finer hand. The tweezers' tip moves one point without a tremble; delicacy is as much the tool's part as the heart's. One small light finds its place."},"ICON-0532":{"nm":"Earring Storage Plate","on":"plate","de":"So a single earring never goes lost in a drawer again. Slot each pair into its place and the morning rush of choosing grows lighter. Tidying is a small kindness offered to your future self."},"ICON-0533":{"nm":"Ring Sizer Loop","on":"loop","de":"A little bundle of loops that turns finger circumference into a number. Trying on each fitting size one by one is like slowly coming to know what fits you just right. Like that relief when it fits perfectly."},"ICON-0534":{"nm":"Watch Band Pin","on":"pin","de":"When a watch band loosens, this one tiny pin fastens time back onto the wrist. The deepest hidden part lasts the longest, a thing a long-worn watch knows in silence."},"ICON-0535":{"nm":"Necklace Anti-Tangle Plate","on":"plate","de":"Compartments divided so thin chains can't tangle with one another. A tangle-free morning begins with the little dividers parted last night. Ease, in the end, is a mind set in order before the hand ever reaches it."},"ICON-0536":{"nm":"Brooch Back Clasp","on":"brooch back clasp","de":"The more dazzling the front, the more silent the back. A small clasp that firmly supports the brooch pinned to a hem; behind every visible shine there's always a nameless hand holding on. A spot all the more reliable for being unseen."},"ICON-0537":{"nm":"Sunglasses Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A soft cloth gently wraps the lenses that blocked the summer light. A small pouch that guards one pair's view from the jostling of a bag. The heart that treasures something always comes as a soft layer like this."},"ICON-0538":{"nm":"Belt Hole Punch","on":"punch","de":"For a waist gone a notch smaller, or a season gone a notch larger. Punch just one more hole and the belt fits the body again. It's always me that changes, and quietly fitting to me is this little tool's work."},"ICON-0539":{"nm":"Scarf Ring Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clip that gathers a slipping scarf to one point and holds it. Style that kept coming loose in the wind finally settles into place. Even elegance sometimes leans on this little clip, neatening a day that nearly came undone."},"ICON-0540":{"nm":"Charm Loop Set","on":"charm loop set","de":"A set of little loops to hang on the side of a bag. The heart of keeping what you love close by; hanging the day's mood on one charm is a small ritual only you know, and somehow it's a delight."},"ICON-0541":{"nm":"Lint Remover Canister","on":"canister","de":"When a sweater seems to age overnight with pills, roll this canister gently over it and it wears the face of new again. The light whir that lifts away the wear is somehow reassuring. A beloved garment comes alive once more."},"ICON-0542":{"nm":"Fabric Scent Card","on":"card","de":"Tuck it deep in the closet and it quietly fills the days with fragrance. A letter written in scent instead of words, a page read without unfolding. Every morning you take out a garment, the tenderness penned yesterday spreads first."},"ICON-0543":{"nm":"Anti-Static Pin","on":"pin","de":"On a winter morning when a skirt clings to your legs, one pin gently undoes that stick. A small peace that soothes even invisible friction; when one little annoyance vanishes, the day runs far smoother."},"ICON-0544":{"nm":"Portable Clothes Brush","on":"brush","de":"Just before stepping out the door, a streak of dust settled softly on the shoulder. Unfold the folded brush, one swipe, and the first impression is tidy again. Finishing always happens at the door, and neatness is completed by that one touch."},"ICON-0545":{"nm":"Laundry Bag Label","on":"label","de":"Cage the things that mustn't mix in a mesh bag, and a label quietly writes their names. Even laundry has its place, and a place comes with a small marker. The order of an easily tangled day grows from this little name tag."},"ICON-0546":{"nm":"Stain Remover Pen","on":"pen","de":"Even the mark a single drop of coffee left on a shirt slips quietly away when you dab at it. A pen that doesn't cover a mistake but gently erases it. Everyone needs one chance to start the day clean again."},"ICON-0547":{"nm":"Shoe Shine Cloth","on":"shoe shine cloth","de":"One wipe with the cloth and the leather wins back its glow. The longer the shoes are worn, the deeper the shine sets in. The luster is a reward for the time walked together, the shoes quietly etching those years onto the instep."},"ICON-0548":{"nm":"Shoelace Tip Cap","on":"cap","de":"A little cap fastened on the end of an untied lace. So you won't glance away before the finish line, the end is sealed tight. One well-tied lace sends a step farther; a small precaution becomes the courage to run to the end."},"ICON-0549":{"nm":"Hanger Name Chip","on":"chip","de":"Among look-alike hangers, this one little chip quietly tells you 'my spot.' A silent guide that eases the morning rush of mix-ups; with less trouble searching, the day's start feels lighter too."},"ICON-0550":{"nm":"Lens Tweezers Tin","on":"tin","de":"There are times you need a tip more precise than a fingertip. Tweezers that lift a small lens without a tremble wait their turn inside the tin. Precision always lies quietly ready, asleep until called, then awake at once."},"ICON-0551":{"nm":"Mini Cotton Pad Pack","on":"mini cotton pad pack","de":"A small bundle holding just exactly enough for one use. It trims the bulk in your bag while the softness stays the same. Packing light is a kindness too, and a light day moves into the space you pared away."},"ICON-0552":{"nm":"Blotting Paper Case","on":"case","de":"Press away the shine spread over a midday nose with one thin sheet. The papers asleep in neat rows inside the case; for the moment you draw one out, anyone pauses briefly to look tenderly at themselves in the mirror."},"ICON-0553":{"nm":"Folding Comb Mirror","on":"mirror","de":"Folded it's a palm; opened it's a mirror and comb. A little all-in-one that handles a quick fix-up from a corner of the bag. Neatness isn't grand; it's closer to a heart that can open up anywhere for one quick touch."},"ICON-0554":{"nm":"Travel Razor Cap","on":"cap","de":"It safely puts the sharp blade to sleep in a travel bag. Thanks to this dull yet sturdy cap, even fingers fumbling in a busy morning won't get cut. Looking out for things is always covering a danger one step ahead."},"ICON-0555":{"nm":"Lip Balm Loop","on":"loop","de":"A small shield dangling from a bag strap. No worry of it rolling around a pocket and cracking; dry lips stay always within reach. Keeping something close is, in the end, a heart that puts what's needed at the nearest distance."},"ICON-0556":{"nm":"Hand Sanitizer Holder","on":"holder","de":"Press it one-handed and a handful of cleanliness drops out. Hang it by the door, on the desk, anywhere, and the habit of clean hands grows that much closer. A good habit isn't grand; it begins within arm's reach."},"ICON-0557":{"nm":"Slim Tissue Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A sleek frame holding a handful of tissues. Without bulging a pocket, it's always quietly ready for a sudden runny nose or tears. A sheet to slip to someone; the slimmer the readiness, the finer it is."},"ICON-0558":{"nm":"Mini Mouthwash Bottle","on":"bottle","de":"On a day you must meet someone after eating spicy ramen, this little bottle quietly handles a quick freshening. A single sip of crispness sometimes becomes great confidence, making a hesitant greeting far lighter."},"ICON-0559":{"nm":"Shimmer Powder Chip","on":"chip","de":"Dab a touch on your fingertip and lay it on your cheek, and it spreads like stardust scattering under the lights. An ordinary cheek sparkles in an instant by the magic of this one little chip. Light always arrives like this, on powder dusted at the fingertip."},"ICON-0560":{"nm":"Glitter Toning Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"Where it sparkles too much to be comfortable, this sticker gently dims the light. Taking off one layer of dazzle is part of adornment too; the subtlety left in that pared space sometimes becomes a sense all its own."},"ICON-0561":{"nm":"Stone Pickup Pen","on":"pen","de":"A small stone caught underfoot while walking down the road. A pen that bends down on purpose to pick it up. The heart that gently gathers with a fingertip what you might have just passed by; tenderness always begins with stopping."},"ICON-0562":{"nm":"False Lash Storage Plate","on":"plate","de":"A small plate to lay false lashes down neatly, one by one. Even after they're peeled off, their lovely curve never goes astray. The quiet, tidy comfort of storage that says even what's set down for a while remembers its place."},"ICON-0563":{"nm":"Double-Eyelid Tape Cutter Cap","on":"cap","de":"Two blades meet and sever a knot in one stroke. The cleaner the cut, the neater the next knot. From a fingertip that ties well and cuts well, even a fresh start unravels far more lightly."},"ICON-0564":{"nm":"Face-Line Tape","on":"face-line tape","de":"One strip along the jawline, applied carefully, holding your breath. Contouring isn't drawing a line that wasn't there but tracing the place already lovely. A touch that tenderly follows the grain that was always there."},"ICON-0565":{"nm":"Light-Reflecting Powder","on":"light-reflecting powder","de":"A powder that drinks in light to the fullest and gives it back gracefully. Though it doesn't shine on its own, it brightens by scattering received light into fine pieces. Like passing on borrowed tenderness to another, sparkle grows the more it's shared."},"ICON-0566":{"nm":"Makeup Setting Fan","on":"makeup setting fan","de":"A fan's breeze holding a painstaking look together until the day's end. So it won't crumble, so it won't run, it quietly cools and sets. So a carefully tended face stays clear until the stage curtain falls."},"ICON-0567":{"nm":"Color Corrector Palette Chip","on":"chip","de":"Little pieces that soothe and right a misaligned hue, one compartment at a time. Even a color that floated alone brightens at last with a complementary shade beside it. Only when color clasps hands with color does it become one clear canvas."},"ICON-0568":{"nm":"Neck Scarf Pack","on":"neck scarf pack","de":"Wrap it around your neck and the cold air of a dawn practice room softens considerably. Warm as a grandmother's hand wrapping it round her grandchild's neck. Cold always comes first to the thinnest places, so it embraces the nape first."},"ICON-0569":{"nm":"Heated Eye Mask Envelope","on":"envelope","de":"A small envelope to hold a warmed eye mask. The moment you open the flap, a drowsy warmth seeps slowly over your eyelids. A tender ritual before sleep, sealing away a weary day for a while, then releasing it."},"ICON-0570":{"nm":"Portable Humidifier Filter","on":"filter","de":"A small straining membrane that returns moisture to a parched room. From the unseen inside, it quietly filters out what clouds. The dampness filling the room is a clarity kept by someone's unseen effort."},"ICON-0571":{"nm":"Vitamin Organizer Box","on":"box","de":"A box that divides a day's pills compartment by compartment. Taking them faithfully is a vow to stand on stage tomorrow too. In each little compartment, a heart that cherishes oneself is set in tidy order."},"ICON-0572":{"nm":"Sleep Earplug Case","on":"case","de":"A home for the earplugs that briefly shut out the world's noise. Even quiet needs tending, so they lie neatly within the case. A deeply slept night is what lets the next day's voice wake clear, as rest knows well."},"ICON-0573":{"nm":"Cool Towel Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clip that bites firmly onto the shoulder so a chilled towel won't slip off. On a sweltering day, one streak of coolness against the nape carries you through a long afternoon. Even a small coolness, held in place, lingers long."},"ICON-0574":{"nm":"Stretch Ball Bag","on":"bag","de":"A bag to put back the ball that loosened your body. Stretching wide then drawing small again resembles an inhale and an exhale. Between unfolding and gathering, both body and mind slowly grow firm."},"ICON-0575":{"nm":"Compression Bandage Roll","on":"compression bandage roll","de":"A band that wraps a twisted ankle round and round. It isn't squeezing but quietly bracing. The more strained a place, the more it needs a hand that endures silently beside it, the roll whispers as it winds."},"ICON-0576":{"nm":"Condition Check Tag","on":"tag","de":"A tag you write your condition on in one line and hang. Honestly marking the good and the bad is a small courage. Write today's self instead of pretending you're fine, and someone will read that one line and quietly look after you."},"ICON-0577":{"nm":"Shoe Freshener Capsule","on":"shoe freshener capsule","de":"A scent capsule popped inside a shoe. A small, faint comfort offered to feet that roamed the stage all day. The best scent for the spot that worked hardest; tenderness reaches all the way to the toes, missing nothing."},"ICON-0578":{"nm":"Insole Size Chart","on":"chart","de":"A chart with the foot size clearly marked even on an insole. One perfectly fitting pair makes footsteps on stage light. Taking each different stride into account; a good fit is, in the end, a heart that looks deeply at the other."},"ICON-0579":{"nm":"Shoehorn Keyring","on":"ring","de":"A keyring with a shoehorn shrunk to palm size. A small consideration that smooths the brief moment of slipping on a shoe. Feet setting out on a road always carry, hanging gently alongside, someone's tender helping hand."},"ICON-0580":{"nm":"Bag Dust Cover","on":"cover","de":"A cloth that gently covers a beloved bag from dust. Even while unused, it puts the bag softly to sleep and guards its grain. The things your heart lingers on, though seldom touched, carry quiet care like this."},"ICON-0581":{"nm":"Strap Adjuster Pin","on":"pin","de":"A pin that fits a loosened strap snugly to the body. Too loose and it slips off the shoulder; too tight and breath grows short. In the small adjustment of finding just-right, a stage costume and a heart both find ease at last."},"ICON-0582":{"nm":"Zipper Lubricant Pen","on":"pen","de":"Draw it once across a stiff zipper and it glides smoothly again. How refreshing the sound of something jammed slipping free. What sets a stalled spot flowing again is a single streak of smoothness."},"ICON-0583":{"nm":"Sneaker Cleaner Tip","on":"sneaker cleaner tip","de":"A bristle tip that wipes a dust-caked sneaker clean, point by point. Off the stage, it carefully erases the unseen traces of practice. Looking at the toe gone white again, it feels like tomorrow you could run with a fresh heart."},"ICON-0584":{"nm":"Waterproof Spray Cap","on":"cap","de":"A waterproofing cap that rolls raindrops into beads and lets them fall. Layering one coat in advance so nothing gets soaked is a tenderness that looks far ahead. Knowing rainy days will come, you draw one layer of film over a clear today."},"ICON-0585":{"nm":"Leather Protector Cloth","on":"leather protector cloth","de":"A cloth laid gently over leather to keep it from creasing. It guards the grain like an old hand wrapping a folding screen in hanji paper. The longer you'll keep a thing close, the slower you go; breaking in is just another name for the time spent caring."},"ICON-0586":{"nm":"Carrier Name Belt","on":"carrier name belt","de":"A name belt that lets you spot your own among countless bags at a glance. Among luggage circling the conveyor, it raises its hand with a single letter. No matter how far you travel, one name is the reassurance of meeting again."},"ICON-0587":{"nm":"Compression Bag Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clip that presses swollen luggage flat and seals it. It's less emptied than neatly folded away. From the fingertip that trims the household tidy, even greed grows smaller too, the firmly pressed luggage quietly tells."},"ICON-0588":{"nm":"Travel Detergent Sheet","on":"sheet","de":"A detergent sheet that does the laundry in a washbasin with just one piece. It resembles the wayfarer's wisdom of hand-washing clothes far from home. Traveling light yet still packing along neatness, a traveler's long-held mindset on the road."},"ICON-0589":{"nm":"Neck Pillow Cover","on":"cover","de":"A clean cover freshly slipped onto the pillow that supported your neck. A spot to lean on should always be clean to set the mind at ease. Leaving a place soft and clear so someone can lean comfortably; hospitality begins there."},"ICON-0590":{"nm":"Luggage Scale Strap","on":"strap","de":"A strap that hoists a bag up to gauge its weight. Before leaving, you hold the luggage's weight in your hand in advance. Between what to take and what to leave, a moment of quietly weighing even the heart's weight too."},"ICON-0591":{"nm":"Shoe Pouch Pair","on":"shoe pouch pair","de":"A pair of pouches holding two shoes side by side, left and right. Easily lost apart, they're reassuring matched together. Things that always go together have a power to quietly look after one another."},"ICON-0592":{"nm":"Extra Bag Loop","on":"loop","de":"On a day when one hand falls short, a little loop to hang a bag on for a moment. A spare slot for days with more luggage than you can possibly carry. Just having a place to hang it for a while makes the shoulders far lighter."},"ICON-0593":{"nm":"Travel Itinerary Chip","on":"chip","de":"Etch the day's route clearly onto one chip. Where to meet and where to flow next, a guideline drawn in advance for footsteps poor at finding the way. A road traveled together, noted slot by slot, seldom wanders lost."},"ICON-0594":{"nm":"Multi-Adapter Cap","on":"cap","de":"A cap that meshes snugly even into the outlets of an unfamiliar country. Different in shape, yet connected as one in the end. Joining things that came from different places; harmony quietly begins with one small conversion."},"ICON-0595":{"nm":"Transit Card Sleeve","on":"transit card sleeve","de":"A clear sheet that protects the card each time it brushes the turnstile. The daily commute, every worn-in tap mark, wrapped gracefully. Even an ordinary road becomes a memory when treasured, as this thin layer proves."},"ICON-0596":{"nm":"Ticket Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clip that neatly grips a ticket so quick to crumple. Lose a ticket on the road and even your heart shakes loose. The smaller the paper, the more firmly you hold it; the reassurance of a journey comes from that one slot."},"ICON-0597":{"nm":"Transfer Memo Chip","on":"chip","de":"A little chip with where to transfer noted in one line. At every confusing fork, a single word jotted in advance opens the way bright. A memo is a tender hint quietly slipped to your future self who might lose the way."},"ICON-0598":{"nm":"Gate Pass Tag","on":"tag","de":"A pass tag quietly recognized as you go through the gate. Even a road that seemed blocked slides open once you carry your own qualification. To pass through openly is to step lightly into the next slot without a moment's hesitation."},"ICON-0599":{"nm":"Taxi Receipt Holder","on":"holder","de":"Each small slip bears the clear imprint of a road traveled that day. Gather the receipts that rolled around in every direction and tuck them neatly together, and even an unremarkable day stacks up, slip by slip, into a proper journey."},"ICON-0600":{"nm":"Bicycle Reflective Band","on":"band","de":"A band that catches passing lights on a dim road and quietly sparkles. Though it doesn't shine on its own, it brightens by someone else's light. To make yourself visible is a night road's tender plea to please return home safe."},"ICON-0601":{"nm":"Luggage Wheel Cover","on":"cover","de":"The reason your suitcase corners stay flawless after rolling thousands of times across airport conveyors is this little cover wrapped around the wheels. The part that meets the roughest road first—quietly protecting someone is always tucked away where no one notices."},"ICON-0602":{"nm":"Headrest Cover","on":"cover","de":"On a long bus ride, you slip one over the headrest and lean toward the window. The scent of the last passenger, yesterday's fatigue—none of it reaches this far. A clean place to rest your head is a surprisingly big comfort on an unfamiliar road."},"ICON-0603":{"nm":"Parking Spot Pin","on":"pin","de":"\"Which floor, which space was it again?\" Anyone who has wandered an empty parking garage knows how reassuring this pin is. A single marker stuck in place of fading memory, setting your way back in advance."},"ICON-0604":{"nm":"Room Key Lanyard","on":"lanyard","de":"How does a room key vanish so easily? Thread it on a lanyard and loop it around your wrist, and you'll never forget the one room waiting for you tonight. Even in a strange city, the small relief of having your own spot dangles at your wrist."},"ICON-0605":{"nm":"Door Sign Chip","on":"chip","de":"When rehearsal begins, you hang a chip on the door. Do not disturb—this is time for pure focus. The deep hush backstage is quietly kept by little signals like this."},"ICON-0606":{"nm":"Toiletry Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Toothbrush, face wash, a palm-sized towel. No matter where you go, pack just this pouch and the end and start of each day are tidied by the same familiar hands. A small handful of housekeeping that makes a strange bed feel like home."},"ICON-0607":{"nm":"Spare Towel Clip","on":"clip","de":"Beside the sink, that spare towel always sat damp with nowhere to go. Pinch it with a clip and hang it, and it finally finds its place. Giving something a spot to dry—kindness usually comes in about this size."},"ICON-0608":{"nm":"Power Strip Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Every time you opened your bag, the chargers were tangled in one knot. Roll the whole power strip up and tuck it inside, and things settle into order. An unraveled cord means a little corner of your heart unwinds before the trip too."},"ICON-0609":{"nm":"Bunk Number Label","on":"label","de":"A number tag on each bunk in the dorm. With one label telling you which spot is yours, even a strange new room becomes home by nightfall. The beginning is always this small."},"ICON-0610":{"nm":"Mini Clothesline","on":"line","de":"Hook both ends between the window frames and it becomes a clothesline. On a sunny day, a few hand-washed socks sway dry and fluffy in the breeze. Even far from home, everyday life dries on a line like this."},"ICON-0611":{"nm":"Slipper ID Tag","on":"slipper tag","de":"When slippers pile up by the door, you can't tell whose is whose. Attach a little tag and even shoes recognize their owner. Living packed in together calls for these kind of friendly markers."},"ICON-0612":{"nm":"Breakfast Coupon Holder","on":"holder","de":"A holder to tuck your breakfast ticket into. On a hungry early morning, this one slip promises a steaming bowl of soup. A day on the road always opens slowly with one warm meal."},"ICON-0613":{"nm":"Ankle Reflector Band","on":"band","de":"Wrap it around your ankle and it throws light back in the dark. On a night walk, it silently waves to an approaching car from afar—\"someone's here.\" Safety glimmers as humbly as this."},"ICON-0614":{"nm":"Wet Wipe Cap","on":"cap","de":"A cap that fits snugly over the mouth of a wet-wipe pack. Each sheet pulls out smoothly, and the rest don't dry out. It may seem trivial, but things you reach for every day always have their reasons."},"ICON-0615":{"nm":"Picnic Mat Strap","on":"strap","de":"Roll the mat into a circle and tie it with a strap. The Han River bank, the shade of cherry blossoms—the moment you spread it out, that spot becomes ours. A strap that carries a palm-sized territory of grass wherever you go."},"ICON-0616":{"nm":"Bug Patch Case","on":"case","de":"A case to hold mosquito patches, a summer-night essential. The thoughtfulness of preparing them before the itch fits inside this one little compartment. The back rows of an outdoor stage are always made secure by small precautions like this."},"ICON-0617":{"nm":"Walk Bottle Hook","on":"hook","de":"A hook to clip your water bottle onto your bag when you head out for a walk. Having water within reach when thirst comes means you can walk that much farther. A small connection that keeps a walker from stopping."},"ICON-0618":{"nm":"Foldable Shopping Basket","on":"basket","de":"Open it and it's a shopping basket; fold it and it fits in your palm. Just right for a bundle of vegetables you've grown fond of while wandering the market alleys. The wisdom of housekeeping has always grown toward less bulk, toward lighter carrying."},"ICON-0619":{"nm":"Windbreaker Clip","on":"clip","de":"On a windy day, it pinches the flapping edge of a tent and holds it firmly. One clip presses down what kept fluttering loose. Outdoors, the most dependable thing is, surprisingly, something the size of a finger."},"ICON-0620":{"nm":"Sun Shade Pin","on":"pin","de":"A pin you stick to the window to slant away the sunlight. When midday light is too harsh, it gently casts a handful of shade. Easing a glare can be, for someone, the kindest touch."},"ICON-0621":{"nm":"Emergency Whistle Cap","on":"cap","de":"A cap that covers the mouth of an emergency whistle. Keeping dust out so it sounds in one breath when truly needed. Some things bring peace just by being near, even as you hope you'll never have to use them."},"ICON-0622":{"nm":"Umbrella Tip Cap","on":"cap","de":"A little cap to slip over an umbrella's tip. When the sharp point is dulled, neither the person beside you nor your own bag gets hurt. Rainy-day manners begin quietly with wrapping a sharp end round and soft."},"ICON-0623":{"nm":"Raincoat Pouch","on":"raincoat pouch","de":"A pouch to roll up a folded raincoat and tuck away. It waits quietly in a corner of your bag until the next downpour. Preparation is, in the end, a sliver of heart that packs away what you may never use."},"ICON-0624":{"nm":"Waterproof Shoe Covers","on":"covers","de":"Pull them over your shoes and rain can no longer seep in. Even on a monsoon walk to school, your socks stay dry. A day where you aren't soaked to the toes changes your mood far more than you'd expect."},"ICON-0625":{"nm":"Anti-Slip Snow Pad","on":"pad","de":"Stick it to the soles of your shoes and icy roads feel far less frightening. That winter when you scurried across snow-piled alleys, this pad quietly held you steady. The dependable strength hidden beneath careful steps."},"ICON-0626":{"nm":"Cooling Neck Ring","on":"ring","de":"Wrap it around your neck and a cool current settles in quietly. The summer wisdom of draping a strand of coolness over your nape even in the sweltering dog days. Each year we learn to endure the heat a little more cleverly."},"ICON-0627":{"nm":"Handheld Fan Stand","on":"fan stand","de":"A stand to prop up a handheld fan. With both hands free, you can turn pages and write instead of fanning. A small breeze makes a long summer at the desk just bearable enough."},"ICON-0628":{"nm":"Hand Warmer Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A pouch to carry a hand warmer in. When you slip your cold fingertips into your pocket to thaw them, a little warmth is already there, waiting. Winter outings are endured on this one handful of heat."},"ICON-0629":{"nm":"Earmuff Case","on":"case","de":"A case to keep earmuffs in. A place to store them carefully until the next cold arrives. Things we can't quite throw away as the seasons turn carry a quiet faith in the winter we'll meet again."},"ICON-0630":{"nm":"UV Sensor Chip","on":"chip","de":"Hold it gently to the light and the chip tells today's UV strength in color. It finally makes the unseen intensity of sunlight visible. You're fastening a small eye for reading the sky onto your wrist."},"ICON-0631":{"nm":"Alley Stamp Board","on":"board","de":"A board you fill by collecting stamps from each shop along the alley. With every square stamped, a map of the neighborhood draws itself clearly in your heart. Memories gathered on foot remain as marks of ink like these."},"ICON-0632":{"nm":"Travel Pin Board","on":"pin board","de":"A small board where you stick a pin for every place you've visited. As the dots multiply, the circumference of your world widens with them. Each pin is a trace that quietly says, \"I was here.\""},"ICON-0633":{"nm":"Little Compass Cord","on":"cord","de":"However long you wander, north alone always stays in its place. The little compass hanging at your chest, when you have no idea which way to go, first gently steadies your wavering heart."},"ICON-0634":{"nm":"Directions Memo Ring","on":"ring","de":"The notes you scribbled while finding your way, threaded onto a ring. \"Turn left at the red mailbox.\" Someone's clumsy handwriting quietly guides a strange alley. A road left on paper rarely fades."},"ICON-0635":{"nm":"Landmark Sticker Book","on":"sticker book","de":"A book you fill with one sticker bought at each destination. Towers, bridges, old fortress walls stack up page after page. Collecting the places you've been is like touching the time you've passed through with your fingertips again."},"ICON-0636":{"nm":"Subway Transfer Chip","on":"chip","de":"A chip you grip tight at the transfer station where lines branch off. That brief moment of choosing where to switch can sometimes turn the whole direction of a day. With one small choice, the city shows a different face."},"ICON-0637":{"nm":"Neighborhood Quest Card","on":"card","de":"\"Today, as far as this neighborhood's bakery.\" Draw one card and the day's destination is set. Even a familiar alley you pass all the time becomes a new road once a mission appears. A card that reminds you adventure isn't far away."},"ICON-0638":{"nm":"Shop Card Holder","on":"holder","de":"A holder to tuck the business cards you got from your favorite shops. The tasty place, the kind owner—they gather one slot at a time. Growing fond of a city begins from little slips of paper like these."},"ICON-0639":{"nm":"Course Completion Badge Board","on":"board","de":"A board where finishing a walking course to the end earns you a badge. The reward of going the distance remains in your hand as a round piece of metal. The pride only those who walked all the way know is clearly set here."},"ICON-0640":{"nm":"Bag Lock Keyring","on":"ring","de":"A small lock-and-keyring you fasten to your bag's zipper. It guards your precious things tightly while jingling at the bag's edge. A traveler's rather clever companion, where security and decoration become one."},"ICON-0641":{"nm":"Anti-Loss Tag","on":"tag","de":"It crouches in the deepest dark of your bag, and at the very moment everyone's given up, it blinks faintly. \"Right here.\" The sound of something you thought lost returning to your fingertips. Small as it is, it stays by its owner to the end."},"ICON-0642":{"nm":"Zipper Lock Ring","on":"ring","de":"Click—once it's fastened, no ordinary hand can open it. A grit that blocks a hurried fingernail and a sly approaching finger alike. Safety reminds you, with its solid weight, that it's okay to be a little stiff sometimes."},"ICON-0643":{"nm":"Anti-Theft Bell Strap","on":"strap","de":"An unseen gatekeeper that keeps the goods on the shelf from stepping out before checkout. When an honest hand brushes past, it stays silent to the end. A bell that doesn't ring is the most peaceful bell of all."},"ICON-0644":{"nm":"Contact Cover Label","on":"label","de":"It quietly lays a layer over the name and number on a parcel box. Who lives here, where it's going—only the recipient needs to know. Covering well is its own kind of kindness, it says, quietly keeping its place."},"ICON-0645":{"nm":"Passport Cover Band","on":"band","de":"A strange airport, dozens of identical covers circling the conveyor at dawn. Among them it waves \"this way\" in a color only you know. A little coat dressed onto the document setting off on a long journey. Even as the cover wears, the trip stays bright."},"ICON-0646":{"nm":"Cash Sorting Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Bills on the left, coins on the right, emergency money in a compartment no one knows. It's the first place a hand fresh from the market reaches for. Even a tangled day finds its place inside, neatly and with a jingle."},"ICON-0647":{"nm":"Security Seal Sticker","on":"security seal","de":"Peel it once and a mark stays. A small, honest conscience that can never quite hide \"someone opened me.\" Beneath every box that arrived sealed and safe lies this friend's unwavering silence."},"ICON-0648":{"nm":"Emergency Contact Chip","on":"chip","de":"A lost child's pocket, the inside of a laptop bag, the end of a dog's leash. Even when the moment can't speak, it calls out the number clearly in its place. One small chip holds a whole \"please take me home.\""},"ICON-0649":{"nm":"Selfie Stick Remote Cap","on":"cap","de":"Group photos where someone always got cut off for lack of arm length. Now a flick of the button at the end fits the whole family into one frame. In that instant everyone smiles, I quietly press the shutter and leap in."},"ICON-0650":{"nm":"Lens Pouch Cord","on":"cord","de":"A cord that hugs spare lenses close so they don't knock about in your bag. Since one piece of glass is one landscape, you don't shake that weight carelessly. A photographer's care is tied into every knot."},"ICON-0651":{"nm":"Filter Case Ring","on":"ring","de":"One thin sheet turns the same sky into different light. A place to keep those little spells neatly in a round nest. Each time you open the case, your fingertips flutter a moment—which sunset shall I capture today?"},"ICON-0652":{"nm":"Tripod Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A hand-span folded, three steady legs unfolded. You gently roll up the friend that will hold the scene in place of your trembling hands. The heavier the gear, the softer the cloth it deserves to lie on."},"ICON-0653":{"nm":"Camera Strap Patch","on":"camera strap patch","de":"Walk all day and the moment comes when the camera presses on your shoulder. That's when one patch quietly takes on some of the weight. A small, plush comfort laid on the shoulder that walks far for one good shot."},"ICON-0654":{"nm":"Memory Sorting Card","on":"card","de":"On nights when you can't recall which card holds hundreds of memories, colored markers trace the way. Spring trip in blue, first stage in yellow. A small, kindly librarian that gives even memories their own shelves."},"ICON-0655":{"nm":"Charging Cable Roll","on":"charging cable roll","de":"Before cables stage a knot-show in your bag, you wind them round and tuck them neatly to sleep. Tidy one cord and somehow a strand of your heart unwinds along with it. The coiled-up sight is peaceful just to watch."},"ICON-0656":{"nm":"Photo Backup Label","on":"label","de":"\"These photos—did I back them up?\" A small memo that answers that late-night unease in advance. The more precious the moment, the more it must live in two places or more, the label writes out clearly."},"ICON-0657":{"nm":"Composition Frame Board","on":"board","de":"Look at the world through the square window and you see at once what to include and what to leave out. A good photo isn't about adding more but taking away well—the empty frame teaches that first."},"ICON-0658":{"nm":"Coin Purse Charm","on":"coin purse charm","de":"It dangles at the edge of your bag, holding a few coins. The little treasure vault that opens first before a vending machine or a steaming fish-bun stall. That jingle is the sound effect of small happiness."},"ICON-0659":{"nm":"Receipt Spindle","on":"spindle","de":"Slips of paper you nearly threw out get skewered one by one. What you ate and bought today—the receipt is a more honest diary than any ledger. Gather a month's worth and it becomes a fairly thick record of living."},"ICON-0660":{"nm":"Market Basket Tag","on":"market basket tag","de":"It hangs on the wrist heading to market and roams the stalls together. A block of tofu, a bundle of green onions, even the kindness thrown in for free. It takes on all that weight without complaint. A friend more thrilled to fill than to empty."},"ICON-0661":{"nm":"Souvenir Magnet Board","on":"board","de":"Pick one at each destination and stick it on the fridge, and the kitchen becomes a small world map. The cities you've visited hang side by side, whispering \"let's go again.\" Even plain steel has the power to hold memories."},"ICON-0662":{"nm":"Regional Stamp Book","on":"regional stamp book","de":"One stamp per page, the alleys you walked come alive again in ink. The red marks gathered touring the whole country are a map of your footsteps. The fewer the empty squares, the more the next journey quietly beckons."},"ICON-0663":{"nm":"Wrapping Cord Reel","on":"wrapping cord reel","de":"Long, long patience unspooling endlessly to tie up a single gift box. It grants a neat knot only to hands that know when to cut. Coiled up, it waits quietly for its next turn."},"ICON-0664":{"nm":"Gift Cushion Pack","on":"gift cushion pack","de":"It cushions a fragile heart in a soft embrace. Even in a jostling delivery truck, it holds firm and plush—\"it's okay, I've got you.\" It guards in advance even the bright smile of the one who opens the box."},"ICON-0665":{"nm":"Price Tag Cover Sticker","on":"price tag cover sticker","de":"A kind little white lie that quietly covers the price of a gift. \"You don't have to know how much—just take the heart,\" it says, settling softly over the tag. Not hiding, but making that heart shine all the more."},"ICON-0666":{"nm":"Mini Shopping Cart Chip","on":"chip","de":"You can't push a real cart, but this little friend dangling from your fingertip holds all the excitement of a trip to the store. Small as it is, the flutter of \"what shall I buy today?\" weighs no less than the real thing."},"ICON-0667":{"nm":"Glow Shoe Clip","on":"clip","de":"A sparkle at the tip of a sneaker out for a night walk, sending a passing car the signal \"someone's here.\" The first little light to come greet you in a dark alley. Safety always begins quietly at the toes."},"ICON-0668":{"nm":"Mini Flashlight Cap","on":"cap","de":"Slip it over a flashlight's head and the light spreads farther, softer. A little magician that paints a cluster of stars on a dark tent ceiling. On nights when the dark is a bit scary, there's no better friend."},"ICON-0669":{"nm":"Home-Safe Button","on":"button","de":"Press it and the line \"I got home safe\" flies off to family far away. Instead of the sound of the front door late at night, one small button delivers the news. Someone falls asleep waiting for this signal."},"ICON-0670":{"nm":"Reflective Sticker Roll","on":"reflective sticker roll","de":"Cut a square and stick it on a bag, a bike, an umbrella, and the night road grows far less dangerous. A sleepyhead that wakes up bright the moment it meets a headlight. Coiled up, it waits for the next darkness to come."},"ICON-0671":{"nm":"Emergency Taxi Card","on":"card","de":"Tuck it in a wallet slot and even an empty stop late at night feels less daunting. A number, a line of address written like a promise—\"I'll take you home.\" Who knew the word emergency could be so reassuring."},"ICON-0672":{"nm":"Night Path Map Band","on":"band","de":"You walk the dimly-lit streets with it wrapped around your wrist. Which alley is bright, where it goes dark—it slips you the shortcut only the night knows. A band that ties itself by your side so you never lose direction in the dark."},"ICON-0673":{"nm":"Safety Alarm Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Yank it in an emergency and it cries out loud enough to startle the whole alley. The rest of the time it hides quietly in the pouch, saving its voice for that single moment. The biggest shout, held in the smallest bag."},"ICON-0674":{"nm":"Doorway Light Keyring","on":"ring","de":"Goodbye to nights fumbling for the keyhole at the dark end of the hall. Hanging by the door, it greets the returning hand with a round glow. \"Good work, you're home,\" the keyring says first."},"ICON-0675":{"nm":"Lodging Return Memo","on":"memo","de":"\"Take your umbrella, turn off the lights when you leave.\" A short reminder on the fridge guards the empty room. A little note for the one who'll return. The kindness in one sheet of paper follows quietly all the way to the door."},"ICON-0676":{"nm":"Cable Tidy Comb","on":"comb","de":"It combs tangled cords smooth and straight, like brushing hair. The jungle of cables behind the desk turns tidy in a few strokes. It's not only hair that gets tangled, the comb gently reminds."},"ICON-0677":{"nm":"Pen Holder Divider","on":"pen holder divider","de":"Pencils here, highlighters there, scissors in the end slot. It divides a small village inside one cup and gives each pen its place. With compartments, your hand no longer wanders. The start of a little order on the desk."},"ICON-0678":{"nm":"Monitor Memo Clip","on":"clip","de":"It hangs on the monitor's side and pushes \"today's to-do\" right up to eye level. A small notice board seen head-on, no chance to forget. One clip quietly catches a mind that keeps trying to put things off."},"ICON-0679":{"nm":"Drawer Sorting Tray","on":"tray","de":"Clips and rubber bands, pushpins and erasers. It gives each little tribe in the drawer its own room. When your hand reaches into compartments, search time shrinks and a corner of your heart grows lighter."},"ICON-0680":{"nm":"Dust Brush Tube","on":"tube","de":"A single speck of dust on a lens becomes a giant blot in a photo. So the brush waits inside its tube, always primed and spotless. A diligent fingertip that keeps a cleanliness no one ever notices."},"ICON-0681":{"nm":"Desk Mat Corner","on":"desk mat corner","de":"A hand-span of softness laid in one corner of the desk. Pens don't roll off, and instead of cold glass, a warm grain supports your wrist. A kindly surface that offers its place first, so the writing of a long night stays steady."},"ICON-0682":{"nm":"Mouse Cord Holder","on":"holder","de":"When the cord tangles, somewhere the heart tangles too. A touch that catches a stray strand in advance and lays it down neatly. Hardly noticed, it quietly tidies the grain of the desk—a small, diligent grooming."},"ICON-0683":{"nm":"Charging Dock Stand","on":"stand","de":"Tilt a device lying flat upright and the screen finally meets your eyes. Even the wait while it charges becomes a tidy time. To prop something up is to give even a thing at rest its proper posture."},"ICON-0684":{"nm":"Small Trash Bin Label","on":"label","de":"Even the smallest bin gets its own name. The single line \"toss it here\" calls a quiet order onto a cluttered desk. A label is, in the end, a small greeting that tells an object: your use is here."},"ICON-0685":{"nm":"Partition Board Pin","on":"pin","de":"It presses a sheet of paper firmly onto the board. Entrusting to the wall a feeling you don't want to forget. Today's resolve dangling on the pin's tip sways slightly in the breeze, catching you each time you pass."},"ICON-0686":{"nm":"Label Frame Chip","on":"chip","de":"One square border turns ordinary writing into a clear, single sentence. A chip that wraps a tidy dignity around easily-scattered memos. Not to confine, but to embrace important words so they aren't lost."},"ICON-0687":{"nm":"Clear Drawer Handle","on":"handle","de":"Put a handle on a see-through drawer and you can view what's inside without opening it carelessly. A hand-span of distance—visible, yet not approached. Even transparency needs manners, the drawer whispers."},"ICON-0688":{"nm":"Lid Lock Clip","on":"clip","de":"Leave it open and the scent and color quietly slip away. With one small clamp biting the lid shut, yesterday's color remains whole into tomorrow. Sealing is, in fact, the work of protecting what you cherish."},"ICON-0689":{"nm":"Desiccant Holder","on":"holder","de":"A small sentinel that loathes dampness and silently keeps its post. Keeping dry air close is the first condition of long storage, this tidy holder quietly reminds. That's how dryness is preserved."},"ICON-0690":{"nm":"Storage Basket Tag","on":"storage basket tag","de":"A little name tag on each basket. Decide which compartment holds what, and the time spent searching turns straight into resting time. Tidying is a kind note handed in advance to your future self."},"ICON-0691":{"nm":"Mini Partition Board","on":"board","de":"A small divider that quickly raises a cozy little room on your desk. With this one board, a quiet corner turned slightly away from the world appears. A snug spot all your own, fit for focus to settle in."},"ICON-0692":{"nm":"Bag Stand","on":"bag stand","de":"A stand that gently props up the backs of bags that kept toppling over. Just by standing them in a row, choosing the right one gets much easier. Standing things upright is caring for the next hand in advance."},"ICON-0693":{"nm":"Empty Slot Marker Chip","on":"chip","de":"A chip that deliberately marks emptiness. Leaving a spot to be filled is a plan in its own right. A blank is not laziness, but a hand-span of margin politely left open for something soon to arrive."},"ICON-0694":{"nm":"Toothbrush Cover Cap","on":"cap","de":"You grow more particular about the brush that touches your mouth. A little cap that blocks out even a single speck of dust. Tending to unseen cleanliness is the small devotion that opens each morning fresh."},"ICON-0695":{"nm":"Soap Dish Mesh","on":"soap dish mesh","de":"A mesh that gently lifts the soap so it won't go soft sitting in water. The principle that letting the water drain keeps it around longer—it quietly proves this every day from the lowest, smallest spot in the bathroom."},"ICON-0696":{"nm":"Shampoo Pump Clip","on":"clip","de":"It gently holds the pump head so one press dispenses just the right amount. The habit of using sparingly is the foundation of housekeeping that goes far. One small clip kindly keeps wastefulness in check."},"ICON-0697":{"nm":"Razor Hook Cap","on":"cap","de":"Sharp things get their own little house. Slot the razor into the cap and hang it, and both moisture and danger drain away. Handling sharpness carefully is, in the end, also a way of cherishing yourself."},"ICON-0698":{"nm":"Shower Towel Ring","on":"ring","de":"A long towel forms a loop and reaches the back you couldn't touch. Along that single grain where bubbles slide, a kindly warmth that scrubs your own back spreads warm through the whole bathroom."},"ICON-0699":{"nm":"Drain Strainer Pack","on":"drain strainer pack","de":"One small net that lets the water through and catches the bits. In a place no one sees, it quietly prevents clogs. The things working in the lowest spot keep the home's flow moving, the drain reminds us without a word."},"ICON-0700":{"nm":"Suction Hook Board","on":"board","de":"It makes a new spot on the wall without driving a single nail. Press it on, peel it off, and not even a trace remains. The art of staying a while and leaving no mark behind—the suction cup knows this light courtesy well."},"ICON-0701":{"nm":"Bathroom Slipper Tag","on":"bathroom slipper tag","de":"A pair set neatly before the threshold. The care of a home where you take off your shoes carries thoughtfully right up to the bathroom door. A name tag quietly assigns the spot for this small welcome that warms cold toes."},"ICON-0702":{"nm":"Mini Rinse Cup","on":"cup","de":"A small round cup that holds a mouthful for brushing teeth. In the brief moment of rinsing, it quietly takes on the start and end of a day. Not fancy, but by your side every day—simplicity is the longest-lasting housekeeping."},"ICON-0703":{"nm":"Duster Sleeve","on":"duster sleeve","de":"A sleeve slipped over the feathers of a brush that gathers dust as if stroking it. Like a bird that gently folds its wings when not in flight, a tool that knows where to rest stays by your side a long time."},"ICON-0704":{"nm":"Lint Roller Refill","on":"lint roller refill","de":"Peel one layer and a fresh, clean surface springs up beneath. The sticky inner leaves that gather fuzz and hair. Inside a round refill that fills up again when used up, the virtue of diligent repetition is wound."},"ICON-0705":{"nm":"Rag Clamp","on":"clamp","de":"A clamp that bites the rag firmly in place of your hand. It keeps a hand-span of distance between the cold floor and your fingers. One handle that takes on the grubby work makes hard cleaning far lighter."},"ICON-0706":{"nm":"Crevice Brush Cap","on":"cap","de":"A little hat that protects the soft tip of a thin brush made to dig into narrow gaps. A heart that tends even the corners hands can't reach. The one who cleans the unseen places grows the home's embrace a hand-span wider."},"ICON-0707":{"nm":"Spray Bottle Label Ring","on":"ring","de":"A small name tag perched softly on a spray bottle's shoulder. Whether it holds clear water or detergent, it tells you clearly in a single line. A label that erases confusion in advance is a quick-handed homemaker's long habit."},"ICON-0708":{"nm":"Tissue Refill Band","on":"band","de":"A band that fits a fresh roll into the empty spot and ties it firm. The simplest touch that joins what was cut off back together. Someone's heart, refilling before it runs out, is wound round this little loop."},"ICON-0709":{"nm":"Cleaning Glove Hook","on":"hook","de":"A hook that hangs damp gloves to dry just after the wet work is done. It offers the hardworking hands a place to rest a while. As the moisture slowly dries, a short break catches its breath for the next task."},"ICON-0710":{"nm":"Broom Hanger Pin","on":"pin","de":"Hang a broom upside down and the bristles stay straight instead of bending. A posture that waits upright for the next yard. A small but sturdy spot that helps it keep its shape even after its work is done."},"ICON-0711":{"nm":"Trash Bag Clip","on":"clip","de":"It bites the mouth of the bag firmly, sealing it tight so nothing leaks out. One touch closing the end snugly makes cleanup far neater. Finishing, in the end, begins with closing well."},"ICON-0712":{"nm":"Clothespin Bin","on":"bin","de":"A bin where clothespins, easily lost when scattered, all live together. It gives the little ones a shared home to stay in. Gather the small foot-soldiers of your fingertips in one place and you can find them at a glance when needed."},"ICON-0713":{"nm":"Sock Pairing Ring","on":"ring","de":"An odd sock always slips off somewhere. Tie each pair with a ring before washing and even after they dry soft and fluffy, the two won't part. Sorting is a small promise made in advance against disappearing."},"ICON-0714":{"nm":"Laundry Ball Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"It tumbles round and round inside the washer, tapping awake the grime soaked into clothes. A rhythm that strokes the laundry with its round body. Amid the rushing water, it carries laundry's old instinct—tapping—wound inside a pouch."},"ICON-0715":{"nm":"Wool Wash Measuring Cap","on":"cap","de":"Delicate clothes get just a delicate amount. A measuring cap that scoops exactly one capful of wool detergent. In one small marking lies the careful touch of handling wool. Easing off the excess is devotion too."},"ICON-0716":{"nm":"Fabric Mending Patch","on":"fabric mending patch","de":"A small patch gently laid over a worn spot. The fingertip heart that tends a frayed place instead of carelessly throwing it out. Each mended mark keeps, in fine detail, the pattern of years passed alongside that garment."},"ICON-0717":{"nm":"Drying Rack Pin","on":"pin","de":"A pin that quietly holds down the drying rack so the laundry doesn't blow away. Even on days the wash billows in the sun, it helps keep its place amid the swaying. The role of one small but dependable counterweight."},"ICON-0718":{"nm":"Underwear Wash Bag Tag","on":"underwear wash bag tag","de":"Delicate underwear is washed separately inside a net. A net that wraps the soft things snugly from the rushing water. One small tagged pouch reminds us that carefully protecting the fragile is housekeeping too."},"ICON-0719":{"nm":"Detergent Scoop Hook","on":"detergent scoop hook","de":"Hang the powder-detergent scoop neatly on the wall. No more fuss of dropping it in the tub and wetting your hand. The tidy habit of always keeping the same tool in the same spot is held firmly in this little hook."},"ICON-0720":{"nm":"Clothesline Stopper","on":"clothesline stopper","de":"It bites the clothesline's end tight, so even loaded with heavy laundry it won't slip loose. The final knot that holds out to the end, keeping a taut line from sagging. A solid finish hangs on this."},"ICON-0721":{"nm":"Pillowcase Label","on":"label","de":"The spot your cheek touches first each night, with a thumbnail-sized label stitched inside. Who reads the tiny print listing the wash temperature? Still, it's the closest guide of all, keeping watch beside a sleeping face."},"ICON-0722":{"nm":"Blanket Clip","on":"clip","de":"On a night with the window open, the blanket won't run off even as the breeze comes in. Because a clip with its mouth shut tight is gripping the corner. A wordless hand that holds the edge in place of the sleeper."},"ICON-0723":{"nm":"Night Light Shade Board","on":"board","de":"\"When light reaches your eyes, sleep slips away.\" With one shade board someone quietly set up, the light steps back and only faintly wets the foot of the bed. A small partition that lends a hand-span of darkness."},"ICON-0724":{"nm":"Bedside Gap Pocket","on":"bedside gap pocket","de":"Picture that gap between mattress and wall your hand could never reach. The remote that rolled away, the glasses too, now gather here. A pocket the bed quietly unfolds to catch the things you almost lost."},"ICON-0725":{"nm":"Glasses Storage Tray","on":"tray","de":"Take off your lenses and the world blurs soft, and a shallow dish catches that brief defenselessness. Come morning, even without fingers fumbling, the glasses are always waiting in the same spot."},"ICON-0726":{"nm":"Alarm Clock Stand","on":"stand","de":"Six a.m., atop the sturdy footing where the most hated sound rings out. Steady and unshaking, it props the clock and, in the end, opens someone's day. It bears, without a word, the blunt promise of waking."},"ICON-0727":{"nm":"Bedside Cable Holder","on":"holder","de":"The charging cable that used to slide down past the headboard no longer drops to the floor. Because a small holder gently grips the cord's end. Within arm's reach—a touch that has tidied the night's path."},"ICON-0728":{"nm":"Pajama Storage Band","on":"band","de":"A band that wraps once around neatly folded pajamas and ties them. Even easily-rumpled softness needs grooming. For tomorrow night's me, today's me rolls them up tidily—a small bit of readiness."},"ICON-0729":{"nm":"Scent Card Holder","on":"holder","de":"Set a scented card at a slant and, like turning a page, you turn the season by your nose. From lavender to citrus—it becomes a diary of that day written out in smell."},"ICON-0730":{"nm":"Key Dish Pad","on":"pad","de":"A corner by the entryway where keys used to clatter down. A dish lined with a soft pad swallows that sharp sound. A small mat quietly receives the first motion of the one who's come home."},"ICON-0731":{"nm":"Umbrella Drip Cap","on":"cap","de":"Rainwater trickles from the tip of the umbrella you carried in. One cap catches that drip neatly, so someone has, in advance, foreseen and stopped the little puddle that would have spread across the floor."},"ICON-0732":{"nm":"Mask Hook Chip","on":"chip","de":"A thumbnail-sized chip stuck on the wall by the door. Like the last ritual of heading out, a mask hangs here. A small memory device that holds eye level at the door so you don't forget what to bring."},"ICON-0733":{"nm":"Parcel Knife Sheath Cover","on":"cover","de":"A protective cover slipped over the blade that cuts open parcel boxes. It quietly covers the risk of a cut hidden behind the thrill of unboxing. An unnoticed thoughtfulness that opens the end of a wait safely."},"ICON-0734":{"nm":"Shoe Brush Stand","on":"stand","de":"The spot where a shoe brush rests, still damp after its scrubbing. Even holding moisture, the floor stays dry. Even a tool that creates cleanliness needs a place to rest, the small stand reminds us."},"ICON-0735":{"nm":"Visitor Memo Board","on":"board","de":"\"Stopped by for a moment.\" A short line of writing left on the entryway memo board. A little plaza where people who just missed each other share across time. On one square of paper, a greeting, a request, and a heart pile up overlapping."},"ICON-0736":{"nm":"Door Draft Stopper Roll","on":"door draft stopper roll","de":"The draft that seeped through the finger-wide gap under the door. A rolled-up stopper quietly blocks that passage. It holds one more layer of warmth in the room that had been leaking away unseen."},"ICON-0737":{"nm":"Door Stopper Charm","on":"door stopper charm","de":"A little charm that props the base of a wide-open door so it won't swing shut again. It holds its weight steady for the breeze and footsteps passing through. A kindly stubbornness that keeps the door open."},"ICON-0738":{"nm":"Entryway Light Switch Cover","on":"cover","de":"The entryway switch you fumbled for late at night. A glow-in-the-dark cover softly marks its place in the darkness. So your hand doesn't wander—a small guide that shines first, before the light comes on."},"ICON-0739":{"nm":"Cup Holder Pad","on":"pad","de":"The moment a cup set on the table starts to slide, one pad gently catches its foot. A coaster that holds its place calmly, leaving not a single mark even as water beads up."},"ICON-0740":{"nm":"Car Scent Clip","on":"clip","de":"A small scent clip hanging inside the car. Riding the vent's breeze, a faint fragrance slowly fills the narrow space. A kind comfort in the driver's seat, warming even the boredom of waiting at a red light with scent."},"ICON-0741":{"nm":"Seatbelt Cover","on":"cover","de":"A soft cover slipped over the belt that crosses your shoulder. The scratchiness against your neck slips away. Even a strap meant for safety can have kindness added, this hand-span of cloth says."},"ICON-0742":{"nm":"Parking Number Cover Board","on":"board","de":"A board that quietly covers the sign marking your spot in an underground garage before you take a photo. Everyone has information they'd rather not leave behind. One layer carefully erased from a scene of everyday life."},"ICON-0743":{"nm":"Bicycle Bell Cap","on":"cap","de":"Ring-ring. The bright greeting a bicycle offers at the corner of an alley. A cap over the bell guards that sound even in the rain. At one small ring, people smile and step aside."},"ICON-0744":{"nm":"Handlebar Grip Ring","on":"ring","de":"A ring that softly wraps the feel of the handlebar in your palm. Even after gripping and riding a long while, your hands don't go numb. The farther the road, the more the comfort of where you hold shortens that distance."},"ICON-0745":{"nm":"Helmet Label Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"A name sticker on the inside of a helmet. Among identical safety helmets, it cries out softly, \"this is mine.\" The most personal mark, inscribed atop the hardness that protects your head."},"ICON-0746":{"nm":"Wheel Reflector Cap","on":"cap","de":"A cap that only begins its work once the sun sets. It catches passing light and reflects the wheel clearly. In the dark, it sends with light the small signal \"someone's here.\""},"ICON-0747":{"nm":"Car Key Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A car key that used to get scratched, knocking against other keys in your pocket. A soft pouch wraps that surface snugly. The wish that something you hold every day stay scratch-free and last long is held within."},"ICON-0748":{"nm":"Suction Shelf Pin","on":"pin","de":"A suction shelf pin that sticks to the wall with no nail driven. Even a wall you don't want to mark gains one compartment of storage. The skill of hanging housekeeping in a room you're just borrowing, leaving no trace."},"ICON-0749":{"nm":"No-Drill Hook Board","on":"board","de":"Imagine being able to hang something without boring into the wall. A no-drill hook board quietly takes on light loads. The wish not to damage a borrowed space is held gracefully in one small hook."},"ICON-0750":{"nm":"Magnetic Organizer Bar","on":"magnetic organizer bar","de":"The sound of metal clicking into place. Sweep up the small tools scattered everywhere with a magnet and a hectic workbench lines up tidy in a row, a small satisfaction following along."},"ICON-0751":{"nm":"Gap-Filler Rod","on":"rod","de":"Picture that narrow, forgotten slot between the fridge and the wall. A slender rod fills that gap with usefulness. A thrifty bit of cleverness that draws storage out of space once deemed worthless."},"ICON-0752":{"nm":"Adhesive Pad Sheet","on":"sheet","de":"An adhesive pad sheet that, once stuck, holds even heavy things with ease. Peel it off and, amazingly, not a single mark remains. A quiet, stubborn strength that bears weight from out of sight."},"ICON-0753":{"nm":"Over-Door Hook Cap","on":"cap","de":"A hook cap that just hangs lightly over the top of a door. Bags and towels dangle right at hand's reach. A hanger born without a single nail adds one more bit of breathing room to a cramped space."},"ICON-0754":{"nm":"Cable Wall Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clip that gathers cords drooping down the wall into a single tidy line. The tangle behind the desk straightens into a clean run. Unseen tidying makes even the air of the room feel lighter."},"ICON-0755":{"nm":"Lamp Base Pad","on":"pad","de":"A pad you slip gently beneath the foot of a standing lamp. It leaves no scratches on the desk and stills even the faintest tremor. Even raising the light begins with a floor that won't shake."},"ICON-0756":{"nm":"Anti-Slip Adhesive Plate","on":"plate","de":"The mat that kept sneaking out from underfoot finally comes to a halt, for the adhesive plate grips the floor tight. An unnoticed safety net that quietly clears away the near-fall before it happens."},"ICON-0757":{"nm":"Precision Driver Cap","on":"cap","de":"\"This one tiny screw just won't come loose.\" A cap fitted over the tip of a precision screwdriver guards the blade. The most delicate tool of the fingertips, opening up the palm-sized world inside a machine."},"ICON-0758":{"nm":"Hex Wrench Ring","on":"ring","de":"A ring that threads several hex wrenches onto a single loop. The metal, lined up by size, fans out with a sweep. The tidy rhythm of a hand picking out just the one it needs in a single move."},"ICON-0759":{"nm":"Mini Tape Measure Charm","on":"charm","de":"A charm fixed to a mini tape measure that fits right in your palm. It dangles from a keyring and tags along anywhere. A little friend that measures and answers any length that suddenly piques your curiosity, right on the spot."},"ICON-0760":{"nm":"Screw Sorting Box","on":"box","de":"A sorting box where mismatched screws each find their own compartment. Even the little parts that once rolled about in a jumble gain order. The hand that learns to tidy first, before fixing anything."},"ICON-0761":{"nm":"Glue Nozzle Cap","on":"cap","de":"Closed, I won't harden; left open, I dry out, I live in the space between. With every drop that falls, somewhere something broken is being joined again. One little lid quietly guards the border between stillness and flow."},"ICON-0762":{"nm":"Level Keyring","on":"ring","de":"A palm-sized honesty dangling at the end of a bunch of keys. It's always this little bubble that's first to notice a tilted shelf. I carry in my pocket a friend who quietly tells me the world has gone a touch crooked."},"ICON-0763":{"nm":"Tweezer Tip Cap","on":"protective cap","de":"The sharper a thing is, the more it needs a garment to settle it down. Cap the tips gently and neither your hand nor the parts get hurt. The first courtesy in handling something sharp is to softly cover its point, and this little cap takes on that kindness."},"ICON-0764":{"nm":"Small Cutting Mat","on":"mat","de":"A board whose scars heal by themselves even after thousands of blade passes. The next task is laid over the cut, and again it mends. A quiet floor that gives of its own body so other things may be cut clean."},"ICON-0765":{"nm":"Repair Parts Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A pouch that purses its mouth shut so a single screw, a single spring won't vanish forever. The little things left over after a repair wait quietly here for their next turn. It's always such humble little compartments that keep things from being lost."},"ICON-0766":{"nm":"Snack Bag Clip","on":"clip","de":"Keeping an opened bag crisp comes down, in the end, to one decisive pinch. A small promise to leave no chance for it to go soggy. The habit of clamping the end down snugly saves tomorrow's snack."},"ICON-0767":{"nm":"Jelly Portion Cup","on":"cup","de":"To share one bag among many, you first have to split it fairly. The heart that scoops an equal share into each little cup. Sharing, I believe, begins with exactly the same amount, so no one feels left out."},"ICON-0768":{"nm":"Chocolate Foil Scrap","on":"chocolate foil scrap","de":"The silver that wrapped the sweetness crumples easily at the fingertips. Smooth it and it glints for a moment; fold it and it becomes a memory. A scrap of light that grows prettiest only after it's all eaten, take one more look before tossing it."},"ICON-0769":{"nm":"Snack Label Strip","on":"strip","de":"What's inside, how long it stays good, I speak for the silent bag in its place. The moment a single strip is stuck on, even a snack gains a name and a promise. Sorting is, in truth, the most tender way of remembering."},"ICON-0770":{"nm":"Candy Sorting Box","on":"box","de":"Don't put the sour ones and the sweet ones in the same compartment. The work of splitting them ahead of time so the hand won't hesitate. When the little boxes line up in a row, the joy of choosing quietly doubles."},"ICON-0771":{"nm":"Cookie Cushion Paper","on":"cookie cushion paper","de":"Thin paper tucked between cookies so they won't bruise along the way. The more fragile a thing is, the gentler the company it needs. Sometimes softness protects better than firmness."},"ICON-0772":{"nm":"Donut Box String","on":"string","de":"A single crossed knot takes charge of the cake's safe passage inside the box. It becomes a handle, a seal, a mark of giddy anticipation. The moment this string comes undone is somebody's birthday."},"ICON-0773":{"nm":"Bread Bag Tie","on":"tie","de":"Twist once, fold, and slip me on, and the bread's softness is sealed until tomorrow morning. A small, stubborn insistence on blocking out the air. Keeping something soft for a long time is always the job of something firm."},"ICON-0774":{"nm":"Snack Swap Tag","on":"snack swap tag","de":"Your share for me, my share for you. Remember the thrill of writing names on little tags and trading snacks that day? The paper on a sharing heart always has a friend's name written neatly across it."},"ICON-0775":{"nm":"Straw Stopper Cap","on":"cap","de":"When you pause for a moment between sips, you close me. So nothing spills, so it won't go cold, so it waits quietly right there. The work of a little stopper guarding the opening for the moment your lips return."},"ICON-0776":{"nm":"Tumbler Name Ring","on":"ring","de":"A little ring that says 'this one's mine' among a row of tumblers standing side by side. One color, and the mix-up gently melts away. A single ring is enough to mark, clearly, what's yours."},"ICON-0777":{"nm":"Cup Holder Sleeve","on":"cup holder sleeve","de":"A single layer of corrugated paper slipping in between a hot cup and your palm. A gesture of care tucked in so you won't get burned or lose your grip. Guarding the space between is what completes a safe, sound cup."},"ICON-0778":{"nm":"Ice Tray Label","on":"label","de":"There are people who write the date they made each batch of ice. With the belief that even coldness has an order. A single little label lets the time in the freezer flow honestly, one turn after another."},"ICON-0779":{"nm":"Tea Bag Tongs","on":"tongs","de":"Watching over the steeping time, you lift it out at just the right moment. The deft touch of knowing when to stop before it grows too strong. A tea's depth is decided less by how long you steep it than by the timing of when you pull it out."},"ICON-0780":{"nm":"Drip Filter Stand","on":"stand","de":"It holds up the filter and stands silent so the hot water can drip down slowly. It knows well that hurrying makes the aroma thin. Even the work of supporting patience calls for an unshakable stance."},"ICON-0781":{"nm":"Bottle Strap","on":"strap","de":"A strap that hangs the water bottle on your wrist or shoulder to walk along with you. A way of companionship that keeps it always near without you having to deliberately pack it. Sometimes a little tie is the kindest way not to forget."},"ICON-0782":{"nm":"Can Lid Cover","on":"cover","de":"It covers the mouth of a half-finished can to keep out dust and stop it going flat. A little hat that takes charge of freshness until the next sip. Even the act of gently covering what's been briefly opened holds its share of care."},"ICON-0783":{"nm":"Drink Coupon Holder","on":"holder","de":"The free tenth cup, it cradles the stamp card so that promise won't be lost. So the days filled in one square at a time don't get crumpled. Inside this holder, the diligent footsteps of a regular pile up."},"ICON-0784":{"nm":"Lunchbox Band","on":"band","de":"A band that hugs the lunchbox once around so the lid won't pop open. A small reassurance that no broth will leak inside the bag. The safe passage to lunchtime is in the keeping of this snug single loop."},"ICON-0785":{"nm":"Side-Dish Cup Set","on":"side-dish cup set","de":"Give each side dish its own place and the flavors won't mingle. Kimchi as kimchi, greens as greens, each distinct. The compartments these little cups make are the lunchbox's order, and a tenderness atop the cook's touch."},"ICON-0786":{"nm":"Chopstick Case","on":"case","de":"A little home that keeps clean and carries the chopsticks that shared all three meals of the day. A quiet companion that holds its neatness even inside a school bag. The care of carrying them along is, in the end, what makes a tidy meal."},"ICON-0787":{"nm":"Sauce Bottle Label","on":"label","de":"Soy sauce or vinegar? It gives clarity to the bottle you used to confuse. The moment a single line is stuck on, the fingertips' hesitation vanishes. The pace of a busy kitchen is quietly made by little markers like these."},"ICON-0788":{"nm":"Gimbap Rolling Sheet","on":"sheet","de":"A thin sheet of seaweed that rolls rice and filling into one body. Wrap it firmly so it won't fall apart when sliced. The thrill of a picnic morning comes rolled up round from this single layer."},"ICON-0789":{"nm":"Pick Holder Cup","on":"cup","de":"Stand the skewers and toothpicks all in one place, and the hand won't fumble when the moment comes. Giving even the pointy things a home of their own. Tidying is, in the end, a small kindness for the next hand to reach in."},"ICON-0790":{"nm":"Ice Pack Cover","on":"cover","de":"Wrap the ice pack in one more layer to hold onto the coldness a little longer. Keeping the bag from getting wet with condensation, too. Keeping the chill to the very end is always the work of this thick single layer."},"ICON-0791":{"nm":"Lunchbox Divider","on":"lunchbox divider","de":"A small wall raised so rice and side dishes won't trespass on each other's place. The peace of a single compartment where the broth won't spill across. A lunchbox split into sections holds, intact, the meticulous heart of the one who made it."},"ICON-0792":{"nm":"Meal Order Card","on":"card","de":"Soup first or rice first? A card that gently suggests today's course. A kind bit of guidance saying it tastes better eaten in order. It quietly tells you that even a meal has a flow, like a story."},"ICON-0793":{"nm":"Measuring Cup Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"A little sticker beside the markings pinpoints 'up to here.' A marker that gets the amount you always second-guessed right in one go. Accuracy springs from one small guideline like this."},"ICON-0794":{"nm":"Silicone Lid Handle","on":"handle","de":"A little handle that lets you lift a hot lid without burning your fingers. It quietly lends you the courage to open a steaming pot. Safety always comes from setting up a place to grip ahead of time."},"ICON-0795":{"nm":"Mini Clip Hanger","on":"mini clip hanger","de":"A little clip that gives a place to dishcloths and bags that had nowhere to hang. It turns a cluttered patch of wall into a tidy scene. One habit of hanging things up makes the kitchen feel that much lighter."},"ICON-0796":{"nm":"Oil Brush Cap","on":"cap","de":"Cover the tip of the oil brush and both dust and hardening pass it by. A hat that keeps that softness until the next dish. A small care for one's tools, in the end, preserves the flavor for a long time."},"ICON-0797":{"nm":"Salt Spoon Pot","on":"pot","de":"A little spoon that lives tucked inside the salt pot. It scoops up the precision of a single pinch, carefully, every time. The deft touch of seasoning is the heart this little spoon remembers."},"ICON-0798":{"nm":"Timer Magnet Board","on":"board","de":"Stuck to the fridge door, it counts the 3 minutes for ramen and times the 30 seconds for a workout. With a single magnet, time about to slip by lingers before your eyes. A diligent little circle that briefly pins the passing moment to the wall."},"ICON-0799":{"nm":"Pot Handle Cover","on":"cover","de":"A layer that wraps around so you won't grab a heated handle bare-handed. A little shield standing between the heat and your palm. Carrying a pot safely always begins with this soft wrapping."},"ICON-0800":{"nm":"Cutting Board Grip Rubber","on":"cutting board grip rubber","de":"When I'm laid under it, the cutting board slips no more. A scrap of rubber bracing from below whenever the chopping wobbles. Stability is the work of biting down firm in a place unseen."},"ICON-0801":{"nm":"Kitchen Glove Clip","on":"clip","de":"A place where the hand that moved ceaselessly before the flame pauses for a moment. Pin a flapping glove to the wall, and a short breather until the next meal begins. Tidying is, in the end, another name for tenderness."},"ICON-0802":{"nm":"Coffee Stirrer Holder","on":"holder","de":"Beside the counter, a spot where slender sticks lean shoulder to shoulder, stacked neatly. Poised to draw a swirl in someone's morning cup, lined up in rows just like a choir about to join voices."},"ICON-0803":{"nm":"Coaster Set Band","on":"band","de":"A band that gently catches the small clink of a glass meeting the table. Bundle the round coasters together and the welcome for guests is ready. Hospitality always begins, like this, in such small places first."},"ICON-0804":{"nm":"Syrup Label Chip","on":"chip","de":"A single name on the bottle. Sweet, rich, that one short word soothes a busy morning into something a little neater. A label is paper for jotting down a small promise in advance."},"ICON-0805":{"nm":"Dessert Pick Pot","on":"pot","de":"A pot where the pointed sticks that spear up a piece of fruit live together. Before they're planted like flags on a dessert plate, they wait quietly here for their turn. Even sweetness has its order."},"ICON-0806":{"nm":"Muddler Sleeve","on":"muddler sleeve","de":"A paper coat hugging a handful of stirring sticks. It soaks up the moisture a cold drink sheds, keeping the fingertips that hold the glass dry. Unseen care always comes from the edges."},"ICON-0807":{"nm":"Takeout Carrier Tag","on":"takeout carrier tag","de":"When two hands aren't enough, a little handle carries the cups for you. It holds the packed-up warmth so not a drop spills, seeing that warmth off to the corner of someone's alley."},"ICON-0808":{"nm":"Cafe Buzzer Cover","on":"cover","de":"A coat that quietly wraps the wait until the buzz goes off. Guarding the glowing ticket of your turn in a corner of the cafe, it holds, too, the thrill that your number will soon be called."},"ICON-0809":{"nm":"Stamp Coupon Ring","on":"ring","de":"Paper where filling all ten squares earns a cup on the house. With each stamp added, the name 'regular' grows a little too. A humble little joy, threaded onto a small ring."},"ICON-0810":{"nm":"Coffee Bean Sample Bag","on":"bag","de":"A bag that holds a handful of beans and offers the aroma first. The acidity and sweetness brushing past your nose, that first impression decides the fate of a cup. Fragrance arrives faster than any explanation."},"ICON-0811":{"nm":"Fridge Label Magnet","on":"magnet","de":"A little magnetic nametag that taps onto the fridge door. Jot down what went in and when, and even a side dish nearly forgotten reclaims its turn. Housekeeping is the work of pinning down flowing memory."},"ICON-0812":{"nm":"Storage Date Chip","on":"chip","de":"A scrap that clearly engraves the day something was packed. A little witness that quietly tells you, even days later, this is still fine. Freshness is kept by fingertips that remember the date."},"ICON-0813":{"nm":"Portion Container Band","on":"band","de":"A band that hugs the waist of a divvied-up container all the way around. It pulls the rattling lid in tight, keeping a small order inside the fridge. Tying something up resembles the work of tidying the heart."},"ICON-0814":{"nm":"Seal Clip Color Strip","on":"strip","de":"Colorful clips that bite snugly at a bag's mouth. Red for spicy, yellow for sweet, the hand knows just from the color. The kitchen's traffic lights guide the way, like this, without a word."},"ICON-0815":{"nm":"Freezer Pack Nametag","on":"tag","de":"A nametag laid gently atop something frozen. It reassures the frost-covered bag so it won't forget what it once was. A small note of greeting passed to ingredients gone into their winter sleep."},"ICON-0816":{"nm":"Vegetable Storage Net","on":"vegetable storage net","de":"A loose mesh that generously cradles soil-dusted vegetables. Grandmother's kitchen knew long ago that giving them room to breathe lets them last. Ventilation is a tender margin offered to vegetables."},"ICON-0817":{"nm":"Bottle Cap Sorting Cap","on":"cap","de":"A sorting cap that pairs up lids one by one, by size. Finding a lost match again is more tender than you'd think. Match up a fitting pair and the kitchen, too, falls into neater order."},"ICON-0818":{"nm":"Egg Tray Label","on":"label","de":"A marker neatly assigned to each of the ten little nests. The household wisdom of telling you to use the older eggs first. Even a single morning fried egg holds the heart of minding the order."},"ICON-0819":{"nm":"Leftover Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"Write 'this is mine!' and stick it on, and even the fridge knows a moment's peace. A cute little declaration of war, claiming the owner of the midnight snack in advance. Family rolls along today, too, on such trivial little treaties."},"ICON-0820":{"nm":"Utensil Rest Piece","on":"utensil rest piece","de":"A little piece that gently props up spoon and chopsticks so they won't touch the table directly. This small tidiness quietly raises the grace of a meal. Table manners grow, unnoticed, in places like these."},"ICON-0821":{"nm":"Napkin Holder Ring","on":"ring","de":"A ring that quietly slips on and holds a napkin that would scatter in the wind. It gathers the white paper waiting its turn to unfold, etching a small order neatly onto the table."},"ICON-0822":{"nm":"Table Mat Corner","on":"table mat corner","de":"A piece that gently presses down and soothes a mat's lifted corner. The table teaches every day that only when one end is held does the whole lie flat. Even a corner has its own share of responsibility."},"ICON-0823":{"nm":"Small Condiment Tray","on":"tray","de":"A little tray that holds a dish of soy sauce and a pinch of salt side by side. The wide embrace of a table that gives even an accompaniment its own place. Korean cuisine deepens in the heart that minds the little extras."},"ICON-0824":{"nm":"Table Number Chip","on":"chip","de":"The number called out as 'table so-and-so!' in a bustling restaurant. It assigns an order to the waiting and keeps fairness for all. What this single chip holds is a small promise, and a warm bowl soon to come."},"ICON-0825":{"nm":"Water Cup Marker Band","on":"band","de":"A band wrapped around a water glass to quietly tell whose it is. A little flag marking your spot among look-alike cups. At a shared table, such consideration heads off needless mix-ups."},"ICON-0826":{"nm":"Side Plate Sorting Pin","on":"pin","de":"A pin that sorts the side plates you serve onto by color. It draws a kindly line between yours and mine, making the joy of sharing all the cleaner. Share the warmth, but keep the hygiene tidy."},"ICON-0827":{"nm":"Menu Screen Board","on":"board","de":"The time spent pondering, slipped behind an open menu board. Even that brief hesitation over what to eat is, in truth, part of the meal. What shall it be today, it gently shields that little thrill."},"ICON-0828":{"nm":"Place Card Holder","on":"holder","de":"A small stand that holds a nametag upright. Whether at an event or a feast, it clearly announces that here is your place. Hospitality is completed only the moment a name is called."},"ICON-0829":{"nm":"Muffin Cup Sleeve","on":"muffin cup sleeve","de":"A paper coat snugly wrapping the plump waist of a fresh-baked muffin. It holds the warm body so it won't slip from your hand, keeping the warmth safe until the very moment you take a bite. Even dessert needs a coat."},"ICON-0830":{"nm":"Piping Bag Cap","on":"cap","de":"A stopper that keeps the tip of a cream-piping bag tightly shut. It seals the mouth snugly so not a drop leaks out while it rests. The little flower atop a cake blooms from this restraint."},"ICON-0831":{"nm":"Cookie Cutter Ring","on":"ring","de":"A round set of molds that cut dough into stars and bears. The same flour wakes into dozens of expressions through fingertips. Whatever you bake, what first touches the dough is always devotion."},"ICON-0832":{"nm":"Dough Scraper Charm","on":"dough scraper charm","de":"A flat hand that thriftily gathers the dough and cleanly divides it. That diligence of minding even the handful stuck to the bowl decides the volume of a loaf. Baking is the work of a sparing hand."},"ICON-0833":{"nm":"Measuring Spoon Board","on":"measuring spoon board","de":"A board that lays out measuring spoons neatly, without a wobble, a teaspoon, half a tablespoon. One precise spoonful sets the balance of flavor straight. Behind the phrase 'a deft touch' hides, in truth, careful measuring."},"ICON-0834":{"nm":"Oven Mitt Hook","on":"hook","de":"A hook to hang the mitt that stood guard before a hot oven. The thick hand that fended off burns lingers within reach even while resting. Safety always begins with what stays in its proper place."},"ICON-0835":{"nm":"Cooling Rack Clip","on":"clip","de":"Tongs that neatly bite onto the rack where fresh-baked treats cool. It holds them so they won't shift while the steam escapes, waiting together for the crispness to be complete. Even cooling calls for a handful of patience."},"ICON-0836":{"nm":"Cake Topper Pick","on":"cake topper pick","de":"A pick that perches the five letters of 'Happy Birthday' atop a cake. Just before the candles go out, this little flag lights up one person's day the brightest. Celebration shows best when raised high."},"ICON-0837":{"nm":"Sugar Powder Shaker","on":"shaker","de":"A shaker that holds one last light scatter. It settles like white snow over a fresh-baked dessert, turning an ordinary slice into a little gift. The finishing touch comes from the lightest hand."},"ICON-0838":{"nm":"Triangle Gimbap Label","on":"label","de":"Peel the wrapper in order 1, 2, 3 and the seaweed comes back crisp on that triangle. A single line that lets you spot at a glance a hearty friend from the convenience store at dawn. The peckish nights after late study cling right here."},"ICON-0839":{"nm":"Cup Noodle Lid Holder","on":"holder","de":"A prop that quietly presses down so the lid won't lift during the 3-minute wait. It takes the place of the chopsticks once laid on top to keep the steam from escaping. That brief stretch while the noodles cook is the most thrilling moment of a midnight snack."},"ICON-0840":{"nm":"Hot Bar Skewer Cap","on":"cap","de":"A little cap that grips the end of a skewer snugly. It guards so it's easy to bite into, with not a drop of sauce on your hand. The fun of snacking outside a bunsik shop is always completed by such small things."},"ICON-0841":{"nm":"Plastic Bag Handle","on":"handle","de":"Hook it on your fingers and the plastic creaks faintly. The weight of the groceries leans to one side, and the walk home leaves a red mark on your palm. Within that light sound, a day's worth of housekeeping hangs and sways, heavy."},"ICON-0842":{"nm":"Receipt Fold Clip","on":"clip","de":"Fold a long-unspooled receipt in half and snap it shut, and the day's spending becomes one tidy bundle. As the ink-scented paper stacks up, the small memories of housekeeping fall neatly into order too."},"ICON-0843":{"nm":"Microwave Tag","on":"tag","de":"Before the ding sounds, the tag quietly reckons the time to warm. A small guide noting how many minutes and seconds, and the name of what to heat. Even the heart waiting its turn to grow warm has markings like these."},"ICON-0844":{"nm":"Discount Sticker Roll","on":"discount sticker roll","de":"Each time you peel off a square, a sticky little squeak tickles your fingertips. When the red numbers unspool in a row, someone's shopping basket grows a little lighter. A roll of small kindness, coiled round and waiting."},"ICON-0845":{"nm":"Sauce Pouch Ring","on":"ring","de":"Something tangy bursts at the corner of your mouth and an ordinary day turns a touch sweeter. When the pouch dangling from a round ring sways with each step, one small sweetness follows me all day in my pocket."},"ICON-0846":{"nm":"Convenience Store Basket Chip","on":"chip","de":"Grip it and the plastic flexes lightly. A shop bright with light late at night, deep enough to hold a couple of triangle gimbap and one drink. A kindly vessel of just one meal's worth, where even alone you aren't lonely."},"ICON-0847":{"nm":"Macaron Box Band","on":"band","de":"A single band gently embraces the box so the colorful macarons won't scatter. Anyone who's received a gift knows by their fingertips that the thrill just before untying the ribbon is, in fact, the sweetest."},"ICON-0848":{"nm":"Fruit Net Clip","on":"clip","de":"Gather the mouth of the mesh and pinch it shut, and the scent of apples slips softly through the netting. One small hand that holds them so they won't tumble out. A wordless, tender urging to eat them soon, before they go soft."},"ICON-0849":{"nm":"Jam Jar Lid Cloth","on":"jam jar lid cloth","de":"It calls to mind my grandmother's summer kitchen, covering jar lids with a round cloth and tying them with a rubber band. A single checkered swatch seals in the sweet time and devotion of jam ripening. A deft touch is stored away, covered, like this."},"ICON-0850":{"nm":"Cookie Tie Ribbon","on":"ribbon","de":"Tuck fresh-baked cookies into cellophane and twist the tie shut, and the scent of butter seeps right to the ends of the ribbon. The hand offering something homemade to someone always trembles a little. A knot that ties up the heart along with it."},"ICON-0851":{"nm":"Chocolate Divider Board","on":"board","de":"Square by square, it sets a place so the chocolates won't touch each other. So they won't melt, so they won't be crushed. What a little divider guards to the very end is, in the end, one whole piece of heart to hand to someone."},"ICON-0852":{"nm":"Tea Gift Label","on":"label","de":"Atop the label wrapped around a tea bag, a name written out neatly by hand. The little paper hints in advance that brewing it brings the scent of grass rising with the steam. A cup that warms your hands even before you drink."},"ICON-0853":{"nm":"Candy Bottle Necklace","on":"candy bottle necklace","de":"A necklace made by looping a string around the neck of a bottle full of colorful candy. With each step, a small sound like rolling beads tumbles inside. A proud treasure of childhood, wearing sweetness around the neck."},"ICON-0854":{"nm":"Gift Spoon Charm","on":"gift spoon charm","de":"With one little charm dangling at the end of the handle, an ordinary spoon becomes a gift before you know it. A light, clear jingle with each scoop. A tiny ornament that adds a small flourish to the heart you're giving."},"ICON-0855":{"nm":"Snack Thank-You Tag","on":"snack thank-you tag","de":"The wish to give back even a little of what you received. A thank-you tag tucked gently onto a snack bag. In place of the 'thank you' you couldn't quite finish saying, a small greeting passes quietly from hand to hand."},"ICON-0856":{"nm":"Masking Tape Sample Ring","on":"ring","de":"Patterns cut and stuck a span at a time line up in a little strip. While you slowly pick which color you like with your fingertips, the very thought of decorating tints the day in many hues. A swatch row where even deliberating is a joy."},"ICON-0857":{"nm":"Sticker Tweezer Cap","on":"cap","de":"Cap the pointed tip of the tweezers and even a fingernail-sized sticker stays unharmed. A precise hand that gently lifts up corners your fingers could never reach. Handling what you love always comes with a little caution."},"ICON-0858":{"nm":"Diary Corner Seal","on":"diary corner seal","de":"Stick seals on the four corners of a diary and the flapping pages settle down as if by magic. The feel of paper pressed gently, a small rite that neatly seals today away. A record grows firm starting from the corners."},"ICON-0859":{"nm":"Punching Guide Board","on":"board","de":"A board that tells you in advance where to punch a hole. Line it up quietly along the dotted line and there's no going astray. The heart that gauges once more without rushing, accuracy always comes quietly from that one beat of small ease."},"ICON-0860":{"nm":"Paper Scrap Tray","on":"tray","de":"The paper crumbs left from scissor-work gather softly into the tray. A brief lodging for the little scraps, so the desk won't get messy. The aftermath of crafting is tidied, like this, without a sound."},"ICON-0861":{"nm":"Color Ink Pad","on":"pad","de":"Press the pad lightly and lift, and color spreads moist on your fingertips. Red, yellow, blue, a small rainbow that comes off in a single stamp. A soft little spot for planting color, tap by tap, onto white paper."},"ICON-0862":{"nm":"Decorative Tape Roll","on":"decorative tape roll","de":"The pattern unspooling round and round goes on without end. Peel off a span and stick it on, and flowers bloom in a once-plain spot. A roll of small magic, coiled round and waiting, growing prettier as your hand goes."},"ICON-0863":{"nm":"Theme Stamp Cap","on":"cap","de":"A little hat that snugly wraps the stamp head so the ink won't dry. It quietly keeps watch so the next pattern stays crisp. A color stored away well blooms just as vivid on the next sheet of paper."},"ICON-0864":{"nm":"Deco Punch Scrap","on":"deco punch scrap","de":"The little pieces the punch drops with a tap. Confetti of colored paper cut into stars and hearts and petals gathers in a soft heap on your palm. Little jewels too pretty to throw away, so you end up sticking them somewhere again."},"ICON-0865":{"nm":"Bobbin Label Ring","on":"ring","de":"A small label with the name of each colored thread written on every bobbin. A tender marker that points to its place before it gets tangled. Tangled thread, and the heart too, are far easier to unravel with a single nametag."},"ICON-0866":{"nm":"Needle Book Cover","on":"cover","de":"A soft cover for the felt-page book where needles are stuck close together. Open it and the sewing tools lie neatly arrayed to greet me. A little volume that tenderly puts the pointy things to sleep, so fingertips won't get hurt."},"ICON-0867":{"nm":"Fabric Sample Ring","on":"ring","de":"Rough or soft, the slow time of tracing the grain of cloth, one by one, with your fingertips to choose. Among the swatches gathered neatly by color, before becoming a garment, fabric quietly waits to be touched first."},"ICON-0868":{"nm":"Embroidery Hoop Loop","on":"loop","de":"Set the cloth in the round hoop and tighten, and it goes taut like a drumhead. A small signal that you're ready to embroider stitch by stitch. What the hoop holds firm is not the cloth, but the focused heart."},"ICON-0869":{"nm":"Button Sorting Capsule","on":"button sorting capsule","de":"Buttons that used to roll about settle in neatly by color into each capsule slot. The household wisdom of dividing them into small portions so none get lost. Even gathering scattered things takes this much devotion."},"ICON-0870":{"nm":"Tailor's Chalk Holder","on":"holder","de":"A holder that grips tailor's chalk, the kind that draws lines on cloth, comfortably in hand. It braces firmly something that breaks easily. The calm first resolve before picking up the scissors, that the first line straight makes the garment straight too."},"ICON-0871":{"nm":"Pin Jar","on":"jar","de":"Inside the clear jar, sewing pins clink and rattle against one another. Hold it to the light and a tiny gleam settles on each needle's tip. A snug little vessel that gathers in one place, and gently puts to rest, things dangerous when scattered."},"ICON-0872":{"nm":"Mending Tape Roll","on":"mending tape roll","de":"A magic strip that quietly sticks fast when ironed over a torn spot. Without a single stitch, a worn garment gently mends. The heart that patched and wore on rather than threw away is coiled, layer by layer, inside the round roll."},"ICON-0873":{"nm":"Patch Template Paper","on":"patch template paper","de":"A sheet of template paper with the patch shape drawn in advance. A dotted line kindly guides the path the scissors will take. Sketching out first the outline of what you want to make, the thrill always begins from this faint underdrawing."},"ICON-0874":{"nm":"Watercolor Jar Cap","on":"cap","de":"Cap it over the jar's mouth and not a drop spills, no matter how the tinted water sloshes. It covers even the worry of murky rinse water spreading across the desk. A quiet stopper that silently guards the place where you paint."},"ICON-0875":{"nm":"Pastel Protector Band","on":"band","de":"Wrap a band around a pastel that leaves a powdery smudge, and your fingers get less dirty. Paper that gently wraps the soft color so it won't crumble. The softer it is, the more gently you must hold it, so it colors gently on paper too."},"ICON-0876":{"nm":"Colored Pencil Extender Cap","on":"cap","de":"Fit a cap onto the end of a worn-down colored pencil and one stub grows long again. The heart that won't easily toss something just because it's gotten short. From the fingertips that use it to the very end, the drawing's color deepens richer down to the last square."},"ICON-0877":{"nm":"Brush Wash Cup Hook","on":"hook","de":"Hang the rinse cup on a hook and the water drops fallen from the brush trickle down. Before painting the next color, the short, clear stillness of rinsing the brush. Even in that sound of growing clean, a quiet rhythm flows."},"ICON-0878":{"nm":"Palette Knife Cap","on":"cap","de":"A little cap that snugly covers the blade of the knife that spreads and scrapes paint. It quietly keeps the sharp tip from going dull. The texture of thickly laid color is born from this one well-tended edge."},"ICON-0879":{"nm":"Canvas Clip","on":"clip","de":"A sturdy clip that pulls canvas cloth taut over a frame and holds it fast. Bite it tight and the painting surface stretches drum-tight. Only with an unshaking ground can the brushstrokes that run across it roam freely."},"ICON-0880":{"nm":"Drawing Board Strap","on":"strap","de":"Sling the strap over your shoulder and the board follows behind your back. Settle down anywhere and that becomes your very own studio. A little studio worn on the back, setting off lightly in search of a scene to draw."},"ICON-0881":{"nm":"Acrylic Paint Tube","on":"acrylic paint tube","de":"Add one drop of water and it's dawn; one less and it's midnight. The same blue opens a different sky every time at the fingertips. The moment you squeeze out a tube, today's color of heart spreads across the paper."},"ICON-0882":{"nm":"Gradient Sample Sheet","on":"gradient sample sheet","de":"This paper knew first that a sunset doesn't redden all at once. Little steps crossing from pale to deep. The eye walks slowly between them, gently following the time of color ripening."},"ICON-0883":{"nm":"Crochet Hook Cap","on":"cap","de":"A thimble-small shield you fit on before the yarn digs into your finger. A hand long practiced at knitting knows. Only by staying unhurt can you carry it tenderly all the way to the final stitch."},"ICON-0884":{"nm":"Knitting Ring Marker","on":"knitting ring marker","de":"One marker and where you've reached comes clear again. The reassurance of never counting the same stitch twice. The heart, too, only that way, when you gently mark the place you've come from, keeps from losing its way."},"ICON-0885":{"nm":"Row Counter Charm","on":"row counter charm","de":"Quiet proof of one finished row piles up, square by square. Even work that seemed endless, counted off one at a time, is suddenly past the halfway mark. A small tally carries today's heart through to the end."},"ICON-0886":{"nm":"Thread Tail Tidy Pin","on":"pin","de":"Leave a loose thread end as it is and there's no telling where the next knot will tangle. A touch that tidies, in advance, a place that won't be seen. Tenderness, more often than not, moves first in places out of sight, like this."},"ICON-0887":{"nm":"Knot Practice Cord","on":"cord","de":"An overhand knot, a bow knot, a ring knot. You tie and untie the same cord until the hand memorizes the form. When clumsy fingertips turn smooth one night out of nowhere, that single strand is the first to know."},"ICON-0888":{"nm":"Yarn Label Band","on":"band","de":"A little strip noting on each skein its weight and color. It's a habit born of nights spent searching in vain for the same yarn only after it ran out. A record is a tender memo to your future self."},"ICON-0889":{"nm":"Gauge Ruler Piece","on":"gauge ruler piece","de":"How many stitches fit in 10 centimeters, that small number sets the size of a whole garment. That a palm-sized piece holds the measure of the whole is, when you lift it, a rather weighty thing."},"ICON-0890":{"nm":"Buttonhole Marker","on":"buttonhole marker","de":"Before sewing on a button, you mark a single dot where to make the hole first. Thanks to that soon-to-vanish mark, the placket won't go crooked. Devotion, more often than not, lingers quietly in a place that goes unseen in the end."},"ICON-0891":{"nm":"Small Tassel Loop","on":"loop","de":"Like the tassel at the end of a norigae, a small loop creates the sway. The eye always lingers on what dangles and quietly stirs. A texture that comes softly alive each time the wind passes by."},"ICON-0892":{"nm":"Mini Paint Bottle","on":"bottle","de":"Handling paint properly is not about hoarding it but using it precisely. A color where one drop is enough, gauged with a hand kept beside the little bottle. Restraint comes from setting greed down, just once."},"ICON-0893":{"nm":"Small Sanding Stick","on":"small sanding stick","de":"You start on the coarse side and move gradually to the fine. There's no surface anywhere that grows smooth in a single pass. From fingertips that lower the grain one step at a time, a once-rough spot slowly turns soft."},"ICON-0894":{"nm":"Model Clip Stand","on":"stand","de":"Hold a glued part in your hand and you leave fingerprints. Clip it gently and your hands go free, and the drying quietly finishes on its own. Even waiting grows lighter when someone props it up for you."},"ICON-0895":{"nm":"Glue Work Plate","on":"plate","de":"Let a drop of glue fall on the desk and the trace lingers long. The habit of laying down a single plate first. Half the work, perhaps, begins from that very wish not to soil the place."},"ICON-0896":{"nm":"Parts Sorting Compartment","on":"parts sorting compartment","de":"Mix dozens of same-shaped parts together and assembly soon becomes a maze. The touch of dividing them into each compartment cuts down, in advance, the time you'd spend lost. Tidying is a kindness handed to your future self."},"ICON-0897":{"nm":"Assembly Order Chip","on":"chip","de":"A little chip noting which numbered part to fit first. Keep to the order and it won't easily fall apart. A model, and any day built up step by careful step, grows sturdy upon that quiet promise."},"ICON-0898":{"nm":"Mini Brush Hook","on":"mini brush hook","de":"Lay a used brush down and the bristles get pressed and bent. A spot to hang it upside down to drain the moisture. Those who keep their tools close for a long time are, if anything, busier and more tender after the work is done."},"ICON-0899":{"nm":"Plastic Scrap Pot","on":"pot","de":"A pot where the offcuts snipped from the frame quietly gather. They seem discarded, yet one day they return as a small detail. The pot knows, waiting silently, that even leftovers have their turn."},"ICON-0900":{"nm":"Finishing Spray Cap","on":"cap","de":"The final coat, sprayed too close, just runs straight down. From a span's distance, lightly, lightly. Laying on a gloss is, perhaps, also practice in setting the heart's greed down just once."},"ICON-0901":{"nm":"Lead Refill Case","on":"case","de":"Thin pencil lead snaps so easily inside a pocket. Laid neatly in a little tube, not a single stick goes to waste. Tidying up is, in the end, a quiet way of caring for tomorrow's self in advance."},"ICON-0902":{"nm":"Eraser Sleeve","on":"eraser sleeve","de":"A tiny paper coat worn over an eraser. The blacker it grows with use, the more traces of corrections it has gathered. To erase is also a gentle permission to start over from the beginning."},"ICON-0903":{"nm":"Nib Storage Tube","on":"tube","de":"Pen nibs crack when they dry out and bend when they're bumped. One small tube to lay them down separately keeps the grain of your writing intact for a long time. A tool handled gently glides gently in return."},"ICON-0904":{"nm":"Fountain Pen Ink Sample","on":"fountain pen ink sample","de":"Inks you test one drop at a time. A color you thought was teal becomes a deep sea on the page. Color is something you always have to meet in person; the shade you picture in your mind so often misses the mark."},"ICON-0905":{"nm":"Book Dart Tin","on":"tin","de":"A little flag tucked into the spot where you left off. Open the book next time, and yesterday's self waves and waits for you. Even the place you paused becomes a promise, the gentle work of that small marker."},"ICON-0906":{"nm":"Flag Tab Pack","on":"flag tab pack","de":"Peel off one sheet and stick it down, and the story starts again right from there. When the little flags line up along a book's edge, scattered thoughts gather neatly into a single map."},"ICON-0907":{"nm":"Clip-Gathering Magnet","on":"magnet","de":"A small magnet that sweeps up scattered clips in one go. The smaller a thing is, the easier it's lost, so one gathering force quietly rescues a messy desk. There is gentleness even in pulling things close."},"ICON-0908":{"nm":"Pencil Cap Set","on":"pencil cap set","de":"Little hats that wrap pencil tips and guard the inside of your bag. Anything sharp is bound to poke something, so it needs a hand to cover it gently. Kept keen, yet kept from causing harm."},"ICON-0909":{"nm":"Desk Nameplate Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"The moment you write your name and stick it on the desk, that spot finally becomes someone's own. When even a hand's-width of space gets an owner, the very way you settle your heart there changes."},"ICON-0910":{"nm":"Jump Rope Handle Cap","on":"cap","de":"A cap slipped on before the handle ends fray and split. The rhythm of a rope spun over a thousand times is remembered by the palm before the head. A beat carved into the body is not easily forgotten."},"ICON-0911":{"nm":"Yoga Ring Strap","on":"strap","de":"Hold the ring and slowly open your body. The tighter the strap pulls, the more your stiff shoulders unwind, layer by layer. Stretching is less about forcing a pull and more about waiting quietly until the body opens."},"ICON-0912":{"nm":"Ping-Pong Ball Case","on":"case","de":"A white ball so light it rolls far away, and crumples flat the moment you step on it. One little case protects that most fragile ball until the next match. Sturdiness often comes from being softly wrapped."},"ICON-0913":{"nm":"Badminton Grip Tape","on":"badminton grip tape","de":"Wind one neat layer around a handle that slips with sweat. On a well-wrapped grip, the racket becomes part of your hand. The secret of playing by feel rather than force hides in this thin single layer."},"ICON-0914":{"nm":"Little Score Chip","on":"chip","de":"One point, then another. Moving small chips, you stack the score up piece by piece. When the count is visible, the match grows clearer, and the courage to catch up by a single point quietly rises too."},"ICON-0915":{"nm":"Sneaker Direction Clip","on":"clip","de":"Neatly placed toes always face the same way. A small turn of the hand when you take them off. One little tidying makes tomorrow morning's steps feel that much lighter."},"ICON-0916":{"nm":"Whistle Lanyard","on":"lanyard","de":"Hang a whistle around your neck and you gain the right to say stop. The sight of a whole field halting at once at a single short blast. The hearts that trust that small sound gather and become a promise."},"ICON-0917":{"nm":"Ball Pump Needle Tube","on":"tube","de":"Even a deflated ball turns taut again with one thin needle. That needle kept safe in a little tube renders the whole pump useless the moment it's lost. When the smallest thing matters most."},"ICON-0918":{"nm":"Mini Cone Marker","on":"mini cone marker","de":"From here to there, a little cone draws a boundary you couldn't see. With no line at all, people naturally fall in line by following the marker. Order quietly grows from small signals like this."},"ICON-0919":{"nm":"Token Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A pouch that gathers jingling tokens in one place. Cinch the mouth and nothing scatters. Even small, trifling things need a place to be held before they can do their part, the pouch shows without a word."},"ICON-0920":{"nm":"Card Shuffle Mat","on":"mat","de":"On a slick desk, cards don't sit well in the hand. One mat makes both shuffling and picking up far smoother. Even in playing well, there's a gentle preparation of choosing the surface first."},"ICON-0921":{"nm":"Board Tile Corner Guard","on":"board tile corner guard","de":"When a board game night ends, someone quietly tends to the board's four corners first. Because they know a deepened crease warps the next round. In the fingertips that smooth the edges lies the wish to play together again tomorrow."},"ICON-0922":{"nm":"Dice Cup Lid","on":"lid","de":"That brief instant when everyone shakes, rolls, and holds their breath together. It's a little ceiling that keeps the dice from leaping out. Under the lid, today's luck catches its breath a moment, then rattles its way out."},"ICON-0923":{"nm":"Tile Aligning Board","on":"board","de":"The more thrilled someone is by the play, the more crooked their row gets. Quietly nudging tilting tiles back into a neat line. Alignment is a hand that gently takes in someone's giddy impatience."},"ICON-0924":{"nm":"Score Chip Tin","on":"tin","de":"The fuller a tin of chips gets, the hotter the game grows too. When the round scores clatter together in your palm, that sound becomes a joy before winning or losing ever does."},"ICON-0925":{"nm":"Turn Marker Ring","on":"ring","de":"A little ring that tells you it's your turn now. For that one moment you slide it over a notch, everyone's eyes gather quietly on me. A loop that turns slowly between waiting and anticipation."},"ICON-0926":{"nm":"Game Piece Stand","on":"stand","de":"The more easily a piece topples, the firmer its footing must be. One stand holds its place even on a slightly wobbling board. The small thing must hold up so the big thing above can stand tall."},"ICON-0927":{"nm":"Rulebook Clip","on":"clip","de":"A rulebook always sneaks its pages over while left open. Before the breeze lets the pages run off, this clamp gently bites down one page. The rules must be held in place for the play to last to the end."},"ICON-0928":{"nm":"Pick Case Strap","on":"strap","de":"A guitar pick always slips your fingers right at the most exciting part. One strap dangling from the case stops that little escape. Only those who've lived a night when the music stopped are grateful for this strap."},"ICON-0929":{"nm":"Reed Storage Tube","on":"tube","de":"A reed loses its voice the moment it dries. Inside a moist tube, a slender sliver of cane waits for the next performance. A place to rest your breath first, before you blow it back in."},"ICON-0930":{"nm":"String Winder","on":"winder","de":"When a string slackens, the pitch quietly sags too. Slowly turning the handle to reclaim the tension; care always comes from the wrist. A tidy sound begins from small acts of order like this."},"ICON-0931":{"nm":"Instrument Cloth","on":"instrument cloth","de":"When a performance ends, a faint sweat lingers on the instrument too. One sweep with a soft cloth brings back the shine and lets today's notes settle calmly. A caring heart always shows in the finishing."},"ICON-0932":{"nm":"Tuning Pin Cover","on":"cover","de":"Left bare, tuning pins rust before you know it. One small cover slows the seasons of the metal by a beat. Those who tend the unseen corners first are the ones who play for a long time."},"ICON-0933":{"nm":"Music Stand Clip Light","on":"music stand clip light","de":"Backstage in the dark, there are moments when only the score must be bright. A little lamp clipped to the stand, gently letting its light pour down. A handful of glow lighting the way so the notes don't lose their path."},"ICON-0934":{"nm":"Practice Mute Cap","on":"cap","de":"Dawn practice always quietly quarrels with the neighbors' sleep. Slip on one cap and a booming sound shrinks to a whisper. There is music that grows while guarding someone's sweet slumber."},"ICON-0935":{"nm":"Drum Pad Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"Little markers stuck onto a drum pad. Where to strike for which sound; the eyes learn the way before the hands memorize it. A beat is carved slowly into the body like this."},"ICON-0936":{"nm":"Melody Memo Chip","on":"chip","de":"A hummed melody vanishes fast if you don't catch it. A few bars hastily jotted on a chip sometimes grow into a whole song one day. Inspiration always returns to the hand that diligently takes notes."},"ICON-0937":{"nm":"Book Cover Band","on":"band","de":"It's a nuisance when a half-read book flops open on its own inside a bag. One band gently ties the pages so they stay obedient. A promise to fold things neatly for the next page."},"ICON-0938":{"nm":"Page Holder Ring","on":"ring","de":"A day you want to hold a book open in one hand and sip warm coffee. A ring slipped onto your finger holds the pages for you. A little ease begins from small inventions like this."},"ICON-0939":{"nm":"Reading Timer Chip","on":"chip","de":"Sit down for just one chapter and the night somehow grows deep. Press the chip to set a time, and even reading gains a rest stop. The dearer the thing you love, the more you need the gentle courage to know when to stop."},"ICON-0940":{"nm":"Book Corner Guard Cap","on":"guard cap","de":"The dearer the book, the more its corners quietly wear away first. Slip on one cap and the cover's corners are kept rounded and safe. A small armor you tuck on to hold close what you wish to keep for a long, long time."},"ICON-0941":{"nm":"Reading Note Band","on":"band","de":"There are moments when a single line drops a weight into your chest. A reflection copied onto a band stays on that page like a bookmark. The warm temperature of an underline, known only to the one who read it."},"ICON-0942":{"nm":"Library Return Tag","on":"library return tag","de":"The due date always arrives a day too early. When the date written on the tag quietly nudges your back, even a borrowed book gains the courtesy of an ending. For the next person's hands, the library waits like that."},"ICON-0943":{"nm":"Book Light Clip","on":"clip","de":"A night you stay awake to read alone beside sleeping family. One small light clipped to the book's edge is enough. You don't have to push all the darkness away; for one page, a quiet stretch of time will do."},"ICON-0944":{"nm":"Book Scent Card","on":"card","de":"Old books smell of sunlight and paper mingled together. This card, said to hold that scent in a single sheet, opens to revive a used-bookstore alley at the tip of your nose for a moment. Memory bookmarks pages with scent too."},"ICON-0945":{"nm":"Read-To Marker Pin","on":"pin","de":"How far did I read? A little pin that erases that helpless question. Pin it to the last sentence and tomorrow's self won't wander anymore. A gentle marker that remembers the place you paused in your stead."},"ICON-0946":{"nm":"Phone Strap Charm","on":"charm","de":"One charm hung on a phone strap makes a person look a little different. A favorite color, a favorite shape. A small taste held in the hand gently sways the mood of the day."},"ICON-0947":{"nm":"Camera Lens Guard Cap","on":"guard cap","de":"The fate of travel photos rests on a single lens. The moment you lift off the guard cap is the heart's readiness to press the shutter. A small ritual, the first to open its eyes before capturing a scene."},"ICON-0948":{"nm":"Charging Port Plug","on":"charging port plug","de":"Dust inside a bag always targets the charging port first. Block that little opening with one plug and the port stays clean for a long time. Here is a diligence that tends even to the unseen gaps."},"ICON-0949":{"nm":"Phone Grip Pop Ring","on":"ring","de":"Propping a phone at an angle just to watch a video in comfort. Pop out the ring on the back and both hand and screen breathe easier. One little raised stand stretches out an easy evening hour."},"ICON-0950":{"nm":"Screen Wipe Patch","on":"screen wipe patch","de":"A screen full of fingerprints somehow blurs the heart as well. One swipe with a patch and the world comes into focus again. Cleanliness is sometimes a brief task of a single finger."},"ICON-0951":{"nm":"SIM Pin Case","on":"case","de":"A SIM ejector pin is a sprite that vanishes only when you truly need it. Keep it in one slot of a case and you no longer scour the whole house for a hairpin. A small bit of order quietly rescues an urgent moment."},"ICON-0952":{"nm":"Wireless Charging Pad Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"A night when it fills up on its own as you rest it gently on the pad. A stuck-on sticker marks the spot where the phone should lie down. An unseen current silently tops up a day's worth of energy."},"ICON-0953":{"nm":"Notification Cover Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"Some notifications are easier on the heart left covered. One sticker quiets the little glow of the dawn. Sometimes not looking is a gentle way of protecting yourself, too."},"ICON-0954":{"nm":"Lens Guard Ring","on":"ring","de":"The instant a camera lens touches the floor, your heart drops with a lurch. One ring wrapped around it quietly fends off the little fall. A rim that shields, first of all, the eye that captures memories."},"ICON-0955":{"nm":"Cable Name Tag","on":"tag","de":"Picking out my own from a tangled, knotted heap of cables at last. One tag finally gives a charging cord a name of its own. A little flag pointing out the path among messy cords."},"ICON-0956":{"nm":"Charger Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Chargers in a travel bag always quarrel, tangled with one another. Gather them neatly into one pouch and they finally make peace. The art of packing lies in gently calling the scattered things together into one place."},"ICON-0957":{"nm":"Power Strip Label","on":"label","de":"The holes of a power strip all look the same, confusing every time. Label them to assign whose spot is whose and a busy morning goes far smoother. A small name tag reduces the little daily quarrels of life."},"ICON-0958":{"nm":"Cord Winder Reel","on":"cord winder reel","de":"Unwound to use, wound back up again, a cord's tidy day. Reel it onto one spool layer by layer and the tangles vanish cleanly. The hand that returns things to their place after use makes tomorrow lighter."},"ICON-0959":{"nm":"Magnetic Connector Cap","on":"cap","de":"A magnetic connector gathers fine metal dust before you know it. Cover it with a cap and sticky grime won't cling on. A device touched by one more caring hand stays beside you longer."},"ICON-0960":{"nm":"Power Bank Band","on":"band","de":"Leave a power bank and its cable apart and one of them always disappears. Tie them with a band and the two finally become a pair. A little knot you gently fasten just before heading out, telling them to travel together."},"ICON-0961":{"nm":"Plug Dust Cap","on":"cap","de":"An empty outlet socket lets dust quietly set up house in just a few days. When this little cap guards the spot in its stead, the charger that plugs in next can draw a clean first breath. A gatekeeper that keeps the empty time spotless."},"ICON-0962":{"nm":"Cable Color Ring","on":"ring","de":"On a night spent fumbling for mine in tangled cords, who said let's give them colors? Blue is you, yellow is me. With one little loop, we no longer mix each other up. A trace of a fond promise left in a corner of the rehearsal room."},"ICON-0963":{"nm":"Adapter Sorting Chip","on":"chip","de":"Round prongs and flat prongs, 110 and 220. A chip that quietly memorized the faces of outlets that differ by country. In a corner of the suitcase for that first trip across the sea to the stage, this little sorting card was always tucked in."},"ICON-0964":{"nm":"Ear Tip Sorting Tray","on":"tray","de":"They say ear canals differ in depth and width from person to person. Laying out large, medium, and small side by side, choosing the one pair that fits your ear just right. A gentle procedure of fitting the body first, before listening to sound."},"ICON-0965":{"nm":"Case Silicone Ring","on":"ring","de":"Stage costumes get attention down to every stitch, yet a case's corners always strike bare. When this thin silicone rim gently wraps the edge, even on a dawn when it slips from your hand, the screen greets the morning unharmed."},"ICON-0966":{"nm":"Noise-Cancel Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"There are days you want to switch off the world's sounds for a while. This little sticker on a headphone ear is a marker that turns on the silence. A charm that carries the crowd's cheers and the subway's noise off to a distance, just until one song ends."},"ICON-0967":{"nm":"Ear Hook Set","on":"ear hook set","de":"When you dance, one earbud always runs off first. Hook on these loops that gently embrace the ear, and even amid fierce choreography the music alone stays in your ears to the end. A small discovery the practice-room folks passed around."},"ICON-0968":{"nm":"Cleaning Brush Cap","on":"cap","de":"A little hat slipped on so the dust on the bristle tips won't scatter again. The hand that long ago stood a broom upside down after sweeping already knew that even a cleaning tool needs cleaning."},"ICON-0969":{"nm":"Charging Dock Base Pad","on":"pad","de":"The charging dock kept sliding on the desk because it had no feet. Once this thin pad on the bottom took the feet's place, the device stayed put and quietly filled up its energy all night."},"ICON-0970":{"nm":"Left-Right Marker","on":"left-right marker","de":"Left L, right R. One extra dot is marked so you can tell even fumbling in the dark. The wish never once to mistake the left foot and right foot on stage is stamped, intact, on this little marker."},"ICON-0971":{"nm":"Audio Splitter Jack Cap","on":"cap","de":"That jack where one stream of sound was shared among many, its end should be capped while it rests. So dust won't seep into the circuit. A small, careful hand wishing to send the song you listened to together flowing clear the next time too."},"ICON-0972":{"nm":"Earphone Cable Winder","on":"earphone cable winder","de":"Like the old motion of winding a skein of thread, an earphone cord wound round here grows neat. The moment music that tumbled tangled through a bag is set in order. Tomorrow's unwinding will be that much lighter."},"ICON-0973":{"nm":"Lens Cap Holder Strap","on":"strap","de":"Every time you opened the lens, the cap always lost its way. Tie it to a strap fastened beside the camera and you no longer fumble a pocket in vain. To keep from losing a thing, tie it close by; the hand learned this first."},"ICON-0974":{"nm":"Hot Shoe Cover Charm","on":"hot shoe cover charm","de":"Into the empty hot shoe atop the camera, you slip a small ornament. That one charm with no function at all somehow makes the heavy, blunt gear look as dear as your very own. The act of growing fond of a tool."},"ICON-0975":{"nm":"Strap Adjuster Buckle","on":"strap adjuster buckle","de":"Each time the bag strap digs into your shoulder, you loosen and tighten this buckle a little. One pass of the fingers to choose a length that fits your body. Even carrying a load is, in the end, caring for yourself, the buckle quietly tells you."},"ICON-0976":{"nm":"Filter Stack Case","on":"case","de":"A little home where glass pieces that split the light are laid down in layers. Haze and clarity, sunset and night. Like a drawer where weather is chosen and stored in advance, the photographer always opens this case first before setting out."},"ICON-0977":{"nm":"Blower Dust Cap","on":"cap","de":"A rubber bulb that puffs air to chase off dust is, at its own mouth, just as weak to dust. While it rests, cap it with this. There's something tender in a tool that wipes others quietly covering its own mouth first."},"ICON-0978":{"nm":"Shutter Button Cover","on":"cover","de":"The shutter pressing itself in a bag, snapping a hundred shots of empty sky, is something everyone goes through once. This little cover over the button prevents that wasted effort. A small lock, to capture only the moments you truly wish to keep."},"ICON-0979":{"nm":"Battery Sorting Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"It's always a fiasco when the spent and the full mix together in one pocket. A colored sticker on each battery quietly sorts out that confusion. Red is empty, green is reliable. A wordless traffic light kept on at a shoot."},"ICON-0980":{"nm":"Camera Bag Divider","on":"camera bag divider","de":"Partition the bag so lens, body, and spare battery don't knock against each other. The act of building several little rooms inside one load. Each spot has its owner, so nothing loses its place even when shaken."},"ICON-0981":{"nm":"Shooting Glove Pad","on":"pad","de":"A winter outdoor shoot, where only the fingertip that presses the shutter must not go cold. A thick pad on the palm, gloves that leave sensation at the fingertips. The field's gentle compromise, holding warmth and precision in one hand."},"ICON-0982":{"nm":"Tablet Nib Tube","on":"tube","de":"That a stylus nib wears down like a pencil lead is something those who've long held a tablet know. This little tube where spare nibs are rolled together is like a fingertip's emergency fund, topping up the lines that must not break off."},"ICON-0983":{"nm":"Keycap Tray","on":"tray","de":"On the day you pulled each keycap to wash and refit them, this tray became a little tidal flat. The sight of consonants and vowels lying compartment by compartment, drying off. There is care you only see once you've taken something apart."},"ICON-0984":{"nm":"Mouse Feet Pack","on":"mouse feet pack","de":"The secret to a mouse gliding across the desk lies in these little feet stuck to its bottom. A bundle you swap in when they wear down. The toil of things that silently bear up the smoothness from an unseen place."},"ICON-0985":{"nm":"Laptop Stand Pad","on":"laptop stand pad","de":"It resembles a notebook, but it's really a rubber pad that props up a laptop. Lifting the screen slightly to eye level to straighten a bent neck. A consideration that sets the posture right, for someone who writes and gazes for a long time."},"ICON-0986":{"nm":"Webcam Cover Slider","on":"webcam cover slider","de":"Slide a finger to cover the lens, slide it again to open. The wish to be seen only when you want to be seen. In this one little slider dwells the great relief called privacy. The closing sound is somehow reassuring."},"ICON-0987":{"nm":"USB Sorting Label","on":"label","de":"Five similar black sticks, and no way at all to tell what's stored on which. Stick on a little label to give it a name, and only then does it become one of your own. A thing must have a name to call before it's easy to find."},"ICON-0988":{"nm":"Desk Pad Corners","on":"desk pad corners","de":"When a desk pad's corners keep curling up, even handwriting goes crooked. These little parts that gently press down the four corners guard the flat peace atop the desk. The surface must be still for the fingertips to be calm too."},"ICON-0989":{"nm":"Hub Stand Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clamp that stands a hub, where many cords gather, at an angle on the desk's edge. The sight of unruly cords gathering and tidying into a single point. The knack for binding the tangled into one strand lives here too."},"ICON-0990":{"nm":"Screen Cleaner Spray Cap","on":"cap","de":"A little stopper for the mouth of a spray that wipes fingerprints from a screen. Always shut it tight so the liquid won't leak or dry out. To see clearly, you must first spare the means of cleaning; the humble order of housekeeping."},"ICON-0991":{"nm":"Memory Card Wallet","on":"memory card wallet","de":"Days' worth of stage footage sleeps quietly inside a card no bigger than a fingernail. Lose it and a whole day vanishes entirely, so you gather it dearly into a little wallet. A home that holds the smallest yet greatest of memories."},"ICON-0992":{"nm":"External Drive Label Ring","on":"ring","de":"Five black external drives sleep in a drawer with identical faces. The act of sticking on a label and naming them 'that summer,' 'unreleased clips.' A task of fastening a clear index onto a hazy memory."},"ICON-0993":{"nm":"Backup Check Chip","on":"chip","de":"Whether the backup is done or not, the heart frets over that razor's-edge difference. This little chip slipped into the finished spot tells you 'it's safe up to here.' Reassurance comes from leaving a mark behind."},"ICON-0994":{"nm":"Cloud Memo Token","on":"token","de":"A token that floats a single line of memo up to a storehouse somewhere in the sky. A little magic where, wherever you power on, that writing comes out to meet you. The night sky where you flew a kite and wrote a wish now seems to settle gently onto your palm."},"ICON-0995":{"nm":"USB Guard Cap Set","on":"USB guard cap set","de":"Left tumbling in a bag with the connector exposed, the contacts are bound to wear. Cap each end with a little hat and keep them as one set. The act of laying the unused time gently to sleep. The quietest preparation for the next connection."},"ICON-0996":{"nm":"Data Case Band","on":"band","de":"A band that wraps and fastens snug around a device holding precious data. Loop it once and bind it tight so nothing knocks about in a jostling bag. The hand that once knotted a bundle with care lives on in the digital, too."},"ICON-0997":{"nm":"File Sorting Tag","on":"tag","de":"When hundreds of files pile up nameless, the searching itself becomes wandering. The moment you attach colored tags and open up branches, a path appears through the messy heap. Tidying is, in the end, the work of opening a road."},"ICON-0998":{"nm":"Password Hint Card","on":"card","de":"Write a password in full and it's dangerous; don't write it at all and you forget. So you leave only a clue that only you understand. Like 'that city of the first stage.' A clever, gentle way of remembering that writes down the road, not the answer."},"ICON-0999":{"nm":"Storage Date Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"Don't note the day you put it away, and storage soon becomes forgetting. A date sticker on each box carves a clear 'since when.' The heart of the old pantry that wrote down the day the soybean paste was made carries on, on this little paper."},"ICON-1000":{"nm":"Mini Ring Light Cap","on":"cap","de":"A cap that covers the light-hole of a little lamp casting a round glow. Lay the light to rest a while so the lens won't get scratched in a bag. Keeping the darkness before it's switched on is one way of cherishing the brightness, too."},"ICON-1001":{"nm":"Mount Tightening Screw","on":"mount tightening screw","de":"Just one more turn. The loose gap disappears, and a heavy reassurance settles beneath your palm. Behind a stage that doesn't wobble there's always someone's one deft turn of the wrist. What a small screw bears up is an unseen solidity."},"ICON-1002":{"nm":"On-Air Marker Chip","on":"chip","de":"The moment the red light comes on, the footsteps in the hall quietly rise to tiptoe. Before the words 'On Air,' everyone holds their breath. That even the silence beyond the door is a heart turned toward someone is what this little chip quietly announces."},"ICON-1003":{"nm":"Chat Memo Pad","on":"pad","de":"Catching with your fingertips the cheers that would slip past the screen. Time when each word that would flow away stays, neat and clear, on paper. To record is a place where the tenderness of wanting to reach, even belatedly, lingers."},"ICON-1004":{"nm":"Silent Keyboard Cover","on":"cover","de":"Two in the morning, and the sound of pressing keys vanishes as if by a lie. A thin film, so as not to wake the breathing of a soundly sleeping roommate. The quietest consideration always begins in a soundless place."},"ICON-1005":{"nm":"Mic Arm Clip","on":"clip","de":"Between lips and mic, just exactly the distance where a song doesn't waver. This little clip holds that promise fast. Backstage, there is always a hand like this, come ahead to hold things steady."},"ICON-1006":{"nm":"Backdrop Clamp","on":"clamp","de":"Even when the wind blows, the backdrop doesn't stir. Because one little jaw biting firmly at the corner holds the whole scene in place. Behind an unwavering view, there's someone in an unseen spot gritting their teeth."},"ICON-1007":{"nm":"Stream Deck Label","on":"label","de":"Atop dozens of buttons, little name tags keep the hand from losing its way. One line of label erases a single live-broadcast mistake in advance. Composure comes from the letters written down before the trembling starts."},"ICON-1008":{"nm":"Timestamp Button","on":"button","de":"Press it down and a little flag is planted on the flowing time. The act of stamping the now that will never return. Looking back long after, that marker has become a door into memory."},"ICON-1009":{"nm":"Tag Reader Keyring","on":"keyring","de":"Hold it close and beep, information wakes up. A little companion dangling from a keyring, jingling in your pocket. An ordinary day carries on safely through small signal tones like this."},"ICON-1010":{"nm":"Smart Plug Label","on":"label","de":"Name each outlet and you no longer wander over which cord is which. The heart of giving a name even to unseen electricity. Tidiness is another face that tenderness briefly borrows to wear."},"ICON-1011":{"nm":"Temp-Humidity Sensor Stand","on":"temp-humidity sensor stand","de":"A palm-sized sentinel that wordlessly watches the room's temperature and moisture. Comfort never opens its mouth, but this stand quietly tends to your condition every moment. Well-being is kept safe, quietly, like this."},"ICON-1012":{"nm":"Door Sensor Cap","on":"cap","de":"A little eye that doesn't miss the instant a door softly opens. It silently passes on the sign that someone has come home. What guards an empty house is always, like this, the wordless things."},"ICON-1013":{"nm":"Remote Button Holder","on":"holder","de":"Remotes that rolled about here and there finally find a place of their own. A small spot that gently holds what was nearly lost, a hand that carves in advance the promise to meet again."},"ICON-1014":{"nm":"Sleep App Token","on":"token","de":"Each night you sleep well, one round reward rolls in and piles up. Sleep, too, gathers up bit by bit like practice, the app tells you tenderly. The smallest prize in the world, handed to a you who rested well."},"ICON-1015":{"nm":"Timer Cube Base","on":"base","de":"While three minutes tick steadily by, the cube counts its time without a waver. One palm-sized spot that gently bears it up from below. Even waiting needs a floor it can stand on with peace of mind."},"ICON-1016":{"nm":"Notification Light Cover","on":"cover","de":"So it's not too bright, it softly wraps the light in one layer. A notification may be urgent, but let the eyes alone be at ease. Consideration is a heart that quietly measures even the strength of light."},"ICON-1017":{"nm":"Battery Change Card","on":"card","de":"When this card appears, it means it's time to replace the little heart inside the device. A gentle hint to see to it before it stops. The secret to a long companionship lies always in a watchfulness a beat ahead."},"ICON-1018":{"nm":"Joystick Cap Set","on":"joystick cap set","de":"Tiny hats slipped on so the thumb won't slide. The sense at the fingertip grows that much clearer. This one little cap can even decide the win or loss of a round played with sweaty hands."},"ICON-1019":{"nm":"Switch Dock Cover","on":"cover","de":"It gently covers the resting spot of a console from dust. Because even a briefly sleeping device needs one blanket. A caring heart shows more clearly, in fact, when something isn't in use."},"ICON-1020":{"nm":"Handheld Console Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"When on the move, always inside this. A pouch that wraps a handheld console softly in its embrace. So it stays unfazed even knocked this way and that in a bag; it's best to wrap precious things one more time."},"ICON-1021":{"nm":"Button Sticker Ring","on":"ring","de":"Lay just one little picture atop a plain button and, in that moment, it becomes wholly your own. The act of leaving your own mark on an identical device. Individuality always blooms quietly from trivial spots like this."},"ICON-1022":{"nm":"Game Cartridge Case","on":"case","de":"A game you sank into all night sleeps soundly inside this little case. Open the lid again and that night wakes back up, intact. Memories, surprisingly, are often held in a box no bigger than a palm."},"ICON-1023":{"nm":"Cooling Fan Stand","on":"stand","de":"While the breeze cools the heat, a spot that props the device at a slight tilt. It makes room for an overheated body to catch its breath. To run far, you must also know how to pause a moment and cool down."},"ICON-1024":{"nm":"Wrist Strap Pin","on":"pin","de":"Loop it around your wrist and fasten the pin, and no matter how fierce the motion, the controller won't leave your side. This strap that looks like a nuisance is, in fact, the reassurance that lets you romp with an easy heart."},"ICON-1025":{"nm":"Analog Grip Cap","on":"cap","de":"Dress a new coat over a grip gone smooth and shiny from long handling. Leave the feel your hand knows as it is, and only the surface like new. A moment when familiarity and a little thrill rest side by side in one hand."},"ICON-1026":{"nm":"Save Slot Label","on":"label","de":"On each save slot, write clearly whose adventure it is. One line of label silently guards the journey of the past few days. Precious memories are best given a name carved in, so they aren't overwritten."},"ICON-1027":{"nm":"Recorder Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A machine that holds sound grows more precious for what's inside it. You carry it tucked gently into a soft pouch that shields it from shocks. Someone's voice may be sleeping in there, so all the more carefully."},"ICON-1028":{"nm":"Windscreen Cap","on":"cap","de":"Sweep away the sound of the wind and leave only the voice. A fluffy hood gently slipped over a mic for outdoor recording. A little strainer that picks out only the sincerity from amid the unruly noise."},"ICON-1029":{"nm":"Voice Memo Label","on":"label","de":"This one's a lyric that came to mind, this one a hummed melody. You stick a colored name tag on each voice memo. The scattered shards of inspiration finally find their places and fall into line."},"ICON-1030":{"nm":"Sampling Button Chip","on":"chip","de":"Press it down and a sliver of pre-stored sound pops out. A raindrop, applause, someone's laugh, fragments of the world wake at your fingertip. Music is the gentle chorus of little chips like these."},"ICON-1031":{"nm":"Sound-Gathering Envelope","on":"envelope","de":"You gently gather into this envelope the sounds you happen to pick up while walking. The grain of the wind, even the hush of a dawn alley. The materials that will someday become a song always gather modestly, like this."},"ICON-1032":{"nm":"Mini Tripod Feet","on":"mini tripod feet","de":"Three legs unfold a little stage atop the desk. Instead of a shaking hand, they stand firm and hold the scene in place. A sharp single shot is born, at last, from three feet quietly standing still."},"ICON-1033":{"nm":"Recording File Tag","on":"tag","de":"Onto hundreds of recording files, you attach a short tag one by one. So you can see at a glance which one is the first line that first flowed out on which day. A small signpost that helps you find scattered voices again."},"ICON-1034":{"nm":"Waveform Sticker Band","on":"band","de":"A wavy-patterned band molded after the very shape of sound. Wrap it around a notebook or a case and it's as if the music is visible before your eyes. A gentle illusion that makes the heard into the seen."},"ICON-1035":{"nm":"Headset Hook Pin","on":"pin","de":"When practice ends, it gently prepares a resting spot for the weary headset. One little hook driven into the desk's edge. A tidy desk is a place to hang tomorrow's drive in advance."},"ICON-1036":{"nm":"Mini Gift Box Band","on":"band","de":"The last loop wrapped around a gift box's waist. With this one band, the heart is finally complete. Sincerity is often conveyed first from the hand that smooths the outside, more than from what's within."},"ICON-1037":{"nm":"Ribbon Tail Cap","on":"cap","de":"Gently wrap and finish a ribbon's end so it won't unravel. One detail that hardly catches the eye quietly changes a gift's first impression. When the finishing is fine, the heart reaches finely too."},"ICON-1038":{"nm":"Sealing Wax","on":"sealing wax","de":"Drop one hot bead to seal the envelope. Like an old letter, a weighty promise not to open it carelessly. Formality sometimes holds a warm weight like this."},"ICON-1039":{"nm":"Thank-You Card Holder","on":"holder","de":"It props up straight a card bearing words of thanks so it won't crease. So the heart stands upright as it's conveyed. Gratitude lingers in the heart longer when even its shape is neat."},"ICON-1040":{"nm":"Star-Shaped Filler Paper","on":"star-shaped filler paper","de":"Paper cut into star shapes plumply fills the gaps in a box. The cotton of a heart that wishes nothing be hurt even when shaken. Even in the dark inside the wrapping, a little star is afloat."},"ICON-1041":{"nm":"Gift List Tag","on":"tag","de":"Before the recipient's blank, the pen pauses a long while. The face that comes to mind as you write the name, the seasons spent together. The instant it's tied on, this little paper becomes a secret no one can read until it's undone."},"ICON-1042":{"nm":"Congrats Stamp Ring","on":"ring","de":"Press it down and a round congratulation prints out clearly. While you wait the brief moment for the ink to dry, the heart imagining whom to hand it to is the warmest. If there's a flaw, it's that you want to stamp it one more time."},"ICON-1043":{"nm":"Gift Cord Bobbin","on":"gift cord bobbin","de":"Wound with care, then merrily unspooled at someone's fluttering fingertips. In that brief moment of winding and unwinding, a heart bound to the thread becomes, at last, a gift."},"ICON-1044":{"nm":"Knot Charm (Not a Flower)","on":"knot charm (not a flower)","de":"Not an imitation of a flower, but a shape where a single strand embraces its own body again and again and blooms on its own. The patience of fingertips that chose knots all night long remains as one small bud like this."},"ICON-1045":{"nm":"Lucky Coin Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"The heart of slipping a few coins into the pocket of someone setting off on a long road. The act of filling it not with weight but with tenderness. The jingle at each step stands in for a wish that they fare well."},"ICON-1046":{"nm":"Wish Capsule Charm","on":"wish capsule charm","de":"Inside a round shell, one folded wish sleeps soundly. That opening it makes it come true is a lie, but that holding it unopened keeps that wish alive forever is the truth."},"ICON-1047":{"nm":"Protective Knot Cord","on":"cord","de":"A cord woven firm with five-color threads, turning bad energy back behind you. Like the grandmother's hand that tied a knot around a wrist in childhood, in each bound spot someone's prayer is finely set."},"ICON-1048":{"nm":"Little Paper Crane Case","on":"case","de":"A little home that keeps just one paper crane safe from harm, of the thousand that must be folded to become a wish. Because if even one wing is creased, the very devotion poured into that night quietly comes undone."},"ICON-1049":{"nm":"Sparkle Stone Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Little flecks of light fallen from a stage costume, a spot to sweep up what you can't bring yourself to throw away. Even the sparkle that once clung and followed you for a week sleeps here as obediently as on your palm."},"ICON-1050":{"nm":"Good-Omen Stamp Chip","on":"chip","de":"A little token you quietly add when choosing a good day. Not at a fortune-teller's threshold, but on my own desk, a sliver of fond superstition you gently stamp, wishing only good things for this one day."},"ICON-1051":{"nm":"Wish Bracelet Card","on":"card","de":"A single sheet of paper printed in the shape of a bracelet, holding someone's quiet wish. Even if it can't be clasped around your wrist, tuck it deep in your wallet and that heart stays tied to your side, walking with you always."},"ICON-1052":{"nm":"Doorstep Salt Jar","on":"jar","de":"Coarse salt poured into a small jar, set gently by the door. An old reckoning that turns away bad spirits and welcomes only kind guests. Each salty grain is a little gatekeeper watching over our home."},"ICON-1053":{"nm":"Lucky Number Cover Tag","on":"lucky number cover tag","de":"Right before you scratch, everyone is a winner for a moment. This tag, gently covering the lucky number, guards that final second when hope swells the most. Even if your scratching fingers tremble, it pretends not to notice and keeps its eyes shut."},"ICON-1054":{"nm":"Birthday Candle Keeper Cap","on":"cap","de":"A tidy little heart that keeps even a once-lit candle safe until next birthday. If last year's wish still hasn't come true, this year you can simply pick up where you left off and wish again, a tender bit of reckoning."},"ICON-1055":{"nm":"Anniversary Countdown Ring","on":"ring","de":"A cheeky thing that slips a D-day onto your finger. Each time the number of days left ticks down a notch, your heart gets pulled that much closer too. It insists, all on its own, that it will glow when it reaches 0."},"ICON-1056":{"nm":"Party Hat Strap","on":"strap","de":"A slender strap that holds a party hat snugly on your head. The guest of honor soon complains it's stuffy and pulls it off, but in the photo that one shot keeps it on forever. That's mission enough."},"ICON-1057":{"nm":"Little Cake Pick","on":"little cake pick","de":"A tiny marker stuck into a cake the size of two finger joints. Even atop a sweetness that vanishes in one bite, the celebration stands tall. Small as it is, a birthday is still a birthday, and today the star is you."},"ICON-1058":{"nm":"Party Popper Label","on":"label","de":"A paper popper that makes no bang but looks the most dazzling. The moment it's stuck on, an ordinary piece of mail transforms into a letter from a party. Many people leave it on, too reluctant to peel it off."},"ICON-1059":{"nm":"Photo Hanger Clip","on":"clip","de":"Afraid of dropping the memories strung along the line, I always keep my mouth firmly shut. As long as a photo is held in my grip, not even the breeze through the window can let those days fall away."},"ICON-1060":{"nm":"Date Balloon Patch","on":"date balloon patch","de":"A balloon-shaped patch with a number on it. Stick it to your clothes and the whole neighborhood learns which special day it is today. Peel it off and a mark remains, and even that faint mark becomes one more keepsake."},"ICON-1061":{"nm":"Gift Exchange Marker","on":"gift exchange marker","de":"A playful marker that gently muddles which hand received and which hand gave. A small, tender rule of the gift-swapping table, asking you to remember not so much who gave it as what passed between you."},"ICON-1062":{"nm":"Anniversary Table Number","on":"anniversary table number","de":"A little number stood up at each banquet table. Settling in advance who sits where so no one feels awkward, it holds the warm wisdom of people who have hosted many feasts."},"ICON-1063":{"nm":"Doorknob Gift Bag","on":"doorknob gift bag","de":"A way to pass along your heart without ringing the bell. Hang it slyly on the doorknob and slip away as if fleeing, and the startled face of whoever finds it becomes the greatest gift returned to the giver."},"ICON-1064":{"nm":"Secret Delivery Label","on":"label","de":"Nothing is written on its face. Keeping the sender hidden to the very end is this label's small pride. The longer the recipient tilts their head and smiles, the more perfectly its secret mission is fulfilled."},"ICON-1065":{"nm":"Doorbell Memo Chip","on":"chip","de":"A small note left in place when you can't muster the courage to knock. A short line like 'just dropped by' lingers longer than a doorbell's ring. Because crooked, scrawled handwriting has a face of its own."},"ICON-1066":{"nm":"Box Cutter Safety Cap","on":"cap","de":"When a box cutter's blade carelessly aims for your finger, a little hero quietly steps in front. It safely guards your fingertips, hurried by excitement for the new thing, all the way to the last cut."},"ICON-1067":{"nm":"Bubble Wrap Piece","on":"bubble wrap piece","de":"I was born to be pressed. Somehow, with that little pop, the day's tension melts loose. Now and then there are days I'm loved longer than the very thing I was wrapped around."},"ICON-1068":{"nm":"Arrival Time Pin","on":"pin","de":"A pin that marks exactly what time it arrives. Even a vague wait grows easier to bear once it has a single coordinate. How many times you'll peek out the front door until then is entirely up to you."},"ICON-1069":{"nm":"Parcel Locker Keyring","on":"ring","de":"A small companion for the person who keeps forgetting the parcel locker code. It dangles on the keyring, and its quiet talent is drawing out an 'oh, right' at the crucial moment."},"ICON-1070":{"nm":"Entryway Basket Tag","on":"entryway basket tag","de":"A nametag on the basket in the corner of the entryway. On it is the wordless promise, 'leave it here.' Even empty, a spot that waits for someone's heart is never lonely."},"ICON-1071":{"nm":"Address Cover Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"On a box you're throwing out, you leave the name but wipe away the address. The name is fine for all to know; where you live stays your secret. The moment you peel and stick this single layer, a little peace of mind is born."},"ICON-1072":{"nm":"Snack Tin Label","on":"label","de":"A label that tells you at a glance what's inside the tin. But the catch is, writing 'snacks' somehow makes you feel reassured even without opening the lid. The label can't take responsibility for your appetite, though."},"ICON-1073":{"nm":"Little Necklace Pendant","on":"little necklace pendant","de":"A small charm that quietly shares your body heat beneath your clothes. Always touching a spot no one can see, it's all the more dear for that. The closest friend that walks along at your chest."},"ICON-1074":{"nm":"Pawprint Stamp Mat","on":"mat","de":"Press it to a paw and a row of little prints is left behind. A daily walking diary, neatly noting on paper who walked where. The first ink-stained step is always the clearest."},"ICON-1075":{"nm":"Fur Brush Cap","on":"cap","de":"A small cap that tidily handles the fur tangled in a brush. In shedding season, when one stroke gathers a fistful, without this cap the whole house turns into a fluffy snowfield. A diligent cleaner who works without leaving a trace."},"ICON-1076":{"nm":"Walk Bag Case","on":"case","de":"A small home that neatly carries the bags you need on a walk. This case quietly proves every day that only those who pack ahead get to stroll at ease. That one bag you'll be in trouble without."},"ICON-1077":{"nm":"Name Cover Tag","on":"tag","de":"A tag that slyly hides the real name and leaves only the nickname. In this world there's a kind of tenderness you'd rather not show just anyone. That special way of being called, known only to those who know, hides gently right here."},"ICON-1078":{"nm":"Water Bowl Mat Pad","on":"pad","de":"Laid beneath the water bowl, I'm always damp. Catching the droplets that splash in every direction, I keep the floorboards dry. No one praises me, but I never complain either."},"ICON-1079":{"nm":"Toy Mending Thread","on":"thread","de":"A doll with a burst seam isn't thrown away but stitched up again. With each spot you fill, stitch by stitch, the time spent with that little one grows sturdy once more. Mending is, in the end, gently postponing a goodbye."},"ICON-1080":{"nm":"Memento Photo Necklace","on":"memento photo necklace","de":"The heart of wearing your brightest-smiling shot around your neck. That day in the photo, instead of being mounted still, sways along with every step and reaches all the way to today. That good moment never stops."},"ICON-1081":{"nm":"Mood Color Chip","on":"chip","de":"If hearts had hues too, what color would yours be today? The moment you pick a chip and set it on your desk, the feelings words couldn't quite say spread quietly outward. Sunset glow or dawn light, both are fine; it's a little mirror that gently reflects the you of that day."},"ICON-1082":{"nm":"Today's Record Marble","on":"today's record marble","de":"When the day winds down, today gathers round inside the marble. The things you did well and the things you fumbled all roll in together and tuck themselves away. Set it on your palm and yesterday's you feels a touch warm, patting your back, telling you you lived today well."},"ICON-1083":{"nm":"Praise Note Jar","on":"jar","de":"Kind words scatter too easily, so you fold them one by one into this jar. When praise pools like fragrance, you open the lid on nights your heart feels hollow. Pull out a bit of tenderness someone offered and read it again, and that day's warmth comes back to life."},"ICON-1084":{"nm":"Reconciliation Ribbon Cord","on":"cord","de":"A tangled heart is like a knot; undoing it takes care too. When two people grasp each end of the cord and pull slowly, a lovely ribbon forms before you know it. Reconciliation isn't cutting but tying again, this cord quietly tells you."},"ICON-1085":{"nm":"Gratitude Token","on":"token","de":"On days when 'thank you' won't leave your lips, you slip someone a token instead. The hand that receives it reads your whole heart from that little weight. A sincerity that arrives ahead of words, affection carried across in a single round bead."},"ICON-1086":{"nm":"Break Time Marker","on":"break time marker","de":"Even a practice room that's been running all day needs a beat to catch its breath. Hang this marker on the door and time slows for a while. Anyone who has lived through a breathless day knows that a song needs a rest to breathe."},"ICON-1087":{"nm":"Secret Feelings Drawer","on":"secret feelings drawer","de":"There are days you can't lay out everything in your heart. On those days you tuck sorrow and flutter alike into a small drawer of the mind and close it. It's all right to leave them for now, because a day will come to open it slowly and sort it all out."},"ICON-1088":{"nm":"Smile Sticker Roll","on":"smile sticker roll","de":"Peel off one square and a smiley mark transfers to your fingertip. A little cheer to stick gently on the corner of a notebook or a friend's locker. When a tiny sun rises on the paper, the day of whoever finds it grows a little brighter."},"ICON-1089":{"nm":"Well-Wishes Bell Charm","on":"well-wishes bell charm","de":"The wish to reach you far away has gathered into a single bell. Shake it and a clear sound carries your greeting in your stead. On days you couldn't bring yourself to ask 'how are you,' this little ringing rides the wind and reaches you first."},"ICON-1090":{"nm":"Spring Rain Cover Pin","on":"pin","de":"On rainy spring days, the things you cherish are the ones that get soaked most easily. Fasten the cover with this pin and the raindrops slant off and away. The heart of cradling one precious book close, a little pin stands in for that tenderness."},"ICON-1091":{"nm":"Summer Cooling Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"One quick press on the back of a hand worn out by midsummer heat. A cool sensation spreads like mint and the sweat eases a touch. That coolness of lying on the wooden veranda fanning yourself, mimicked dutifully by a palm-sized sheet of paper."},"ICON-1092":{"nm":"Autumn Plaid Cloth Scrap","on":"autumn plaid cloth scrap","de":"A scrap of checkered cloth that resembles an autumn field. It's the trace of someone carefully patching a worn spot. The heart that mends rather than discards, little cloths gathering to warmly revive what was frayed."},"ICON-1093":{"nm":"Winter Glove Clip","on":"clip","de":"Winter gloves somehow keep running off, one at a time. Link the pair with this clip and your chilled hands won't lose their way. The wish not to lose them settles into a small piece of metal, keeping the two side by side."},"ICON-1094":{"nm":"Rainy Season Waterproof Tag","on":"rainy season waterproof tag","de":"In the rainy season even a nametag blurs in the rain. This waterproof-coated tag protects its writing even under pouring rain. A line that stays clear after the rain clears, so that whose this is will never be forgotten to the end."},"ICON-1095":{"nm":"First Snow Keeping Jar","on":"jar","de":"First snow vanishes the moment it touches your hand, so you saved at least that thrill in a jar. What's trapped in the glass isn't snow but the heart that fluttered that day. Shake it and a whole winter swirls again, carrying you back to that morning."},"ICON-1096":{"nm":"Holiday Envelope Band","on":"band","de":"A single red band wrapped around a holiday envelope. Everyone knows the affection in the giving hand outweighs whatever's inside. The heart that wraps blessings together with wishes of good health is bound up neatly within this slender band."},"ICON-1097":{"nm":"Picnic Dish Band","on":"band","de":"Spread the mat and unpack the lunchbox, and the wind keeps lifting the lids. Fasten the dishes snugly with this band and the picnic won't fall into disarray. The heart of protecting a packed meal to the last is held in one small band."},"ICON-1098":{"nm":"Seasonal Scent Sample Card","on":"card","de":"So you can tell the season without even opening it, the scent of that time of year is held in a single card. Flowers in spring, the smell of dry leaves in autumn. The instant it brushes your nose the whole season comes back, 'this is the air of April.'"},"ICON-1099":{"nm":"Price Tag Clipboard","on":"price tag clipboard","de":"This one clipboard put to rest the stall's headache of price tags forever blowing away. It holds the numbers firmly and presents them straight to the customer. A shop's first greeting begins with one honest line that never goes askew."},"ICON-1100":{"nm":"Open Sign Flip Board","on":"board","de":"Flip this board and hang it at the door, and the shop finally wakes. From 'preparing' to 'welcome.' A small signal announcing the start of the day, the spot the owner's hand reaches first every morning."},"ICON-1101":{"nm":"Loyalty Stamp Pad","on":"pad","de":"Fill all ten squares and somehow something good comes your way. Each stamp is a regular's footstep, affection built up over time. In every mark pressed until the ink dries, a small promise to return lives and breathes."},"ICON-1102":{"nm":"Paper Bag Handle Cap","on":"cap","de":"A paper bag's handle is always weak against weight. Slip on this cap and the about-to-snap cord turns sturdy. The wish to carry what's inside safely home, a small fitting that supports that journey to the very end."},"ICON-1103":{"nm":"Counter Coin Tray","on":"tray","de":"This tray quietly eases the hesitation of passing change from hand to hand. The sound of coins jingling into their place. Giving and receiving grows warmer thanks to this round little courtesy."},"ICON-1104":{"nm":"Point Stamp Chip","on":"chip","de":"Today's steps pile up neatly into a single chip. A curious reckoning where the more you gather, the lighter your heart feels. The joy of filling up little by little resembles the delight of watching an empty jar grow full before you know it."},"ICON-1105":{"nm":"Shelf Number Pin","on":"pin","de":"On every shelf a little number is fondly pinned. A quiet guide telling you where everything is. The heart of marking the spot ahead of time so you don't wander, even order can carry such warmth."},"ICON-1106":{"nm":"Sample Skewer Cup","on":"cup","de":"A small cup holding out a bite to taste. Even a hesitant customer gently opens their heart at this one morsel. The generosity of urging, 'do try one,' dangles from the skewer's tip and holds the first-timer's steps."},"ICON-1107":{"nm":"Reservation List Holder","on":"holder","de":"The names of today's guests stand neatly in this holder. A tender promise that even waiting has its turn. Standing a single sheet upright becomes the first careful preparation to welcome someone's day."},"ICON-1108":{"nm":"Wall Photo Line Clip","on":"clip","de":"Hang a line on the wall and clip photos onto it one by one. Smiling moments dangle side by side and dry like laundry. Hang your memories where the sunlight falls, and each time you pass, that day's laughter flutters again."},"ICON-1109":{"nm":"Mini Rug Corner","on":"mini rug corner","de":"A small rug laid at the edge of the room. A spot that spreads warmth first onto the cold floor. The handspan your bare feet touch first, where the toes of one home again finally settle and grow drowsy at ease."},"ICON-1110":{"nm":"Nameplate Cover Cloth","on":"nameplate cover cloth","de":"A length of cloth gently veiling the nameplate. Hiding the name for a while is its own kind of household charm. A lovely drape over the border of inside and out, hung softly with the wish to rest quietly today."},"ICON-1111":{"nm":"Light Cord Clip","on":"clip","de":"This clip holds a dangling light cord tidily in place. A hand that straightens the path so the light won't scatter. Smooth out one messy cord as evening sets in, and the light in the room and the heart both grow calmer."},"ICON-1112":{"nm":"Poster Magnet Cap","on":"cap","de":"A small magnet cap for putting a poster on the wall. The paper holds its place without poking a single pushpin hole. The hand that handles what it cherishes is always gentle, and the heart of keeping it from harm is held here."},"ICON-1113":{"nm":"Curtain Tassel Cord","on":"cord","de":"A tassel cord that ties the curtain back to one side. It opens a lovely path for the morning sunlight to come in. Give the tasseled cord one pull and a bright day surges into the room and stays."},"ICON-1114":{"nm":"Candle Holder Label","on":"label","de":"A small label stuck on a candle holder. It neatly notes which scent is burning and when it was first lit. Giving a name to a fragrance you love, that tidiness makes the air in the room all the more tender."},"ICON-1115":{"nm":"Display Shelf Rubber Feet","on":"display shelf rubber feet","de":"Four rubber feet propping up a shelf so it won't wobble. From an unseen spot they bear the weight in silence. Small and low and easy to overlook, but what holds firm at the very bottom is what lasts the longest in the end."},"ICON-1116":{"nm":"Direction Sign Arrow Charm","on":"direction sign arrow charm","de":"For the one hesitating over which way to go, a single arrow quietly points the way. A tender gesture saying, don't lose your path. Thanks to the heart someone set up first at each fork, today too you press on without wandering."},"ICON-1117":{"nm":"Island Invitation Key Cord","on":"cord","de":"A key cord placed in the hand of the one inviting you to the island. Take it and now you too are family here. The hospitality of welcoming a strange guest into the warm inside is held firmly in the small promise dangling at the cord's end."},"ICON-1118":{"nm":"Closeness Temperature Chip","on":"chip","de":"A single chip slyly tells you the temperature between two people. Whether it's still an awkward blue or has somehow turned a warm crimson. The speed at which affection deepens is hard to measure, but the palm senses that warmth first."},"ICON-1119":{"nm":"Preference Sample Box","on":"box","de":"When you don't yet know what someone likes, you gather little samples into a box and hand it over. Within the joy of choosing, a taste slowly grows. Which one will become yours, the box is full of thrilling possibility."},"ICON-1120":{"nm":"Care Reservation Pin","on":"pin","de":"The promise to look after someone is pinned clearly into this single pin. Write down the name and the time and your heart won't lose its way. That tender give-and-take of taking turns watching each other's children lives and breathes right here."},"ICON-1121":{"nm":"Growth Record Capsule","on":"growth record capsule","de":"Just as the marks of measured height stack up one line at a time on a doorframe, this capsule quietly seals away the you of yesterday. Open the lid far in the future and you'll know, how far those once-tiny steps have walked."},"ICON-1122":{"nm":"First Meeting Keepsake Band","on":"band","de":"The flutter of first clasping hands is tied gently into a single band. The knot isn't there to be undone but to keep that day's warmth living on at your wrist."},"ICON-1123":{"nm":"My Room Decor Label","on":"label","de":"\"This is my spot.\" The moment one small label is stuck on the corner of the desk, the once-strange room finally breathes and becomes My Room. A nametag is the first place the heart comes to rest."},"ICON-1124":{"nm":"Bonding Marble Jar","on":"jar","de":"Shake it and roll, the sound of two drawing one notch closer rolls along. By the time the jar fills to the brim, just calling your name will have laughter come out to greet you first."},"ICON-1125":{"nm":"Debut Prep Seal","on":"debut prep seal","de":"The last sheet that closes the envelope. This far is preparation; turn the next page and it's the stage. Pressing it down firmly with a fingertip, the trainee steadies their breath. At last, it's beginning."},"ICON-1126":{"nm":"Water","on":"water","de":"The most common, so the most precious. In a practice room at dawn with the lights out, a single sip lifts a person who'd collapsed back to their feet. A tenderness with no shape of its own that seeps into any vessel."},"ICON-1127":{"nm":"Clear Water","on":"clear water","de":"A transparency that brightly reflects even the pebbles at the bottom. A mountain spring never once boasts of its own clarity. A heart with nothing to hide is always like this, seen all the way to the bottom."},"ICON-1128":{"nm":"Seawater","on":"seawater","de":"The moment it touches your tongue, far-off waves come rolling in. In one salty sip the horizon and the gulls and the harbor you left behind are all dissolved whole. The sea always lingers in memory with a salty taste."},"ICON-1129":{"nm":"Ice","on":"ice","de":"It shrinks away on your palm, vanishing as much as you grip. Hard as it looks, it knows it will return to water in the end. Ice is a river that has paused its breath for a while."},"ICON-1130":{"nm":"Snowball","on":"snowball","de":"One tightly packed lump flies white, cutting across the alley. Giggling laughter and cheeks flushed red with cold. The whitest toy winter slips into children's hands."},"ICON-1131":{"nm":"Soil","on":"soil","de":"It cradles seeds, drinks the rain, and silently takes in passing footsteps. A black skin that embraces everything. At the first place of all that grows, there is this single handful."},"ICON-1132":{"nm":"Fertile Soil","on":"fertile soil","de":"Push your fingers in and a black richness wraps softly around them. The secret behind grandmother's vegetable patch staying green every year was right here. Well-aged soil whispers of a bountiful harvest with the scent of manure."},"ICON-1133":{"nm":"Clay","on":"clay","de":"The moment it takes in moisture, it obediently accepts any shape. A tender flesh that becomes a bird, becomes a bowl, following your touch. While the wheel turns, a handful of earth finally begins to dream."},"ICON-1134":{"nm":"Sand","on":"sand","de":"Fine grains that slip away between your fingers. The harder you hold on, the faster they pour out, ever resembling time. In one handful of beach, countless yesterdays lie sleeping."},"ICON-1135":{"nm":"Pebbles","on":"pebbles","de":"Stones worn round at the streamside. They're the trace of water caressing them long and long until the sharp edges wore away. The farther one has rolled, the more gently it nestles into your hand."},"ICON-1136":{"nm":"Stone","on":"stone","de":"A lump set carelessly at the roadside. One person kicks it and passes by; another quietly picks it up to build a tower. The same stone becomes a burden or a wish, depending on the heart."},"ICON-1137":{"nm":"Flagstone","on":"flagstone","de":"A broad flat stone crossing an old palace courtyard. Hundreds of years of shoes treading over it have worn a dip in its center. Each person who steps on it, one foot at a time, adds another layer of time there."},"ICON-1138":{"nm":"Limestone","on":"limestone","de":"The shells from its days as a sea hardened layer upon layer into a white stone. Put it in a kiln and it unwinds into lime, painting walls pure white. Calm as it looks, it's a stone that holds a whole era within."},"ICON-1139":{"nm":"Coal","on":"coal","de":"An old forest fallen into a blackened sleep. Ferns from hundreds of millions of years ago, congealed firm deep underground. Set it alight and the sunlight long buried away blazes awake once more."},"ICON-1140":{"nm":"Charcoal","on":"charcoal","de":"It holds the fire but quietly swallows the smoke. Wood pressed black inside the kiln blooms red without a word atop the brazier. The more silent a thing, the longer it stays warm."},"ICON-1141":{"nm":"Twig","on":"twig","de":"A branch that has silently bent rather than break knows the way of yielding. At every spot that endured a harsh wind a knot forms, and true sturdiness is, in the end, the mark of having bent well."},"ICON-1142":{"nm":"Log","on":"log","de":"Within its cut rings, a hundred springs and winters are stacked round upon round. The years a single tree lived out lie down whole, now quietly awaiting its turn to become the pillar of a house."},"ICON-1143":{"nm":"Lumber","on":"lumber","de":"Each time the plane passes, a fragrant grain is laid bare, layer by layer. As the rough wood turns smooth, the sawdust piles on the floor like yellow snow. The trimming hand awakens its usefulness."},"ICON-1144":{"nm":"Plank","on":"plank","de":"It floors a hall, builds a bench, encloses a fence. When the squarely sawn boards gather, one by one, a place for people to live finally stands. Ordinary things stack up to become a home."},"ICON-1145":{"nm":"Bamboo","on":"bamboo","de":"Hollow within, yet upright before the wind. Old scholars longed to resemble its resolve, severing at each joint and sprouting anew. Here stands a thing all the more upright for being empty."},"ICON-1146":{"nm":"Cork","on":"cork","de":"Press it down and let go, and it swells back to its original thickness. Looking at this grain, light yet tenacious, you learn that softness is by no means weakness. From bottle stoppers to bulletin boards, it quietly holds things up."},"ICON-1147":{"nm":"Grass","on":"grass","de":"Trampled, it stands again with the next rain. A green tenacity that covers a whole field without a single name. Don't make light of its smallness; what announces spring first is always this lowly place."},"ICON-1148":{"nm":"Straw","on":"straw","de":"What's left golden in the field after the autumn harvest. Woven, it became a roof; laid out, it became a warm bed. The heart that, having given up every grain, covers people to the very last."},"ICON-1149":{"nm":"Reed","on":"reed","de":"When the wind brushes by, rustle, rustle, the whole riverside sings. A stalk that, hollow inside, cries all the farther. The reed isn't the least bit ashamed that its very swaying is its song."},"ICON-1150":{"nm":"Cotton","on":"cotton","de":"When the ripe boll pops open, a little cloud of a blossom blooms. This light, soft fluff becomes thread and becomes cloth, gently warming someone's shoulders on a cold winter night."},"ICON-1151":{"nm":"Wool","on":"wool","de":"Rub it on your hands and an oiliness lingers and warmth quietly remains. The coat a sheep wrapped around itself to endure the cold mountains. That sheared-off warmth now moves on into a person's winter."},"ICON-1152":{"nm":"Thread","on":"thread","de":"Thin as it is, barely there, it's always this that rejoins two fallen ends. Weak as a single strand, woven together it becomes a whole cloth. In the work of joining, thickness doesn't matter."},"ICON-1153":{"nm":"Cloth","on":"cloth","de":"Weft and warp cross countless times to form a single width. It's the result of threads that would unravel alone holding tight to one another. That the closer the weave, the warmer it is, holds true between people too."},"ICON-1154":{"nm":"Leather","on":"leather","de":"The more it's used, the more the marks of handling soak in, growing little by little to resemble its owner. As the first stiffness wears in, the color deepens and the grain softens. That sheen carved by time can be imitated by nothing."},"ICON-1155":{"nm":"Feather","on":"feather","de":"Light enough that you feel no weight even resting it on your palm. A single strand holding the memory of flying through the sky just as it was. Please don't forget, that the lightest thing rose the highest."},"ICON-1156":{"nm":"Seashell","on":"seashell","de":"Grandmother's words to hold it to your ear suddenly come to mind. On its inner rainbow sheen the sea you left behind is carved whole, so that even an empty shell carries the swell of a bygone time."},"ICON-1157":{"nm":"Coral","on":"coral","de":"Hardened like stone, yet once it was surely a breathing colony. In the slow sea it spends hundreds of years stretching out its branches. The sturdiest branch grows only after the longest wait."},"ICON-1158":{"nm":"Pearl","on":"pearl","de":"Unable to bear the irritation of a single grain of sand, the oyster quietly wrapped it in light. Embrace your pain and round it off and it grows this lustrous, a small comfort the sea offers."},"ICON-1159":{"nm":"Seaweed","on":"seaweed","de":"A green ribbon draped slippery over the shore rocks at low tide. Grip it and a fishy sea-smell rushes over you. Rootless, entrusting its body to the current, the sea quietly tends its garden."},"ICON-1160":{"nm":"Laver","on":"laver","de":"Hold one black sheet briefly to the fire and it greens and a savory smell spreads. That morning of rolling it round freshly cooked rice. Thin as it is, it amply embraces the happiness of one meal."},"ICON-1161":{"nm":"Salt","on":"salt","de":"I'm the white crystal the sea left out in the sun. A single pinch deepens a bland soup, but a slip of the hand buries every flavor. Only a hand that knows the right measure can wield me properly."},"ICON-1162":{"nm":"Glass Shard","on":"glass shard","de":"Only at the place it broke does it finally bend light into a rainbow. A talent it never knew while whole. Even a broken thing keeps a share of sunlight to give, the shard lying by the window quietly tells you."},"ICON-1163":{"nm":"Glass","on":"glass","de":"Being transparent doesn't only mean having nothing to hide. It's erased its own form in letting the light pass through whole. Even in dwelling there unseen, there's a cool tidiness when a hand touches it."},"ICON-1164":{"nm":"Glass Bottle","on":"bottle","de":"It has to be empty inside to hold something. Jam, a handful of wildflowers, or a folded letter, its name changes with whatever comes in. A vessel unafraid of emptiness is the most generous."},"ICON-1165":{"nm":"Empty Bottle","on":"bottle","de":"I love the stillness that comes after the last drop is drunk. Someone throws me away; someone rinses me and sets me on the windowsill to fill me with sunlight. To find use again where things have ended, that's the second life of the emptied."},"ICON-1166":{"nm":"Paper","on":"paper","de":"I lie spread out white, ready to take down anything. It's always me who gazes longest into the heart of one hesitating over the first line. The patience of a blank page runs a handspan deeper than ink."},"ICON-1167":{"nm":"Old Paper","on":"old paper","de":"Yellowed isn't aging but enduring. In every fold the warmth of the hands that opened and read it has soaked in. Old paper, so as not to be forgotten, writes down the time that flowed by in its own color."},"ICON-1168":{"nm":"Ink","on":"ink","de":"It starts as a single drop, becomes a sentence, and once dry remains like a promise. Smudged, it's the trace of that day just as it smudged. Since my job is to make things irreversible, people press me down once more, carefully."},"ICON-1169":{"nm":"Iron Ore","on":"iron ore","de":"A stone that slept a red sleep underground. Only after passing through fire does it finally yield the iron within. Hardness isn't hard from the start; it's a name received after passing through the heat."},"ICON-1170":{"nm":"Iron Ingot","on":"iron ingot","de":"Only after the ore endured the fire did it cool into a single lump. This cold, heavy shape becomes a bridge, a blade, a hoe. Because my use isn't yet decided, I can become anything."},"ICON-1171":{"nm":"Copper Ore","on":"copper ore","de":"I came out of the earth wearing a green-apple rust. Melt me and bells ring, statues stand, wires flow. Even while asleep in the pitch-dark ground, I always waited for my turn to be called into something."},"ICON-1172":{"nm":"Copper Ingot","on":"copper ingot","de":"Keep it around long enough and it tailors a blue garment for itself by its own hand. Some call that hue a flaw; some caress it as the pattern of years. The metal unashamed of its changing color is the longest loved."},"ICON-1173":{"nm":"Gold Ore","on":"gold ore","de":"A single speck met by panning river sand again and again. Precious not for being rare but for never changing. Old folk pressed it into hands as a token, telling them to resemble a heart that doesn't rust."},"ICON-1174":{"nm":"Gold Ingot","on":"gold ingot","de":"It lies as a single lump, neither dulling nor rusting. It has heard the most of people's greed, yet I myself covet nothing. Just a heavy silence faithful only to the work of shining."},"ICON-1175":{"nm":"Scrap Metal","on":"scrap metal","de":"It hasn't run out of use; it's awaiting its next use. Broken nails and dented cans gather together to meet the hot fire again. To me, the word discarded means resting for a while."},"ICON-1176":{"nm":"Screw","on":"screw","de":"Alone I can do nothing. Only when twisted in to bind two boards tight do I finally play my part. The knack of a small body holding a large thing, even that tightening force holds devotion."},"ICON-1177":{"nm":"Nail","on":"nail","de":"Once driven in, I rarely back down. With each strike of the hammer what deepens isn't a wound but a promise. If it's a matter of firmly joining something, I gladly offer up my head."},"ICON-1178":{"nm":"Gear","on":"gear","de":"I push my neighbor's teeth and turn together. I don't try to race ahead alone but know how to match the pace beside me. Like a clock whose time flows only when teeth mesh, I believe harmony is itself motion."},"ICON-1179":{"nm":"Spring","on":"ring","de":"The more it's pressed, the more it gathers within the force to spring back. Bending isn't giving up but readying to unfurl again. A small coil that rebounds as much as it absorbed the shock, where flexibility is itself strength."},"ICON-1180":{"nm":"Wire","on":"wire","de":"On the outside a quiet sheath, on the inside a path that flows without rest. From unseen places it carries light and sound. Like a hand that silently connects things backstage, it's a passage all the more trusted for going unseen."},"ICON-1181":{"nm":"Battery","on":"battery","de":"It stows away half a day's bright light, bit by bit, within its small body. Spent, just refill it, it says, never taking emptiness for an end. It holds a small evening to light someone's long night."},"ICON-1182":{"nm":"Light Bulb","on":"light bulb","de":"A single slender filament glows red and pushes back the dark. It burns its own body not to heat the room but to light it. Hottest at the moment it switches on, and so the brightest, a small sun of a single instant."},"ICON-1183":{"nm":"Lens","on":"lens","de":"It gathers scattering light and sets it sharp at a single point. It quietly summons the far-off stars and the tiny letters on your palm alike. Helping the act of seeing, it hides its own form, a clear, round matchmaker."},"ICON-1184":{"nm":"Rubber","on":"rubber","de":"Press it or stretch it, it returns to its place in the end. Those who mocked it as soft still choose me to wear on a rainy day. The work of softly taking in a harsh shock, tenacity lives even within this pliancy."},"ICON-1185":{"nm":"Plastic Piece","on":"plastic piece","de":"A small piece broken off the main body. It nearly got thrown out, but gather many and it becomes something new again. Not light because it's small, but able to travel far because it's light, a part of something."},"ICON-1186":{"nm":"Rope","on":"rope","de":"Only by twisting many strands does it become a single line. Alone it unravels easily, but woven it hauls a boat and binds a load. An old knot of cooperation, rough on the palm, made tougher for being twisted together."},"ICON-1187":{"nm":"Sailcloth","on":"sailcloth","de":"It doesn't hate the wind but takes it full to its chest. Only when taut and swelling does it send the boat far, so even a headwind becomes my strength. The way to advance by embracing rather than resisting the fierce, I learned at sea."},"ICON-1188":{"nm":"Anchor Fragment","on":"anchor fragment","de":"It's but one corner of an anchor, yet it remembers that weight in full. The days of gripping the deep bottom and bringing a ship to a halt. Even broken off now, it's a heavy fragment that knows the weight of staying."},"ICON-1189":{"nm":"Ship Nail","on":"ship nail","de":"A nail that held down a deck pitching on the waves, point by point. Even rusted red by the salt, it never let go of its place to the end. Holding fast to a drifting thing takes grit too."},"ICON-1190":{"nm":"Waterproof Cloth","on":"waterproof cloth","de":"It makes no fuss about the work of blocking rain. It silently takes what pours from above and keeps what's below dry. Plain as it is, a sturdy single layer that covers someone's load from getting wet."},"ICON-1191":{"nm":"Dye","on":"dye","de":"Seep quietly into plain cloth and it finally becomes a color. Indigo or madder, the mothers of old stained their fingertips dressing cloth in color. Even in the work of sinking in and soaking through, there's a depth that hardly fades."},"ICON-1192":{"nm":"Fragrance Oil","on":"fragrance oil","de":"A single drop and a wide field unfurls at once, filling the room. A guest who arrives first though unseen by the eye. A scene that touches the nose first, slyly tugging at the hem of sleeping memories."},"ICON-1193":{"nm":"Wax","on":"wax","de":"Take in heat and it flows; cool and it hardens, keeping its shape. Moving between softness and firmness, it quietly molds anything. A tender material that seals and closes and polishes, changing its expression with the temperature."},"ICON-1194":{"nm":"Candle","on":"candle","de":"It slowly melts its own body to light one square of darkness. When it's all burned, only its shortened height remains, but the time it warmed someone's night never disappears. An upright wick that knows the way of shining as it grows small."},"ICON-1195":{"nm":"Compost","on":"compost","de":"Rotting things gather together to become the richest soil. Discarded peels and dry fallen leaves become the meal of spring's new sprouts. In the very spot you thought was over, the next life quietly steadies its first breath."},"ICON-1196":{"nm":"Rice","on":"rice","de":"It takes eighty-eight touches of the hand to hold a single grain in your palm. From planting to threshing, a farmer's whole year is held entirely in this small grain. A steaming bowl of rice is, in itself, someone's four seasons."},"ICON-1197":{"nm":"Brown Rice","on":"brown rice","de":"With only its outer husk lightly peeled, it kept its original color just as it was. That it grows nuttier the more you chew is the taste of an honesty that didn't rush. The grain's firm stubbornness, refusing to be milled smooth and keeping its rough grain."},"ICON-1198":{"nm":"Wheat","on":"wheat","de":"It remembers the golden field bowing its head all at once in the wind. Becoming bread and noodles and dumpling-dough, it warms tables all over the world. A grain that, for being so common, has seeped all the deeper into people's lives."},"ICON-1199":{"nm":"Flour","on":"flour","de":"Only after becoming a fine white powder does it finally ready itself to become anything. Meet water and it swells; meet fire and it cooks. With no fixed form, it's a gentle base that takes whatever shape the hands knead it into."},"ICON-1200":{"nm":"Dough","on":"dough","de":"Powder and water blend into a single lump beneath the palm. The more you knead it the chewier it grows; the longer you wait the rounder it swells. Rush and it turns tough, so the time of rising alone cannot be hurried, says the old bakery."},"ICON-1201":{"nm":"Breadcrumbs","on":"breadcrumbs","de":"Brush the fine white dust off your fingertips and before you know it your sleeves have gone white too. As a coating they turn crisp; piled up soft, they look like the first snow. It's the lightest trace a loaf leaves behind from baking, yet even small things grow into something useful."},"ICON-1202":{"nm":"Pasta Noodles","on":"pasta","de":"The moment you fan a handful into boiling water, a far-off sunlight crosses into the kitchen. Long strands are work for the wrists, and al dente is the patience of waiting just slightly underdone. Look at that sheen as it winds round and round the fork."},"ICON-1203":{"nm":"Instant Noodles","on":"instant noodles","de":"A packet snuck onto the stove at dawn, all the stage makeup wiped away. The three minutes it takes the noodles to soften are the most private of the whole day. The tension cools along with your breath as you blow on it, and behind fogged glasses today quietly comes to an end."},"ICON-1204":{"nm":"Rice Cake","on":"rice cake","de":"Only after rice endures the pounding of the mortar does it become tteok. Plain, as injeolmi, as songpyeon—the same grain earns a hundred names from the hands that shape it. Set on a feast table, it calls to affection before the mouth; it tastes best shared."},"ICON-1205":{"nm":"Soup Rice Cakes","on":"soup rice cakes","de":"Slice a cylinder of tteok on the diagonal and the rounds come out like little coins. Is it rice cake floating in the white broth, or a round little wish? Finishing a bowl on New Year's morning adds a year to your age—a tender way, this country's way of counting."},"ICON-1206":{"nm":"Potato","on":"potato","de":"Knock off the dirt and a round face appears. A tuber that swelled in silence through the winds off the Gangwon slopes—fluffy when steamed, savory when fried. Even on lean-pocketed days, it honestly filled the family's bellies."},"ICON-1207":{"nm":"Sweet Potato","on":"sweet potato","de":"When the roasted-sweet-potato drum went up at the mouth of the alley, that was winter beginning. Peel back the foil and the yellow steam warms your fingers first; that sweetness is the root's reward for enduring the cold. Just right for blowing on, splitting in two, and sharing the warmth."},"ICON-1208":{"nm":"Carrot","on":"carrot","de":"A single orange spear driving straight down through the soil. You'd think only rabbits liked it, but sauté it and a hidden sweetness wakes, drop it in soup and it adds color too. The old folks who said it's good for the eyes were, by and large, right."},"ICON-1209":{"nm":"Radish","on":"radish","de":"One white, heavy root and the winter table is set. Bracingly cold as dongchimi, refreshing as radish soup, crisp as kkakdugi. Nothing goes to waste—even the green tops are dried under the eaves and kept as siraegi—a thrifty vegetable."},"ICON-1210":{"nm":"Onion","on":"onion","de":"Peel the skin and a single tear rolls down. The sharp, stinging flesh turns sweet as a lie once it meets hot oil. Its name is written on the first line of nearly every Korean dish—the quiet lead that silently lays down the foundation of flavor."},"ICON-1211":{"nm":"Green Onion","on":"green onion","de":"Scatter the thinly sliced white base and green tops over the broth and only then does a bowl feel truly finished. Stand the leftover root in a cup of water and it shoots up again—a little windowsill garden for the household-minded."},"ICON-1212":{"nm":"Garlic","on":"garlic","de":"Six cloves gathered in a circle make one bulb. The pungent root that, they say, turned a bear into a woman. Mince it with the flat of a blade and the aroma flares up at once; without a handful of it, neither kimchi nor stew makes any sense at all."},"ICON-1213":{"nm":"Ginger","on":"ginger","de":"A small, knobby root like a tangle of knots. Just one slice quiets the fishy smell and warms a chilled body from within. On nights you groaned with a cold, that warm cup steeped with honey began with this sharp little bite."},"ICON-1214":{"nm":"Napa Cabbage","on":"napa cabbage","de":"Salt the tight-packed leaves and only then does kimchi's first chapter open. In late autumn it piled up like mountains in every yard. The whole family sitting around to make a batch was a promise to get through the long winter together."},"ICON-1215":{"nm":"Cabbage","on":"cabbage","de":"Peel the round, layered leaves one by one and there's no end to it, so before long your heart slows and eases. Blanched, it's tender; sautéed, sweet. Beneath a plain exterior, this vegetable hides an unexpected gentleness."},"ICON-1216":{"nm":"Lettuce","on":"lettuce","de":"Lay a slice of meat in the cupped leaf, add a dab of ssamjang, and cram a full mouthful in. At a circle of people wrapping and eating, anyone quietly lets formality drop—this is nothing less than the hospitality of green."},"ICON-1217":{"nm":"Leaf Lettuce","on":"leaf lettuce","de":"The first leaf to rise in a corner of the garden. Pick it and it grows back, filling the table all summer long. That fresh green scent—rinsed in cold water and wrapped up by hand—is, for some, the whole taste of home."},"ICON-1218":{"nm":"Spinach","on":"spinach","de":"That cartoon green that gave a burst of strength when the can was emptied. Blanched, it shrinks to a handful, but its scent and vigor stay whole. Good seasoned by hand or stirred into soybean soup—a vegetable never to be taken lightly just for being common."},"ICON-1219":{"nm":"Bracken Fern","on":"bracken fern","de":"Snap the tender shoots the spring mountain offers, then boil and dry them. Only after all that long labor do they reach the ancestral table or the bibimbap bowl. Layered with care for all the trouble it takes, it's a precious herb the mountain raised over one season."},"ICON-1220":{"nm":"Wild Greens","on":"wild greens","de":"Seemingly nameless, yet each holds a scent of its own—spring's gift. Grandmother's hands know at a glance which leaf on the mountain path is good to eat. In one basket of greens, a whole season comes along, scent and all."},"ICON-1221":{"nm":"Mugwort","on":"mugwort","de":"The bitter-yet-fragrant herb that first breaks through frozen ground. Made into rice cake, the light of spring goes straight into your mouth. Come the first month they believed boiling it into soup warded off the year's misfortune, so spring always arrived on this scent."},"ICON-1222":{"nm":"Perilla Leaf","on":"perilla leaf","de":"A single leaf is enough to stain the whole mouth with its scent. Pair it with golden grilled pork belly, or pickle it stacked in soy sauce, and a bowl of rice vanishes in no time. This singular aroma feels right only at this land's table."},"ICON-1223":{"nm":"Green Pepper","on":"green pepper","de":"A hollow green fruit that breaks with a crisp crunch. The faint bitterness wakes a dulled appetite, and sautéed in oil its color turns brighter still. Chopped fine and scattered, it freshens any dish in an instant."},"ICON-1224":{"nm":"Bell Pepper","on":"bell pepper","de":"Red, yellow, orange—colors like traffic lights filling a whole basket. Bite one raw and the sweet juice trickles out; just the color brightens the table. The saying that good-looking vegetables whet the appetite fits this one exactly."},"ICON-1225":{"nm":"Tomato","on":"tomato","de":"The round red that's forever argued over—fruit or vegetable? Simmered long, its flavor deepens; eaten raw, it's wonderfully fresh. It's the fruit that gathers midsummer sun most honestly, so one bite bursts open a whole bright afternoon."},"ICON-1226":{"nm":"Cucumber","on":"cucumber","de":"The green that cools summer heat most refreshingly. Float it in cold soup and your mouth goes crisp and chilled; pickle it as sobagi and the crunch comes alive. On sweltering days you can even slice it thin and lay it over your eyes—cool inside and out."},"ICON-1227":{"nm":"Squash","on":"squash","de":"It hangs round at the end of the vine, slowly filling with sweetness into late autumn. Stewed soft it becomes a yellow porridge that settles the stomach; fried it turns into a golden jeon. Hung beneath the eaves, it serves as a dependable pantry all winter."},"ICON-1228":{"nm":"Young Squash","on":"young squash","de":"The light-green that swells by the day in the summer garden. Cubed into soybean stew, fried golden as jeon—so tender it's gentle even for a small child's mouth. Common, and all the more welcome for it: a regular at the midsummer table."},"ICON-1229":{"nm":"Eggplant","on":"eggplant","de":"A long fruit glossed all over with purple sheen. Soak up oil and it turns endlessly soft; steam it through and the grain is fine as silk. Plain as it seems, it pairs well with anything—the table's gentle supporting player."},"ICON-1230":{"nm":"Corn","on":"corn","de":"Yellow kernels lined up neat, one beside another. A summer snack steamed in the pot, blown on and bitten into; also the welcome sign that the fields have ripened. Inside that fuzzy bundle of silk, the sweetness is packed full."},"ICON-1231":{"nm":"Soybean","on":"soybean","de":"Small, hard beads drink water overnight and plump up. Ground fine into soy milk, fermented soft into jang—most of this land's table protein began right here. Bury a single bean in the soil and it returns as a whole plant again."},"ICON-1232":{"nm":"Tofu","on":"tofu","de":"When soybeans drink water, are ground and set, they become a white block with square, even corners. Soft and unassuming, it never insists on its own color in any soup. It collapses gently even at the touch of a spoon—a food whose virtue is plainness itself."},"ICON-1233":{"nm":"Red Bean","on":"red bean","de":"Boil the small red beads through and a deep, dark-red sweetness steeps out. On the longest night, a warm bowl of red-bean porridge once drove off both the cold and evil spirits—that heart lives in it still. Layered through steamed cake, that red was nothing less than devotion."},"ICON-1234":{"nm":"Red Bean Paste","on":"red bean paste","de":"Boiled red beans mashed fine, then reduced and reduced into a smooth filling. A spoonful between bread, inside rice cake, atop shaved ice—one thread of sweetness warms even old memories. All that long time of straining and reducing becomes the sweetness itself."},"ICON-1235":{"nm":"Mushroom","on":"mushroom","de":"After the rain clears, it lifts its head without a sound in the dim shade of the forest. The soil's craft, growing its own scent without a single handful of sun. Add just a pinch to soup and a deep savoriness steeps out without meat—a secret the forest keeps hidden."},"ICON-1236":{"nm":"Shiitake Mushroom","on":"shiitake mushroom","de":"A brown umbrella with its cap spread wide. Dried bone-dry in the sun, its scent grows several times deeper, so one dried cap can carry a whole pot of broth. A sturdy pillar of the vegetarian table, and a long favorite of those who know deep flavor."},"ICON-1237":{"nm":"Pine Mushroom","on":"pine mushroom","de":"Deep in an autumn pine forest, it lifts its head only beside the pines. It can't be cultivated and must be found on foot, which makes its scent all the more precious. Lightly grilled with just a touch of salt, a stretch of forest enters your mouth."},"ICON-1238":{"nm":"King Oyster Mushroom","on":"king oyster mushroom","de":"Tear the thick stem along the grain and the chewiness comes right into your hand. It grows sturdily through every season, so it's never far from the table. Grilled or sautéed—within its generous flesh, an easy heartiness is packed full."},"ICON-1239":{"nm":"Strawberry","on":"strawberry","de":"At the far end of a winter-hardened greenhouse, it ripens red the earliest. One bite is sweet and tart, just like early spring's first greeting. Set a single round one atop a cake and even an ordinary today turns into an anniversary."},"ICON-1240":{"nm":"Blueberry","on":"blueberry","de":"Pop one and a bright tartness spreads through your whole mouth. Pick up the little purple beads one by one and before you know it the tub is empty; scattered over white milk, a small night sky unfolds right there."},"ICON-1241":{"nm":"Apple","on":"apple","de":"Bite into one and autumn shatters with a crisp snap. That red the orchard grandmother wiped with her apron and handed over is a color that comes only from long holding of sunlight. The firmer it is, the better it knows how to stay sweet to the last."},"ICON-1242":{"nm":"Pear","on":"pear","de":"Peel the skin and your fingertips go cool first. Front row of the Chuseok ancestral table—the moment its chilled, sweet juice fills your mouth, a small measure of autumn's night breeze quietly comes and sits beside you."},"ICON-1243":{"nm":"Peach","on":"peach","de":"Where each peach blossom fell, a fuzzy summer takes shape. Press it lightly and the scent spreads first; the moment you bite in, the whole season follows into your mouth."},"ICON-1244":{"nm":"Grapes","on":"grapes","de":"Purple beads hang as one cluster, leaning shoulder to shoulder. Pop one and the tart comes first, the sweet half a beat behind—like a tidy chorus called up by summer's last days."},"ICON-1245":{"nm":"Green Grapes","on":"green grapes","de":"The light green lets the sunlight pass straight through, lighting a lamp in every bead. Seedless and clean, its sweetness is without a single excess, like a first phrase freshly drawn out."},"ICON-1246":{"nm":"Lemon","on":"lemon","de":"Scratch the yellow peel with a fingernail and the scent snaps awake at the tip of your nose. One drop and your lips pucker on their own, yet at the end of that sourness there's a strange corner where the whole day turns bright."},"ICON-1247":{"nm":"Lime","on":"lime","de":"Smaller and deeper green than a lemon, this little fruit greets you first with its sharp, zesty scent. One slice wakes even lukewarm water in an instant—a small handful of refreshment, tiny but tough."},"ICON-1248":{"nm":"Orange","on":"orange","de":"The moment you peel it, the smell of sunlight clings to your fingers. Put each segment in your mouth and pop, pop—little balloons of sweet juice burst, and the round thing rolls even your mood round."},"ICON-1249":{"nm":"Tangerine","on":"tangerine","de":"Remember that taste—peeling them with your feet tucked under the warm-floor quilt in winter? The scent spreading from under your nails turned the whole room yellow. One bag is an excuse for the family to gather round."},"ICON-1250":{"nm":"Banana","on":"banana","de":"There were days I made a meal of one yellow thing that rolled out of my bag in a corner of the practice room at a hungry dawn. Soft, sweet, and filling—the kindest of stopgaps."},"ICON-1251":{"nm":"Pineapple","on":"pineapple","de":"You have to get past a layer of thorny skin before the yellow flesh shows. Hold a piece in your mouth and the sweet-tart stings the tongue, while the smell of a southern sea lingers at your lips."},"ICON-1252":{"nm":"Mango","on":"mango","de":"Pull the ripe flesh apart by hand and a sticky sweet scent wets your fingers. As the deep yellow melts and vanishes in your mouth, a sweet dream like a short summer nap passes by."},"ICON-1253":{"nm":"Coconut","on":"coconut","de":"Shake the hard shell and you hear water sloshing inside. Crack it open—white flesh and cool juice—a little jar holding a far-off sea whole, swaying within."},"ICON-1254":{"nm":"Dragon Fruit","on":"dragon fruit","de":"Its pink-scaled look gives you pause at first, but split it and the white inside is dotted with tiny black seeds. Plain in taste yet flashy in dress—a sly trickster, inside and out exactly opposite."},"ICON-1255":{"nm":"Kiwi","on":"kiwi","de":"Cut the fuzzy brown in half and a green jewel appears. Spoon up a section where black seeds are set like stars, and one tart bite shakes you awake from sleep."},"ICON-1256":{"nm":"Chicken","on":"chicken","de":"Lay it in an oiled pan and the golden sizzle cooks first. Mild and tender, it slips easily onto anyone's table—a regular for an easy meal."},"ICON-1257":{"nm":"Pork","on":"pork","de":"On the grill it sizzles, fat popping as it browns. On those company-dinner nights of cramming a full mouthful wrapped in lettuce with a dab of ssamjang, its savory richness warms the whole table."},"ICON-1258":{"nm":"Beef","on":"beef","de":"Along each red grain, fat is finely marbled and gleams. Set it on a hot stone plate and the aroma fills the room first; the moment a slice enters your mouth, the day's weariness quietly loosens."},"ICON-1259":{"nm":"Bacon","on":"bacon","de":"On the morning skillet it crisps up, the fat dancing. That salty smell alone draws even the late-sleeping family, rubbing their eyes, into the kitchen—a meal the scent calls first."},"ICON-1260":{"nm":"Sausage","on":"sausage","de":"The scored cuts split wide open, bursting with juice. The red octopus shape that held down one corner of the lunchbox was a small luxury that childhood lunchtimes enjoyed."},"ICON-1261":{"nm":"Pepperoni","on":"pepperoni","de":"A round, spicy slice curls up from the edges atop the hot cheese. When a little oil pools, that's the peak of the whole pie—small, yet round and rich in presence."},"ICON-1262":{"nm":"Patty","on":"patty","de":"Shape it thick, set it on the grill, and it browns from the edges in. Tuck vegetables between a pressed-and-grilled round and a heartiness that fits in one hand is complete."},"ICON-1263":{"nm":"Egg","on":"egg","de":"Crack it open and the yolk slides out like a round little sun. Great mixed into fresh-cooked rice, great as the yellow stripe inside gimbap—the most common and so the most affectionate protein."},"ICON-1264":{"nm":"Milk","on":"milk","de":"A cold bottle left at the door at dawn—the day often opened with that coolness against the palm. Steaming when warmed, savory when chilled—a white that stays by your side anytime."},"ICON-1265":{"nm":"Cheese","on":"cheese","de":"A yellow slice slowly crumbles atop warm bread. The heart waiting for that one moment it stretches—the more it melts, the deeper and richer its savoriness grows."},"ICON-1266":{"nm":"Cheddar Cheese","on":"cheddar cheese","de":"Its deep orange foretells a salty taste at a glance. Slice it thin into a toast and the savory flavor spreads through your mouth—as clear in color as it is clear in flavor."},"ICON-1267":{"nm":"Butter","on":"butter","de":"Drop a piece into a hot pan and it melts away, savory steam rising. Spread on bread, mixed into rice—a yellow magic that makes anything it touches a touch softer."},"ICON-1268":{"nm":"Whipping Cream","on":"whipping cream","de":"The more you whisk, the more the runny white swells into firm clouds. The moment you spoon a dollop onto a cake, an ordinary afternoon brightens like a little birthday."},"ICON-1269":{"nm":"Yogurt","on":"yogurt","de":"Slide in a spoon and the tart white lifts smoothly. Mix in a piece of fruit and morning grows lighter; one cup and the stomach settles calmly—the taste of a gentle start."},"ICON-1270":{"nm":"Mackerel","on":"mackerel","de":"Set it on the grill and the oil pops, filling the kitchen with smoke both fishy and savory. The hands that picked out the bones and laid it over rice—the deepest devotion in an everyday meal."},"ICON-1271":{"nm":"Salmon","on":"salmon","de":"Pink grain lies stacked layer upon layer. Served cold it unravels softly in the mouth, grilled the oil seeps through savory—a firm taste that swam home against a far-off sea."},"ICON-1272":{"nm":"Tuna","on":"tuna","de":"Pop the can lid and a salty scent rushes up. There were times in a tiny rented room at night when one can mixed into rice or wrapped in seaweed became a hearty meal."},"ICON-1273":{"nm":"Cod","on":"cod","de":"Its clear flesh is so mild that boiling it draws a refreshing broth from the very start. A white fish that endured the knife-edged wind of a winter harbor—one hot bowl of stew and even chilled hands slowly thaw."},"ICON-1274":{"nm":"Shrimp","on":"shrimp","de":"Curl its back round and as it cooks the gray flushes rosy. Pop of springy bounce and a savory scent—peel and eat them one by one and the plate is somehow already empty."},"ICON-1275":{"nm":"Crab","on":"crab","de":"Picking the white meat from the hard shell is a small time of patience. The piece you put in your mouth at the end of that labor is sweet—an autumn sea entering your mouth whole."},"ICON-1276":{"nm":"Squid","on":"squid","de":"On the grill it curls into rounds, raising a savory smell. One chewy bite dipped in chili sauce and the salty sea follows along."},"ICON-1277":{"nm":"Clams","on":"clams","de":"In the clear broth they open their mouths and quietly give up their scent. As it bubbles and simmers, the sea's smell spreads, and one slurp warms and loosens a chilled stomach."},"ICON-1278":{"nm":"Fish Cake","on":"fish cake","de":"Dip it on the skewer into hot broth and steam rises in curls. On a cold day before a street cart, hands cupping broth in a paper cup and blowing on it—a small comfort the alley offers."},"ICON-1279":{"nm":"Kimchi","on":"kimchi","de":"Inside the jar it slowly ripens, growing a sour, deep scent. Tear it by hand and lay it over fresh-cooked rice and that's enough; the taste that differs house to house is that home's own history."},"ICON-1280":{"nm":"Pickled Radish","on":"pickled radish","de":"A yellow piece crunches, breaking briskly in the mouth. The steady partner beside a roll of gimbap or a plate of snack food—its sweet-tartness rinses a greasy mouth fresh."},"ICON-1281":{"nm":"Pickles","on":"pickles","de":"Cucumbers hold their breath briefly in salt, then open their eyes in vinegar. Not to miss the moment the crunch returns, the glass jar never leaves the sunlit windowsill. Time, slowly pickling, brings the flavor."},"ICON-1282":{"nm":"Red Chili Paste","on":"red chili paste","de":"A red that endured a whole year inside the jar. Behind the heat a soybean sweetness quietly hides, so one spoonful makes a stew finally our family's own face. A depth the yard's jang crocks raised on sunlight."},"ICON-1283":{"nm":"Soybean Paste","on":"soybean paste","de":"The meju block embraced its mold and lived through a winter. Its savory depth is a tightrope walk between just-ripe and over-ripe—Grandmother knew that line from a single sniff at her fingertips. A taste that deepens as long as you wait."},"ICON-1284":{"nm":"Soy Sauce","on":"soy sauce","de":"The darker the soybeans turn, the deeper their inner self. One drop revives a green dish and lends shine to a braise, so every color in the kitchen finally begins from this warm brown. A savoriness beyond the salt."},"ICON-1285":{"nm":"Black Bean Paste","on":"black bean paste","de":"Even the same black has a different grain. The sweet-salty finish of being fried once more with caramel—mix it into noodles and that black sheen shakes your appetite awake. The first button of Chinese wok flavor."},"ICON-1286":{"nm":"Curry Powder","on":"curry powder","de":"A yellow powder where many spices mingle peaceably in one spoon. Dissolve it in water and it bubbles up, warming the whole house—it becomes the preview of the heartiest bowl on a rainy evening."},"ICON-1287":{"nm":"Pepper","on":"pepper","de":"Ground whole, the scent lives; ground in advance, the scent quietly slips away. The last turn is always just before you cut the heat—a small period the cooking hand sparingly sets down."},"ICON-1288":{"nm":"Chili Powder","on":"chili powder","de":"Sun-dried peppers under the autumn light at last complete their red. Whether ground fine or coarse decides the kimchi's character, so a cook's touch comes, in the end, from choosing this powder's grain."},"ICON-1289":{"nm":"Salt","on":"salt","de":"Seasoning means stepping toward the under-salted side a pinch at a time. Salt once added can't be undone, so a seasoned hand always puts in a little less at the last and tastes. What you hold back is your room to breathe."},"ICON-1290":{"nm":"Sugar","on":"sugar","de":"It soothes bitterness and rounds off the corners of sour. But sweetness mustn't let its presence be caught, so the better the seasoning, the more sugar slips quietly out of sight at the end. A sweetness that knows how to hide."},"ICON-1291":{"nm":"Honey","on":"honey","de":"A jar the bees gathered crossing the flower fields thousands of times. When it hardens, revive it in a warm-water bath; stir it into tea and it gently wraps the throat. A golden spoonful of one whole season reduced down."},"ICON-1292":{"nm":"Cooking Oil","on":"cooking oil","de":"Swirl it once round a hot pan and the ingredients forget to stick. Pour too early and it burns, too late and it clings, so the single beat as the smoke just begins to rise is the rule of frying. You measure the moment by sound."},"ICON-1293":{"nm":"Olive Oil","on":"olive oil","de":"In the green of the first press, a grassy scent and a slight peppery bite live together. Drizzled at the end rather than set over heat, that scent survives to the last, so leaving it uncooked is its most honest use."},"ICON-1294":{"nm":"Sesame Oil","on":"sesame oil","de":"Drip a single drop at the end and the seasoned greens finally declare themselves complete. Its savoriness easily escapes over the flame, so it's always the period quietly added once all the cooking is done."},"ICON-1295":{"nm":"Vanilla Bean","on":"vanilla bean","de":"Split one pod and scrape out the black seeds, and the dessert changes into a garment of scent. Not throwing away even the spent husk but burying it in sugar—an old thrift the pastry chef inherited."},"ICON-1296":{"nm":"Cacao","on":"cacao","de":"White pulp and bitter seeds inside the fruit. Only after fermentation and sun-drying are they translated into the sweetness we know. Before becoming chocolate, it wears the first face closest to the wild."},"ICON-1297":{"nm":"Chocolate","on":"chocolate","de":"A finicky nature that melts away from the mere warmth of a palm. It must be set near 28 degrees for the snap and gloss to come alive, so behind the sweetness hides, surprisingly, a fussy rule of temperature."},"ICON-1298":{"nm":"Coffee Beans","on":"coffee beans","de":"Before grinding, one bean is close to a hard silence. But meet hot water and it swells up, pouring out its scent—the first signal that wakes the morning always begins from this small bean."},"ICON-1299":{"nm":"Tea Leaves","on":"tea leaves","de":"Stay too long in hot water and it turns astringent; too short and it's flat. To quietly reckon the time the leaves slowly unfurl—to steep tea is to measure waiting with your fingertips."},"ICON-1300":{"nm":"Mint","on":"mint","de":"Crush it and bitterness seeps out, so a tender leaf to handle ever so gently. Tap it lightly to wake the sleeping scent, and float it in a glass on a sweltering day—and midsummer settles a tone cooler."},"ICON-1301":{"nm":"Herbs","on":"herbs","de":"Add them stem and all for deep scent, use only the leaves for clarity. Dried they grow stronger, fresh they turn crisp—the kitchen's expressions widen as wide as the range of scent one bundle holds."},"ICON-1302":{"nm":"Chestnut","on":"chestnut","de":"Inside a thorny husk hides a glossy kernel. Score it and roast it and it splits with a pop, giving off a sweet scent—the warmth of a roasted-chestnut bag in a cold-wind alley feels close enough to hold."},"ICON-1303":{"nm":"Peanut","on":"peanut","de":"Its savoriness is completed over the roasting flame. A small kernel you shell one at a time until you lose track of time—shared sitting round on the wooden floor, the stories get shelled along with it, bit by bit."},"ICON-1304":{"nm":"Almond","on":"almond","de":"Blanch it lightly and peel it and the inside turns whiter and softer. Crushed and ground it's like milk, roasted whole it's crisp—the range of transformation in one nut widens a confectioner's imagination."},"ICON-1305":{"nm":"Sesame Seeds","on":"sesame seeds","de":"Shake them gently over low heat and at some moment they begin to pop. The instant just before that sound stops is the most savory time—roasting sesame turns out to be a thing you do by ear."},"ICON-1306":{"nm":"Sugarcane","on":"sugarcane","de":"Chew a single joint and the sweet juice seeps out along with a grassy scent. A stalk that must be reduced and reduced to become the sweetness we know—sugar's beginning is, surprisingly, this green and this tall."},"ICON-1307":{"nm":"Raw Sugar","on":"raw sugar","de":"A rough sweetness that holds its own color, having gone through less refining. A faint, earthy depth lingers, so hands that love the honesty of a thing before it's polished smooth seek it out on purpose."},"ICON-1308":{"nm":"Cacao Beans","on":"cacao beans","de":"The seeds just taken from the pod are bitter and astringent. They must quietly endure several days of fermentation before the scent blooms, so sweetness is a small prize this bean receives after long patience."},"ICON-1309":{"nm":"Cacao Nibs","on":"cacao nibs","de":"There isn't a single grain of sugar in the bits of crushed roasted bean. Put them in your mouth and bitterness comes first, savoriness following late, so you meet cacao before sweetness, most honestly."},"ICON-1310":{"nm":"Green Coffee Beans","on":"green coffee beans","de":"Green beads still carrying a raw scent. As they are, the aroma lies soundly asleep, so until they receive the baptism of fire, they quietly remain a possibility that doesn't yet know what it will become."},"ICON-1311":{"nm":"Roasted Coffee Beans","on":"roasted coffee beans","de":"On the brown surface where oil has lightly seeped out, the scent has pooled full. They must be ground before they cool for that scent to stay whole, so a cup's fate is quietly decided within a few days of roasting."},"ICON-1312":{"nm":"Vanilla Bean","on":"vanilla bean","de":"One stalk of scent dyes a whole pot of milk through. Stick even the spent pod into a sugar jar and days later all the sugar turns fragrant—a luxury with not a single part to throw away."},"ICON-1313":{"nm":"Pepper","on":"pepper","de":"The scent of a single peppercorn fades from the moment it's ground. So you keep it whole on the table and crush it as you go—freshness blooms from a heart that doesn't put things off."},"ICON-1314":{"nm":"White Pepper","on":"white pepper","de":"The bead, smoother for having its husk removed, is subtle rather than sharp. Born from the care of leaving not one black speck in a white sauce—the delicacy of an unseen place."},"ICON-1315":{"nm":"Cinnamon","on":"cinnamon","de":"Steep one piece and a warm spiciness slowly spreads through the tea. Added whole rather than as powder, the scent lasts longer, so the depth of a winter drink comes from this dried bark's perseverance."},"ICON-1316":{"nm":"Clove","on":"clove","de":"In one flower bud shaped like a little nail, scent is densely concentrated. Add too much and it swallows a dish whole, so the restraint of a single bud quietly keeps the balance of flavor."},"ICON-1317":{"nm":"Nutmeg","on":"nutmeg","de":"Keep the seed whole and grate a little as you go. It has a nature of scattering its scent quickly once pre-ground, so the last touch of one quick scrape makes a milk's aroma all the deeper."},"ICON-1318":{"nm":"Cardamom","on":"cardamom","de":"Pop the green pod and a cool, bracing scent spills out from inside. Crushing just a pod or two into tea lends an ordinary cup, all at once, the fragrance of a faraway land."},"ICON-1319":{"nm":"Saffron","on":"saffron","de":"Red threads, barely three gathered from a single flower. Dissolved in warm water, the yellow light slowly spreads, so preciousness is also the weight of time spent picking by hand, one by one."},"ICON-1320":{"nm":"Turmeric","on":"turmeric","de":"Grind the root from the soil and it dyes even your fingertips yellow. It has a nature where the scent wakes only when lightly sautéed in oil, so curry's golden hue is a color this small root drew up over the flame."},"ICON-1321":{"nm":"Bay Leaf","on":"bay leaf","de":"The leaf they say was set on a victor's brow. Float one in boiling water and through the steam the cheers of an old arena briefly rise. Even on days you didn't win, breathing in its scent becomes a green comfort that quietly holds the you of today."},"ICON-1322":{"nm":"Coconut Milk","on":"coconut milk","de":"The white juice that flows out only when you crack the hard shell. In a corner of a market in a hot country, stick in a straw and take one sip and the midday thirst cools clean away. The cool sweet scent spreading through your mouth brings the shade of the tropics."},"ICON-1323":{"nm":"Coconut Oil","on":"coconut oil","de":"Hardened, it's white as first snow; warmed in the palm, its scent spreads softly. The island grandmother's kind, household wisdom—handing it over saying one tub is enough from head to toe—is held whole inside the round jar."},"ICON-1324":{"nm":"Dried Banana","on":"dried banana","de":"Laid out under the sun for a few days, the yellow flesh turns chewy. Bite one piece sparingly at a time and the sticky sweet scent of a rainy harvest season quietly revives in your mouth. Slowly ripened sweetness holds a season that way."},"ICON-1325":{"nm":"Dried Mango","on":"dried mango","de":"The soft flesh, concentrated under the sun, was reborn as amber jelly. Sour, sweet, and chewy—all three tastes are in one piece, so roll it slowly in your mouth and one bag stretches the afternoon long."},"ICON-1326":{"nm":"Dried Pineapple","on":"dried pineapple","de":"Unlike its thorny exterior, the flesh inside is utterly yellow and bright. Dried in the sun, its tartness concentrates, so just one bite raises the corners of your mouth on their own. The fresh aftertaste at the end of a piece lingers long."},"ICON-1327":{"nm":"Tropical Fruit Basket","on":"basket","de":"Freshly picked colors blend together in one basket. Mango's orange, banana's yellow, pineapple's gold—before you even reach to choose, summer pushes in through the tip of your nose first. An armful that brightens the heart just to look at."},"ICON-1328":{"nm":"Bundle of Seaweed","on":"bundle of seaweed","de":"The sea's hair, gathered from the tide-bared rocks. The sound of waves is tangled into its salty briny scent, so soak it gently in cold water and a faintly fishy sea-smell slowly drifts as far as the kitchen. A handful spreads a small tidal flat across the table."},"ICON-1329":{"nm":"Dried Seafood","on":"dried seafood","de":"A handful of sea dried firm. Tear it along the grain by hand and, along with the saltiness, the briny wind of an old harbor unwinds. An old friend beside the warm-hearted table that makes you crave a bowl of makgeolli on its own."},"ICON-1330":{"nm":"Dried Squid","on":"dried squid","de":"Its ten legs spread out neat and dried in the sun. Grill it lightly until a savory scent rises, then tear it along the grain. With that chewy taste, the dignity of a late-night snack plate rises a notch."},"ICON-1331":{"nm":"Salted Fish","on":"salted fish","de":"Buried in coarse salt, fish learns how to endure time. One bite of its deeply salted flesh empties a bowl of rice in an instant—a fond secret a seaside grandmother passed down by her fingertips."},"ICON-1332":{"nm":"Salted Shrimp","on":"salted shrimp","de":"Little shrimp ripen slowly in salt, reborn as savory depth. The moment you add a spoonful into napa cabbage at kimchi season, that salty scent spread across the whole yard. That one spoonful decides the year's kimchi taste."},"ICON-1333":{"nm":"Anchovy","on":"anchovy","de":"A finger-sized body takes on the depth of a whole pot of broth. The childhood kitchen of chatting while pulling off heads and guts—small, yet a grateful fish standing firmly at the center of the household."},"ICON-1334":{"nm":"Kelp","on":"kelp","de":"A long black band grown beneath the sea. Put it in cold water and gently lift it out just before the boil—a promise that broth-makers have kept down the generations. Deep savoriness never, ever hurries."},"ICON-1335":{"nm":"Hijiki","on":"hijiki","de":"The bumpy texture pops on the tongue. The seaweed that dyed the tide-rocks green in spring—seasoned by hand, it spreads a small, fresh sea across a corner of the table. The taste of chewing spring."},"ICON-1336":{"nm":"Pearl Oyster","on":"pearl oyster","de":"A round light crafted by long holding between two firm shells. From turning the discomfort of one grain of sand into a jewel, the sea never once rushed. Set it on your palm and the weight of that long patience rests there too."},"ICON-1337":{"nm":"Coral Ornament","on":"coral ornament","de":"The sea's tree branch that the waves shaped over hundreds of years. Touched by light, it spreads into pink and orange, so just sitting quietly on a shelf dyes a whole room into a warm island. Even the rough grain against your fingertips feels fond."},"ICON-1338":{"nm":"Shell Button","on":"button","de":"Where the shellfish flesh left, the iridescent inner side was cut into a round. Sewn on a lapel, a little rainbow sparkles at your fingertips each time you fasten it. The last fond gift the sea left behind, giving all it had as it departed."},"ICON-1339":{"nm":"Glass Marble","on":"glass marble","de":"Roll it on your palm and the light trapped inside rolls right along. In those days of crouching in the alley playing marbles, oblivious to the setting sun, the pocket of a child who'd won one more was unusually heavy and proud."},"ICON-1340":{"nm":"Juniper Carving","on":"juniper carving","de":"Along each carved grain, a subtle scent seeps out. People of old burned this wood to gather a scattered heart. Hold one piece quietly and a calm slowly rises from your fingertips."},"ICON-1341":{"nm":"Incense","on":"incense","de":"A slender stalk slowly burns, opening a path upward. Follow the curve the smoke draws with your eyes and a heart that hurried all day soon slows its step and lingers quietly in place."},"ICON-1342":{"nm":"Dye Flower","on":"dye flower","de":"Loosen the color hidden in the petals into a boiling pot and the clear cloth slowly takes on that hue. Borrowing for a while the color nature painted in advance—dyeing was, at heart, a fond greeting offered to the flowers."},"ICON-1343":{"nm":"Indigo Dye","on":"indigo dye","de":"A deep, mellow blue drawn from fermenting and re-fermenting the indigo plant. Each time you dip and lift the cloth, it shifts its color slowly from sky-blue to sea-blue. A color of waiting, blooming only when you set down impatience."},"ICON-1344":{"nm":"Crimson Dye","on":"crimson dye","de":"Steep the madder root and a sunset asleep in the soil wakes inside the pot. It was the most festive, brightest color in the village, the one that dyed a new bride's skirt-hem beautifully on the wedding day."},"ICON-1345":{"nm":"Gold Thread","on":"thread","de":"Drawing gold finer than a hair, it's spun one strand at a time with devotion. Wherever it's embroidered it holds the light, so even in a dark room with the lamp out, that pattern alone rises softly bright on its own."},"ICON-1346":{"nm":"Silk","on":"silk","de":"The thread a silkworm spits must be woven and woven again to barely make one bolt. A touch that slides like spring water across the back of the hand—a fine-grained cloth that people of old held a whole season and slowly raised."},"ICON-1347":{"nm":"Pearl Button","on":"button","de":"Only the inner light of the pearl was chosen and shaped into a round. Each time you fasten one on a jeogori lapel, your fingertips turn briefly elegant. Small, yet a tidy bead that quietly lifts the grace of an outfit."},"ICON-1348":{"nm":"Map Fragment","on":"map fragment","de":"Beyond the torn edge, an unknown coastline breaks off abruptly. They say only one who gathers the remaining pieces reaches the treasure—but perhaps the very journey of wandering after it on the wind was already the treasure."},"ICON-1349":{"nm":"Old Sea Chart","on":"old sea chart","de":"Sea routes blurred by saltwater and a faded compass drawing. Trace with a fingertip the lines some sailor drew by the stars alone on a pitch-dark night, and an island long vanished slowly rises again on the old paper."},"ICON-1350":{"nm":"Message in a Bottle","on":"message in a bottle","de":"A single rolled-up sheet inside a glass bottle washed up by the waves. A greeting—no telling who sent it or when—has finally reached someone's hand. With heart enough, even the sea becomes a slow postman like this."},"ICON-1351":{"nm":"Drifted Crate","on":"crate","de":"The adventure lasts right up until the moment you pry open the lid, swollen stiff with brine. Whether what waits inside is treasure or just empty sand, a crate that has drifted far always washes ashore carrying the story of some unknown face along with it."},"ICON-1352":{"nm":"Little Key","on":"little key","de":"A worn scrap of metal that nestles right into your palm. Even though which door it opens has long been forgotten, a gentle weight lingers heavy at your fingertips, the kind that makes you think of unlocking before locking."},"ICON-1353":{"nm":"Silver Coin","on":"silver coin","de":"A round piece of silver, its pattern faded under countless thumbs. A single coin that was once someone's fare or a weary night's lodging; stroke its cold surface and the warmth of an old transaction faintly stirs back to life at your fingertips."},"ICON-1354":{"nm":"Gold Coin","on":"gold coin","de":"Set it on your palm and its heavy weight stirs the heart first. A single coin glowing yellow in the sun, it seems to promise riches if you hold it, yet what truly shines brightest is the flutter just before it lands in your hand."},"ICON-1355":{"nm":"Captain's Seal","on":"captain's seal","de":"The captain's promise, pressed firm into red wax. A single mark could raise an order and chart a rough course. Authority, in the end, was one small, solid stamp that everyone aboard the same ship agreed to believe in together."},"ICON-1356":{"nm":"Handheld Mic","on":"mic","de":"The moment you grip it, a strangely reassuring weight fills your palm. Whether you're offering a trembling first hello or finally belting out the high note, this one little rod quietly lends wings to your voice."},"ICON-1357":{"nm":"Wireless Mic","on":"mic","de":"With the cord gone, the whole stage opened up wider. Run all the way to the back of the seats and your voice never once cuts out, as if someone is gently nudging your back, telling you to run and sing to your heart's content."},"ICON-1358":{"nm":"Stand Mic","on":"mic","de":"Standing firm at your feet, it waits silently for the singer. When both hands are freed, the song spreads through your whole body instead of your fingertips. There's a clear charm in holding one spot to the very end, this rod quietly says."},"ICON-1359":{"nm":"Pop Filter","on":"filter","de":"A single round layer of cloth blocking the front of the mic. It softly filters out harsh breaths and lets only the clear voice through. Making someone heard means quietly shielding from a place that stays unseen to the very end."},"ICON-1360":{"nm":"In-Ear Monitor","on":"in-ear monitor","de":"Slip it snug into your ear and your own song comes clearly back to life beyond the roar of tens of thousands. The smallest, most secret companion, it keeps you from missing the beat on a stage flooded with light and sound."},"ICON-1361":{"nm":"Headphones","on":"headphones","de":"The moment they cover your ears, the world shrinks a notch and only the song looms large. A round little room no one can intrude upon. Strangely, alone inside headphones, you are not alone."},"ICON-1362":{"nm":"Sheet Music","on":"sheet music","de":"When the black dots settle quietly onto the lines, silent paper begins to hold sound. Writing you hear rather than read. The instant you open it, a song that had stood still breathes again."},"ICON-1363":{"nm":"Vocal Score","on":"vocal score","de":"A little circle is drawn at every place to breathe. Inhale here, gently release there. A tender map that clears a path so the voice comes to no harm."},"ICON-1364":{"nm":"Piano Score","on":"piano score","de":"A page where ten fingers ask the way at once. The left hand grips the roots, the right hand draws the song. Two hands telling different stories finally fold into one at the last measure."},"ICON-1365":{"nm":"Guitar Chord Chart","on":"chart","de":"The first foreign language fingers ever learn, its very first word is written here. When six dots gather into circles, only then does a single note ring out. On each night of pressing and pressing again, calluses grow at the tips."},"ICON-1366":{"nm":"Metronome","on":"metronome","de":"Tick, tick, an unwavering step beats at your side. When your heart races ahead, it holds you back slowly, slowly from behind. Because rhythm, in the end, is a promise to walk together."},"ICON-1367":{"nm":"Tuner","on":"tuner","de":"When the needle slides to dead center, the note finally finds its place. That single point, neither high nor low. Being in tune, it turns out, is this: no longer trembling, just quietly coming to rest."},"ICON-1368":{"nm":"Piano Keys Card","on":"card","de":"Flip it one page at a time and the keys walk right into your palm. A little universe of seven slots, from C up to B. Even on nights without a real piano, the song quietly grows here."},"ICON-1369":{"nm":"Guitar Pick","on":"guitar pick","de":"A small, sturdy sliver wedged between thumb and forefinger. Drop it and it vanishes forever beneath the chair, but the moment you hold it, all six strings ring out at once."},"ICON-1370":{"nm":"Drumsticks","on":"drumsticks","de":"When the two cross in midair, a signal drops right there. One, two, three, four. Everyone's scattered hearts begin to beat at the same pace, matched to those four counts."},"ICON-1371":{"nm":"Tambourine","on":"tambourine","de":"One shake and a clear sound scatters in every direction, like sunlight shattering into tiny pieces. Light as it looks, it's the first beat your hand reaches for when the mood starts to fade. No one can dismiss it for being small."},"ICON-1372":{"nm":"Dance Sneakers","on":"dance sneakers","de":"For feet that spin gliding across the floor, friction becomes a weapon. Every spin, turned again and again, is etched into the worn soles. The coolest move always begins from one sturdy pair."},"ICON-1373":{"nm":"Knee Pads","on":"knee pads","de":"Only those who have knelt countless times and risen again know the gratitude in this single thin layer of cloth. Something that keeps the floor from being frightening anymore, courage is sometimes wrapped around the knees like this."},"ICON-1374":{"nm":"Wrist Guard","on":"wrist guard","de":"Wrap the bending joint in advance and even a strained move becomes a little more forgiving. The wrist says nothing, enduring alone until it hurts. That long silence, one layer takes on instead."},"ICON-1375":{"nm":"Ankle Guard","on":"ankle guard","de":"At the end of a high jump comes the landing, and at the end of that landing is the ankle. The lowest place, where it takes on the weight of the whole body. This little band quietly watches over tomorrow's practice."},"ICON-1376":{"nm":"Stretch Band","on":"band","de":"Pull it and it resists, straining to return to where it was. While you endure that resistance, the body grows a little longer without noticing. Stretching, in the end, is the mark left by time spent enduring."},"ICON-1377":{"nm":"Yoga Mat","on":"mat","de":"The moment you unroll it, a patch of ground that's one person's share appears on the floor. A small territory for lying down, kneeling, and steadying your breath. The start and end of the day are quietly tied up on this single sheet."},"ICON-1378":{"nm":"Foam Roller","on":"foam roller","de":"Press firmly on a knotted spot and it hurts at first, then soon feels good. There's always a little pain in loosening what has stiffened. Because body and mind both have to be pressed once before they can release."},"ICON-1379":{"nm":"Dumbbell","on":"bell","de":"Lift the same weight and lift it again. Just one more time than yesterday, that's all. In repetition with nothing flashy about it, the arm thickens without a word. A lump of iron that is only ever honest."},"ICON-1380":{"nm":"Kettlebell","on":"bell","de":"One handle swings the whole body around. As the round weight circles in an arc, the balance of the one who holds on is put to the test. To stay unshaken, you first have to know your own center."},"ICON-1381":{"nm":"Jump Rope","on":"jump rope","de":"Leap over the rope whisking past underfoot, and leap again. Like that game of counting with friends out in the yard, the higher the numbers climb, the more your breath catches and your laughter grows."},"ICON-1382":{"nm":"Running Shoes","on":"running shoes","de":"A pair whose true worth you only know once you're out on the road. Cut through the dawn air running the same path again, and the corner that felt far yesterday is right before you today. The feet remember the distance."},"ICON-1383":{"nm":"Workout Towel","on":"workout towel","de":"Wipe the sweat from your brow and a single line of today's effort is soaked there. Wash it and the trace disappears, but however much you shed piles up somewhere, neatly. The most honest cheer always dries at your side."},"ICON-1384":{"nm":"Water Bottle","on":"bottle","de":"Empty it and fill it, dry and take a sip. That simple round trip silently sustains the day. Like a bucket rising and falling at the well, the day begins again from the act of filling."},"ICON-1385":{"nm":"Protein Shake","on":"protein shake","de":"Shake it well and down a gulp, and the muscle you broke today fills back up tomorrow. The taste isn't fancy, but the body knows this is the language of recovery. Growth is always sipped quietly."},"ICON-1386":{"nm":"Energy Bar","on":"energy bar","de":"A single bar flattened in your pocket. Emergency rations to fill the empty hours between meals. Nothing grand, but this one small bite lets you hold out for one more move in the afternoon."},"ICON-1387":{"nm":"Throat Lozenge","on":"throat lozenge","de":"Roll it around your mouth and cool mint gently soothes a roughened throat. On days you talked a lot, on nights you sang a lot, one small drop pats down the prickly path. There's a clear use for sweetness too."},"ICON-1388":{"nm":"Vocal Tea","on":"vocal tea","de":"Warm steam heats the throat, and with one sip the tension in your shoulders loosens away. An old remedy, like the ginger tea Grandma used to brew. A tender hello offered to the voice before singing."},"ICON-1389":{"nm":"Honey Water","on":"honey water","de":"Slowly stir a spoonful of honey into lukewarm water. The very cup the grown-ups would always make whenever your throat felt scratchy. Not medicine, not a drink, just a sweetness that quietly soothes the body from within."},"ICON-1390":{"nm":"Humidifier Tank","on":"tank","de":"A vessel that releases a little mist into the room. On winter nights when dry air claws at your throat, it shares moisture unseen. Caring for someone usually flows quietly like this."},"ICON-1391":{"nm":"Rest Coupon","on":"rest coupon","de":"A single slip of paper saying it's okay to rest. The moment you take it in hand, the weight on your mind grows one notch lighter. That stopping is also a kind of practice, this little ticket grants you permission instead."},"ICON-1392":{"nm":"Practice Schedule","on":"schedule","de":"Over the time written into each box, the day settles down little by little. Vocals in the morning, choreography in the afternoon, rest in the evening. Even a daunting tomorrow, once ruled into sections, becomes something worth walking through."},"ICON-1393":{"nm":"Attendance Stamp","on":"attendance stamp","de":"Press down a single mark to show you came again today. As the slightly smudged circles add up box by box, a diligence that seemed like nothing has somehow become a road. A small proof of each day."},"ICON-1394":{"nm":"Praise Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"Instead of saying well done, quietly stick on a single star. A glimmer the size of a fingernail, yet the moment it settles in the corner of a notebook, the whole day brightens. Praise is small, but strangely it shines for a long time."},"ICON-1395":{"nm":"Mental Notes","on":"notebook","de":"A page where the heart that trembled backstage is loosened out into words. Write honestly even about the days that didn't go well, and somehow it feels lighter. The heart grows sturdier the more you look into it."},"ICON-1396":{"nm":"Image Training Card","on":"card","de":"Close your eyes and hold it, and a stage quietly unfolds in your mind. Walking one lap in advance around a spot you haven't yet stood on. A path drawn in imagination arrives one step ahead of the actual toes."},"ICON-1397":{"nm":"Expression Mirror","on":"mirror","de":"In front of the mirror you smile, then freeze, making the same face a hundred times over. Here you learn that joy and sorrow both need practice. Because an expression is the act of copying the heart out to the outside."},"ICON-1398":{"nm":"Choreography Notes","on":"notebook","de":"A page where the path the feet and arms will travel is copied out as drawings. Arrows quietly tell you where the body should go on every eight-count. Even a move that just wouldn't stick is slowly tamed upon this page."},"ICON-1399":{"nm":"Choreo Video Chip","on":"chip","de":"Hundreds of moves are stored intact in one small chip. Play it through once more before sleep, and your fingertips move along that path on their own. Repetition is yet another record, copied out through the body."},"ICON-1400":{"nm":"Stage Blocking Chart","on":"chart","de":"A single map of the stage looked down on from above. Who meets where and scatters to where, all promised in advance with lines and dots. To draw one picture together, you first have to share out the paths."},"ICON-1401":{"nm":"Rehearsal Pass","on":"rehearsal pass","de":"The seats are empty and the lights still sleep. This one pass lets you in among that stillness. The stage when no one is watching, and so the time to meet your most honest self begins right here."},"ICON-1402":{"nm":"Style Book","on":"style book","de":"What mood shall I dress in today? Even a single shirt has a feeling that suits it, this book quietly tells you. The more pages you turn, the more a small eye for it gathers at the fingertips that once hesitated before the mirror."},"ICON-1403":{"nm":"Hairspray","on":"hairspray","de":"One spritz and not even the wind can carelessly tousle it. A small ambition to hold those few minutes on stage flawlessly in place. The perfect moment is always finished atop trivial stubbornness like this."},"ICON-1404":{"nm":"Makeup Palette","on":"makeup palette","de":"Twelve slots of color are twelve different moods. Which expression to sing in today, the fingertips choose first and the heart follows behind. In each emptying slot, the days left on stage are quietly stained."},"ICON-1405":{"nm":"Costume Pin","on":"pin","de":"In the most dazzling moment, there's a small pin holding the fabric from a spot that stays unseen. So it won't slip, so it won't come undone. The shine on stage always stands upon someone's steadfastness."},"ICON-1406":{"nm":"Name Board","on":"name board","de":"The moment a name fills the once-blank board, one hazy promise comes into focus. Who will stand in this spot, a single line of writing decides. A name is the shortest and firmest resolve."},"ICON-1407":{"nm":"Fan Service Card","on":"card","de":"The recipient is just one person, and to that one person it's the whole world. The act of pressing several nights' worth of gratitude into one short greeting. The heart overflows like this even on paper the size of a palm."},"ICON-1408":{"nm":"Signature Practice Sheet","on":"signature practice sheet","de":"At first even your own name comes out drawn strangely. Through dawns of stroking it a hundred times and refining it a thousand, until the hand memorizes the flow before the heart does. That's how one name finally becomes a signature."},"ICON-1409":{"nm":"Interview Question Sheet","on":"interview question sheet","de":"\"What do I say to this question?\" The fingertips gripping the paper tremble a little. Not memorizing answers but lining up sincerity in order, because an interview, like a confession, is in the end a question of the heart's sequence."},"ICON-1410":{"nm":"Vocabulary Book","on":"vocabulary book","de":"The most worn corner points to the word looked at the longest. As long as it takes one unfamiliar sound to settle on the tongue, the distance to a world you've never visited draws a hand's-breadth closer."},"ICON-1411":{"nm":"Pronunciation Card","on":"card","de":"The rolling 'R', the slipping 'S'. There are dawns spent flipping the cards one by one, taming the tongue. As your speech grows clearer, so does the face of someone you want to reach with those words."},"ICON-1412":{"nm":"Live Checklist","on":"live checklist","de":"Mic on, in-ears checked, blocking reviewed. With each square that fills, the unease in your chest empties one box at a time. Before going on stage, thoroughness is the quietest kind of courage."},"ICON-1413":{"nm":"Condition Patch","on":"condition patch","de":"There's a spot that spreads warm the moment you apply it. A strained shoulder, a stiff calf, a palm-sized comfort that quietly answers the small signals the body sends. Resting well is also a part of practice."},"ICON-1414":{"nm":"Ice Pack","on":"ice pack","de":"Lay it gently on a swollen ankle. Only as the cold slowly seeps in do you finally realize how much you ran today. Recovery behind the stage always arrives soundlessly like this."},"ICON-1415":{"nm":"First-Aid Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Bandages, painkillers, a hand mirror. There comes a moment when this little pouch packed with nothing-special things becomes the most reassuring of all. Kindness prepared in advance shines brightest before an unexpected crisis."},"ICON-1416":{"nm":"Cue Card","on":"card","de":"Someone slips it up from beyond the camera. The one line you nearly forgot is written there in neat letters. Behind a show that flows without a hitch, there's always a hand like this, never caught on screen."},"ICON-1417":{"nm":"Mission Envelope","on":"envelope","de":"The most heart-pounding moment is just before tearing the envelope open. Whatever's inside, that brief gap of thrilling not-knowing-yet. The charm of variety shows lives whole within that one sealed instant."},"ICON-1418":{"nm":"Name Tag","on":"tag","de":"A small name pinned at the chest stands in for the first hello. Among people who don't yet know each other, one name tag cracks the ice of awkwardness. From the moment a name is called, a relationship begins."},"ICON-1419":{"nm":"Penalty Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"A single sheet slapped on the loser's forehead bursts everyone into laughter. Too friendly to call a punishment, even losing becomes a lasting memory. A small, tender mark made so everyone can laugh together."},"ICON-1420":{"nm":"Random Penalty Card","on":"card","de":"No one knows until it's drawn. Ten spins of elephant-trunk, or a round of aegyo. The moment you entrust your whole fate to one slip of paper, it's the laughter that loosens free first."},"ICON-1421":{"nm":"Hint Card","on":"card","de":"Something like a hand quietly offered to a stuck spot. It doesn't give the whole answer, but it points the way. A good hint isn't the solution, but the act of gently handing over the courage to think once more."},"ICON-1422":{"nm":"Chance Card","on":"card","de":"A single chance to flip a tilted board in one stroke. When you draw this card decides the match. Luck saved up and saved up only proves its worth at the most decisive moment."},"ICON-1423":{"nm":"Time-Out Card","on":"card","de":"It's okay to stop for a moment, this card says for you. To raise your hand boldly when you need a breath, stopping is a legitimate strategy too, and resting well is also a seat of skill."},"ICON-1424":{"nm":"Laugh Button","on":"button","de":"Tap, and the instant you press it a bright burst of giggling laughter pours out in full. A truly funny scene calls for even a sound effect to slip in and help. The warmth of a gathering is heated up from one small prank like this."},"ICON-1425":{"nm":"Sound Effect Remote","on":"sound effect remote","de":"One button for applause, another for jeers. A wizard who shapes the mood with just the fingertips sits quietly in the control room. Direction never caught on screen is what makes that scene breathe alive."},"ICON-1426":{"nm":"Clapperboard","on":"clapperboard","de":"Clack, and with that crisp sound a cut begins. Between dozens of NGs and a single OK, this black board counts every moment out clearly. It's the first beat that the record steps into."},"ICON-1427":{"nm":"Marking Tape","on":"marking tape","de":"The moment your toes touch that line, the lights drop lightly down as if they'd been waiting. The one slot you memorized until it wore thin, the stage is finally completed by a small colored strip drawn on the floor."},"ICON-1428":{"nm":"Lighting Filter","on":"filter","de":"The same face is wholly transformed by the color of light. Dawn dwells in a blue filter, sunset in a red one. Atmosphere is never far away, it's quietly folded inside a single thin sheet of colored paper."},"ICON-1429":{"nm":"Camera Battery","on":"camera battery","de":"Once the red light starts blinking, the heart grows anxious first. Because the best scene always comes at 1 percent remaining. One spare in your pocket becomes the relief of catching your breath."},"ICON-1430":{"nm":"Memory Card","on":"card","de":"A whole day's laughter and sweat pack densely into a chip the size of a fingernail. So small it's easy to lose, and all the more precious for it. The weight of the memories it holds can never be measured by size."},"ICON-1431":{"nm":"Polaroid Film","on":"polaroid film","de":"Click, and then a quiet wait. The few seconds as a face slowly surfaces over the once-white sheet are strangely thrilling. Even an instant photo in your hand needs exactly one spoonful of patience."},"ICON-1432":{"nm":"Photocard Film","on":"photocard film","de":"Which expression will be printed onto this single sheet stays a secret until the very moment it prints. The face that will become someone's bias is born right here. One small piece of paper holds such a great heart."},"ICON-1433":{"nm":"Photocard Sleeve","on":"photocard sleeve","de":"A photocard is never touched with bare hands. Press one corner and even that day's smile aches. To wrap your bias carefully in a single clear sheet, even cherishing takes this much devotion."},"ICON-1434":{"nm":"Toploader","on":"toploader","de":"Slide it between two stiff sheets and not even time can crumple it carelessly. Don't bend, don't fold. Keeping something precious always borrows one layer of sturdiness."},"ICON-1435":{"nm":"Sticker Pack","on":"sticker pack","de":"Peel them off one by one and stick them on a diary corner, on the back of a laptop. With one small picture, a colorless day is dyed in every shade. There's no age limit on the wish to decorate what's around you."},"ICON-1436":{"nm":"Marker Pen","on":"pen","de":"At the sound of ink whispering across paper, the line grows longer and longer. Over an album held out with a fluttering hand, a meeting of just a few seconds lingers for ages. The heart crosses over along the tip of the pen."},"ICON-1437":{"nm":"Signed Album","on":"signed album","de":"Open the cover and a familiar curving signature greets you first. A bond formed through music draws a hand's-breadth closer on paper. To keep it is to quietly hold that moment still."},"ICON-1438":{"nm":"Light Stick Battery","on":"light stick battery","de":"\"Turn on, please.\" Hands are busy swapping in batteries right before entering. So that among tens of thousands of lights, my one won't go out, a small battery lights up that great night bright."},"ICON-1439":{"nm":"Light Stick Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Tucked away neatly without a single scratch, kept safe even for the next night's cheers. Even after the fevered spot has fully cooled, you carry it home stowed with care. A cheering tool has its own place, and there's a heart that tends to it."},"ICON-1440":{"nm":"Slogan Banner","on":"slogan banner","de":"A sentence written on long cloth unfurls across the seats. In the moment a cheer too hard to say aloud opens wide, one person's sincerity becomes everyone's shout. That cloth itself becomes a voice."},"ICON-1441":{"nm":"Mini Banner","on":"mini banner","de":"A small cheer that fits right in your palm. The banner hung far away belongs to everyone, but this one flutters only at the edge of your desk. Swaying quietly, it proves that being small in size doesn't make the heart small too."},"ICON-1442":{"nm":"Fan Letter","on":"fan letter","de":"I rewrote the recipient's name three times and erased the first sentence seven. My fingertips tremble right before sealing the envelope because the heart is too honest. A sincerity heavier than a single stamp is folded inside."},"ICON-1443":{"nm":"Gift Wrap","on":"gift wrap","de":"The wrapping knows better than anyone that the most thrilling moment is the one second before it's opened. Even knowing it's fated to be torn soon, it wraps itself in the finest texture, resembling the heart of the one who gives it."},"ICON-1444":{"nm":"Ribbon","on":"ribbon","de":"Tie it too tight and it stifles, too loose and it slips, so finding the spot just between is the devotion. The shape of the heart is held in one knot chosen by the fingertips. The last line of a gift is always written by the ribbon instead."},"ICON-1445":{"nm":"Thank-You Card","on":"card","de":"A thank-you said aloud scatters on the wind, but written by hand it lingers long. The act of sending back the kindness received, with a little more piled on top. As you press out each letter, the heart deepens twofold."},"ICON-1446":{"nm":"Lunchbox Coupon","on":"lunchbox coupon","de":"With this one slip of paper, the worry over lunch loosens away. Freshly cooked rice with steam rising, a meal of side dishes filling each compartment is promised. A little charm that sturdily guards a hungry afternoon."},"ICON-1447":{"nm":"Snack Coupon","on":"snack coupon","de":"It exists to be pulled out at three in the afternoon, when peckishness sends a faint signal. A coupon that knows one small sweet lifts your mood half a hand's-breadth. Not a big reward, but it arrives softly at exactly the moment you need it."},"ICON-1448":{"nm":"Cafe Coupon","on":"cafe coupon","de":"A warm cup and one seat by the window, that's all this coupon promises. It may seem like nothing, but to someone it becomes a small prize for surviving the day. A tender invitation whose aroma arrives one step ahead."},"ICON-1449":{"nm":"Dorm Cleaning Pass","on":"pass","de":"Throw the windows wide, shake out the blankets, a day when not even a speck of dust escapes. Who knew that not having to do it yourself would be such a luxury. When the room sparkles, the heart quietly tidies up too."},"ICON-1450":{"nm":"Repair Kit","on":"repair kit","de":"A screwdriver, tape, a few unidentifiable parts. All gathered, it seems there's nothing it can't fix, yet open it up and there's always one piece short. Still, a box of confidence that somehow makes you feel reassured just holding it."},"ICON-1451":{"nm":"Lucky Ticket","on":"lucky ticket","de":"A blank ticket with no seat and no number. The point is that what good thing comes today isn't written on it. Filling that blank is up to the one who carries it around in their pocket."},"ICON-1452":{"nm":"Dice","on":"dice","de":"A friend who knows the word fairness best. It takes no one's side and loves all six faces equally. For that one moment it leaves your palm and tumbles rolling away, even skill and connections briefly cede their seat to luck."},"ICON-1453":{"nm":"Travel Pass","on":"pass","de":"A promise that from here to there, one step is enough. A magical slip of paper that folds a long road small and tucks it in your pocket. On days you hesitate to set off, there's no better excuse-blocker than this."},"ICON-1454":{"nm":"Retry Pass","on":"pass","de":"Instead of reaching a hand to the fallen, a ticket that quietly nudges the back, telling you to try again. It tells you most softly that failure isn't the end but a brief comma. The courage for one more time fills up here."},"ICON-1455":{"nm":"Quick Finish Pass","on":"pass","de":"A tender cheat key that skips the waiting just a little. Who could blame a heart that can't bear even 3 minutes? Here lies a slightly foul-feeling joy, like flicking the sand of an hourglass along with a finger."},"ICON-1456":{"nm":"Production Booster","on":"production booster","de":"Same hands, same time, yet double the output. Whirring merrily atop the workbench as if to say don't ask the secret. A small device that quietly lends wings to two diligently moving hands."},"ICON-1457":{"nm":"Affinity Candy","on":"affinity candy","de":"Even awkwardness hard to untangle with words melts away before something sweet. A bond that grows a hand's-breadth closer than yesterday over one candy unwrapped together. A cute little discovery, that sweetness is the speed of growing close."},"ICON-1458":{"nm":"Mood Recovery Jelly","on":"mood recovery jelly","de":"On an upsetting day, something cold and soft works like a charm. Take one bite and a cloudy expression quietly loosens. Mending the heart is a precious thing by nature, so the R grade wasn't slapped on for nothing."},"ICON-1459":{"nm":"Sparkle Powder","on":"sparkle powder","de":"Sprinkle it lightly over something ordinary and suddenly it turns special. Its true identity is just glittering powder, yet the moment it dusts on, the world looks a little more giddy, how curious. Like a seasoning of happiness flicked onto daily life."},"ICON-1460":{"nm":"Stage Tape","on":"stage tape","de":"Stand on the stage and countless lights all at once seek you out. A small X on the floor silently marks that spot. What is most precise from an unseen place ends up holding up the grandest stage."},"ICON-1461":{"nm":"Cable Tie","on":"cable tie","de":"A little hero that tidies tangled cords neatly in one stroke. That once tightened it can't be undone is both its flaw and its charm. An essential that those serious about tidiness quietly keep on hand."},"ICON-1462":{"nm":"Spare Cable","on":"cable","de":"An item with no presence when you have it, only longed for keenly when you don't. Asleep deep in the bag backstage, it wakes with a flash at the decisive moment. It proves the word preparedness with its very body."},"ICON-1463":{"nm":"Rehearsal Check Sheet","on":"sheet","de":"A paper packed box by box with blocking, cues, even costume changes. If even one check here is missing, someone's heart sinks. A perfect stage only raises its curtain after this sheet is fully filled in."},"ICON-1464":{"nm":"Set Signboard","on":"board","de":"Here is a cafe, there an alley, follow the arrows into an entirely different world. A lie painted on plywood, yet before the camera it becomes real. An honest guide that devoted its whole life to pointing the way."},"ICON-1465":{"nm":"Mini Trophy","on":"trophy","de":"A golden piece that somehow makes you feel a hand's-breadth taller the moment you receive it. It shines on your desk, saying it's truly okay not to be first, that it knows all you strove for today. The great comfort a small reward offers."},"ICON-1466":{"nm":"Backpack","on":"backpack","de":"The moment you sling it on, it feels like you could set off anywhere. There may be little inside, but possibility fills it to the brim. Adventure always begins with the act of cinching these shoulder straps tight."},"ICON-1467":{"nm":"Compass","on":"compass","de":"Even lost, you don't panic, because the needle's tip always points north. The way it wavers for a while and finally finds its place is so like the human heart. It's okay to wander, it tells you with its trembling tip."},"ICON-1468":{"nm":"Notebook","on":"notebook","de":"The first page is always empty. Only the one holding the pen knows what to write. I simply wait, for today's thoughts to become writing and settle quietly upon me. The R grade is the weight of possibility soon to be filled."},"ICON-1469":{"nm":"Pencil","on":"pencil","de":"That it's okay to be wrong is this tool's most tender side. As long as its eraser friend is near, you can start over as many times as you like. It grows shorter the more it's sharpened, but the shortness is proof it was loved long."},"ICON-1470":{"nm":"Film","on":"film","de":"The moment light passes through, that day's color is fixed intact. That once a cut goes by it can never be undone is both the tension and the charm. The choice of those who deliberately remember a beat slower in a fast age."},"ICON-1471":{"nm":"Instant Camera","on":"instant camera","de":"Click, and then a brief wait. Hold it and wave it lightly, and a blurry moment gradually comes into focus. A slightly magical machine that captures this very spot, intact, onto a single sheet of paper."},"ICON-1472":{"nm":"Old Photo","on":"photo","de":"How much the color has faded means how much time has passed. At every worn corner, someone's touch lingered. That the oldest photo holds the clearest memory is, perhaps, because of those touches."},"ICON-1473":{"nm":"Scrapbook","on":"scrapbook","de":"Scraps too dear to throw away gather and gather into one volume. A faded movie ticket, a dried petal, one short memo. Odds and ends to others' eyes, but to the one who opens it a whole season is wholly revived."},"ICON-1474":{"nm":"Voyage Log","on":"voyage log","de":"Today's wind and waves, and one line of the heart. Writing it faithfully even on uneventful days is the rule of the voyage. Proof that you arrived safely is always written somewhere within this thick record."},"ICON-1475":{"nm":"Map Fragment","on":"map fragment","de":"It's only one corner of the whole, yet without it you'll never find the way in the end. The thrill of a torn edge clicking perfectly into another fragment. The R grade has the presence of a puzzle's final piece."},"ICON-1476":{"nm":"Message in a Bottle","on":"message in a bottle","de":"Not knowing who will read it, it entrusts itself quietly to the waves. It expects no reply, only wishes this heart will reach somewhere. The slowest yet most romantic way of sending mail."},"ICON-1477":{"nm":"Dice","on":"dice","de":"Six faces smiling roundly as if to say, you again? The same shape, yet giving a different answer with each roll is this friend's unchanging caprice. The moment it leaves your hand, you briefly entrust the choice to fate."},"ICON-1478":{"nm":"Pinwheel","on":"pinwheel","de":"It only comes alive when the wind blows. Left still, it's just paper wings, but let someone blow on it and it begins to spin merrily. Not being ashamed to receive help is this little flower's wisdom."},"ICON-1479":{"nm":"Picnic Basket","on":"basket","de":"Open the lid and the smell of gimbap greets you first. Green grass, a spread-out mat, and hands sharing food with hands. The days this basket filled up were, curiously, always under a clear sky."},"ICON-1480":{"nm":"Vase","on":"vase","de":"Place just one stem and the very air of the room changes. When empty, waiting silently is its proper duty. The room's most humble stage prop, lowering its own presence to make the flower shine all the more."},"ICON-1481":{"nm":"Petal","on":"petal","de":"When the wind carries one away, spring grows that much lighter. The old tree in the yard offers the same greeting every year, that falling too is one strand of the work of blooming. Scattering isn't the end, but a letter mailed in advance to next spring."},"ICON-1482":{"nm":"Rose","on":"rose","de":"Raising thorns first is a promise not to be touched carelessly. Within is hidden the reddest of hearts. Someone laid a single stem quietly at the foot and left, writing their heart in color alone instead of a name."},"ICON-1483":{"nm":"Lily","on":"lily","de":"Beside the pristine white porcelain, this white flower was always placed. May its scent travel far yet its bearing never falter. From that spot where it chose purity over splendor, the lily silently keeps one measure of dignity."},"ICON-1484":{"nm":"Tulip","on":"tulip","de":"Standing in a row with heads slightly bowed, somehow so tidy. The flower that takes the front row of the spring bed. Its honesty of blooming all at once and falling all at once stains the short season most deeply."},"ICON-1485":{"nm":"Hyacinth","on":"hyacinth","de":"On one stalk it hangs small bells densely packed. Shake it and there's no sound, but the scent rings through the room instead. At the cusp of spring, a tender luxury that wholly swaps out the room's air with a single vase."},"ICON-1486":{"nm":"Frog Specimen","on":"frog specimen","de":"A small body where time has stopped inside a glass case. The label reads: 'Paddies and reservoirs; liveliest the day after rain.' Only after stopping does even the temperature of the waterside where a creature lived remain on record."},"ICON-1487":{"nm":"Lizard Specimen","on":"lizard specimen","de":"Even as a specimen, the cleverness of dropping its tail and fleeing can't be erased. A small guest who loved sun-warmed stone walls. The note beside it has neatly written the direction of the sunny spot it loved to climb."},"ICON-1488":{"nm":"Mole Record","on":"mole record","de":"The diary of one who travels underground is written in the grain of the soil. Where it dug and where it stopped, a map of unseen paths. Time spent living with one's back to the light becomes, for someone, the most diligent record."},"ICON-1489":{"nm":"Shell Specimen","on":"shell specimen","de":"A solid pattern the waves polished and sent over thousands of times. The tidal-flat folk could tell which sea it came from by the grain of the shell alone. The shape of a sea that once lived and breathed is held intact in a palm-sized specimen."},"ICON-1490":{"nm":"Coral Specimen","on":"coral specimen","de":"In the deep sea it grows barely a hand's-breadth over hundreds of years. It looks like branches, but it's really a house built together by countless small lives. The slower a thing is, the longer it remains, the coral proves in silence."},"ICON-1491":{"nm":"Aidong Clue","on":"aidong clue","de":"A fragment of a story scattered somewhere on the island. One small scrap of paper quietly points to the next step. Every adventure, in the end, begins with picking up trivial traces like these, the old guide says."},"ICON-1492":{"nm":"Signature Piece","on":"signature piece","de":"When the scattered pattern finds its place, a single mark is finally completed. A piece engraved with someone's unique grain. It hides its meaning until matched, and the moment it's matched, it finally becomes a name."},"ICON-1493":{"nm":"Stage Memory Shard","on":"stage memory shard","de":"Even after a song ends, residual heat lingers among the seats. Peel off that warmth and harden it and it becomes a small shard like this. Scattered fragments of applause and shouts, gathered quietly, wholly revive that night."},"ICON-1494":{"nm":"Debut Stamp","on":"debut stamp","de":"The day your name was first called out, the ink mark stamped on the back of your hand. Even the care of drying it gently so it wouldn't smudge was part of the starting line. One small stamp keeps a certain day from ever being erased."},"ICON-1495":{"nm":"Top Idol Medal","on":"medal","de":"A heaviness permitted only to those who reach the highest place. But this medal is heavy not because of the metal. It's because the weight of the countless hands that filled the stage together gathers intact in one point."},"ICON-1496":{"nm":"Little Key","on":"little key","de":"The dorm's first key was always to the innermost room. A place where you learned to open before you learned to lock. On the day of leaving, the warmth a palm left behind lingers long upon the cold metal."},"ICON-1497":{"nm":"Treasure Chest","on":"chest","de":"Until it's opened, no one knows what's inside. That not-knowing is the treasure chest's real treasure. In the brief moment of lifting the lid, anyone returns for a while to the flutter of childhood days."},"ICON-1498":{"nm":"Blueprint","on":"blueprint","de":"Upon lines ruled box by box lives a building not yet raised. To unroll the drawing is to walk through tomorrow once in advance. One well-drawn line holds up a tomorrow that won't collapse."},"ICON-1499":{"nm":"Recipe Card","on":"card","de":"On one well-thumbed card, Grandma's handcraft is written as measurements. Vague words like 'a pinch of salt' are the most precise secret. The blurrier the writing, the clearer the kitchen where that dish once simmered comes to mind."},"ICON-1500":{"nm":"Facility Permit","on":"facility permit","de":"A single sheet of paper turns an empty lot into 'a spot you can use.' A new building always needed the village's stamp first. Permission, in the end, is a warm seal saying it's all right to begin something here."},"ICON-1501":{"nm":"Harbor Permit","on":"harbor permit","de":"Before a ship can drop anchor, it first needs this single slip of paper. The faded seal of the port is the first greeting to those who come from afar. Between leaving and arriving, the harbor always opens its heart with a single sheet of paper."},"ICON-1502":{"nm":"Island Citizenship Token","on":"token","de":"A small certificate that you've become one of the island's own. When a new neighbor moved in, the old village would add their name to the rolls and share warm rice cakes. It's only a piece of paper, but on it is written the bright welcome: 'Now you're one of us, too.'"},"ICON-1503":{"nm":"Lodging Nameplate","on":"lodging nameplate","de":"With a single name hung beside the door, an empty room finally becomes someone's home. Even in the old guest quarters, a plaque carved with the master's name was the first thing hung. A nameplate is small, but within it is the warmth of 'someone lives here.'"},"ICON-1504":{"nm":"Fandom Stamp","on":"stamp","de":"Even the care of licking it and pressing it down firmly was part of one complete letter. The act of fixing a beloved feeling to a small piece of paper and sending it far away. Even in the digital age, someone still mails their heart by hand."},"ICON-1505":{"nm":"Sparkle Isle Badge","on":"sparkle isle badge","de":"Pin it to your collar and a little light follows wherever you go. Meet someone wearing the same badge on the street, and you understand each other without a word. The sparkle isn't a boast, but a quiet signal: 'We love the same island.'"},"ICON-1506":{"nm":"Workbench","on":"workbench","de":"A scarred tabletop bears witness to the hands that made the most things. The place where things were fixed, joined, and refined. More than a clean desk, a cluttered workbench actually holds far more stories."},"ICON-1507":{"nm":"Storage Box","on":"box","de":"The more precious something is, the sooner you decide its place. People of old, too, kept precious documents apart in chests of paulownia wood. To store something well is, in the end, to fold today neatly away for someone in the future."},"ICON-1508":{"nm":"Supply Crate","on":"crate","de":"When there's plenty, gather it; when there's not enough, take it out. Here lies the wisdom of an age when a well-stocked storehouse meant a steady heart. To stockpile is to hand a kind meal in advance to your future self."},"ICON-1509":{"nm":"Cooler Box","on":"box","de":"A chest packed with ice held onto coolness even in midsummer. It's as if the old wisdom of the ice house has been carried over, palm-sized. To keep something cold is to let the freshest moment linger a little longer."},"ICON-1510":{"nm":"Water Pump","on":"water pump","de":"Work the handle up and down, and water deep underground rises up. An honest machine that gushed only after a single dipper of priming water was poured in. The wellside learned early the truth that you must give before you receive."},"ICON-1511":{"nm":"Water Purifier","on":"water purifier","de":"A small miracle in which murky water grows clearer, layer by layer. People of old filtered water by layering sand and charcoal in earthen jars. Clarity isn't gotten for free; it's the care of filtering slowly."},"ICON-1512":{"nm":"Watering Can Stand","on":"stand","de":"The moment the watering can has a place to rest, the flowerbed's day grows tidy. Deciding where to hang a tool is the habit of someone who loves their work. Once a single spot is set, the whole yard becomes a little neater."},"ICON-1513":{"nm":"Fishing Rod Stand","on":"stand","de":"People may leave until the bite comes, but the fishing rod holds its place. The patient posture of fishing away the years by the river is fixed right here. A stand, in the end, is a rest for setting impatience down for a while."},"ICON-1514":{"nm":"Foraging Basket","on":"basket","de":"Mother's handful, carrying a fistful of wild greens and a single field flower. Through the gaps in the woven bamboo, the scent of earth quietly seeps out. Depending on what you fill it with, an empty basket can become either spring or autumn."},"ICON-1515":{"nm":"Mortar and Pestle","on":"mortar and pestle","de":"Thump, thump, grinding grain to a steady beat woke the village's day. A tool whose pounding once filled the alleys on holidays. To make the hard soft takes the steady rhythm of a working hand."},"ICON-1516":{"nm":"Cutting Board","on":"cutting board","de":"Every mark the knife leaves behind carves the history of a meal. A scarred wooden board is a kitchen's medal for the busiest hands. To cut something begins with the wish to serve it with care."},"ICON-1517":{"nm":"Pot","on":"pot","de":"The bubbling of a boil is more tender than any music. On a peckish dawn, the 3 minutes waiting for the noodles to cook is the most private comfort. Across the round bottom, the warmth of wanting to feed someone heats up."},"ICON-1518":{"nm":"Frying Pan","on":"frying pan","de":"The skill of cooking something through in an instant over the flame rests on this single pan. The better-seasoned the surface, the less it sticks and the more it gleams. A long-used iron pan is itself proof of the years the kitchen has lived."},"ICON-1519":{"nm":"Oven","on":"oven","de":"While you close the door and wait, magic quietly happens inside. The time when dough rises and color ripens. Even when you can't see it, if you wait in faith, a warm result opens the door and steps out."},"ICON-1520":{"nm":"Blender","on":"blender","de":"Put even something hard in here and in an instant it becomes a smooth drink. A small whirlpool where different ingredients mix and a new flavor is born. Harmony, in the end, is each one giving up a little of its own edges."},"ICON-1521":{"nm":"Whisk","on":"whisk","de":"One flick of the wrist traps the air, and the runny stiffens as fast as you whip. While the bubbles rise like peaks, it isn't only the batter that swells. The wish to feed someone today swells right along with it."},"ICON-1522":{"nm":"Grinder","on":"grinder","de":"Turn the handle on a handful of beans, and the aroma breaks apart first between the teeth. By the time your arm aches, the grounds are finally fine, and the first sip deepens as much as the effort. Care always begins at the wrist."},"ICON-1523":{"nm":"Flour Mill","on":"flour mill","de":"Grain goes in between the stones and comes out as white flour. It's all right if it's not fine the first time; just grind it twice more. Even making the coarse fine has its order, the flour mill quietly reminds us."},"ICON-1524":{"nm":"Sawing Bench","on":"sawing bench","de":"When a log comes up, the saw first reads the grain. Steer around the knots and cut only along the straight path, so the board won't warp. To cut wood is, in the end, to lay out neatly the time a single tree lived through."},"ICON-1525":{"nm":"Sewing Machine","on":"sewing machine","de":"Whirr—the sound of the needle catching the cloth and racing fills the late night. A single seam joins two panels into one body, and in every hidden stitch inside a stage costume, someone's sleepless hours are firmly sewn."},"ICON-1526":{"nm":"Dyeing Table","on":"dyeing table","de":"Dip white cloth and lift it out: at first it's pale green, then meeting the air it finally turns blue. That color said to come only after steeping the indigo three times. That waiting itself becomes color—I first learned it before this dyeing table."},"ICON-1527":{"nm":"Camera Tripod","on":"camera tripod","de":"The moment its three legs spread and meet the ground, the shaking world goes still. A shot that would have trembled in your hand grows clear upon the promise of these three points. To gaze at something for long, you must first know how to stand still."},"ICON-1528":{"nm":"Light Stand","on":"light stand","de":"Set a light atop a single pole, and anywhere in the room becomes a small stage. Tilt the angle slightly and shadows lengthen, expressions come alive. It doesn't erase the dark, but kindly sets even the darkness in its place."},"ICON-1529":{"nm":"Microphone Stand","on":"microphone stand","de":"The moment you set the height, the distance between mouth and song is fixed. Let go with your hands, and the voice stays right there. Only on a stage where both hands are free does the song sung with the whole body truly begin."},"ICON-1530":{"nm":"Music Stand","on":"music stand","de":"When the open page leans at a slant, the notes line up at the player's eye level. Even when the next measure comes at a single gesture, the rest doesn't waver. Behind someone's performance there is always a wordless place."},"ICON-1531":{"nm":"Garden Plot","on":"garden plot","de":"Turn the soil and draw the furrows, and small lines of promise appear upon the earth. The few days after the seed is buried seem like nothing, but one morning tender cotyledons push up through the soil. It's a sight seen only by those who waited."},"ICON-1532":{"nm":"Fertile Garden Plot","on":"fertile garden plot","de":"The same seed, yet in this soil the leaves grow twice as large. Poke in a finger and dark, soft earth follows up under your nails. Growing well was, in the end, the work the unseen ground quietly did underfoot."},"ICON-1533":{"nm":"Greenhouse","on":"house","de":"Beneath a glass ceiling, the seasons flow a beat slower. Even when frost falls outside, inside it's moist with the humidity of midsummer. For the things weak against the cold, someone has gently caught the sunlight in the roof."},"ICON-1534":{"nm":"Herb Bed","on":"herb bed","de":"Brush the leaves with your fingertips and the scent greets you first. Basil, rosemary, mint—call each name and a different smell clings to your fingers. A single small bed gently transforms the whole kitchen."},"ICON-1535":{"nm":"Orchard","on":"orchard","de":"In spring with shade of blossoms, in autumn with the weight of fruit, the branches bow. Climb the ladder, pick one, take a bite, and a year's worth of sunlight stored as sweetness bursts in your mouth. It's like a reply the tree hands to a person."},"ICON-1536":{"nm":"Mushroom Log","on":"mushroom log","de":"Drill holes in a felled log and plant the spawn, and the dead tree raises something once more. A few days later, on the morning the caps sprout in clusters, a new life quietly begins in the place you thought was the end."},"ICON-1537":{"nm":"Beehive","on":"hive","de":"Press your ear close and you hear a low, busy hum inside. Thousands of wingbeats gather to make barely a single spoonful of sweetness. A day's labor of flying through the flower fields pools here, sticky and golden."},"ICON-1538":{"nm":"Chicken Coop","on":"chicken coop","de":"Before dawn breaks, the ones perched on the roost rustle first. Slip a hand into the warm straw and you grasp an egg still holding its warmth. The place that announces morning first is the first to set the morning table."},"ICON-1539":{"nm":"Pasture","on":"pasture","de":"A broad field where the scent of grass mingles with the scent of sunshine. Over the backs slowly chewing their cud within the fence, the shadows of clouds drift by. In this place with nothing to rush, even time flows slowly, as if grazing."},"ICON-1540":{"nm":"Cheese Workshop","on":"cheese workshop","de":"Freshly drawn milk slowly hardens through curdling and aging. Wait a few months on a shelf cool as a cave, and deep flavor steeps into the white mass. Cheese is a name given only to milk that did not rush."},"ICON-1541":{"nm":"Tofu Workshop","on":"tofu workshop","de":"Soak the beans, grind them, boil them, and the raw bean milk turns nutty. A single drop of brine gathers the scattered into soft tofu, and pressed gently, it takes on square edges. Here is a hand that soothes a scattered heart into shape."},"ICON-1542":{"nm":"Jangdokdae Crock Terrace","on":"jangdokdae crock terrace","de":"On a sunny corner of the yard, short earthen jars cluster together, basking in the light. Lift a lid and the scent of aged time wafts up. The taste of the paste Grandmother fermented is, in truth, eating up the years one spoonful at a time."},"ICON-1543":{"nm":"Mill","on":"mill","de":"When the stones turn with a rumble, grain unwinds into flour. White dust drifts through the sunlight, and people waiting to make a basinful of rice cakes wait their turn. The village's feast day always seemed to begin at this threshold."},"ICON-1544":{"nm":"Bakery","on":"bakery","de":"Through the crack of the oven door, the scent of butter and sugar leaks out. As the risen dough turns golden, footsteps passing the shop unconsciously slow. A single loaf of freshly baked bread holds a tenderness no one can resist."},"ICON-1545":{"nm":"Snack Food Cart","on":"snack food cart","de":"The vinyl awning flaps in the wind and the tteokbokki broth simmers down. An evening of gulping paper-cup broth with a single fish-cake skewer, a place that melts away cold and hunger all at once. A small comfort set at the end of the alley."},"ICON-1546":{"nm":"Western Kitchen","on":"western kitchen","de":"The pan heats up and the olive oil sizzles. With a single turn of the heat, a sauce can thicken or burn. Here, where even the balance of colors on the plate is weighed, a meal becomes a carefully staged performance."},"ICON-1547":{"nm":"Chinese Kitchen","on":"chinese kitchen","de":"Over a fierce flame, the wok spins this way and that as if dancing. In the brief instant the flames leap up, the aroma of the ingredients is sealed in whole. Fast and hot, the secret of Chinese cooking hides in that one breath you'll miss if you hesitate."},"ICON-1548":{"nm":"Cafe","on":"cafe","de":"Push the door and the scent of coffee beans and soft music greet you first. A window seat, a cooling latte, an open notebook. To let you catch your breath in a busy day, the city has hidden small rooms like this here and there."},"ICON-1549":{"nm":"Dessert Shop","on":"dessert shop","de":"Inside the glass case, colorful cakes line up waiting for customers. The moment the tip of the fork parts the cream, the corners of your mouth lift first. A small, sweet prescription that makes even a sad day bearable with a single slice."},"ICON-1550":{"nm":"Butcher Shop","on":"butcher shop","de":"Under red light, the meat lies neat along the grain. At a single word—\"This one's good today\"—the knife slides at exactly the right thickness. The heartiness of the dinner table quietly begins with this hand that keeps the same place every day."},"ICON-1551":{"nm":"Seafood Prep Station","on":"seafood prep station","de":"A workstation where the dawn's fishy smell mingles with the cold of ice. Scales fly and hands go numb, yet the eye that picks the freshest never stops. Here, the things just up from the sea find their way to the table."},"ICON-1552":{"nm":"Salt Field","on":"salt field","de":"Trap the seawater, and the sun and wind do the rest. Wait a few days for the water to dry, and white crystals sprout on the floor like stars. A handful of saltiness is, in fact, a gift the sea and sky slowly made together."},"ICON-1553":{"nm":"Seaweed Drying Rack","on":"seaweed drying rack","de":"On a long line, kelp and sea mustard hang side by side, swaying in the wind. The things heavy with seawater darken to deep green as they dry. The sea's most frugal flavor, made together by sunlight and the salt breeze, hangs here."},"ICON-1554":{"nm":"Small Pier","on":"small pier","de":"Wooden planks half-sunk in the water sway lightly underfoot. Just the right spot to tie up one small boat. Setting off far away and returning safely both begin and end at this single berth."},"ICON-1555":{"nm":"Harbor Warehouse","on":"harbor warehouse","de":"Open the wooden door cured by sea wind, and nets, barrels, and ropes are stacked to the ceiling. Cargo bound for a far voyage and cargo just arrived rest a while under one roof. A place like a transfer station where leaving and returning briefly brush past each other."},"ICON-1556":{"nm":"Lighthouse","on":"lighthouse","de":"Only when the night sea grows darkest does it finally begin its work. The light spinning round cuts through the fog and says, \"There is a way here.\" A tall watchman that, for someone's safe return, refuses to the end to fall asleep."},"ICON-1557":{"nm":"Shipyard","on":"shipyard","de":"Raise the keel and fit the ribs, and the skeleton of a ship takes shape. In a yard where the sound of hammers rings all day, a ship that doesn't yet know the taste of water dreams of its first voyage. A place that grows sturdy first, in order to leave."},"ICON-1558":{"nm":"Recording Booth","on":"recording booth","de":"When the door closes, every sound from outside vanishes in an instant. All you hear past the headphones is your own breath and the beat. In the silence of this small room, a voice that may tremble freely is finally born."},"ICON-1559":{"nm":"Music Room","on":"room","de":"Harmonies leaking through the cracks of the door fill the corridor. Someone fingers the scale, someone counts the beat. A place where clumsy sounds and seasoned sounds may mingle, a kind classroom where every song first takes its steps."},"ICON-1560":{"nm":"Piano Room","on":"piano room","de":"Open the keyboard lid and a faint layer of dust sits on the white keys. The moment fingers touch them, a clear resonance spreads through the room. If there are evenings not lonely even when alone, it's probably because of this single piano."},"ICON-1561":{"nm":"Dance Room","on":"dance room","de":"Press down with your toes and the floor pushes back up. While the four walls of mirrors copy the same move four times, the body memorizes the choreography half a beat ahead of the rhythm. The room where sweat and breath linger longest; the moves raised here walk out onto the stage."},"ICON-1562":{"nm":"Gym Room","on":"gym room","de":"Weight never lies. People seek me out every dawn because they love that honesty—exactly as much as you lift is credited to your shoulders. What's slowly carved into the mirror isn't muscle, but the hours you endured without giving up."},"ICON-1563":{"nm":"Yoga Room","on":"yoga room","de":"Breathe in deeply and it feels as if the wooden floor swells along with you. A room where you slowly fold away a day that came rushing in; on a single mat, anyone returns to the pace of their own breath. Even a hurried heart sets itself down here for a while."},"ICON-1564":{"nm":"Dressing Room","on":"room","de":"Just before stepping onto the stage, people briefly become someone else here. When the bulbs around the mirror warm the face evenly, the trembling clings to the tip of the powder puff and slips away behind the collar. The place where transformation begins and ends."},"ICON-1565":{"nm":"Costume Room","on":"room","de":"Until a single stage outfit is finished, the clothes hanging here are put on and taken off dozens of times. A mannequin turning with basting pins stuck in it, seam lines drawn in chalk. Behind the sparkle, there's always the mark of someone's needlework left behind."},"ICON-1566":{"nm":"Broadcast Set","on":"broadcast set","de":"Only the one side the camera shows needs to look real—I learned that early. Go around behind the plywood and there's only an empty frame. To prop up the splendor of the front is always the lot of unseen lengths of wood."},"ICON-1567":{"nm":"Photo Studio","on":"photo studio","de":"The first trick is to throw light from three directions to erase the shadows. The key light brings out the face, the fill light the shade, the backlight the tips of the hair. In the instant the shutter falls, a single white backdrop captures today's best smile."},"ICON-1568":{"nm":"Concert Hall","on":"concert hall","de":"In the high-ceilinged darkness I always hold the same promise: that when the curtain rises, even the empty seats will hold their breath as one. For that single instant when the first beat drops, I stand quietly empty all year long."},"ICON-1569":{"nm":"Fan Meeting Booth","on":"fan meeting booth","de":"The distance between hand and hand is exactly one desk wide. A short greeting, a trembling autograph, a word never quite said pass by in a line. Within this small cubicle, a beloved feeling long nurtured comes face to face for the first time."},"ICON-1570":{"nm":"Bed","on":"bed","de":"It was always I who first received the end of the day. Once the legs heavy from practice and the tremor left behind backstage have all settled, morning begins again on light tiptoes. Saying goodnight, I hold you without a word."},"ICON-1571":{"nm":"Bunk Bed","on":"bunk bed","de":"Between the upper and lower bunks, five rungs of a ladder join two people. Small voices shared after the lights go out, glow-in-the-dark stars stuck to the ceiling. The cramped lodging grows widest thanks to the stories climbing up and down the ladder each night."},"ICON-1572":{"nm":"Shelf","on":"shelf","de":"What you set upon it shows who you are. A letter received, a first trophy, a faded admission ticket line up side by side. I'm not furniture for showing off, but a place that quietly displays memories one couldn't bear to throw away."},"ICON-1573":{"nm":"Desk","on":"desk","de":"With a lyrics notebook open, fresh lines are drawn again over erased marks. Paper cups piled up through the night and a single melody barely salvaged. The slow work of moving the heart into words always unfolds quietly upon this flat surface."},"ICON-1574":{"nm":"Chair","on":"chair","de":"\"Sit for a moment\" is, surprisingly, a tender thing to say. However long the meeting drags or practice runs over, the backrest silently bears a person's weight. The longer someone has been standing, the more they welcome me—I know this."},"ICON-1575":{"nm":"Sofa","on":"sofa","de":"To turn the late-night lodging into a living room, I alone am enough. Squeeze in together watching variety shows, and before long one of you has fallen asleep against the armrest. The sunken middle seat proves that home's warmth."},"ICON-1576":{"nm":"Table","on":"table","de":"Gather around it and no one sits at the head. Freshly boiled stew, the clatter of spoons, the day's happenings all gather to the center. When a single round surface spreads out, even a scattered day sits down together once more."},"ICON-1577":{"nm":"Wardrobe","on":"wardrobe","de":"Whenever the season turns, old stories spill out from inside. Stage costumes and everyday clothes shoulder to shoulder, the clothes wait their next turn behind the closed door. Only when you open the door is the day you'll wear today finally decided."},"ICON-1578":{"nm":"Mirror","on":"mirror","de":"Praise or flaw, I return both with the same honesty. The place for one last check before stepping onto the stage; before me, people compose their expressions and straighten their posture. The most honest friend never says a single word."},"ICON-1579":{"nm":"Vanity Table","on":"vanity table","de":"In each small drawer a different face sleeps. One tube for the stage, one for every day, one limited edition saved away. Sit before the mirror, and you slowly begin by deciding just who you'll become as you step out today."},"ICON-1580":{"nm":"Rug","on":"rug","de":"The feel that bare feet first touch sets the room's temperature. The traces of sitting around snacking and rolling about remain as lint. Furniture that works from the lowest place, warming the cold floor a hand's width warmer."},"ICON-1581":{"nm":"Curtain","on":"curtain","de":"How much morning to let in is mine to decide. Draw me slightly and sunlight stretches in long; close me tight and even sleeping in becomes forgivable. Standing between window and room, adjusting the amount of light is always the part entrusted to me."},"ICON-1582":{"nm":"Lamp","on":"lamp","de":"The same room becomes an entirely different time of day depending on the color of light. Yellow light stretches the evening long; white light wakes the dawn sharply. A palm-sized magician who, with a single switch, slyly changes the day's mood."},"ICON-1583":{"nm":"Wall Clock","on":"clock","de":"The sound of the second hand is heard only in a quiet room. As practice deepens you forget me, then glance up to find that outside the window it's already dawn. Never blaming the time that has passed, I simply point to the next tick in silence."},"ICON-1584":{"nm":"Vase","on":"vase","de":"Even when the flowers wither, I do not leave my place empty. A vessel that holds a received feeling for a while; as long as there's a hand to change the water, the table stays bright. Even when empty, I stand in the shape of waiting for someone."},"ICON-1585":{"nm":"Poster Frame","on":"frame","de":"Hanging a beloved face on the wall takes care, too. A spot the sunlight doesn't touch directly, a single nail set perfectly level. A sheet of paper laid carefully behind glass is the first to greet me each morning as I step into the room."},"ICON-1586":{"nm":"Photocard Board","on":"photocard board","de":"Whether to file them alphabetically or by release order—that happy dilemma is where fandom begins. A single empty slot is the spot for a bias not yet met. As it fills one card at a time, the board becomes a small chronicle all my own."},"ICON-1587":{"nm":"Lightstick Stand","on":"stand","de":"Battery out, handle up. There's a knack even to the angle at which you lean and stand it. Waiting for the next cheer to come, the stick turns off its light right here and lays its body down neatly. Rest well, and it lights up brighter."},"ICON-1588":{"nm":"Trophy Shelf","on":"trophy shelf","de":"The front row holds the oldest one. From a small contest's statuette to a grand stage's cup, they line up not by height but by the order of the heart. Each time I polish them, the tremor of that day onstage clings to my fingertips again."},"ICON-1589":{"nm":"Picnic Basket","on":"basket","de":"Open the lid and the scent of spring sunlight leaks out first. Gimbap, a thermos, and a single mat stacked neatly, ready to head for the fields. The steps of whoever carries me are somehow always a hand's breadth lighter than usual."},"ICON-1590":{"nm":"Small Flowerpot","on":"small flowerpot","de":"A hand's width of windowsill is enough for me. A small green that generously endures even when you often forget to water it. In a corner of a busy person's desk, I unfurl one more leaf each day, quietly passing along today's regards."},"ICON-1591":{"nm":"Large Flowerpot","on":"large flowerpot","de":"While my height grows, the person grows along with me. When the broad leaves taking up a corner of the living room catch the sunlight and cast shade, the season quietly enters the room too. A reward known only to those who don't forget to water."},"ICON-1592":{"nm":"Scented Candle Set","on":"scented candle set","de":"The moment you light the wick, the room's air settles a notch lower. The scent slowly spreads, warming away and sending out yesterday's leftover fatigue. With a single small flame, closing the end of a busy day like a quiet ritual."},"ICON-1593":{"nm":"Mini Fridge","on":"mini fridge","de":"Open the door late at night and a cold can of drink welcomes me. A small humming whir makes the empty lodging a little less lonely. I can't run a big household, but for taking care of a peckish dawn, there's nothing like me."},"ICON-1594":{"nm":"Bug Net Headpiece","on":"bug net headpiece","de":"The moment you set it on your head, a summer field follows up onto your shoulders. The round net gently filters the sunlight, and with each step the scent of grass sways softly. A hat that wraps a whole season around you, fine even if you catch not a single dragonfly."},"ICON-1595":{"nm":"Foraging Net Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Slung at your waist, it becomes a companion in foraging. Cinch the opening slightly and what you've caught won't slip back out—the first knack learned in the fields. A single light cloth pouch tidily holds a day's harvest in its arms."},"ICON-1596":{"nm":"Insect Observation Jar","on":"jar","de":"For a guest who only stays a while, air holes matter most—this I know. A small breathing path bored in the lid, a single blade of grass laid on the bottom. Sending it back to the grass once the observing is done is part of the pair, too."},"ICON-1597":{"nm":"Specimen Pin Case","on":"case","de":"There's skill even in the single angle at which you set a pin aslant. Too deep and it breaks, too shallow and it wobbles, so you must divide the force in your fingertips precisely. A case that quietly holds the care of one who wishes to gaze long upon a small life."},"ICON-1598":{"nm":"Terrarium Lid","on":"lid","de":"Tending the border between inside and out is my job. Close too tight and it suffocates, leave it too loose and it loses its way, so I always leave a gap like a hatch mark. To protect is clearly different from shutting in."},"ICON-1599":{"nm":"Butterfly Feeding Dish","on":"dish","de":"Set cotton soaked in sugar water in the center and the wings gather round. The trick is to hold it shallow and wide, at a depth where small feet won't sink. A single dish quietly calls together the guests who stop by a sunny garden for a while."},"ICON-1600":{"nm":"Insect Lure Lamp","on":"insect lure lamp","de":"Leave it faintly lit in the dark and small wings gather following the light. Keep the brightness soft, the spot far from people. A most kindly tout that settles the humming summer night a good deal quieter."},"ICON-1601":{"nm":"Insect Sticker Label","on":"label","de":"Six legs and a pair of antennae—within a nail-sized scrap of paper, a small life sleeps. Stick it lightly on the corner of a notebook, and a hand's width of meadow quietly unfolds between the pages."},"ICON-1602":{"nm":"Foraging Permit Tag","on":"tag","de":"Before picking up the bug net, the grown-up asks first: how many, and how far. This single small tag draws a kind line between excited curiosity and a promise to keep."},"ICON-1603":{"nm":"Bait Tin","on":"tin","de":"Open the lid and a fishy, cool dawn smell rises up. What calls the fish may not be the bait, but a heart that knows how to wait quietly until the bobber trembles."},"ICON-1604":{"nm":"Bobber Case","on":"bobber case","de":"A small wardrobe where colorful bobbers lie sleeping, cell by cell. Some are a still lake's morning, some a fierce current's noon. For each expression of the water, the fitting partner is neatly folded away."},"ICON-1605":{"nm":"Fishing Line Spool","on":"fishing line spool","de":"Don't wind loose line around your fingers. Reel it back neatly onto this round tool and even the tangles quietly come undone. It resembles the touch that tidies a day gone slack."},"ICON-1606":{"nm":"Hook Remover","on":"hook remover","de":"Only those who've stung themselves pulling a caught hook bare-handed recognize this tool. A path that hurts less, both for the small creature and for my fingertips. Consideration always begins at these little ends."},"ICON-1607":{"nm":"Clam Shovel Cover","on":"cover","de":"A single layer wrapping the shovel blade just dug from the mudflat. So that mud and saltwater don't gnaw at the edge, it gently tucks a thin, soft rest between the sea and the tool."},"ICON-1608":{"nm":"Tide Table Card","on":"card","de":"When the water comes in and when it goes out, a palm-sized card quietly tells you. A small calendar a person has copied down of the old promise the moon and the sea made together."},"ICON-1609":{"nm":"Aquarium Cleaning Brush","on":"brush","de":"Gently sweep away the green algae caught on the glass wall, and light seeps back into the small world underwater. Brightening someone's day usually flows as quietly as this."},"ICON-1610":{"nm":"Tank Temperature Chip","on":"chip","de":"A single number blinks, and when it stops at the right degree, the fish are finally at ease. A cell of warmth neither too cold nor too hot. Care reaches even to the unseen places."},"ICON-1611":{"nm":"Marine Life Observation Tube","on":"tube","de":"A small guest staying a while inside the clear tube. Quietly count the dorsal fin and send it back to the sea. To observe isn't to possess, but to borrow for a little while."},"ICON-1612":{"nm":"Fossil Brush","on":"brush","de":"What wakes the grain of stone asleep for tens of millions of years isn't a hammer but the soft tip of a brush. Before a time that would crumble if you rushed, carefulness becomes the deepest courtesy."},"ICON-1613":{"nm":"Excavation Brush Cap","on":"cap","de":"When the brush tip dries out, even the soil won't fall away cleanly. A small cap keeps the brush's breath moist. A hand that cherishes its tools takes the first step of the dig."},"ICON-1614":{"nm":"Strata Sample Plate","on":"plate","de":"Within a hand's width of soil, hundreds of years are layered fold upon fold. Scoop it quietly onto this plate, and the patterns of time, unseen until now, draw their lines and slowly surface."},"ICON-1615":{"nm":"Bone Fragment Tray","on":"tray","de":"Lay the scattered fragments cell by cell, and a life once scattered to the wind slowly gropes its way back to its place. Restoration is the work of kindly asking after a lost order."},"ICON-1616":{"nm":"Restoration Tape","on":"tape","de":"A thin single strip that joins the broken place. It doesn't bother to hide the scar, but tenderly embraces and holds it fast. It quietly proves that even what was broken can be made whole again."},"ICON-1617":{"nm":"Display Nameplate Cover","on":"cover","de":"A single sheet that gently covers the label beyond the glass so it won't fade. It holds the wish that the short sentence of who lived, and where, may be read clearly even far into the future."},"ICON-1618":{"nm":"Vault Tag","on":"tag","de":"A deep room where treasures that never stepped into the light lie sleeping. Everything within bears a small name tag—so that, even without standing in a bright place, they're never forgotten."},"ICON-1619":{"nm":"Museum Donation Envelope","on":"envelope","de":"Someone hands over what they spent a lifetime gathering, without a word. What's held in this envelope isn't an object but a long-cherished heart. Sharing becomes the longest-lasting exhibit, shining upon someone."},"ICON-1620":{"nm":"Specimen Number Chip","on":"chip","de":"Right where you collected it, you quietly assign a small number. When, and where, you first met it. A discovery left unrecorded soon scatters like the morning mist."},"ICON-1621":{"nm":"Meteor Shard Bottle","on":"bottle","de":"A shard that fell streaking across the night sky is trapped inside a glass bottle. A single ray of light that faded before you could even make a wish now sparkles again, ever so gently, in your hand."},"ICON-1622":{"nm":"Seashell Wind Chime Cord","on":"cord","de":"Thread shells gathered one by one at the shore onto a string and hang it from the eaves. Each time the wind passes, with a clinking rattle, that summer's sea quietly follows its way into the house."},"ICON-1623":{"nm":"Rainbow Dewdrop","on":"drop","de":"A single drop beading on a leaf tip after the rain clears. Within that round shape, the whole sky and all seven colors are held in a circle. There are times when the smallest thing holds the broadest view."},"ICON-1624":{"nm":"Fog Collecting Bottle","on":"bottle","de":"I brought home a bottle full of dawn mist from the mountain skirts. Grasp it and it's cool, hazed milky white. A small, tender greed to keep beside you, for a while, what cannot be held."},"ICON-1625":{"nm":"Dewcatcher Cup","on":"cup","de":"A small cup that catches the dew the grass blades gathered drop by drop through the night. Not even a single mouthful, yet the clearest, purest part of the morning pools there in stillness."},"ICON-1626":{"nm":"Breeze Ribbon Pin","on":"pin","de":"A ribbon tied in the very image of the grain the wind left as it passed. Pin it in your hair and with each step a gentle breeze follows, swaying softly. The lightness of a spring day, quietly fastened into a single pin."},"ICON-1627":{"nm":"Wave Sound Capsule","on":"wave sound capsule","de":"Hold it gently to your ear and the waves of the far sea roll in. It's as if someone has carefully sealed into a small capsule that sound once kept in a conch shell in childhood."},"ICON-1628":{"nm":"Sand Star Fragment","on":"sand star fragment","de":"Grab a fistful of sand on the night beach, and bits of star crumbs are mixed in, sparkling. Whether they fell from the sky or the waves ground them finely, no one bothers to ask."},"ICON-1629":{"nm":"Island Weather Log Chip","on":"chip","de":"The island's sky changes its mind several times a day. Record clear, fog, and shower neatly onto a small chip, and you can spread out yesterday's sky again today."},"ICON-1630":{"nm":"Cliff Stairs Kit","on":"cliff stairs kit","de":"One step, then another, to go up and down the steep slope. Fit the scattered parts together and even a cliff becomes a leisurely stroll. To make a path is to lay out, in advance, someone's next step."},"ICON-1631":{"nm":"Dirt Path Pattern Roll","on":"dirt path pattern roll","de":"A roll that took the very grain of a soft dirt path. Unfurl it with a whoosh, and a country lane that makes you want to walk barefoot is quietly laid out underfoot."},"ICON-1632":{"nm":"Stone Path Pattern Chip","on":"chip","de":"The pattern of the flagstones that once paved the old alleys is held intact within a small chip. With each step, clack clack, the footsteps of an old village come back to life at your toes."},"ICON-1633":{"nm":"Beach Fence Piece","on":"beach fence piece","de":"A single section of the low fence set on the sand so the waves can't come over. A small, silent border-keeper standing there, drawing a kind line between the sea and the sand."},"ICON-1634":{"nm":"Grass Restoration Patch","on":"grass restoration patch","de":"A piece of green gently laid over a spot trampled bare. In a few days the grasses join hands and fill in the empty place. Nature always knows how to heal itself."},"ICON-1635":{"nm":"Waterway Marker Stake","on":"waterway marker stake","de":"A stake that tells in advance the path the water will flow. So the rainwater won't wander, wondering where to go, a small signpost driven into the ground stands silently even on rainy days."},"ICON-1636":{"nm":"Small Bridge Part","on":"small bridge part","de":"A single piece of a tiny bridge joining the two banks of a stream. Between this side and that, the promise that you can cross over anytime quietly begins with this one small part."},"ICON-1637":{"nm":"Overlook Railing Cap","on":"cap","de":"At the island's highest place, a single finishing piece wrapping the end of that railing. It quietly supports and guards the spot most often touched by the hands of those gathered to gaze far away."},"ICON-1638":{"nm":"Campfire Base","on":"base","de":"Before the firewood goes on, a spot that holds it so the embers won't scatter. Above it, the nights of chatting and gazing up at the stars burn warm for a long, long time."},"ICON-1639":{"nm":"Wallpaper Sample Roll","on":"wallpaper sample roll","de":"A room's mood begins with a single wall. Unfurling a small roll to choose a color is quietly sketching, in advance, just what kind of days you wish to live from here on."},"ICON-1640":{"nm":"Flooring Sample Chip","on":"chip","de":"Gauge first with your fingertips the feel of the floor your bare feet will touch. Warm or cool—on this single small chip hangs the coziness of the days you'll live from here on."},"ICON-1641":{"nm":"Ceiling Hook Set","on":"ceiling hook set","de":"The moment you hang a single hook on the beam, the empty ceiling becomes a place waiting for someone. A wind chime, or a flowerpot? This small iron hook bears the weight, but what to hang is for the dweller's heart to decide."},"ICON-1642":{"nm":"Window Tint Film","on":"window tint film","de":"The midday light is too honest, so you coat the window with a thin single film. The sunlight comes in as it is, but the edges soften, and everything in the room turns gentle apricot. Not a blocking, but a kindly blurring of the light."},"ICON-1643":{"nm":"Doorbell Cover","on":"doorbell cover","de":"Saying that even the bell a guest presses needs clothes, someone fitted it with a round cover. It keeps off rain, keeps off dust, and above all is the first small round mouth to offer the greeting, \"Someone lives here.\""},"ICON-1644":{"nm":"Guestbook Stand","on":"guestbook stand","de":"A stand set up so each one who comes writes their name and goes. Before the ink dries, a line of regards flows from the pen tip. As visiting footsteps stack up line by line, the empty notebook soon becomes this home's thickest album."},"ICON-1645":{"nm":"Furniture Placement Pin","on":"pin","de":"The desk spot you kept hesitating over moving—a single pin drives it into the floor and decides. A small nail that gently holds the furniture's feet. A spot, once set, is one you grow fond of, the wooden floor quietly nods."},"ICON-1646":{"nm":"Storage Label Frame","on":"storage label frame","de":"What's stored where, the drawer can never say. So a name tag is fitted into a square frame to speak for it. The moment a single label settles in, the cluttered compartments reclaim their names and grow calm."},"ICON-1647":{"nm":"Room Diffuser Stick","on":"room diffuser stick","de":"The scent wetting the stick's end slowly spreads upward. Lavender one moment, a rain-cleared meadow the next. When an invisible thread of smell swaps out the room's air, a day's fatigue slips loose from the shoulders of one who's come home."},"ICON-1648":{"nm":"Seed Packet Clip","on":"clip","de":"The seeds bought in spring but never quite planted are clamped firmly, packet and all, with a clip. If even a single grain slips out, next season grows a line shorter. Within the small clasp, next year's garden sleeps whole."},"ICON-1649":{"nm":"Seedling Tray","on":"tray","de":"Fill each cell with soil to make the first room of a young sprout. One life per hole, freshmen growing lined up neatly in a row. Peer in and a morning of green calling the roll cluster by cluster begins anew each day upon the tray."},"ICON-1650":{"nm":"Watering Marker Pin","on":"pin","de":"\"I'm thirsty.\" Since the flowerpot can't speak, a small placard stuck in the soil sends the signal in its place. When the color changes, it's time to water. The smallest interpreter between plant and person fits entirely into this hand's-width stick."},"ICON-1651":{"nm":"Plant Support Tie","on":"tie","de":"A growing stem might wobble under its own weight, so you gently fasten it to a stake with a soft tie. Too tight and it can't breathe; too loose and it topples, so the binding hand needs just the right tenderness. Even growing up needs someone close by."},"ICON-1652":{"nm":"Pest Netting","on":"pest netting","de":"A finely woven net quietly blocks the tiny mouths that target tender leaves. It lets wind and sunlight through and turns aside only what would do harm, an invisible gatekeeper. The garden stays peaceful thanks to the care woven into these tight little meshes."},"ICON-1653":{"nm":"Sunlight Meter Card","on":"card","de":"How much sun falls here? You stand a single card in the flowerbed and quietly ask. The deeper its color grows, the more light it caught today. This little slip of paper sorts out a spot for the child who loves sunshine and the one who prefers shade."},"ICON-1654":{"nm":"Soil pH Test Strip","on":"soil pH test strip","de":"Touch a test strip to the soil and from pink to blue the ground confesses its heart in color. Where it is neither too sour nor too bitter, roots breathe most easily. The soil's hidden feelings are read out one square at a time."},"ICON-1655":{"nm":"Harvest Basket Label","on":"label","de":"Is today's pick lettuce or cherry tomatoes? You clip a name tag onto each basket. On a harvest morning thick with the smell of earth and green, the moment a label goes on, that basket becomes the first marker on the road to the table."},"ICON-1656":{"nm":"Seed Storage Jar","on":"jar","de":"You tuck this year's gathered seeds into a glass jar and mail them off to next spring. Close the lid and time pauses for a while, as the little grains wait their turn in the dark. It's a jar like a letter sent across a whole season."},"ICON-1657":{"nm":"Grafting Tape","on":"grafting tape","de":"Press a cut branch and a new one together, wrap them in tape, and slowly the two become one body. Sap flows again across the break, the wound healing little by little. Joining, in the end, is the act of accepting each other's grain."},"ICON-1658":{"nm":"Pruning Shear Cap","on":"cap","de":"You slip a little hat over the sharp tip of the shears. While the hand that thinned the branches rests, the blade stays keen and the hand stays unharmed. Saying even a finished tool needs pajamas, the garden tucks its tools in with care."},"ICON-1659":{"nm":"Flower Seed Sorter","on":"sorter","de":"Balsam, moss rose, four o'clock—seeds different in name and color each get their own room in a separate compartment. Mix them up and come spring you won't know who's who. The little dividers in the box sketch out the blueprint of a garden not yet in bloom."},"ICON-1660":{"nm":"Planter Caster Tray","on":"planter caster tray","de":"Fit four wheels and even a heavy planter sets off to follow the sunshine. East window in the morning, shade at noon. Greenery once fixed in place rolls along, chasing the light all day in search of the very best spot."},"ICON-1661":{"nm":"Vine Guide Tie","on":"tie","de":"A tendril gropes the empty air, unsure where to go, and the tie quietly leads it onto the right path. Up, and farther up. Give it a place to grasp and, wondrously, the plant takes that hand. Even growing up needs a guide."},"ICON-1662":{"nm":"Flower Language Card Holder","on":"holder","de":"The card tucked beside a flower carries the words that flower offers. Hydrangea says sincerity, daisy says innocence. So that walking the flowerbed becomes a stroll of reading letters, a little holder gently lends a voice to the wordless flower."},"ICON-1663":{"nm":"Garden Sign Cap","on":"cap","de":"Lest wind and rain blur the lettering, you fit a clear hat over the garden sign. \"Tomatoes here,\" \"basil here.\" Names that might have faded stay crisp, so even after a year the garden forgets not a single one of its family."},"ICON-1664":{"nm":"Fertilizer Spoon","on":"spoon","de":"When adding nutrients to the soil, greed only scorches the roots. So one spoon, exactly that much. The little spoon scoops up the right amount and reminds you—a heart that grows things well always comes from fingertips that know moderation."},"ICON-1665":{"nm":"Mist Nozzle","on":"nozzle","de":"Turn the nozzle and the stream scatters down like fog. A tender leaf once battered by a harsh jet softly lifts its head beneath dewlike drops. The same water becomes an entirely different greeting depending on how it's given."},"ICON-1666":{"nm":"Feed Measuring Cup","on":"cup","de":"One cup, two cups. You measure a friend's meal with care, not guesswork. Too much and they leave it, too little and they're sad, so you reckon just the right amount. Sometimes love arrives in the shape of careful measuring."},"ICON-1667":{"nm":"Shedding Brush Cover","on":"cover","de":"In shedding season, a cover tidily wraps the soft fluff tangled in the brush. Cap the brush after grooming and the next day starts fresh and downy too. The sheen of a housemate quietly grows from small tidyings like this."},"ICON-1668":{"nm":"Nail Clipper Cap","on":"cap","de":"You fit a little lid over the sharp tip of the nail clippers, so the finished tool won't scratch the other things in the drawer. After the time of care is done, tucking the tool in to rest completes one full round of caregiving."},"ICON-1669":{"nm":"Collar Charm","on":"charm","de":"Hang a single sparkling charm on the collar and the same old walking path turns a little more special. A small ornament that twinkles in the sun. It may not be flashy, but it's marker enough that this little one is a dearly loved member of someone's family."},"ICON-1670":{"nm":"Pet Health Card","on":"card","de":"Did they eat well today, is anything hurting? You jot a line a day about your housemate's day onto the card. When the condition of a family member who cannot speak is set down in writing, the caring heart grows all the more thorough and steady too."},"ICON-1671":{"nm":"Bed Cushion Cover","on":"cover","de":"You dress the bed cushion in a soft new outfit. Peel off the fabric worn from rolling and nuzzling and the smell of sun-dried fluff drifts up. Keeping cleanest the spot they lie in most is a daily devotion to the one you live with."},"ICON-1672":{"nm":"Little Fence Pins","on":"pins","de":"Press little pins along the edge of the flowerbed to raise a low fence. Not a stern \"don't cross,\" but a gentle border saying this is where the flowers belong. With a line to keep, they can grow at ease within it."},"ICON-1673":{"nm":"Bonding Treat Tin","on":"tin","de":"Even a shy little one pricks up its ears at the rattle of this tin. Inside is a handful of treats that open the heart. Since small promises beat words for growing close, the clinking sound steps forward first."},"ICON-1674":{"nm":"Walk Log Tag","on":"tag","de":"Which path today, and how far? You knot the record onto the tag like a stitch. Gathered footsteps become a map, and gathered maps become memories. Every day walked together piles up neatly on this little tag."},"ICON-1675":{"nm":"Bird Feed Dish","on":"dish","de":"Set the dish on the windowsill, scatter a few millet grains, and nameless guests fly in one after another. The tap-tap of pecking, the flutter of wings. It's a tiny table where one offered handful brings a little concert each morning."},"ICON-1676":{"nm":"Squirrel Watch Tub","on":"tub","de":"Inside the clear tub you meet the round eyes of a squirrel. Cheeks stuffed full of acorns, tilting its head—what a sight. Upon the promise to peek for a moment and soon let it go, you trade a brief hello with a little patch of the wild."},"ICON-1677":{"nm":"Pawprint Plaster Mold","on":"pawprint plaster mold","de":"You pour soft plaster to cast a tiny pawprint. While you wait for it to set, the yard's time pauses for a while. That hand-sized paw stamp, sure to vanish as they grow, the white mold lifts up like forever and gently presses into your two hands."},"ICON-1678":{"nm":"Night Scope Lens Cap","on":"cap","de":"You close a little lid over the lens that gazes into the night. So the glass that watched stars and nests waits for the next night without a speck of dust. Even eyes that see the dark clearly need a single comma of rest through the day."},"ICON-1679":{"nm":"Nest Protection Marker","on":"nest protection marker","de":"Spot a nest among the branches and, instead of drawing near, you set up a marker. \"A bird family lives here, please be quiet.\" Watching but not intruding—that one tender step back is what keeps the nest safest of all."},"ICON-1680":{"nm":"Animal Sound Recorder Chip","on":"chip","de":"The song of the grass thicket, the chirping under the eaves, the night insects—you don't trap them in the chip so much as borrow them a while. A little sound box that, replayed, revives even the air of that moment. So everything once heard never quite disappears."},"ICON-1681":{"nm":"Spotting Scope Cover","on":"cover","de":"Just before a bird takes flight, the forest holds its breath for a moment. In that hush, a single cloth draped over the lens guards the far-off clarity, untouched by even a fingerprint's smudge."},"ICON-1682":{"nm":"Forest Trail Camera Strap","on":"strap","de":"Each time you climb the steep forest trail, the camera taps lightly against your chest. The thudding heartbeat and the shutter sway to the same rhythm, and this single strap holds those moments steadfastly against your chest."},"ICON-1683":{"nm":"Nature Guide Card","on":"card","de":"Even a single blade of grass has a name, the card quietly tells you. Once what you passed by unknowing is given a title, the mountain path suddenly crowds warmly with familiar faces."},"ICON-1684":{"nm":"Sail Repair Patch","on":"sail repair patch","de":"Even cloth that takes the wind full-on bears scars. With one small patch laid gently over the torn place, the sail earns again the right to hold the open sea."},"ICON-1685":{"nm":"Knot Practice Board","on":"board","de":"Up, down, once more around—the order your hands have memorized becomes a knot. On a night when the storm pounds the deck, that one procedure binds person and ship together as one."},"ICON-1686":{"nm":"Anchor Chain Cap","on":"protective cap","de":"Don't make light of this little hat fitted over the chain's end. Rust grows secretly within, so one cap standing against the sea wind quietly lengthens the anchor's life."},"ICON-1687":{"nm":"Course Marker Flag","on":"course marker flag","de":"On a day so thick with fog the way ahead is erased, a single flag speaks the path in its place. One point of color streaming in the wind finally loosens the stiffened shoulders of the lost helmsman."},"ICON-1688":{"nm":"Cabin Keyring","on":"ring","de":"Upon the swaying sea, a little ring hangs on the narrow cabin door. As long as the key keeps its place, a room to return to is never locked away from you."},"ICON-1689":{"nm":"Waterproof Map Case","on":"case","de":"In the rain, a paper map erases the way first. While a single sheet stays dry inside the clear case, even a soaked journey never quite loses its bearings."},"ICON-1690":{"nm":"Ship Lamp Wick","on":"ship lamp wick","de":"The oil the wick slowly draws up finally blooms into flame. One point of light on the deck, and at that small flicker the vast distance of the night sea quietly draws nearer."},"ICON-1691":{"nm":"Distress Signal Cloth","on":"distress signal cloth","de":"At a distance no voice can reach, the hand that waves a red cloth high travels farther than words. This single banner cuts through the wind, crying out in your place that someone here is alive."},"ICON-1692":{"nm":"Sea Wind Direction Pin","on":"pin","de":"The one who knows where the wind blows from sets the course. On the single direction a little pin quietly points, the fate of this whole day's sailing comes to lean."},"ICON-1693":{"nm":"Folding Shovel Cover","on":"cover","de":"Fold the blade and cover it, and even the diligent shovel catches its breath a while. The last thing the hand that dug all the earth does is to tend tomorrow's blade so it won't go dull."},"ICON-1694":{"nm":"Pocket Compass Case","on":"case","de":"The needle always points north without a tremor, but what protects that needle is the sturdy case. The more often one has lost the way, the more dearly one cherishes a sense of direction."},"ICON-1695":{"nm":"Camp Dish Net","on":"camp dish net","de":"You hang the washed dishes in the net to dry in the morning sun. A day at camp begins with the sound of water drying, and that small thing fills the tent reassuringly."},"ICON-1696":{"nm":"Camping Permit Card","on":"card","de":"Permission to stay a night on this mountain. The moment a single sheet of paper is in your hand, even the unfamiliar forest becomes your ally for a while and gently takes in your little tent."},"ICON-1697":{"nm":"Trail Flag Tie","on":"tie","de":"Tie a flag at every fork and the way back won't scatter in the dark. One small marker left by the one who went ahead quietly nudges the back of the steps that follow."},"ICON-1698":{"nm":"Waterproof Match Tin","on":"tin","de":"A match drowns in a single drop and falls silent forever. Sealed in a tin that not a bead of water can enter, the spark waits dry and still, just for the coldest night."},"ICON-1699":{"nm":"Portable Water Filter","on":"filter","de":"Even water cloudy enough to make you hesitate clears once it passes this filter. A little device that sets down doubt before thirst—the belief that you can drink is itself a sip of peace."},"ICON-1700":{"nm":"Emergency Blanket Pack","on":"emergency blanket pack","de":"Folded, it fits in your palm; unfolded, it becomes one person's warmth. So the word \"emergency\" weighs a little less, the blanket waits in a corner of the bag, always ready to grow warm."},"ICON-1701":{"nm":"Night Marker Bracelet","on":"night marker bracelet","de":"On a mountain path fallen into darkness, a single wrist gives off a quiet light. That small band announcing each other's place ties those walking together with an invisible, tender thread."},"ICON-1702":{"nm":"Miner Helmet Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"The sticker on the helmet is the miner's other name tag. In the deep tunnel where even light is precious, you fondly recognize a comrade by that small picture caught in the lamplight."},"ICON-1703":{"nm":"Ore Vein Marker Pin","on":"pin","de":"Where you've found a vein, you gently set a pin. One point shining alone in the dark kindly tells whoever comes next to start digging from here."},"ICON-1704":{"nm":"Crack Measuring Ruler","on":"ruler","de":"Measuring the crack splitting the wall is slow, dogged patience. Has it widened a hand's breadth since yesterday? The small number the ruler reports catches a collapse before it comes."},"ICON-1705":{"nm":"Relief Rubbing Paper","on":"relief rubbing paper","de":"You lay paper over the pattern carved in stone and tap the ink ever so softly. The moment a touch from a thousand years ago rises in black grain, the rubbing seats fallen time across from you for a while."},"ICON-1706":{"nm":"Ancient Coin Case","on":"case","de":"This little piece of metal, asleep and kept from rust, holds the last voice of a vanished nation. A whole age dwells in one coin, slowly aging within the clear case."},"ICON-1707":{"nm":"Crystal Shard Stand","on":"stand","de":"Even a crystal that locks light within needs something to lean on. The moment it rests gently on a little stand, the easily broken thing finally unfolds its radiance in full."},"ICON-1708":{"nm":"Cave Map Fragment","on":"cave map fragment","de":"A torn map slyly shows only half its secret. Until the day you find the remaining piece, this one sheet keeps the rest of the path half-hidden somewhere in the cave."},"ICON-1709":{"nm":"Rope Descent Carabiner","on":"carabiner","de":"To entrust your body down the cliff, you must first fully trust this carabiner. To hang your weight on a single piece of cold steel—trust, by nature, is just that weighty a thing."},"ICON-1710":{"nm":"Excavation Permit","on":"excavation permit","de":"A single sheet of paper clearly stamped with leave to dig the ground. To wake what is buried, first ask permission—excavation quietly teaches the way of beginning with courtesy."},"ICON-1711":{"nm":"Windbreak Pack","on":"windbreak pack","de":"Spread it with your back to the wind and a square of stillness opens in the middle of the gusty plain. Behind this single layer, a small spark is sheltered and the weary find a moment's rest."},"ICON-1712":{"nm":"Sandstorm Goggle Cover","on":"cover","de":"However fiercely the sand whirls, your sight at least must be kept to the end. A thin cover over the goggles becomes the courage to keep your eyes open and walk on, even through the storm."},"ICON-1713":{"nm":"Rainy Visit Tray","on":"tray","de":"Rainwater drips from the toes of the guest who has come. A tray set quietly by the entrance silently and warmly receives feet gone cold and wet."},"ICON-1714":{"nm":"Heatwave Cooler Tag","on":"tag","de":"A little tag that gently cools the midday heat. Dangling from your bag, it holds its coolness, then slips you a handful of shade right when the sweat begins to bead."},"ICON-1715":{"nm":"Cold Snap Hand-Warmer Belt","on":"belt","de":"A warm belt that wraps once around the waist. As the hand-warmer's heat spreads up the small of your back, even the bitter midwinter plain becomes a bit more bearable."},"ICON-1716":{"nm":"Moisture Absorber Pack","on":"moisture absorber pack","de":"Damp gnaws at things without a sound. While a little pack in the box silently drinks up the moisture, the things you treasure keep their shape, dry and intact."},"ICON-1717":{"nm":"Mud Shoe Cover","on":"cover","de":"There are times when shoes alone must stay clean even as you walk the mire. This thin shield that keeps out the mud makes the steps that cross the threshold home all the lighter."},"ICON-1718":{"nm":"Sea Fog Lamp Cover","on":"cover","de":"When the sea fog tries to swallow the lamp whole, this cover quietly gathers the scattering grain of light. Even in the dim dawn, one harbor light refuses to the last to go out."},"ICON-1719":{"nm":"Lightning Alert Pin","on":"pin","de":"When dark clouds hang low, a single pin offers warning first. The word to crouch low before the lightning strikes—humility before nature is always best learned in advance."},"ICON-1720":{"nm":"Recipe Bookmark","on":"recipe bookmark","de":"A little bookmark slipped between the pages of an open cookbook. When you fumble back for the line you lost before the fire, mother's home-cooked taste wakes again on that page too."},"ICON-1721":{"nm":"Seasoning Portion Stick","on":"seasoning portion stick","de":"Mom always just said \"a pinch.\" Eyeballing could never be exact, yet her hand's touch never wavered. Measuring salt with this stick, you come to see that what had ripened longer than any measure wasn't estimation but love."},"ICON-1722":{"nm":"Fermenting Lid Band","on":"band","de":"Did you know the jar breathes too? When this band hugs the lid snug, inside and out slowly begin to speak. Only after those unhurried days does the waiting finally earn the name of flavor."},"ICON-1723":{"nm":"Aging Label Chip","on":"chip","de":"A little chip with the day it was made written out neatly. The lettering fades while what's inside only deepens. Noting it down as if to forget, then suddenly drawing it out one day—aging is a promise kept just so."},"ICON-1724":{"nm":"Broth Strainer","on":"broth strainer","de":"Clear broth comes only after straining, and straining again. Watch the mesh hold back the bits and let only the essence flow through, and the old kitchen saying—that depth pools where you've taken something away—reaches you through your fingertips."},"ICON-1725":{"nm":"Dough Proofing Cloth","on":"dough proofing cloth","de":"You lay a cloth gently over the dough. While the yeast busily swells beneath that dimness, you first learn the tenderness of things that grow quietly in places unseen."},"ICON-1726":{"nm":"Ingredient Prep Pin","on":"pin","de":"A little pin that splits the grain of a scallion and holds the garlic firmly. Prepping is like a first greeting to the ingredients, so the more carefully you trim, the brighter the evening table glows by a tone."},"ICON-1727":{"nm":"Plating Tongs","on":"tongs","de":"Where to set the last morsel on the plate—in the end, these tongs decide. In that brief instant a skilled hand hesitates a half-beat in midair, a meal quietly becomes a painting."},"ICON-1728":{"nm":"Insulated Lunchbox Cover","on":"cover","de":"The lunchbox handed over at the school gate had to stay warm until the lunch bell rang. The warmth held inside this cover doesn't cool, as deep as the heart of someone who stood at the stove since dawn."},"ICON-1729":{"nm":"Dinner Invitation","on":"invitation","de":"\"Come eat with us sometime.\" Could there be a kinder thing to say? With no grand promise, just to sit at the same table—the oldest invitation Korean can offer is held in this single card."},"ICON-1730":{"nm":"Table Reservation Chip","on":"chip","de":"You write your name and hold the seat. While a little chip binds an empty table to someone for a while, the appointed time draws near, slow as footsteps."},"ICON-1731":{"nm":"Tasting Review Card","on":"card","de":"Faces taking one bite and gravely awarding stars. The honest line written neatly on this card is the warmest nagging there is for making the next dish even better."},"ICON-1732":{"nm":"Lunchbox Thank-You Band","on":"band","de":"You wrap a band around the cleanly emptied lunchbox and send it back. Even the one who never managed to say thanks ties, in this knot at least, the heart they couldn't speak."},"ICON-1733":{"nm":"Allergy Marker Tag","on":"tag","de":"This one little tag quietly guards someone's table. Spelling out plainly what's inside is another name for hospitality—a care that reaches even into the unseen."},"ICON-1734":{"nm":"Taste Memory Spoon","on":"spoon","de":"That flavor that lingered on the tongue was, in truth, the scenery of that day. When one spoonful carries you in an instant back to a childhood kitchen, it seems memory is something the heart, not the stomach, scoops up and keeps."},"ICON-1735":{"nm":"Today's Menu Token","on":"token","de":"What to eat today. Before the hardest question in the world, we lose every time. Flip this token and leave the menu to fate, and your heart, surprisingly, turns light and glad."},"ICON-1736":{"nm":"Shared Table Bell","on":"bell","de":"Ring the bell once and the family scattered through their rooms gathers in one place. That bell over the round table is the dearest translation of the words \"It's ready, come quick.\""},"ICON-1737":{"nm":"Dessert Order Card","on":"card","de":"Sweet things always come last. This card keeps that promise no one knows who made. A small, tender host of the table, saving the peak of appetite for one bite of dessert."},"ICON-1738":{"nm":"Bargaining Token","on":"token","de":"In the heart of the market, \"give me a little off\" and \"I'm already losing money\" clash affectionately. This token is the receipt of an old regular, where the haggling ends, after all, in laughter."},"ICON-1739":{"nm":"Stock Check Pin","on":"pin","de":"You scan the warehouse shelves quietly, find the empty slots, and stick in a pin. Knowing what's left and what's run out—the big work of housekeeping always starts from this small inspection."},"ICON-1740":{"nm":"Stall Cleaning Brush","on":"brush","de":"In the evening after market's close, the low sound of sweeping an empty stall settles over the shop. In the fingertips that wipe down a spot to fill again tomorrow lingers a diligence that ties off the day neatly."},"ICON-1741":{"nm":"Today's Recommendation Card","on":"card","de":"\"This one's good today.\" A card the shop owner slips out. In that recommendation, gently nudging the shoulder of a customer unsure what to pick, a day's worth of pride is tidily held."},"ICON-1742":{"nm":"Loyalty Stamp Holder","on":"holder","de":"Fill ten and one's on the house. This holder, its stamp squares filling up little by little, is another face of the word \"regular,\" for coming often means, in the end, that you love it."},"ICON-1743":{"nm":"Exchange Ledger Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clip that gathers and holds the records of things swapped and returned. The more that's gone back and forth, the thicker the ledger, and by that thickness the trust built with neighbors grows plump too."},"ICON-1744":{"nm":"Sold-Out Tag","on":"sold-out tag","de":"The moment this tag goes on the very last one, your heart strangely fills. It's a short send-off, like \"farewell,\" to a thing departing for someone's table, for some corner of a room."},"ICON-1745":{"nm":"Reserved Item Basket","on":"basket","de":"A basket bearing your name tag holds down one slot on the shelf. That one spot set aside in advance quietly tells you, as you walk in, \"I've been waiting for you all this time.\""},"ICON-1746":{"nm":"Wrapping Counter Mat","on":"mat","de":"The mat laid over the wrapping counter is a stage for busy hands. In the short time paper is folded and string is tied neatly, an ordinary thing slips into becoming someone's gift."},"ICON-1747":{"nm":"Visit Promise Note","on":"visit promise note","de":"\"I'll drop by tomorrow.\" A note penned in a line and tucked into the door crack. Even when you've missed each other's faces, the promise rides on a single sheet, arriving ahead of the person to wait quietly."},"ICON-1748":{"nm":"Neighbor Gift Basket","on":"basket","de":"A basket passed over the wall always comes with the excuse \"I made a bit too much.\" Korean warmth crosses over to this side just so, feigning indifference under a pretense of plenty."},"ICON-1749":{"nm":"Village News Box","on":"village news box","de":"The village's news, big and small, piles up neatly inside this box. Who's just moved in, whose house is holding a feast—a few sheets of paper gather to convey the quiet pulse of the neighborhood."},"ICON-1750":{"nm":"Thank-You Visit Stamp","on":"thank-you visit stamp","de":"You press the gratitude for someone coming firmly down with a single stamp. That one ink stain bled into the paper stays in place longer than the words \"I won't forget.\""},"ICON-1751":{"nm":"Kindness Praise Card","on":"card","de":"A card on which you quietly write the kindness someone offered today and pass it back. In a village that bothers to set small tendernesses down in words, good things keep circling around and coming back."},"ICON-1752":{"nm":"Apology Letter Seal","on":"apology letter seal","de":"Like an apple ripened red, an apology can only be offered after it has ripened enough. This seal pressed firmly onto the envelope is the mark of courage that held a hard-to-say sorry to the very end."},"ICON-1753":{"nm":"Joint Task Chart","on":"chart","de":"A single chart written out in columns of who takes what. Work too heavy alone grows much lighter once names are shared across it—anyone who's worked shoulder to shoulder knows."},"ICON-1754":{"nm":"Neighbor Preference Ribbon","on":"ribbon","de":"You quietly mark what a neighbor likes with ribbons of many colors. To remember someone's tastes is the quietest confession of all that you cherish them, without ever saying so."},"ICON-1755":{"nm":"Invitation Nameplate Ring","on":"ring","de":"A single ring on the nameplate announces \"taking guests today.\" It's a palm-sized marker, yet on it hangs a heart thrown wide open, finished with its preparations to welcome someone."},"ICON-1756":{"nm":"Festival Entry Wristband","on":"festival entry wristband","de":"A faded band worn for days, too dear to take off. Only when it was fastened to your wrist did the festival truly begin. Within it sleeps, kept whole, a day that never quite ended even after it ended."},"ICON-1757":{"nm":"Fireworks Ticket Holder","on":"holder","de":"Just before the night sky bursts, the ticket in this holder holds your fluttering heart tight. It's a promise gripped till your palm sweats, all for that one instant the first firework blooms with a pop."},"ICON-1758":{"nm":"Moon-Viewing Plate","on":"plate","de":"There were nights when it felt as though you'd scooped the whole full moon onto a dish. Lay fresh fruit and songpyeon prettily on this plate and bow to the moon, and one round heart reaches all the way to the edge of the sky."},"ICON-1759":{"nm":"Winter Festival Glove Pin","on":"pin","de":"Even when your hands go numb in the snow, the gloves keep slipping off your wrists. Only once this pin is fastened firmly to your cuff can you finally run about the winter festival to your heart's content."},"ICON-1760":{"nm":"Spring Seed Card","on":"card","de":"A few seeds asleep within the card each await their spring. Bury them in soil and they sprout without fail, like a promise—it seems every beginning springs from one small, solid point."},"ICON-1761":{"nm":"Summer Beach Stamp","on":"summer beach stamp","de":"A wave stamps its mark firmly into the sand and slides back. Knowing it will soon be erased, still it leaves a small mark that someone came here. Summer always stamps once, clear, then drifts off with the briny scent."},"ICON-1762":{"nm":"Autumn Harvest Ribbon","on":"ribbon","de":"The hand that bound the grain ties a ribbon prettily at the last. A single knot that gathers up a year's sweat with care. Even as the fields empty, autumn offers one more greeting, like a sunset, in its loveliest hue."},"ICON-1763":{"nm":"Commemorative Photo Speech Bubble","on":"commemorative photo speech bubble","de":"\"Thank you for coming all this way.\" A greeting never quite spoken aloud swells round upon the paper. A round little piece of heart, gently lending a voice to the silence frozen in a photo."},"ICON-1764":{"nm":"Festival Map Pin","on":"pin","de":"A marker someone stuck in so you won't lose your way in the wide grounds. Even when your feet race ahead toward the folk-music sound, this one pin gently leads the wandering you to the appointed spot."},"ICON-1765":{"nm":"Album Master Key","on":"album master key","de":"What's locked away isn't the record but the time sealed within it. The tremor of the first recording, the dawn of the final mix. Turn the key slowly and the door of that room, known only to its makers, creaks open."},"ICON-1766":{"nm":"Tracklist Card","on":"card","de":"The order of songs on a single sheet is, in truth, the order of the heart. Where it'll catch in your throat, where you'll catch your breath—the paper already knows it all. A thrill that wells up before you even hear the first note."},"ICON-1767":{"nm":"Audio Inspection Tag","on":"tag","de":"Only one who's rewound the same passage a hundred times pins on this tag. One more time, just one more listen. Beside the pass stamp hides someone's night of doubting their own ears until dawn."},"ICON-1768":{"nm":"Preorder Label","on":"label","de":"A promise to wait for something not yet even out in the world. The moment the label goes on, one empty slot is quietly reserved under someone's name. Even a thrilling wait has a number ticket."},"ICON-1769":{"nm":"First Edition Seal Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"It resembles the old touch of covering a jar with hanji and sealing it with paste. A single sheet vowing to keep things just as they first were. Knowing it'll vanish the moment you peel it, you keep gazing at its set ever longer."},"ICON-1770":{"nm":"Comeback Calendar Chip","on":"chip","de":"Add one circle to the calendar and the nights until that day grow one square shorter. The return date is crisp on the little chip in your hand. To one who waits, time is counted just so, by hand."},"ICON-1771":{"nm":"Concept Photo Sleeve","on":"concept photo sleeve","de":"Before the next concept pushes out the color of this one, a clear sheet tucks away its grain with care. So it isn't forgotten when the season turns, it gently guards the hue of days past, corners and all."},"ICON-1772":{"nm":"Teaser Reveal Token","on":"token","de":"Just before lifting the veil, a little coin held in your palm. The moment you hold it out, the locked first scene opens a hand's breadth toward the world. A reveal, in the end, is a matter of who holds out their hand first."},"ICON-1773":{"nm":"Album Display Stand","on":"stand","de":"The moment one low stand lifts an album slightly, an ordinary disc becomes the star of the display. A tender supporting player, propping up from behind, in silence, the angle where the light falls most lovely."},"ICON-1774":{"nm":"Debut Showcase Pass","on":"debut showcase pass","de":"A single pass stamped with the words \"presenting for the very first time.\" From the long corridor backstage to the first applause from the seats, this pass carries you over the trembling threshold of a debut."},"ICON-1775":{"nm":"First Stage Mark Chip","on":"chip","de":"You feel for the chip stuck to the floor with your toe. One square the body knows first, even without looking. The moment you land exactly on the memorized spot, the tremor in your fingertips finally becomes a clear movement."},"ICON-1776":{"nm":"Greeting Speech Card","on":"card","de":"Even the common line \"it's all thanks to you\" is no longer common once written in a trembling hand. A few lines jotted down in advance for fear emotion makes you forget. Sometimes sincerity leans on a single card."},"ICON-1777":{"nm":"Profile Shoot Booking Sheet","on":"sheet","de":"A sheet with the date you're to stand before the lens written out neatly. A timetable for slowly preparing your very best face. As each blank fills in, the nights spent before the mirror grow longer too."},"ICON-1778":{"nm":"Fan Club Sign-Up Slip","on":"fan club sign-up slip","de":"A slip of entry where you shyly write your name and your heart on one line. Saying you like something is always hard, but this one slip spells out those words for you, neatly. A first signature on choosing to be together."},"ICON-1779":{"nm":"Debut Gift Inspection Sheet","on":"sheet","de":"A touch that checks each one over, picturing the person who'll receive it. Are the corners bruised, has any heart gone missing? A gift is loved once already, before it's even handed over, and sets off."},"ICON-1780":{"nm":"Stage Ending Marker","on":"stage ending marker","de":"Just before the curtain falls, a marker placed where the final pose comes to rest. Not a signal of the end so much as a small point that ties the end off prettily. Only a stage well closed opens the next one."},"ICON-1781":{"nm":"Interview Standby Pin","on":"pin","de":"A pin that quietly keeps the hush before the questions begin. During the brief silence of choosing answers in your head, this little marker kindly says in your place, \"Not yet, but soon.\""},"ICON-1782":{"nm":"Debut Keepsake Envelope","on":"envelope","de":"Like the old heart that pressed a precious letter, envelope and all, into the hand of one setting out, a single layer holds the record of a first stage with care. The day you open it far in the future, that day's tremor comes spilling out too."},"ICON-1783":{"nm":"Vocal Breath Straw","on":"vocal breath straw","de":"Practice sending breath out long, in a single stream, through the thin tube's end. Singing, in the end, is well-governed breath—this little straw quietly tells you so each morning. The wind before the sound."},"ICON-1784":{"nm":"Tempo Training Click Chip","on":"chip","de":"Tick, tick, tick—the most honest friend in the world. It reins you in when you rush and nudges your back when you drag. Carving the beat into your body is like a long conversation with this sturdy chip."},"ICON-1785":{"nm":"Dance Line Check Ribbon","on":"ribbon","de":"Where the fingertips stop, where the shoulder opens—you trace the line of the movement with a single ribbon. A well-drawn dance line stays straight and tidy even where the seats can't see."},"ICON-1786":{"nm":"Expression Feedback Card","on":"card","de":"That saying, that even smiling must be learned. A sheet noting down, bit by bit, the angle of the eyes and the height of the lips. The expression the mirror failed to teach, this card kindly tells you in its place."},"ICON-1787":{"nm":"Rap Flow Memo","on":"memo","de":"\"Rest a beat here, pour it all out there\"—a memo sketching the waterway of words in advance. The faster the passage, the clearer the path of breath must be. Within the hastily drawn arrows, a verse's rhythm lives and breathes."},"ICON-1788":{"nm":"Vocal Temperature Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"A voice has warm days and cold days too. A little marker you choose by color and stick on for today's grain. Warming and cooling by turns, the sound wakes each day at a slightly different temperature."},"ICON-1789":{"nm":"Rest Routine Token","on":"token","de":"A coin pressed into your hand with the words that resting well is a skill too. Hold it out and you can pause a while without guilt. To one who's run nonstop, stopping is the most courageous choice."},"ICON-1790":{"nm":"Growth Goal Pin","on":"pin","de":"A little pin stuck in with \"let's try to get this far.\" Though it seems far enough to barely reach, you grow one step toward it each day. A goal is like a tender promise beckoning from far off."},"ICON-1791":{"nm":"Weekly Review Envelope","on":"envelope","de":"You gather a week's sweat and tears neatly into one envelope and hand it over. The well done and the wanting sit side by side inside. Opening it is a small assignment handed to next week's self."},"ICON-1792":{"nm":"Stage Décor Parts Tin","on":"tin","de":"Behind the glittering stage live nameless parts. One screw, one ring gather to float the stars on the ceiling. Open the tin and it's full of the small, patient devotion that silently upholds all the splendor."},"ICON-1793":{"nm":"Costume Concept Board","on":"costume concept board","de":"Pinning fabric scraps and colors one by one, you try on, in advance, an outfit not yet in the world. A stage costume completed first upon the board. Imagination always walks a step ahead of the needle."},"ICON-1794":{"nm":"Color Fitting Chip","on":"chip","de":"The same outfit wears an entirely different face depending on the light. Which color smiles brightest with that person—you find out by holding chips up one by one. Suiting is a discovery at the end of long comparing."},"ICON-1795":{"nm":"Shoelace Sample Board","on":"board","de":"What backs a firm step onstage is, surprisingly, a small lace. So it won't come undone, yet won't pinch either. The tenderest of considerations, made at the lowest place, choosing from laces laid out by their grain."},"ICON-1796":{"nm":"Accessory Inspection Envelope","on":"envelope","de":"The more something sparkles, the more glaringly a single flaw shows. A touch holding the jewelry from the envelope up to the light, checking it over carefully. A heart that examines small things to the end is what guards the stage."},"ICON-1797":{"nm":"Hair Color Patch","on":"hair color patch","de":"A little swatch for trying a new season on your hair in advance. The color tinting just one strand quietly hints at the first impression of the next concept. Change always starts somewhere palm-sized."},"ICON-1798":{"nm":"Nail Concept Card","on":"card","de":"A sheet deciding in advance the little pictures to paint on ten fingertips. So the concept faintly shows in even a gesture, you lovingly dress even the smallest detail in a story."},"ICON-1799":{"nm":"Style Change Ticket","on":"ticket","de":"\"Shall I become a slightly different me than yesterday today?\"—a single ticket that makes that one line possible. Hair, clothes, or mood, this ticket opens the thrilling door to a new look."},"ICON-1800":{"nm":"Size Adjustment Tag","on":"tag","de":"A tag carefully noting where to take in and let out until it fits just right. Like the old touch that mended a child's clothes stitch by stitch, this small adjustment makes the stage a hand's breadth more comfortable."},"ICON-1801":{"nm":"Thumbnail Rough Card","on":"card","de":"A single sheet untouched by color. Above the rough pencil lines, it quietly guesses where the next scene will flow. More thrilling than the finished piece is always this unfinished first line, the quiet editing room reminds us."},"ICON-1802":{"nm":"Filming Consent Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"\"Is it okay to be captured here?\" Instead of words, you place a little round mark over your chest. A single small sticker sets a kind promise between the camera and the heart."},"ICON-1803":{"nm":"Photo Wall Spot Pin","on":"pin","de":"A tiny pin stuck into a corner of the wall. It marks in advance who will stand where. Wherever a pin is set, a smile pauses and becomes a single photograph."},"ICON-1804":{"nm":"Cut Select Chip","on":"chip","de":"A finger pointing to just one among hundreds of cuts. The moment this chip goes down, all the folded-away expressions lived for that single frame. Choosing always resembles a quiet farewell."},"ICON-1805":{"nm":"Behind-the-Scenes Envelope","on":"envelope","de":"Everything that happened behind the camera is kept here. Fold the flap and laughter, bloopers, and sleepy yawns all sleep together. What you come to treasure more than the main feature is often what is tucked inside."},"ICON-1806":{"nm":"Edit Request Memo","on":"memo","de":"\"One more second here, and turn the music down a touch.\" A note crowded with red ink. Someone's particularness adjusts the breath of the video by a single beat. Polish grows on these small touches."},"ICON-1807":{"nm":"Upload Schedule Tag","on":"tag","de":"A little mark on a video set to step out into the world at seven tomorrow morning, all on its own. Even while everyone sleeps, the promise stays awake. Time set in advance never knows how to be late."},"ICON-1808":{"nm":"Thumbnail Frame Cover","on":"cover","de":"A cover wrapping the best first scene. It tidily folds the corners so no fingerprints or dust can touch them. Until it is shown, a first impression is kept this gently."},"ICON-1809":{"nm":"Footage Length Chip","on":"chip","de":"A little chip that gauges how many minutes were filmed today. Longer is not better, nor is shorter lighter. Knowing the right length is the first button of editing."},"ICON-1810":{"nm":"Cheer Slogan Proof Sheet","on":"sheet","de":"A paper to check once more before shouting at the top of your lungs. One wrong letter and a thousand voices scatter. Behind the cheer, an unseen hand of proofreading has come through first."},"ICON-1811":{"nm":"Fan Art Storage Sleeve","on":"fan art storage sleeve","de":"A picture someone drew through the night. A clear little home is offered so it won't be creased. As if what is drawn with the heart must be held with the heart to last, the sleeve embraces it without a word."},"ICON-1812":{"nm":"Fan Letter Sorting Cord","on":"cord","de":"A cord that neatly ties the heaped letters by sender. With each knot, a day's worth of longing is set in order. Here is a hand that won't let a single letter slip away, even if it can't reply to them all."},"ICON-1813":{"nm":"Goods Trade Sign-Up Sheet","on":"sheet","de":"\"Is there anyone who'd swap with mine?\" A paper you write your nervous heart onto and hold out. For the single reason of liking the same thing, two strangers become friends for a little while."},"ICON-1814":{"nm":"Group Cheer Seat Chip","on":"chip","de":"A chip that assigns seats where people in matching colors will sit side by side. When scattered hearts gather into one section, the audience begins to sing like one enormous person."},"ICON-1815":{"nm":"Birthday Ad Receipt","on":"birthday ad receipt","de":"A single receipt held after putting love up on a billboard. What isn't written beside the amount is the devotion gathered through the night. This paper remains as proof of a celebration aimed at just one person."},"ICON-1816":{"nm":"Message Book Cover","on":"cover","de":"A cover wrapping a book gathered from many people's handwriting. Open it and the different hands fold together into one heart. The outside is neat, but the inside is full of a warm commotion."},"ICON-1817":{"nm":"Fan Club Member Pin","on":"pin","de":"A little pin handed only to those who call the same name. The moment it is pinned to the chest, a lonely fondness turns into a promise shared by many. Belonging has a round shape like this."},"ICON-1818":{"nm":"Online Cheer Token","on":"token","de":"A point of light that faraway hands wave beyond the screen. The distance is vast, yet the rhythm is the same. It is proof that cheering arrives without fail, even from unseen seats."},"ICON-1819":{"nm":"Worn Key Fragment","on":"worn key fragment","de":"A chipped scrap of metal. No one remembers anymore which door it once opened. What outlives the locked place is always the useless half of a key like this."},"ICON-1820":{"nm":"Secret Passage Map","on":"secret passage map","de":"An old paper sketching a path hidden behind the ivy. Shortcuts are known only to those who know them. The moment it unfolds, the ordinary island quietly turns its face into a stage for adventure."},"ICON-1821":{"nm":"Cipher Decoding Card","on":"card","de":"A card that returns jumbled, scattered letters to their proper places. When one line falls into order, the next secret beckons. Even a knot that seemed unsolvable begins, after all, with the first letter."},"ICON-1822":{"nm":"Sealed Box Cord","on":"cord","de":"A cord bound tight as if to say do not open. Only the one who tied it knows what sleeps inside the knot. The wish to untie and the wish to protect are bound side by side in this single line."},"ICON-1823":{"nm":"Ruins Puzzle Chip","on":"chip","de":"A small fragment broken off an ancient stone wall. Fit it back into place and someone's craft from a thousand years ago revives at your fingertips. Gathering what is scattered is the work of joining time anew."},"ICON-1824":{"nm":"Island Legend Scrap","on":"island legend scrap","de":"A paper where old tales drifting around the island were copied by hand. Whether they are true or not hardly matters. A story carried from mouth to mouth becomes, in itself, a growth ring of the island."},"ICON-1825":{"nm":"Hidden Marker Stone","on":"hidden marker stone","de":"A stone set seemingly by chance at the roadside. Only to a knowing eye does it quietly point the way. The deeper a secret you wish to bury, the plainer the face it stands there with."},"ICON-1826":{"nm":"Riddle Envelope","on":"envelope","de":"Nothing is written on the outside. This brief moment just before breaking the seal is the most thrilling. Until the answer is in hand, every possibility is still alive inside the envelope."},"ICON-1827":{"nm":"Detective Magnifier Cap","on":"cap","de":"A little cap that quietly fits over the end of the magnifying glass. When not peering through, it lets the lens rest. To see well, you must first protect well, a lesson the detective learns early."},"ICON-1828":{"nm":"Island Loop Bus Ticket","on":"ticket","de":"A single ticket to board the bus that circles the island. The last stop is the starting point again. On a road that comes back around to where it began, the scenery looks a little new each time."},"ICON-1829":{"nm":"Bicycle Rental Tag","on":"tag","de":"A tag dangling from the handle of a borrowed bicycle. A brief freedom is granted until it is returned. When the time of slicing through the wind ends, this tag quietly collects that promise back."},"ICON-1830":{"nm":"Small Boat Boarding Pass","on":"pass","de":"A boarding pass to climb aboard a small boat. On the swaying deck, island and island draw closer. Crossing the waterway always brings along a little thrill and a little seasickness together."},"ICON-1831":{"nm":"Cart Wheel Pin","on":"pin","de":"A pin that holds the cart wheel firmly in place. This one small piece of metal keeps a heavy load rolling. The least noticeable part is often the one that silently bears the most weight."},"ICON-1832":{"nm":"Cable Car Token","on":"token","de":"A round token dropped into the cable car that cuts through the air. The moment your feet leave the ground, the whole island is gathered into one view. The higher you rise, the more generous the scenery grows."},"ICON-1833":{"nm":"Hot Air Balloon Band","on":"band","de":"A band worn on the wrist before climbing into the basket. As the flame swells and the ground falls away, the heart grows lighter too. To rise is to set down your weight for a little while."},"ICON-1834":{"nm":"Water Taxi Call Chip","on":"chip","de":"A little chip for calling a taxi that runs over the water. Raise your hand and a boat comes cutting through the current. What carves a path even where there is none is, in the end, the courage of the one who calls first."},"ICON-1835":{"nm":"Trailhead Entry Pass","on":"trailhead entry pass","de":"A pass handed over at the first gateway into the mountain. From here on, your toes decide the path. The summit may be far, but only those who pass the entrance are promised that view."},"ICON-1836":{"nm":"Harbor Locker Key","on":"harbor locker key","de":"A small key that opens a locker by the docks. With hands lightened after leaving your load, you gaze out at the sea. Having a place to set things down for a while lends you the courage to travel far."},"ICON-1837":{"nm":"Pickling Jar Cap","on":"cap","de":"A jar lid that confines all things tart. Sealed tight, summer's cucumbers keep their crunch until winter. The secret to beating time begins, it turns out, with closing things up well."},"ICON-1838":{"nm":"Drying Rack Label","on":"label","de":"A name tag attached to things spread out to dry on a sieve. Note what was laid out and when, and the waiting won't fall into disorder. Even in the time of sun and wind, there must be such a thing as turns."},"ICON-1839":{"nm":"Smoking Chip Envelope","on":"envelope","de":"An envelope holding chips of fragrant wood. Open the mouth and a scent like a campfire greets your nose first. A flavor deepened by smoke opens slowly, only to one who knows how to wait."},"ICON-1840":{"nm":"Preserved Food Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"A sticker placed on a jar, wishing it well through the whole year. The day it was made and the devotion are written on it. Food kept long always comes with a small note trying to remember that day's handmade taste."},"ICON-1841":{"nm":"Fermentation Clock Tag","on":"tag","de":"Fermentation doesn't trust the clock. It measures time by scent instead of the minute hand. The moment a tangy smell reaches your nose, the tag quietly nods, \"It's ready now.\" Even waiting has its own scale of marks."},"ICON-1842":{"nm":"Fridge Shelf Sorting Pin","on":"pin","de":"Here stands the little traffic cop of the fridge. Vegetables up top, side dishes below, yesterday's leftovers in the front row. Plant one pin and the hand that always fumbled when opening the door soon knows the way."},"ICON-1843":{"nm":"Lunchbox Warming Band","on":"band","de":"Mom wrapped a band around the lunchbox so the warmth wouldn't escape before noon. Untie the band and beneath the steamed-up lid, the morning's care still lies warm, waiting for me."},"ICON-1844":{"nm":"Sauce Aging Bottle","on":"bottle","de":"Good seasoning is never in a hurry. It quietly grants soy sauce and garlic the time to seep into each other. In the bottle's darkness the flavor slowly deepens, and the slow wisdom of the crock terrace moves into a little bottle."},"ICON-1845":{"nm":"Seasonal Jam Label","on":"label","de":"Strawberry in spring, apricot in summer, fig in autumn. A single label writes the season neatly onto the jar. Open the lid in deep winter, and last year's sunlight melts out slowly, one spoonful at a time."},"ICON-1846":{"nm":"Collection Rate Badge Board","on":"board","de":"You needn't bother counting how many you've gathered, for the badge board boasts of it for you. With each empty slot filled, your shoulders rise a little. This isn't a number, but a trail stamped out on tiptoe."},"ICON-1847":{"nm":"Undiscovered Slot Card","on":"card","de":"A spot not yet met. The silhouette on the card offers a promise, its outline only faintly drawn. Empty means soon to be filled, so anticipation always waits for you in the shape of a question mark."},"ICON-1848":{"nm":"Catalog Complete Stamp","on":"catalog complete stamp","de":"That sound of the stamp landing with a thud on the last slot. Close the catalog, open your palm, and a dot of red ink clings there like a medal of completion. That deep relief known only to those who collected to the end."},"ICON-1849":{"nm":"Rarity Color Chip","on":"chip","de":"Even the same shape tells a different story when the color differs. A single chip quietly draws the line between ordinary and precious. A collector's eye always lingers long before that subtle difference in hue."},"ICON-1850":{"nm":"Duplicate Collection Voucher","on":"voucher","de":"Another one, again. On the day you picked up your third of something you already had, this voucher quietly held out its hand. Like a kind comfort that duplicates, if embraced rather than tossed, will one day return as something precious."},"ICON-1851":{"nm":"Collection Box Number Plate","on":"plate","de":"Number each box and the storeroom becomes a little library. Number 17 holds the spring gathering, number 23 what was picked up by the sea. I am a quiet index, sorting scattered memories one line at a time."},"ICON-1852":{"nm":"Display Layout Guide","on":"display layout guide","de":"A display is half made by placement. Tall ones to the back, shining ones to the center. Follow the guide and move things by hand, and the cluttered shelf soon catches its breath like a little gallery."},"ICON-1853":{"nm":"Collectible Duster","on":"collectible duster","de":"The more cherished a thing, the better the dust settles on it. With the soft tip of the brush, gently, you sweep away even the guilt of not looking at it for so long. As you clean, the sleeping memories sparkle again for a moment."},"ICON-1854":{"nm":"Storage Limit Expansion Voucher","on":"voucher","de":"Collect long enough and running out of room becomes a happy worry. The quiet relief of seeing one more shelf added. This isn't greed, but proof that there is that much you love."},"ICON-1855":{"nm":"Friend Invite Code Card","on":"card","de":"To hand over this code is the kindest invitation of all, saying \"come play with me.\" The heart held in a few digits. Only when the friend who received it sets foot on the island does a story just for the two of you begin."},"ICON-1856":{"nm":"Shared Storeroom Key","on":"shared storeroom key","de":"The storeroom door never opens alone. A lock that turns only when two hands, yours and mine, come together. A shared space always holds a shared promise, hung there in the shape of a key."},"ICON-1857":{"nm":"Lost-and-Found Report Tag","on":"tag","de":"A lost thing is precious to someone too. Writing a single line, \"It's here,\" and hanging it up. The tag is a small cord that quietly reconnects a briefly lost heart with its owner."},"ICON-1858":{"nm":"Help Request Flag","on":"flag","de":"Asking for help is not weakness but courage. When the flag goes up, someone comes running from somewhere. What spreads fastest on this island is not rumor, but the hands reaching out toward one another."},"ICON-1859":{"nm":"Emergency Contact Bracelet","on":"emergency contact bracelet","de":"A little reassurance worn around the wrist. Whatever happens, the number written here comes running faster than anyone. A quiet companion, forgotten in ordinary days, that becomes most dependable in the moment of need."},"ICON-1860":{"nm":"Task Division Chip","on":"chip","de":"Who shops and who cooks: share out the chips and there's nothing to quarrel over. The first step in making something together starts with kindly deciding each person's share."},"ICON-1861":{"nm":"Co-Creation Sheet","on":"sheet","de":"What you'd never dare attempt alone becomes possible, like magic, when many gather. As names fill the sheet one by one, the empty slots shrink and the laughter grows. Cooperation quietly grows in the space between the cells."},"ICON-1862":{"nm":"Visiting Manners Card","on":"card","de":"Stepping into someone else's home, you turn careful from the very tips of your toes. What's written on the card isn't grand rules, only small, warm promises like \"line up your shoes, greet first.\""},"ICON-1863":{"nm":"Party Dismissal Bell","on":"bell","de":"Even joy needs an end so the next one can be looked forward to. When the bell rings, everyone gathers their things with reluctant faces. A party that knows how to part well lingers longest in the heart."},"ICON-1864":{"nm":"Mattress Corner Band","on":"band","de":"No matter how smoothly you spread the bedding, the corners always lift. Thanks to a band that firmly grips all four corners, the bed wakes each morning as crisp as a hotel room."},"ICON-1865":{"nm":"Duvet Collar Button Cord","on":"cord","de":"I am the button cord that holds the duvet's collar. No matter how much you toss through the night, I grip tight so the collar can't escape. Bedding without a single wrinkle when you wake: that's the reward of my all-nighter shift."},"ICON-1866":{"nm":"Topper Fixing Clip","on":"clip","de":"The topper tries to slip away the moment it gets a chance. Each time, the clip bites the corner hard and holds its place. A silent stubborn one that keeps the bed in order from an unseen corner."},"ICON-1867":{"nm":"Sheet Wrinkle Smoother","on":"sheet wrinkle smoother","de":"The fine wrinkles a sheet gathers overnight somehow resemble the creases of the heart. Like cloth that turns smooth with one sweep of the smoother, I wish a rumpled day could be pressed out just as gently."},"ICON-1868":{"nm":"Mattress Ventilation Base","on":"base","de":"Even a mattress needs room to breathe. When the base opens an air path below, the dampness drains out and dryness seeps in. Good sleep begins, quietly, from the very air that supports your back."},"ICON-1869":{"nm":"Duvet Cover Zipper Flap","on":"duvet cover zipper flap","de":"That midnight chaos when the filling keeps poking out as you change the duvet cover. Cover the zipper with a flap once and you won't wake from catching it with your foot. A great peace, brought by one little flap."},"ICON-1870":{"nm":"Anti-Clumping Pad","on":"pad","de":"Pillow filling soon bunches to one side, making a little hill. When the pad steadily holds the gap, the flatness stays to the end. Thanks to it, a like-new fluffiness returns without fail every night."},"ICON-1871":{"nm":"Bed Sheet Elastic Hook","on":"hook","de":"A sheet always tries to slowly peel off to one side. Hook the corners and pull it taut, and it won't budge however much you toss through the night. Tautness quietly becomes the foundation of deep sleep."},"ICON-1872":{"nm":"Pillowcase Change Tag","on":"tag","de":"When you suddenly can't recall whether you washed the pillowcase today, a single tag answers clearly. A schedule you keep forgetting from sleeping and sleeping again, this little mark remembers diligently in your stead."},"ICON-1873":{"nm":"Dream Journal Bookmark","on":"dream journal bookmark","de":"A dream that scatters through your fingers the moment you wake, the bookmark pins to the page it marked. Open it and last night's sea and sky are still there, a little bridge laid gently between sleep and writing."},"ICON-1874":{"nm":"White Noise Pebble","on":"white noise pebble","de":"Too quiet a night often wakes you instead. When the pebble releases a sound like soft rustling rain, the heart slowly settles along its grain. A little stone that gently soothes the silence."},"ICON-1875":{"nm":"Temperature-Sensing Sleep Chip","on":"chip","de":"Whether your brow is warm or your toes are cold while you sleep, the chip watches quietly beside you. Thanks to a night-keeper that softly finds the temperature just right for your body, sleep flows on until dawn without waking."},"ICON-1876":{"nm":"Blackout Curtain Clip","on":"clip","de":"Morning sunlight is so diligent it keeps squeezing through the gap in the curtain. Bite both ends hard with the clip and the room turns dark again like the dead of night. A dependable accomplice for one more lie-in."},"ICON-1877":{"nm":"Moonlight Projection Stand","on":"moonlight projection stand","de":"Turn off the light and a moon rises across the ceiling. The soft glow the stand casts up turns the room into a little night sky. The feeling of falling asleep gazing up at the moon, kept right at your bedside."},"ICON-1878":{"nm":"Sleep Sachet Hanger","on":"sleep sachet hanger","de":"A pouch holding lavender and the scent of grass sways gently at your bedside. As the fragrance seeps to your nose, your shoulders loosen, and a single sachet calls sleep before the pillow does."},"ICON-1879":{"nm":"Lullaby Music Box Pin","on":"pin","de":"Wind the spring gently and a little melody unspools. The lullaby that turns out from the tip of the pin closely resembles the rhythm with which Grandma patted your back. Each note slowly grows your eyelids heavy."},"ICON-1880":{"nm":"Humidity Plant Cup","on":"cup","de":"I am a cup that grows plants in clear water instead of soil. Watching the fine roots drift in the water, even the air in the room feels a touch more moist. A little green well, pooled upon the desk."},"ICON-1881":{"nm":"Dream Fragment Collecting Bottle","on":"bottle","de":"Dreams spilled in slumber have no form, and once you wake they leak through your fingers. To stop one fragment about to vanish with the cap, holding it until morning, the wish to remember begins in a place this small."},"ICON-1882":{"nm":"Bedside Glasses Tray","on":"tray","de":"The moment you take off your glasses and set them down, oddly, a day's fatigue comes down with them. This little spot at your bedside is there to receive that one motion. A tray that quietly blurs the world before sleep."},"ICON-1883":{"nm":"Nightstand Coaster Ring","on":"ring","de":"A single round mark left by a water cup may seem trivial, but to the nightstand's wood grain it is a blemish. A little ring fitted to prevent it. A cherishing heart always works quietly in these unseen places."},"ICON-1884":{"nm":"Duvet Folding Squarer","on":"duvet folding squarer","de":"Even folding a duvet square and neat has its grain. Align the corners along this corner-setting tool and even a rumpled heart gets smoothed once. A tidied space is the most proper greeting to open the day."},"ICON-1885":{"nm":"Bedside Charging Cable Hook","on":"hook","de":"A hook hung at the bedside because I hated how the charging cable slips down to the floor through the night. The cable that quietly fills with power while you sleep waits, fully charged, for your fingertips in the morning."},"ICON-1886":{"nm":"Bedside Snack Basket","on":"basket","de":"A basket gathering favorite snacks within arm's reach. A kind preparation made in foresight of a late-night hunger. The rustling sound of picking one in the dark is somehow endearing."},"ICON-1887":{"nm":"Bedtime Book Holder Wing","on":"bedtime book holder wing","de":"A wing that gently props the open page so you won't lose your line even as drowsiness rolls in. The one page you closed just before your eyes shut waits for you in the same place tomorrow night."},"ICON-1888":{"nm":"Bedside Alarm Stone Base","on":"base","de":"Even the alarm clock that wakes the morning needs a place of its own that won't wobble. The round stone base takes its weight heavily and holds its spot like a promise that won't slip even when dawn comes."},"ICON-1889":{"nm":"Sleep Mask Hanging Nail","on":"sleep mask hanging nail","de":"A nail to hang the sleep mask, so the cloth that blocked the light all night can breathe through the day. Giving a dry spot to fabric that has done its duty: small care seeps in this spotlessly."},"ICON-1890":{"nm":"Bedside Flashlight Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clip that holds the little light you need at midnight toward whichever side you want. Bite the flashlight onto the edge of the bed and the hand that groped through the dark grows far more at ease. A touch that sets the direction of light."},"ICON-1891":{"nm":"Partition Curtain Tieback Cord","on":"cord","de":"A tieback cord that holds the curtain dividing a shared space. It's only a thin sheet of cloth, but beyond it is someone's private night. A kind boundary that guards each other's sleep in a shared room."},"ICON-1892":{"nm":"Shared Outlet Splitter Board","on":"board","de":"A wooden board made so many can share the single outlet. It spreads the electricity evenly so no one's night goes dark. Living together begins, after all, with sharing the small things like this."},"ICON-1893":{"nm":"Light Dimming Yield Stone","on":"light dimming yield stone","de":"When the light is too bright, you slip over a stone instead of words. \"Could you turn it down a little?\" This small thing conveys that single line for you. The gentlest request in a shared room."},"ICON-1894":{"nm":"Wake-Up Time Yield Token","on":"token","de":"A little token passed onto the palm of whoever rises first. Who gets more dawn sleep and who wakes earlier, this token decides without a quarrel. The heart that settles the order of yielding by fingertip."},"ICON-1895":{"nm":"Shared Hanger Number Ring","on":"ring","de":"Number rings assigned to hangers shared by many. So no one is confused about whose spot is whose, a single small number quietly makes order. A kind line drawn into a daily life easily mixed up."},"ICON-1896":{"nm":"Bunk Bed Step Cap","on":"cap","de":"A cap fitted over the step that climbs to the upper bunk. So a bare foot touching it is neither cold nor slippery, it looks after the safety of one rung. This small care at the ladder's end firmly supports the dreams up above."},"ICON-1897":{"nm":"Shared Tissue Holder Arm","on":"shared tissue holder arm","de":"An arm-shaped holder for hanging the shared bathroom's tissue. It's positioned so anyone can easily pull a sheet with one hand. It may seem trivial, but it's a touch that smooths many people's mornings."},"ICON-1898":{"nm":"Air Freshener Turn Chip","on":"chip","de":"A chip noting whose turn it is to refill the air freshener. Even a faint thread of fragrance is a promise to take responsibility for in turns. A good scent doesn't come for free; it blooms on someone's turn."},"ICON-1899":{"nm":"Shared Night Light Handle","on":"handle","de":"The handle of a night light that many turn on and off together. The hand that stayed awake the latest gathers in the light last. A quiet promise of those sharing a room, passing around a soft glow."},"ICON-1900":{"nm":"Sofa Armrest Cup Well","on":"sofa armrest cup well","de":"A round cup spot carved into the sofa armrest. You can set the glass down for a moment without worrying about spilling. A resting spot needs a place to put a glass before the heart can truly stretch out at ease."},"ICON-1901":{"nm":"Cushion Insert Zipper Pull","on":"pull","de":"A little pull attached to the zipper that opens and closes the cushion insert. One ring eases the trouble of changing the wash. Tending even to the unseen inside: the kindness of homemaking always hides there."},"ICON-1902":{"nm":"Sofa Backrest Wedge Cushion","on":"sofa backrest wedge cushion","de":"A cushion that fills the gap in the backrest and supports the lower back. It fills the empty space so your back won't ache even after sitting long. The comfort your body recognizes first, sighing \"ah, this is it,\" the moment you lean back."},"ICON-1903":{"nm":"Seat Cushion Corner Band","on":"band","de":"A band that grips the cushion at the corners, the one that used to creep along every time you sat. It fixes it in one spot so it won't slide. Neatness begins from such small, tenacious fastening."},"ICON-1904":{"nm":"Cushion Seam Guard Strip","on":"strip","de":"The first place a cushion wears out is always the corner seam. A guard strip wrapped around that spot in advance, keeping it from bursting. A heart wishing to keep it near for long, as sturdy as stitching."},"ICON-1905":{"nm":"Sofa Crevice Remote Pocket","on":"pocket","de":"The remote that kept vanishing between the cushions finally has a home of its own. A little pocket tucked into the sofa's crevice. Knowing that what you thought was lost is always right there is a bigger reassurance than you'd expect."},"ICON-1906":{"nm":"Lap Blanket Roll Cord","on":"cord","de":"A cord for rolling up and tying a lap blanket. Warmth that scatters when left spread out is tidied away neatly for the next night. Tucked away like this, even warmth can be pulled out and pulled over again tomorrow."},"ICON-1907":{"nm":"Footrest Cover Button","on":"button","de":"A button that fastens the footrest cover, the part that wears out fastest from feet touching it, so it's easy to swap. That one click of the snap extends the cloth's life. A heart wishing to use things long is thorough in the small details."},"ICON-1908":{"nm":"Sofa Leg Glide Cap","on":"sofa leg glide cap","de":"Even a heavy sofa mustn't scratch the floor. A soft cap fitted over the four leg ends tiptoes carefully to spare the wooden floor. Furniture careful down to its feet somehow earns more affection."},"ICON-1909":{"nm":"Remote Holder Stand","on":"remote holder stand","de":"A stand that lines up, side by side in one place, the remotes that used to roll and scatter every which way. When the long and short sticks stand neatly in a row, that alone settles the air of the room a tone calmer."},"ICON-1910":{"nm":"Game Pad Charging Hook","on":"game pad charging hook","de":"A hook to hang and charge the game pad after a rousing round of play. While it hangs and quietly refills its energy, your hands rest a moment too. This one short pause firmly readies the next match."},"ICON-1911":{"nm":"Board Game Piece Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A little pouch holding pieces of every color. The pieces waiting inside one bag for the next round rattle whenever you shake it. At that sound, the thrill of \"one more round?\" wakes first."},"ICON-1912":{"nm":"Dice Rolling Dish","on":"dish","de":"A dish made just for rolling dice. Luck that used to bounce off the table and vanish, the rim keeps inside. In that brief moment as they roll and stop, everyone's breath catches together for an instant."},"ICON-1913":{"nm":"Card Deck Holding Band","on":"band","de":"A band that binds a deck of cards so they won't scatter. Until they're shuffled, that order is itself a promise. In the gesture of slipping off the band to spread the cards, a round's story finally begins."},"ICON-1914":{"nm":"Console Cable Tidy Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clip that grips and combs down the tangled cables behind the console. It silently tidies the clutter in a spot you can barely even see. Tidiness is always completed quietly, like this, from behind."},"ICON-1915":{"nm":"Score Dial","on":"dial","de":"A little dial you turn to show the score. Click, with each notch the number rises, and cheers follow along. Even without counting in your head, your fingertips remember that day's match first."},"ICON-1916":{"nm":"Board Standing Base","on":"base","de":"A base that props the board at a slant, setting the angle so everyone seated around can see the board at a glance. So no one has to crane their neck, it quietly lays out a fair view for all."},"ICON-1917":{"nm":"Turn Order Draw Cup","on":"cup","de":"A cup you slip your hand into to draw for game order. The one stick you grope for and grab decides who goes first. In that brief moment of leaning a little on luck, everyone flutters together inside the round cup."},"ICON-1918":{"nm":"Sharing Snack Divided Dish","on":"dish","de":"A divided dish for serving snacks by kind. Split into sections, you can pick your favorite without hands bumping. The care that counted in those who'd share is held in every compartment."},"ICON-1919":{"nm":"Teapot Cozy","on":"teapot cozy","de":"A cozy that wraps the teapot's shoulders to keep its warmth. It swaddles it so the tea won't cool while it slowly steeps. The fingertip's wish to serve a warm cup warm to the very end."},"ICON-1920":{"nm":"Tea Bag Rest","on":"rest","de":"A rest where a steeped tea bag is lifted out and set to pause a while. It catches even the last drop so none is spilled. A spot offering even a leaf that's done its part a tidy ending."},"ICON-1921":{"nm":"Shared Mug Marker Ring","on":"ring","de":"Six identical mugs on the break room shelf. Instead of asking whose is whose, we slipped on rings of different colors. One small mark quietly ties six people, each with their own taste, to one place at the same table."},"ICON-1922":{"nm":"Popcorn Sharing Basket","on":"basket","de":"As it passes from hand to hand, the savory steam greets you first. If there's something that oddly doesn't dwindle the more you scoop out by the handful, it must be the heart of an evening shared sitting together."},"ICON-1923":{"nm":"Sugar Cube Tongs Holder","on":"holder","de":"Tap a cube of sugar with the tongs into the teacup. Watching the white corners slowly dissolve and vanish: an unhurried etiquette of sweetness, first learned at Grandma's tea table."},"ICON-1924":{"nm":"Tray Anti-Slip Mat","on":"tray anti-slip mat","de":"Even if the tray tilts, the cups keep their place. As things that steadily hold from below always do, the mat alone endures the moment of a near-slip and, in the end, keeps its mouth shut."},"ICON-1925":{"nm":"Drink Straw Stand Cup","on":"cup","de":"Stand the straw upright and neither the drink nor the heart falls into disarray. On an afternoon when the desk turns tidy from one small uprightness, the cup holds a little pillar and quietly props up the languid hours."},"ICON-1926":{"nm":"Cookie Crumb Catcher","on":"cookie crumb catcher","de":"Crisp, the moment a cookie crumbles, the fallen pieces gather here. To take in even the traces left by the tastiest bite: the table's quiet finishing touch, kind even to the last crumb."},"ICON-1927":{"nm":"Photo Clip Hanging Line","on":"line","de":"Pin Polaroids one by one with clips onto a line strung like a clothesline. While today's smiles flutter and dry in the breeze, one stretch of wall becomes a small, bright exhibition of memories."},"ICON-1928":{"nm":"Memory Skein Spool","on":"memory skein spool","de":"A spool with tangled thread untangled and wound neatly. The things carried on, knotted at every snapped place. If you slowly rewind memory like this, a round at a time, a path you thought had shortened lengthens again."},"ICON-1929":{"nm":"Wall Hook Nail Cover","on":"wall hook nail cover","de":"A small round cover that hides a nail hole. Gently cover even the little scar left after taking down what once hung there, and the wall returns to a smooth face as if nothing had happened."},"ICON-1930":{"nm":"Group Photo Insert Frame","on":"group photo insert frame","de":"A group photo of six taken with shoulders pressed close. The moment you slip it into the frame, that day's laughter and warmth are sealed in together. A frame is the hand that most quietly stops a passing day."},"ICON-1931":{"nm":"Memo Cork Board","on":"board","de":"A brown board crowded with pushpin marks. A promise you mustn't forget, someone's note of encouragement, today's to-dos all pin in layer upon layer. A dependable wall by the desk that remembers in your head's place."},"ICON-1932":{"nm":"Wreath Hanging Knot","on":"wreath hanging knot","de":"Even a wreath hung on the door takes the skill of fingertips. The knot must be tied tight so it won't fall in the windy season. The heart that welcomes someone always grows firm from an unseen place first."},"ICON-1933":{"nm":"Wall Clock Pendulum Cover","on":"cover","de":"A cloth cover wrapping the ticking pendulum to keep off dust. Even the work of measuring time receives care like this. Protect it gently from wearing out, and the wall clock stays by our side a little longer."},"ICON-1934":{"nm":"Sticker Collection Board","on":"board","de":"Stickers that used to scatter through every drawer gather on one board and line up. A favorite character, a glittering star, a sheet of handwriting. When the small joy of collecting is neatly aligned, even the heart turns orderly."},"ICON-1935":{"nm":"Bunting Connecting Cord","on":"cord","de":"A cord that joins colorful flags into one line. Birthday or welcome, the moment the cord crosses the ceiling, an ordinary room turns into a party house. Celebrating is the work of joining and stitching together a broken heart."},"ICON-1936":{"nm":"Electric Kettle Cork Trivet","on":"electric kettle cork trivet","de":"A single sheet of cork supporting the hot kettle's base. So the table won't scorch, it embraces that heat alone. A small kindness that steadily props it up so no one's warmth is left as a mark."},"ICON-1937":{"nm":"Toaster Crumb Tray","on":"tray","de":"The crumbs dropped by golden-toasted bread tumble down onto the tray. Just slide it out and shake it off, done. It wordlessly receives the bustling morning and readies itself clean again for the next meal."},"ICON-1938":{"nm":"Microwave Turntable Ring","on":"ring","de":"On the spinning ring, the plate slowly traces one full circle. That rotation, turned so it heats evenly, revives yesterday's rice gone cold into a meal steaming hot once more."},"ICON-1939":{"nm":"Mini Induction Burner Cover","on":"mini induction burner cover","de":"However the oil splatters in all directions, the burner stays clean. One cover divides the fierce heat from your hands. The things that stand in the way unseen keep the kitchen a place that won't get scorched."},"ICON-1940":{"nm":"Rice Cooker Steam Cap","on":"cap","de":"The sound of steam hissing out, ssss. Thanks to a little cap that gently releases the held pressure, freshly cooked rice opens its lid with the softest face. There's no rushing the time of letting it steam."},"ICON-1941":{"nm":"Ladle Stand Holder","on":"holder","de":"Stand the soup-stirring ladle upright. A small heart wishing not to spill a single stain on the counter. The kitchen's neatness always begins from these inconspicuous, trivial spots."},"ICON-1942":{"nm":"Pot Handle Silicone Grip","on":"pot handle silicone grip","de":"Fit the silicone onto a scorching pot handle and your hand won't burn. One layer slipping between the heat and your palm. It guards the one cooking warm meals, from the very closest place."},"ICON-1943":{"nm":"Electric Kettle Limescale Filter","on":"electric kettle limescale filter","de":"Even water boiled daily builds up a faint trace. A fine mesh quietly filters the limescale and pours out only a clear cup. A diligent hand that guards the first sip of tea from an unseen place."},"ICON-1944":{"nm":"Cooking Timer Clip Legs","on":"cooking timer clip legs","de":"Three more minutes, says the timer, biting the table edge tight with its clip legs. While the noodles cook, it stands braced on its little legs, ticking along to count the most awaited moment of the day."},"ICON-1945":{"nm":"Cutlery Drip Cup","on":"cup","de":"Water trickles down from freshly rinsed cutlery. When the drip cup quietly gathers that moisture, the table soon turns dry. Tidiness is a kind diligence that looks after even a single drop of water."},"ICON-1946":{"nm":"Plate Standing Divider Rack","on":"plate standing divider rack","de":"Stand the plates upright, divided into compartments. Dishes that used to scratch each other when stacked each get a spot of their own. Tidying is, in the end, giving everyone their own compartment where they won't collide."},"ICON-1947":{"nm":"Chopstick Pairing Ring","on":"ring","de":"Thread the chopsticks that were left lonely without their match onto the ring and pair the two again. Since a single stick soon loses its use, this little ring keeps order in the drawer by binding them side by side."},"ICON-1948":{"nm":"Branching Cup Tree","on":"branching cup tree","de":"Hang the cups one by one on a stand that branches out like limbs. While the moisture dries on each upturned glass, a corner of the kitchen stands quietly like a small, neat tree."},"ICON-1949":{"nm":"Cutlery Tray Handle","on":"handle","de":"A tray where spoons, chopsticks, and forks lie side by side in compartments. Grab the handle and lift the whole thing out, and setting the table grows much lighter. The aesthetics of order live in the drawer too, without fail."},"ICON-1950":{"nm":"Water Cup Drip-Dry Board","on":"board","de":"Set the washed cups upside down and the water drops fall, drip, drip. While they slowly dry by a sunlit window, the glass calmly regains its first transparency for the next sip."},"ICON-1951":{"nm":"Fork-Gap Tidy Comb","on":"comb","de":"Its fine teeth gently sweep food from between the tines of a fork. Thanks to a touch that tends even the narrowest crevices, the next meal always begins with a flawless, spotless first bite."},"ICON-1952":{"nm":"Anti-Slip Stacking Felt","on":"anti-slip stacking felt","de":"Stack bowls and the porcelain clinks sharply against itself. A single sheet of felt tucked between them quiets that friction. The secret to a long life together is leaving each other a little softer."},"ICON-1953":{"nm":"Teaspoon Hanging Loop Cord","on":"cord","de":"Hang the dainty teaspoon from the loop and fix it to the wall. Never buried in a drawer, it glints in easy reach—a small tool proudly claiming its rightful spot. Even housework has a home for everything."},"ICON-1954":{"nm":"Fridge Compartment Tray","on":"tray","de":"Divide the fridge into sections and each ingredient gets its own little house. Things once jumbled and forgotten find their place, and every time you open the door you can see at a glance what is where."},"ICON-1955":{"nm":"Freezer Bag Standing Clip","on":"clip","de":"Grip a half-empty freezer bag with the clip and stand it upright. So it won't topple and spill, so it's easy to find next time. Even in the cold freezer dwells the shrewd, tidy wisdom of a capable homemaker."},"ICON-1956":{"nm":"Bottle Cap Tightener","on":"cap","de":"A bottle left loosely closed soon goes flat. That one twist of the wrist, tightening the cap firmly, locks the scent and fizz inside intact until tomorrow morning. Diligence shines in the small things."},"ICON-1957":{"nm":"Egg Tray Non-Slip Mat","on":"egg tray non-slip mat","de":"A liner that cradles round eggs in compartments so they won't roll away and crack. The wish to handle the most fragile things with the most care sits small and tender in one corner of the fridge door."},"ICON-1958":{"nm":"Fridge Door Pocket Extender","on":"band","de":"Stretch the fridge door pocket slightly sideways to make one more slot. As the household grows, its space must grow too. In the skill of widening a tight spot, a capable homemaker's heart is reflected."},"ICON-1959":{"nm":"Leftover Pressing Lid","on":"leftover pressing lid","de":"A lid pressed gently over leftover side dishes. It quietly guards them so they won't dry out or pick up other smells. A caring hand carefully puts away even what's left of a single meal."},"ICON-1960":{"nm":"Cold-Air Direction Vane","on":"cold-air direction vane","de":"Which way will the cold air flow? A small vane quietly sets the direction. Nudge the unseen path of the breeze with your fingertip, and the chill reaches even the deepest inner corner."},"ICON-1961":{"nm":"Crisper Moisture Pad","on":"pad","de":"In the darkest corner of the fridge crisper, I silently hold the moisture. The small miracle of yesterday's wilted leaf turning crisp again by morning. Though no one knows it, freshness is always my charge."},"ICON-1962":{"nm":"Soda Can Roll-Stop Ridge","on":"soda can roll-stop ridge","de":"Stuck quietly to the table's edge, it catches the foot of a can about to roll away. A drink almost spilled, a table almost wiped. The peace of mind in housework begins with a small, unnoticed ridge like this."},"ICON-1963":{"nm":"Chore Rotation Dial","on":"dial","de":"Today, who does the dishes, who sorts the recycling. One spin of the arrow and every squabble rolls smoothly away. In a house where five jostle together, taking turns is the kindest kind of peace."},"ICON-1964":{"nm":"Member Cup Silicone Band","on":"band","de":"Five lookalike cups, and a morning of wondering whose is whose. Slip on a wrist-sized colored band and the little promise of \"this one is mine\" rings clear, gracing the breakfast table with gentle order."},"ICON-1965":{"nm":"Portion Bowl Ring","on":"ring","de":"On a busy day, the markings inside the bowl become a reliable friend. One section for rice, one for sides. Neither too little nor too much, a gentle line quietly tells you just how much to eat today."},"ICON-1966":{"nm":"Snack-Sharing Tong Tub","on":"tub","de":"Shove in the whole bag and the spot your hand touched is left over, awkward. Portion it out one by one with tongs and only then does everyone's share come out even. Sharing suits tidy hands more than handfuls."},"ICON-1967":{"nm":"Kettle Duty Nameplate Holder","on":"kettle duty nameplate holder","de":"Boiling the water always fell to the same hands. Since we began hanging name tags in turn on the holder beside the kettle, a warm cup of tea became affection brewed by rotation."},"ICON-1968":{"nm":"Clean-Plate Spatula Chip","on":"chip","de":"A little \"don't leave any\" hangs from the tip of the spatula. It may sound like nagging, but there's nothing hateful in it—because the spirit of the old table, where every meal was treasured, lives here."},"ICON-1969":{"nm":"Personal Cutlery Pouch Hook","on":"personal cutlery pouch hook","de":"Cutlery no longer rattles loose in the drawer. The moment each set goes into its own pouch and hangs on the wall, five family members' places line up side by side. A small tidiness props up each day's peace."},"ICON-1970":{"nm":"Table Seat Cork Chip","on":"chip","de":"Lay cork pieces on the table and it's clear who sits where. The seat you always take, the side face you always face. An assigned place is the quietest proof of the words \"we live together.\""},"ICON-1971":{"nm":"Duty Apron Roll Hook","on":"hook","de":"The apron finished with the dishes isn't tossed just anywhere. Rolled up and hung on the hook, it's ready fresh for the next morning's reach. A heart that thinks of the next person lives in this little knot."},"ICON-1972":{"nm":"Disposable Slipper Fold Bag","on":"disposable slipper fold bag","de":"On the day guests arrive, I unfold bag and all. The disposable slippers tucked neatly inside greet newly arrived feet with cushioned warmth. Hospitality always begins quietly at the entrance."},"ICON-1973":{"nm":"Cotton-Swab Paper-Tail Pocket","on":"cotton-swab paper-tail pocket","de":"When the swabs are used up and only the paper tails remain, I gather their ends tidily. Making room even for what would be thrown away. I know the secret of a neat desk is small kindnesses like this."},"ICON-1974":{"nm":"Sewing Kit Spool Bundle","on":"sewing kit spool bundle","de":"Bundle the colored threads together so the spools won't unravel and tangle. A fallen button, a loosened cuff—this one bundle mends them in no time. Hand-stitching that quietly saves the eve of an important day."},"ICON-1975":{"nm":"Single-Wrapped Soap Piece","on":"single-wrapped soap piece","de":"A neatly individually wrapped piece of soap is set in every guest room. A palm-sized body washes away the day's dust with a single handful of lather. Cleanliness always begins in small places like this."},"ICON-1976":{"nm":"Shower Cap Folding Capsule","on":"shower cap folding capsule","de":"Fold the pleats and it tucks into your palm; open it and it wraps your hair snug. So a styled head won't collapse with one shower. This single layer guards tomorrow morning's tidiness."},"ICON-1977":{"nm":"Toothbrush Protective Sleeve","on":"toothbrush protective sleeve","de":"Bristles are more delicate than you'd think. One sleeve over their tips keeps even bag dust from reaching them. Guarding the unseen places—the real work of hygiene, learned on every trip."},"ICON-1978":{"nm":"Cotton-Pad Single-Pull Tongs","on":"tongs","de":"Cotton pads come out clean only when picked one at a time. Spill them all out and more get wasted. \"One at a time, with care\"—this is the quiet rule atop the vanity."},"ICON-1979":{"nm":"Mini Folding Shoehorn","on":"mini folding shoehorn","de":"Folded, it's in your pocket; opened, at your heel. I take pride in doing a fairly big job with my little body. Even on an oversleeping morning, it was always me who let you slip on your shoes unspoiled."},"ICON-1980":{"nm":"Single Floss Winder","on":"single floss winder","de":"Wind one strand of floss neatly and snip off just what you need when the time comes. A winder no bigger than a fingernail, yet never absent from the work of guarding a bright smile. Even a smile has unseen preparation."},"ICON-1981":{"nm":"Electric Kettle Lid Handle","on":"handle","de":"So the steam of boiling water won't burn your hand, I clip onto the lid. A hand's breadth between the heat and your palm. That small distance safely warms someone's busy morning."},"ICON-1982":{"nm":"Iron Rest Silicone Pad","on":"pad","de":"The most dangerous moment is when you briefly set the iron down mid-press. Stand it on the silicone pad and neither table nor clothes get scorched. Smoothing wrinkles is finished only atop the rest."},"ICON-1983":{"nm":"Anti-Theft Hanger Hook","on":"hook","de":"So a hung garment won't carelessly slip off, the hook clamps its mouth shut tight. A small sentinel guarding the cherished outfit in the closet. To protect is a quiet thing, like this."},"ICON-1984":{"nm":"Kettle Limescale Strainer","on":"kettle limescale strainer","de":"My job is to quietly strain out the limescale drifting in the boiling water. Only after filtering even unseen sediment does a cup of tea turn clear. Devotion always brews in the places no one sees."},"ICON-1985":{"nm":"Hanger Non-Slip Strip","on":"strip","de":"A hanger wrapped with a non-slip strip won't drop even light silk. Anyone who has once seen a garment fall to the floor and crumple knows the gratitude of this single thin line."},"ICON-1986":{"nm":"Iron Cord Tidy Clip","on":"clip","de":"A loose cord trips feet and sends someone stumbling. One touch of the hand to bind it neatly with a clip. Preventing accidents always starts from small, trivial tidying like this."},"ICON-1987":{"nm":"Electric Kettle Base Cup Slot","on":"electric kettle base cup slot","de":"I seat the kettle snug in my slot so it won't wobble. To be in its proper place is to be at ease. There's a reason warm water is heated in the same spot every morning."},"ICON-1988":{"nm":"Trouser Hanger Clip Legs","on":"trouser hanger clip legs","de":"When the clip legs grip the trouser hem firmly, not a single wrinkle forms. A well-pressed outfit is treated well from the moment it hangs. A clean fit is finished inside the closet."},"ICON-1989":{"nm":"Hair Dryer Hanging Hook","on":"hook","de":"Leave the dryer just anywhere and the cord soon tangles. Hang it on the hook and the sink widens, tomorrow morning grows lighter. A tidy spot gently eases a busy day."},"ICON-1990":{"nm":"Minibar Drink Coaster","on":"minibar drink coaster","de":"Rest it quietly under the glass and the droplets won't spread across the table. The thoughtfulness of a single coaster leaves no ring behind. Tidiness is the kindness of leaving no trace."},"ICON-1991":{"nm":"Do-Not-Disturb Door Sign","on":"do-not-disturb door sign","de":"A sign hung on the doorknob softly whispers \"resting now.\" Guarding one breath of a nap at the end of a long day. Even a pause needs someone to tend it with care."},"ICON-1992":{"nm":"Room Service Call Button Cap","on":"cap","de":"Thanks to the cap wrapping the button, even a brushing sleeve won't press it by accident. So you call clearly only when truly needed. One small cover keeps a busy guest room that much tidier."},"ICON-1993":{"nm":"Minibar Ice Tong Legs","on":"minibar ice tong legs","de":"Grab ice barehanded and it's cold and keeps slipping. The tong legs take on that job firmly instead. Hidden behind the start of a cool drink is an unseen helping hand."},"ICON-1994":{"nm":"Room Key Card Slot","on":"room key card slot","de":"Slip the card into the slot and the room's lights pop on. I'm only a small slit, but I'm the first gesture that opens a space to lay down the day's fatigue. The lights come on again at the place you return to."},"ICON-1995":{"nm":"Bottle-Neck Seal Ring","on":"ring","de":"If the seal ring on the bottle's neck is intact, it means no one has touched it yet. A small promise proving it's just as it was. Trust begins with an unbroken seal."},"ICON-1996":{"nm":"Brochure Standing Stand","on":"stand","de":"Stand the brochure at a slant and passing eyes linger of their own accord. The demure posture of information waiting to be opened. Simply keeping it visible makes someone's path that much easier."},"ICON-1997":{"nm":"Minibar Bottle-Opener Flat Chip","on":"chip","de":"Tucked discreetly in a corner of its flat body is a notch for popping bottle caps. Small as it is, it does its job cleanly. The cool first sip of a bottled drink always opens with this little chip."},"ICON-1998":{"nm":"Light Dimmer Knob Cover","on":"light dimmer knob cover","de":"Gently turn the covered knob and the room's brightness slowly shifts. Bright, then soft. Choosing the light at bedtime is a ritual that closes the day with kindness."},"ICON-1999":{"nm":"Suitcase Wheel Stop Wedge","on":"wedge","de":"Slip it under the wheel and the suitcase won't roll off on its own. Even on a sloped station platform, the luggage holds its place. The peace of mind on a departing journey grows firm from this small wedge."},"ICON-2000":{"nm":"Travel Packing Fold Board","on":"board","de":"Lay a shirt or trousers on it and they fold crisp and neat. So the bag's insides won't collapse, so you can step out unwrinkled in the arriving city. Well-packed luggage helps the trip even before you leave."},"ICON-2001":{"nm":"Room Safe Lock Knob","on":"knob","de":"Turn the knob and a small bolt slides inward. Entrusting your valuables is the promise to set your heart fully at ease, just for one night. The lock stands there not as anxiety, but as another name for peace of mind."},"ICON-2002":{"nm":"Suitcase Handle Wrap","on":"suitcase handle wrap","de":"In every worn, hand-smudged spot, someone's departure is etched. Grip this wrap, worn as much as the miles it was dragged, and you quietly come to know that leaving is, after all, a word that holds returning."},"ICON-2003":{"nm":"Travel Pouch Hanging Clip","on":"clip","de":"Hang the pouch on the edge of the sink and the cramped room gains a hand's width. That order in a bag begins with one small clip—the hand that has traveled far already knows this."},"ICON-2004":{"nm":"Charger Multi-Plug Clip","on":"clip","de":"Gather several cables into one outlet. On a night waiting for the charge to fill, here is a small hand that gently holds the scattered cords together in one place."},"ICON-2005":{"nm":"Suitcase Name Tag Loop Strap","on":"strap","de":"Among identical black bags, one strand of strap lets you spot yours. To hang a name is a tender mark that this luggage has a way back to someone."},"ICON-2006":{"nm":"Room Wall Charge-Cord Holder Board","on":"board","de":"A small board on the wall by the bed's head props the charging cord up neatly. On the first night in an unfamiliar room, when one familiar light comes on, even that place becomes home for a while."},"ICON-2007":{"nm":"Luggage Stand Folding Legs","on":"luggage stand folding legs","de":"Unfold the folded legs and the bag lifts a hand's width off the dusty floor. A trunk set down still unpacked quietly holds an unfinished journey, awaiting the next morning."},"ICON-2008":{"nm":"Key Card Slot","on":"key card slot","de":"The card must be inserted for the room's lights to come on. Light that shines only while you stay—a traveler's day is warmed by exactly the brightness this small slot allows."},"ICON-2009":{"nm":"Key Card Strap Loop","on":"loop","de":"Hang the single card around your neck and both hands go free. Tying the worry of loss to one strap is a small cleverness handed down long by travelers with heavy bags."},"ICON-2010":{"nm":"Front Desk Call Bell Button","on":"button","de":"Press it and somewhere at the front desk a clear chime rings out. So that asking for help is never embarrassing, the bell always sits kindly within one reach of the hand."},"ICON-2011":{"nm":"Check-In Number Clip","on":"clip","de":"Pick up the queue-number slip received at the end of the line and fasten it. That even waiting has its turn—order grows from a small promise to quietly cherish each other's time."},"ICON-2012":{"nm":"Room Key Tassel","on":"room key tassel","de":"A tassel hanging from the key's end sways with every step. The heart that slips a touch of charm into usefulness is shown only by those who know the joy of the fingertips."},"ICON-2013":{"nm":"Front Desk Doorbell Cover","on":"front desk doorbell cover","de":"Set the cover over the doorbell and the midday hush goes unbroken. A small thoughtfulness to guard someone's deep sleep—even quiet is something someone made with care."},"ICON-2014":{"nm":"Room Number Door Tag","on":"room number door tag","de":"A note hung on the doorknob bears the room number clearly. A few digits set the place I'll return to tonight, and in an unfamiliar hallway it becomes a small lighthouse."},"ICON-2015":{"nm":"Key Card Magnetic Strip","on":"strip","de":"Hold the black strip to the door's seam and the lock slips open. An age when an unseen signal opens a door—what once felt like magic has now settled into everyday life in the palm of your hand."},"ICON-2016":{"nm":"Check-In Stamp Rest","on":"rest","de":"Each time the stamp falls, the rest takes the ink evenly. So that the single stroke of confirmation stays clear, there is a hand that silently supports from an unseen place."},"ICON-2017":{"nm":"Luggage Cart Hanging Bar","on":"bar","de":"One bar on the luggage cart holds the garment bag up without a wrinkle. To the things that carry a heavy day in our stead, sometimes you want to offer a word of thanks."},"ICON-2018":{"nm":"Trunk Handle Tag","on":"tag","de":"Hang a small tag on the trunk handle. As long as the name field stays blank, a flutter of excitement remains—this bag's next destination is not yet decided."},"ICON-2019":{"nm":"Luggage Cart Wheel Lock Wedge","on":"wedge","de":"Prop a wedge under the wheel so the cart won't roll on a slope. The work of guarding stillness is, at times, the most dependable other face of safety."},"ICON-2020":{"nm":"Luggage Strap Buckle","on":"luggage strap buckle","de":"Cinch the strap tight so a bag swollen with travel things won't burst. Even when the road ends, the volume of memories doesn't shrink, so the buckle holds that weight to the very end."},"ICON-2021":{"nm":"Luggage Cart Hook Cover","on":"cover","de":"The cover over the cart hook leaves not a single mark on the clothes. A heart that anticipates even unseen scratches—good hospitality is finished in such small places."},"ICON-2022":{"nm":"Suitcase Name-Tag Pocket","on":"pocket","de":"A small pocket on the bag's side cradles a name tag. Writing down whose it is, is like inscribing in advance the right to meet again even if it's lost."},"ICON-2023":{"nm":"Luggage Glove Clip","on":"clip","de":"When carrying heavy loads, the clip grips the gloves firmly so they won't slip off. Protecting the hands and doing the job well come, in the end, from one and the same heart."},"ICON-2024":{"nm":"Luggage Net Cover","on":"luggage net cover","de":"Drape the net over and the small bits of luggage won't scatter in every direction. Each tight little mesh keeps from losing the small things amid the bustle of moving."},"ICON-2025":{"nm":"Luggage Cart Memo Holder","on":"luggage cart memo holder","de":"A memo tucked into the cart handle bears the room number. The habit of writing down where to go—the busier the hands, the more they quietly lean on a single line of writing."},"ICON-2026":{"nm":"Tray Plate Cover Dome","on":"tray plate cover dome","de":"Lift the silver dome and steam rises all at once. The heart that covers food to keep it from going cold is devotion itself, the wish to hand over warmth just as it is."},"ICON-2027":{"nm":"Do-Not-Disturb Doorknob Plate","on":"plate","de":"Hang this plate on the doorknob and even footsteps in the hall grow careful. The single phrase \"do not wake me\"—rest, too, becomes whole only when someone guards it."},"ICON-2028":{"nm":"Room Service Paper Napkin Ring","on":"ring","de":"Slip the paper napkin into the round ring to set a tidy shape. The grace of a meal begins with this little loop—care shows itself most clearly in the smallest things."},"ICON-2029":{"nm":"Tray Non-Slip Mat","on":"mat","de":"Lay a mat on the tray and the dishes won't slip. Keeping them in place even amid the sway—even quiet stability holds someone's careful design."},"ICON-2030":{"nm":"Breakfast Order Door Tag","on":"tag","de":"Hang the breakfast order tag on the doorknob and tomorrow morning is promised in advance. Writing down the first meal tonight is yet another face of kind anticipation."},"ICON-2031":{"nm":"Tray Leg Stand","on":"stand","de":"Unfold the tray's legs and even atop the bed it becomes a proper table. A morning spread received where you lie—a small stand turns an ordinary room into a luxurious scene."},"ICON-2032":{"nm":"Teapot Cozy Cover","on":"teapot cozy cover","de":"Drape a cozy over the teapot and the water's warmth lingers long. Like the old nights gathered round the hearth, the wish to keep warmth knows no era."},"ICON-2033":{"nm":"Cleaning Request Door Tail","on":"cleaning request door tail","de":"Hang the cleaning-request tail on the doorknob to leave a wordless signal. A request conveyed without parting the lips—behind a tidy room lies the promise of an unseen hand."},"ICON-2034":{"nm":"Tray Condiment Holder","on":"holder","de":"The holder grips firmly so the condiment bottles won't topple. Keeping the balance of flavor even on a swaying tray is the silent duty of this one small fastening."},"ICON-2035":{"nm":"Reservation Memo Stand","on":"reservation memo stand","de":"Stand the reservation memos upright and the order reads at a glance. So even busy hands won't get confused, it's a small tool of order that holds a single sheet clearly upright."},"ICON-2036":{"nm":"Sightseeing Pin Map Board","on":"board","de":"Push pins into the map and mark one by one the places you want to go. Each pin a thrill not yet visited—travel begins the very moment you spread the map open."},"ICON-2037":{"nm":"Taxi Hail Flag Clip","on":"clip","de":"When hailing a taxi, a clip stands the small flag straight. A signal the flag calls out in place of a raised hand—on the street too, a call must be clear before it reaches."},"ICON-2038":{"nm":"Concierge Doorbell Handle","on":"handle","de":"Press the handle and a clear chime reaches the concierge desk. A signal of welcome that says ask anything you like—in an unfamiliar city, the most reassuring single call."},"ICON-2039":{"nm":"Reservation Number Clip Board","on":"board","de":"Clamp the reservation-number slip to the clipboard so it shows clearly. So the promised seat won't be mistaken, it's a small diligence that holds one line of digits neatly."},"ICON-2040":{"nm":"Tour Pamphlet Display Frame","on":"tour pamphlet display frame","de":"Set out the tour pamphlets and a traveler's hand stops of its own accord. In each sheet picked up one by one, the scenery of roads not yet taken lies quietly folded."},"ICON-2041":{"nm":"Map Stamp Rest","on":"rest","de":"For the first steps into the entrance, it holds the stamp box atop the map steady. When the ink doesn't smear, the way doesn't get confusing either. A spot that silently bears the weight so a small guide stands upright."},"ICON-2042":{"nm":"Umbrella Storage Tag","on":"tag","de":"On an afternoon when raindrops dripped from the eaves, hang one number on each umbrella. When someone who has returned after the rain comes to claim their own, the tag clearly calls up the damp memory."},"ICON-2043":{"nm":"Info Desk Call Bell Holder","on":"info desk call bell holder","de":"Ring it once, ding, and someone comes rushing brightly from the other side. The little bell hung on the desk's corner is the kindest interpreter, conveying even words you couldn't quite get out."},"ICON-2044":{"nm":"Shampoo Dispenser Nozzle","on":"shampoo dispenser nozzle","de":"Open your palm and press lightly, and foam blooms out with a poof. That one dispense as the scent spreads through the bathroom. The chime that wakes a drowsy morning most gently begins right here."},"ICON-2045":{"nm":"Soap Dish Drain Tray","on":"tray","de":"A tray that quietly lets the water pooled beneath the soap drain away. So it won't go soft, won't go mushy. A small, tender thoughtfulness to keep what wears away each day a hand's width longer at your side."},"ICON-2046":{"nm":"Bath Salt Scoop","on":"bath salt scoop","de":"Scoop a spoonful of powder and dissolve it in warm water, and color and scent slowly spread out. As you stir with your wrist, the tub becomes a little lake, and a day's fatigue sinks quietly within it."},"ICON-2047":{"nm":"Lather Net Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Trap a piece of soap in the net and rub, and soft lather rises to fill your palms. A quiet alchemist in one corner of the bathroom, turning the coarse into the gentle."},"ICON-2048":{"nm":"Toothbrush Sanitizing Cap","on":"cap","de":"The wish that what touches the mouth always stay clean. One small cap softly wrapping the bristle tips tends even the unseen places. Cleanliness is made of such small things, stacked up."},"ICON-2049":{"nm":"Swab Tub Lid","on":"lid","de":"A tub where white sticks lie neatly, and a lid that rounds over the top. Open with a pop, close with a click. A tender period to the bathroom's tidiness, finished with a small sound."},"ICON-2050":{"nm":"Bath Oil Drop Bottle","on":"bottle","de":"Tilt it slightly and fragrant oil falls drop by drop. The sheen and faint scent spreading through the tub. Too humble to be luxury, too tender to be ordinary—a single drop."},"ICON-2051":{"nm":"Amenity Tray Divider","on":"amenity tray divider","de":"Across a tray divided into compartments, small bottles each find their place. Things that look cluttered scattered and tidy gathered. One divider keeps the order of a busy morning."},"ICON-2052":{"nm":"Sauna Hourglass Stand","on":"stand","de":"A tender promise to warm your back at least while the sand all runs down. As the hourglass tilted against its stand trickles out the time, in the thick steam a person rests a while, being no one at all."},"ICON-2053":{"nm":"Sheep-Ear Steam Towel","on":"sheep-ear steam towel","de":"Roll the towel's ends and stand them up perky like sheep ears, and the face in the mirror softly relaxes. Amid the hot steam, a small ritual of the sauna where anyone returns briefly to childhood."},"ICON-2054":{"nm":"Sauna Water Ladle","on":"sauna water ladle","de":"Scoop the ladle full and pour it over the heated stones—hiss—and steam shoots up to the ceiling. In that moment the whole body sinks into a warm mist, and old fatigue slowly unwinds in beads of sweat."},"ICON-2055":{"nm":"Foot Bath Temperature Rod","on":"rod","de":"Dip the rod in the water and the markings softly speak up. Neither too hot nor gone cold, just that temperature. Before dipping in your toes, the finger that first asks after the water's well-being."},"ICON-2056":{"nm":"Steam Stone Tongs","on":"tongs","de":"You can't grab a freshly heated stone barehanded. When the tongs grip it firmly and lift, the heat moves to a safe distance. Carefulness, too, is a skill, the sauna quietly says."},"ICON-2057":{"nm":"Sauna Cushion Mat","on":"sauna cushion mat","de":"Lay one on the hot floor and the spot your back touches grows softer. A mat that wordlessly receives a day soaked in sweat. Rest, after all, comes from the right distance from the floor."},"ICON-2058":{"nm":"Foot Bath Salt Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Hold a handful of coarse salt, dissolve it in warm water, and the weariness melts away from the toes up. As the briny steam wraps your calves, a day walked all through finally comes to a stop."},"ICON-2059":{"nm":"Sauna Scent Stone Dish","on":"dish","de":"Drop a few drops of perfume onto the heated stone and the warmed scent slowly spreads through the sauna. Close your eyes and is this a forest or a flower field? The shortest journey, taken through the nose."},"ICON-2060":{"nm":"Heat Pack Cozy Cover","on":"cover","de":"A cloth that wraps the warmed pack snugly to hold the heat long. Just like a heart that hugs it close lest it cool, the warmth resting on your belly keeps you company all night."},"ICON-2061":{"nm":"Aroma Diffuser Sticks","on":"aroma diffuser sticks","de":"Thin sticks draw up the scent and let it drift slowly through the room. A faint fragrance seeping in with each breath. The way a dwelling space gradually comes to resemble that person's scent."},"ICON-2062":{"nm":"Sun Lounger Angle Handle","on":"handle","de":"Turn the handle slowly and the backrest reclines smoothly. A little toward the sun, a little toward the shade. Feeling out the most comfortable angle is a calculation all your own."},"ICON-2063":{"nm":"Poolside Non-Slip Strip","on":"strip","de":"A non-slip strip ringing the water's edge all around. So little feet that come splashing and dashing in delight can stop safely, it's a hidden finish line of safety laid quietly out of sight."},"ICON-2064":{"nm":"Tube Air Valve Loop","on":"loop","de":"A loop carefully tied to the small valve that traps the air. So that the valve, once pulled from the tube, won't float away on the water. A wisdom that heads off a trivial midsummer loss in advance."},"ICON-2065":{"nm":"Pool Step Entry Cap","on":"cap","de":"A cap softly wrapping the end of the step leading down into the water. So bare soles won't get scraped, it cushions the first step of entry. Because every beginning should always be careful."},"ICON-2066":{"nm":"Sun Lounger Cushion Strap Loop","on":"loop","de":"A loop you hook and tie the strap to so the cushion won't slide off. A small promise to hold its place even when the wind blows. One knot pins the afternoon's languor right there."},"ICON-2067":{"nm":"Pool Villa Drink Slot Board","on":"board","de":"A board to tuck a drink glass snug into at the pool's edge. One spot unfazed even by spirited splashing. Setting coolness within reach stretches a midsummer afternoon out long."},"ICON-2068":{"nm":"Wet Swimsuit Hanging Clip","on":"clip","de":"Pick up the dripping swimsuit and leave it quietly to the breeze. While it dries under the sun, the clip stands silently holding on. A quiet, tender wait for the next swim."},"ICON-2069":{"nm":"Parasol Pole Base Weight","on":"parasol pole base weight","de":"A heavy weight set at the pole's base so the parasol won't sway in the wind. The shade stays put in one spot all thanks to this heft. Reliability often hides in the lowest place."},"ICON-2070":{"nm":"Pool Temperature Float Chip","on":"chip","de":"A small chip bobbing on the water, quietly reporting the temperature. Flushing red if too cold, going soft if just right. A cute little fortune-teller reading the water's mood with a single color."},"ICON-2071":{"nm":"Tent Zipper Pull Tassel","on":"tent zipper pull tassel","de":"Give a tug to the small tassel hung at the zipper's end and the tent flap slides open. A handle caught at once even when fingers fumble. It kindly guides the comings and goings of deep night."},"ICON-2072":{"nm":"Tent Cord Butterfly Pin","on":"pin","de":"A pin that bites the cord in a butterfly shape and holds it firm. The fabric that flapped in the wind finally goes still. A camping night is quietly guarded by such small, capable knots."},"ICON-2073":{"nm":"Glamping Mat Air Valve","on":"glamping mat air valve","de":"Put your mouth to it and puff, puff, and the mat slowly swells up. Fill it and shut the valve tight, the floor turns cushiony, and a spot to lay your body under the starlight is finally complete."},"ICON-2074":{"nm":"Tent Ceiling Hanging Hook","on":"hook","de":"A hook hung from the tent ceiling for a lantern or a handkerchief. The wisdom of housekeeping that thriftily uses even the small space overhead. It's like hanging a single star on the ceiling in place of the sky."},"ICON-2075":{"nm":"Sleeping Bag Roll Band","on":"band","de":"A band wound and fastened so the rolled-up sleeping bag won't come undone. A bed that shrinks small again by morning. Getting ready to leave is folding away last night's warmth neatly."},"ICON-2076":{"nm":"Tent Entrance Shoe Rest Board","on":"board","de":"A board set at the tent entrance to hold shoes neatly. Dirt outside, the inside clean. With one threshold, it tenderly divides in from out—a small courtesy of camping."},"ICON-2077":{"nm":"Glamping Lantern Hanging Hook","on":"hook","de":"A bent hook for hanging the lantern. Hook it here and the light spreads round inside the canopy. That spot where you hang one glow in the dark becomes our living room tonight."},"ICON-2078":{"nm":"Tent Vent Roll Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clip that rolls up and holds the vent window. Crack open a path for the breeze and the air inside the tent grows much fresher. One small gap quietly makes room to breathe all night."},"ICON-2079":{"nm":"Tent Floor Ground Mat","on":"mat","de":"A mat laid on the tent floor to block dirt and damp. One layer that spreads a dry bed even over the grass. So you stay in nature yet don't get soaked by it, it quietly lends a hand at your side."},"ICON-2080":{"nm":"Barbell Collar Ring","on":"ring","de":"A ring fastened at each end of the barbell so the plates won't slip off. A small lock that fully trusts the weight of the one lifting. Only when safety holds firm is a limit, at last, renewed by one notch."},"ICON-2081":{"nm":"Kettlebell Handle Cap","on":"cap","de":"On the last set where the iron gnawed at your palm, this one small cap makes the pain vanish. That holding on to the end is harder than lifting the weight—the hand knows it first at the closing point."},"ICON-2082":{"nm":"Plate Insert Wedge","on":"wedge","de":"If the plate wobbles even slightly, your form crumbles before you even lift. A wedge driven thin into the gap holds the center soundlessly. Firmness always begins quietly in the unseen places."},"ICON-2083":{"nm":"Barbell Latch Clip","on":"clip","de":"The fingertips fastening the latch must hold no hesitation. That one small locking click bears up the whole next movement. The body learns first to stake its trust on a single clip."},"ICON-2084":{"nm":"Plate Weight Color Chip","on":"chip","de":"A chip colored differently by weight—the hand recognizes it first even if you can't read the number. Red is heavy, blue is light; remembering weight by color. The body, surprisingly, gauges its strength through the eyes."},"ICON-2085":{"nm":"Kettlebell Floor Rest","on":"rest","de":"Thanks to the rest that widens the surface touching the floor, the floorboards don't get gouged. The marks of a workout need stay only in sweat and muscle. A small heart that won't leave wounds even underfoot is laid out here."},"ICON-2086":{"nm":"Barbell Center Mark","on":"barbell center mark","de":"The mark etched at the bar's middle is the reference point for left-right balance. A hand that grips the center exactly halves the wobble. The moment you know where the center is, you can lift safely at last."},"ICON-2087":{"nm":"Plate Storage Rack","on":"plate storage rack","de":"Used plates go back to their place. The sight of them hung neatly by weight on the rack is a quiet thoughtfulness for the next person. A tidy space is the most dependable safety device, someone believes."},"ICON-2088":{"nm":"Plate Roll-Stop Ledge","on":"plate roll-stop ledge","de":"The accident of a plate on the floor sliding off to crush your foot always comes in one careless instant. The stop-ledge quietly blocks that split second. Big trouble doesn't come from big places—it rolls in from a small gap."},"ICON-2089":{"nm":"Bench Backrest Cushion","on":"bench backrest cushion","de":"If the cushion supporting your back is too hard, even your breathing turns shallow. That border of suitably firm and suitably soft is a balance point only one who has sat long can feel out with the fingertips."},"ICON-2090":{"nm":"Rack Height Adjustment Pin","on":"pin","de":"With one pin that sets the height, the bar fits anyone's shoulders just right. People of different heights sharing the same equipment amiably—one small adjustment hole makes that tender equality."},"ICON-2091":{"nm":"Machine Pulley Cover","on":"machine pulley cover","de":"Inside the cover wrapping the pulley, the cable turns round and round without a sound. A part that hides friction within and offers only smoothness to the hand. A good device never reveals in the end the toil it has paid."},"ICON-2092":{"nm":"Bench Leg Non-Slip Feet","on":"bench leg non-slip feet","de":"Non-slip feet fitted on the four leg-ends hold the bench firmly to the floor. Only when it doesn't wobble can you put your full strength in with ease. Stability, after all, begins from a little friction at the foot."},"ICON-2093":{"nm":"Rack Barbell Holding Hook","on":"hook","de":"The hook for resting the bar must always be at a height within reach. The spot where a tired arm gently sets the bar down at last—that hand's-breadth position safely closes today's workout."},"ICON-2094":{"nm":"Machine Weight Pin Handle","on":"handle","de":"The handle for inserting the pin to select the weight must be smooth so it won't hurt your nails. Even in the brief motion of changing weight, a finish that considered the human fingertip lies quietly hidden, you feel it."},"ICON-2095":{"nm":"Bench Angle Lock Lever","on":"bench angle lock lever","de":"If the lever locking the backrest angle is loose, your form quietly crumbles. The certainty of that moment it fixes with a click. Opening the doors each morning, the operator checks this very sound first."},"ICON-2096":{"nm":"Rack Safety Bar Rest","on":"rest","de":"In the worst moment when the barbell leaves your hands, the safety-bar rest catches that weight in its stead. With a rest unseen, always waiting below, a person can at last push all the way to their limit."},"ICON-2097":{"nm":"Machine Cable End Cap","on":"cap","de":"The small cap that gathers the cable's end is the final knot against unraveling. Binding it neatly so the strands won't scatter—the dignity of a finish always rests at that unnoticed end point."},"ICON-2098":{"nm":"Chalk Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A handful of white powder rubbed on the hands to erase slipping. Unseen like backstage makeup, yet the stability of every move today begins from this one handful. Preparation always starts from the fingertips."},"ICON-2099":{"nm":"Grip Training Clip","on":"clip","de":"A small clip that silently repeats squeezing and releasing builds the strength of your grasp. Grip strength grows slower than the big muscles, so this is also a practice in quietly setting impatience down."},"ICON-2100":{"nm":"Finger Spreader Band","on":"band","de":"A band slipped between the fingers to slowly spread them outward. A hand that used only the gripping muscles regains its spreading strength. As much as gripping tight, gently letting go takes practice too, the hand says."},"ICON-2101":{"nm":"Chalk-Tube Lid","on":"lid","de":"If the powder-tube lid is even slightly loose, the whole bag turns white. One small, snugly fitting cap heads off that little disaster before it happens. Containment always comes down to the stopper."},"ICON-2102":{"nm":"Knee-Support Wrap Band","on":"band","de":"A band wrapped around the knee for support must stop at just the right pressure. Too tight and it cuts off the blood, too loose and it does nothing, so an experienced hand quietly gauges that delicate in-between from memory."},"ICON-2103":{"nm":"Resistance Loop Cord","on":"cord","de":"The stretchy cord that lengthens and snaps back wakes sleeping muscles without a single weight. Resistance doesn't have to be heavy. Even before a gentle pull, the body always answers honestly."},"ICON-2104":{"nm":"Ankle Weight Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A sandbag strapped to the ankle drags each step down with a satisfying heaviness. Add a little weight and even an ordinary walk becomes proper training. It's a small bit of wisdom that slips a touch of effort into daily life."},"ICON-2105":{"nm":"Wrist Roller Bar","on":"wrist roller bar","de":"A roller you slowly wind up to lift a weight hung on a cord. The wrist is the smallest, most often forgotten joint, and this simple tool quietly revives that forgotten strength."},"ICON-2106":{"nm":"Grip-Strength Rubber Ball","on":"grip-strength rubber ball","de":"A rubber ball you squeeze and release keeps your training quietly going even at your desk. Strength built in spare moments lasts longer than strength poured in all at once. Consistency always grows from little things like this."},"ICON-2107":{"nm":"Heart-Rate Belt Buckle","on":"heart-rate belt buckle","de":"If the buckle on the chest strap is even slightly off, the numbers jump. Even the act of listening to your own heart starts with a firm fastening. Every measurement, in the end, begins with a snug, gapless fit."},"ICON-2108":{"nm":"Pulse Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clip that gently bites your fingertip and quietly counts your pulse. Slip it on, steady your breath, and your heart's rhythm rises clearly across a tiny screen. The body always reports its true state."},"ICON-2109":{"nm":"Wrist Monitor Band Case","on":"case","de":"The case that holds a wrist monitor is small but knows its own family. The easier a tiny device is to lose, the more it needs a home to return to. Keeping things safe is its own form of tenderness."},"ICON-2110":{"nm":"Pace Flag Pin","on":"pin","de":"A little flag pin that marks a runner's target spot. A single point set in advance—\"just this far\"—carries heavy feet all the way to the end. The finish line in your heart is always one you plant yourself."},"ICON-2111":{"nm":"Heartbeat Glow Cap","on":"cap","de":"A tiny light that quietly blinks in time with your heartbeat. Watching the rhythm of it switching on and off, your heart swells anew at the thought that being alive could be such a steady thing."},"ICON-2112":{"nm":"Lap-Count Bead String","on":"string","de":"You count your reps with beads flicked over one at a time. You don't have to hold the number in your head—your fingers remember for you. Hand the counting to your hands, and your mind can rest wholly on the movement."},"ICON-2113":{"nm":"Oxygen-Saturation Clip Pad","on":"pad","de":"A clip pad slipped onto your fingertip quietly reads the oxygen in your blood. When the unseen depth of your breath rises as a number, you realize anew that caring for the body is, in the end, simply looking closely."},"ICON-2114":{"nm":"Heart-Rate Zone Color Band","on":"band","de":"A band that divides exercise intensity by color tells you at a glance how hard you're working right now. Blue is easy, red is the limit. It's a quiet promise where color itself becomes a kind, simple language."},"ICON-2115":{"nm":"Measurement Jelly Capsule","on":"measurement jelly capsule","de":"A tiny jelly capsule that measures your body's state holds a day's worth of information in a single bead. Whatever lies inside its clear shell, the wish to know yourself a little better is tucked in there too."},"ICON-2116":{"nm":"Sweat-Towel Hook","on":"hook","de":"The small habit of always hanging it on its own hook instead of tossing it just anywhere keeps a whole room tidy. Like this, which sets aside a spot for the towel to return to, tidiness always shines in the little things."},"ICON-2117":{"nm":"Water-Bottle Lid Tether","on":"tether","de":"The short cord on a water-bottle cap prevents the mishap of the lid rolling away. The wisdom of tethering something easy to lose to your body—one little cord quietly clears away a day's worth of bother."},"ICON-2118":{"nm":"Folding Fan Blade","on":"blade","de":"A fan blade that stirs up a breeze when spread wide open. Like the old fans that cooled sweat on hot days, the simplest tool offers the coolest comfort. A single gust always blossoms from your fingertips."},"ICON-2119":{"nm":"Cooling-Towel Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A small pouch that holds a towel that turns cold when dampened. A single sheet of cloth that cools the heat sleeps there neatly, then settles softly onto a weary nape and quietly carries off the midday warmth."},"ICON-2120":{"nm":"Drip Saucer","on":"saucer","de":"A saucer set out in advance to catch the place where beaded droplets will fall. To make a spot to catch what drips, rather than blame it for running down. The kindness of a kitchen always lingers like this, without a sound."},"ICON-2121":{"nm":"Air-Vent Direction Blade","on":"air-vent direction blade","de":"The moment a head-on blast of air veers slightly aside along a small blade, the stuffy heat of the practice room finally catches its breath. Changing the flow always came down to a small angle like this."},"ICON-2122":{"nm":"Forehead Headband","on":"forehead headband","de":"If your bangs get soaked while washing your face, the whole day comes undone. This band, lifting your hair gently up off your forehead, hands the person at the mirror five dry minutes. You only notice once it's gone."},"ICON-2123":{"nm":"Drinking-Cup Clip Stand","on":"drinking-cup clip stand","de":"When a cup teeters dangerously at the edge of the desk, this clip quietly grips one side. A day that passed without a spill, a sip of water reminds you, is thanks to someone holding the edge in your stead."},"ICON-2124":{"nm":"Vent-Window Hook Handle","on":"handle","de":"A tightly shut window is stuffy, a wide-open one is chilly. This hook handle remembers just the right gap in between. Ventilation is, in the end, a matter of the heart—leaving things open just enough."},"ICON-2125":{"nm":"Cork Block Corner Cap","on":"cap","de":"It's always the sharp corner that hurts when you bump it. So you carve a piece of cork and cap each edge. A spot wrapped softly will no longer hurt anyone's knee."},"ICON-2126":{"nm":"Bolster Strap Handle","on":"handle","de":"Carrying a long pillow is more of a nuisance than you'd think. Attach a single strap and it tucks neatly into one hand. The trick to lifting something heavy lightly depends on where you put the handle."},"ICON-2127":{"nm":"Belt Buckle Fastener","on":"belt buckle fastener","de":"There are days you cinch your waist one notch tighter, and days you let it out one notch. The one that knows your condition most honestly is this little fastener. A bit of metal that silently records the body's candor."},"ICON-2128":{"nm":"Quarter-Block Support","on":"support","de":"A block cut into quarters props up the floor firmly. Not too high, not too low—just that much balance. It quietly shows that to support is to lower yourself and lift up what's above."},"ICON-2129":{"nm":"Egg Bolster Cover","on":"cover","de":"You dress an egg-round pillow in a perfectly fitted coat. Even if it soaks with sweat, you just strip it off and wash it. The household knows that the more something touches your skin daily, the more it needs a fresh layer to change into."},"ICON-2130":{"nm":"Block Leveling Wedge","on":"wedge","de":"If the floor tilts even slightly, everything you carefully stacked wobbles. Slip one thin wedge into the gap and the world regains its level. Setting things straight needs nothing grand."},"ICON-2131":{"nm":"Strap-End Stopper Knot","on":"strap-end stopper knot","de":"You tie a firm stopper knot so the strap's end doesn't fray and flop. A cord with a tidily finished end lasts a long time. One little knot teaches that finishing is harder than starting."},"ICON-2132":{"nm":"Knee-Cushion Folding Pad","on":"pad","de":"That sharp ache every time your knee meets a hard floor. A single pad that folds and unfolds slips gently between knee and floor. It's a tenderness that props up someone's knee in their stead."},"ICON-2133":{"nm":"Block Anti-Slip Base","on":"base","de":"Even the firmest block is useless if it slides. The fine grooves carved into its base grip the floor tight. The secret to staying steady is always hidden on the unseen underside."},"ICON-2134":{"nm":"Alignment Rod Clip","on":"clip","de":"You line the rods up straight and pinch them with a clip. Anyone used to lining things up knows it—that strange little satisfaction that wells up from setting crooked things side by side."},"ICON-2135":{"nm":"Hamstring Strap Loop","on":"loop","de":"When the back of your thigh pulls until a yelp slips out, this loop reaches for the toes your hand can't. Where you couldn't get to alone, a single strand of cord builds a bridge for your leg."},"ICON-2136":{"nm":"Toe-Spreader Pad","on":"pad","de":"Even toes shut up inside shoes all day need a break. On a pad that spreads them apart, the foot finally stretches. An evening that loosens you starting from the farthest place."},"ICON-2137":{"nm":"Posture Angle Gauge","on":"gauge","de":"By eye, there's no telling how many degrees your posture has gone off. When the gauge quietly tells you the angle, the body finally stands straight. A scale that shows the tilt you couldn't see."},"ICON-2138":{"nm":"Pelvis Alignment Wedge","on":"wedge","de":"A languid afternoon, your pelvis stiffened tilted to one side. You prop a single wedge and slowly recover your center. It's not forcing things straight, but helping them find the right place again."},"ICON-2139":{"nm":"Shoulder-Opening Band Buckle","on":"shoulder-opening band buckle","de":"A band that gently straightens hunched shoulders. Tighten the buckle and a curved back slowly opens. Breathe deep with shoulders thrown wide open, and only then does a stage-bow posture appear."},"ICON-2140":{"nm":"Spine Support Wedge","on":"spine support wedge","de":"Lie back and your spine draws its natural curve. A wedge that quietly supports that curve without fighting it. Knowing how to rest well begins with honoring the curve the body was born with."},"ICON-2141":{"nm":"Instep Stretch Wedge","on":"wedge","de":"Stretching the instep always fell a little short. Prop the right wedge and you stretch refreshingly to a depth you couldn't reach. A small slope that helps you reach just a bit farther."},"ICON-2142":{"nm":"Wrist Alignment Rest","on":"rest","de":"When a wrist bent at the keyboard starts to tingle, the rest slides quietly beneath it. The first to look after hands that work long hours are humble, low-lying things like this."},"ICON-2143":{"nm":"Wrist Support Wrap","on":"wrist support wrap","de":"Before lifting something heavy, you wind a wrap once around your wrist. A reassurance that grows with every turn. The habit of wrapping up before you get hurt is the quiet secret of those who train for the long haul."},"ICON-2144":{"nm":"Armband Phone Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Where to keep your phone while running was always a worry. This pouch strapped to your forearm takes that worry away. Run with a favorite song tucked to your arm, and the road feels a good deal shorter."},"ICON-2145":{"nm":"Hand-Gripper Spring Cap","on":"cap","de":"A cap capped over the end of a gripper's spring so it won't jab your palm. Through all the squeezing and releasing, this little stopper keeps the peace between hand and metal. A consideration in an unseen place."},"ICON-2146":{"nm":"Glove Fingertip Thimble","on":"thimble","de":"Grandma's sewing-skilled fingers always wore a thimble. This thimble fitted to a glove's end protects the fingertip. The wish to spare hands that have worked long is uncannily alike, even across generations."},"ICON-2147":{"nm":"Grip Callus Pad","on":"pad","de":"The calluses worn into your palm are the fingerprints left by effort. A pad layered over them makes the next rep possible. Wrapping the hardened spot again, a person hangs on once more."},"ICON-2148":{"nm":"Palm Anti-Slip Tape","on":"palm anti-slip tape","de":"If your palm keeps slipping, you drop what you worked hard to hold. Wrap on the gritty tape and hand and tool become one body. The strength not to lose your grip comes, surprisingly, from friction."},"ICON-2149":{"nm":"Forearm Sweat Band","on":"band","de":"Before sweat that ran down mid-workout reaches your wrist, this band on the forearm soaks it up first. That sweat is nothing to be ashamed of—a soaking-wet cloth silently bears witness."},"ICON-2150":{"nm":"Glove Drying Rack","on":"glove drying rack","de":"Toss them down anywhere and the next morning is misery, but hang them neatly and the breeze dries them soft overnight on its own. The clean scent of well-dried gloves opens tomorrow crisp and fresh."},"ICON-2151":{"nm":"Sportswear Zipper Pull","on":"pull","de":"With soaking-wet hands you simply can't grab a tiny zipper. Attach one pull and it's a single clean tug. A trivial little loop rescues a whole flustered minute."},"ICON-2152":{"nm":"Sweat-Wicking Vent Patch","on":"sweat-wicking vent patch","de":"You place a vent patch on the body's hottest spot. The trapped heat slips quietly out through the patch. The act of opening one little breathing-hole right in the suffocating center."},"ICON-2153":{"nm":"Insole Cushion Piece","on":"insole cushion piece","de":"You cut out only the worn part of an old insole and fit in a new piece. A touch that doesn't toss the whole thing, but swaps out only what hurts. A small repair underfoot lightens the day's every step."},"ICON-2154":{"nm":"Sportswear Iron-On Number Patch","on":"sportswear iron-on number patch","de":"You press a back number into the cloth with an iron. As the heat cools, the number settles firmly onto the fabric. The starting stamp by which people wearing the same number become one team."},"ICON-2155":{"nm":"Shoe-Toe Reinforcement Cap","on":"cap","de":"A reinforcement cap on the toe quietly fends off the fate of a shoe whose tip keeps stubbing. The first place to wear, made the sturdiest. The longer-lasting the shoe, the tougher it is right from the toe."},"ICON-2156":{"nm":"Sportswear Drawcord Knot","on":"sportswear drawcord knot","de":"The moment you give the waist drawcord a tug and tie it, the loose garment hugs the body snug. This firm, won't-come-undone knot holds everything in place through the most intense moves."},"ICON-2157":{"nm":"Ankle-Sock Anti-Slip Band","on":"band","de":"That nuisance of an ankle sock that keeps rolling down into your shoe. A single band holds that slipping fast. A sock so small you paid it no mind finally keeps its place."},"ICON-2158":{"nm":"Sportswear Underarm Sweat Pad","on":"pad","de":"A pad set in advance where sweat wells up most. Soak it through and not a trace shows on the garment's surface. The things that toil silently out of sight keep the stage looking clean."},"ICON-2159":{"nm":"Shoe Heel Pull Loop","on":"loop","de":"After you put a shoe on, give the heel loop a tug and your foot slides right in. That brief convenience that spares you from crouching down. On a busy morning, one loop like this earns its keep."},"ICON-2160":{"nm":"Massage-Gun Head Cap","on":"cap","de":"You swap the head to match the spot you're tapping. Each knotted muscle has its own fitting shape. An evening that picks just the right intensity of comfort for shoulders that endured the day."},"ICON-2161":{"nm":"Massage-Gun Charging Dock","on":"massage-gun charging dock","de":"Even the hand that'll loosen the body all day wakes only once it's charged. While the red light turns to green, you may rest a while. When the blinking stops, the turn to soothe stiff shoulders quietly comes round again."},"ICON-2162":{"nm":"Massage-Gun Intensity Dial","on":"massage-gun intensity dial","de":"Soft, a bit more, that's it. Turning the dial, your fingertips quietly haggle with your own body. Today's pledge—to grow firm only as much as it hurts—is written out clearly between the little notches."},"ICON-2163":{"nm":"Vibration-Ball Holder Ring","on":"ring","de":"Even a well-rolling ball needs a place to pause. This round holder quietly cradles the heart that wants to roll away, keeping its spot until the next turn comes. Rest, too, is part of exercise."},"ICON-2164":{"nm":"Acupressure-Stick Handle Cap","on":"cap","de":"With one small cap on the end, the ache in your palm gently melts away. Between hardness and skin there always needs to be one soft layer. A tender little touch that first rounds off the spot that makes contact."},"ICON-2165":{"nm":"Peanut Roller Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A little sack that holds a peanut-shaped roller. When it rolls out from a corner of your bag, yesterday's resolve to take care of your body today comes tumbling out with it. A small pouch remembers the promise."},"ICON-2166":{"nm":"Foot-Roller Stand","on":"foot-roller stand","de":"If the place you entrust your feet to wobbles, the release wobbles too. This stand propping up the roller grips the floor firmly, making a spot where two tired feet can lean in peace. Reliability comes from not wavering."},"ICON-2167":{"nm":"Roller Core Plug","on":"roller core plug","de":"A small plug that caps off a hollow core. The unseen inside must be filled so the outside doesn't come apart. That spot no one will ever see while it rolls, this quiet part silently holds up."},"ICON-2168":{"nm":"Massage-Stick End Cap","on":"massage-stick end cap","de":"A cap rounded over the end of the stick. So it won't wear, won't scratch—protecting the tip is, in the end, the way to keep it by your side a long time. The wish to wrap the first place to take a hit in the softest way."},"ICON-2169":{"nm":"Taping-Roll Cutter","on":"taping-roll cutter","de":"Pull with one hand and the tape cuts off clean. There's a little knack to tying off and finishing too, and this blade knows the feel of a tidy ending. A clean finish makes the next thing lighter."},"ICON-2170":{"nm":"Tape-End Adhesive Cap","on":"cap","de":"A cap that quietly presses the end down so it won't unravel. Anyone can start, but staying stuck to the very end is always hard. This little hand that holds the final stretch quietly takes charge of today's finish."},"ICON-2171":{"nm":"Wrist Compression Sleeve","on":"wrist compression sleeve","de":"Wrap a single layer around an overworked wrist and the pain arrives a beat late. Like a hand quietly holding yours, compression is sometimes the kindest protection. It isn't squeezing in—it's holding you up."},"ICON-2172":{"nm":"Ankle-Brace Buckle","on":"ankle-brace buckle","de":"The short click of fastening the buckle sets the mind at ease. Wrap the ankle firmly and a courage wells up that says it might be fine to step one stride farther. One small sound becomes a sturdy start."},"ICON-2173":{"nm":"Knee Compression Strap Fastener","on":"knee compression strap fastener","de":"The knee grows steadier the more you pull the strap tight. Won't come undone, yet won't hurt—somewhere between the two is a perfectly fitting notch. The fastener never forgets that spot, every time."},"ICON-2174":{"nm":"Finger-Taping Scissors","on":"scissors","de":"Small scissors that precisely snip the tape wound around a knuckle. Rounded at the tip so they won't nick the skin. The more a tool is meant to care, the more tenderly its blade is honed—these scissors quietly show it."},"ICON-2175":{"nm":"Compression-Band Winder","on":"compression-band winder","de":"A winder that neatly rewinds an unrolled compression band. A hand that carefully rolls up what it's done using won't have it tangle next time either. In each tidily wound layer, today's neatness is steeped."},"ICON-2176":{"nm":"Shin-Guard Strap","on":"strap","de":"A strap that ties on the pad guarding the front of the shin. The mind that first checks the spot likely to be struck is itself preparation. Step onto the field with legs firmly knotted up, and the fear in your heart shrinks by half."},"ICON-2177":{"nm":"Elbow-Brace Clip","on":"clip","de":"A little clip that grips firmly so the brace won't slide down. As trivial as pinching a sheet of paper, yet if this comes loose, everything loosens. One small fastening firmly holds a day's worth of reassurance."},"ICON-2178":{"nm":"Stretching Loop Handle","on":"handle","de":"Grip the loop and stretch your body long, and you see fingertips reaching a hand's-breadth farther than yesterday. It's not only muscle that lengthens as you pull. A stiffened heart, too, unfurls a little in the meantime."},"ICON-2179":{"nm":"Toe-Spreader Spacer","on":"toe-spreader spacer","de":"Spread apart the toes shut up in shoes all day, and a breeze drifts into the cramped space. Some things in this world only grow comfortable once they've been apart a while. Even toes need room to breathe."},"ICON-2180":{"nm":"Calf-Release Wedge Board","on":"board","de":"Tucked wedge-like beneath the calves, your legs gently unwind. One slanted angle quietly lets a day's weight slip away. Reclining at a slight tilt—that, at times, is the most comfortable posture of all."},"ICON-2181":{"nm":"Neck-Release Rest","on":"rest","de":"You lay your neck across it and close your eyes a while. It's all right to set down your heavy head for a moment, this little rest whispers softly to your shoulders from its same old spot. Even leaning takes courage."},"ICON-2182":{"nm":"Stretching-Pole End Cap","on":"cap","de":"A single cap covering the end of a long-reaching pole. With a soft tip, you can rest easy wherever it touches. Whoever you reach toward, rounding off the corners first—consideration always begins quietly like this."},"ICON-2183":{"nm":"Acupressure Cushion Nub Board","on":"board","de":"Lay your body on the bumpy nubs and the day drains out at each pressed-in spot. At that border between ache and relief, shoulders stiff all day slowly unwind as if surrendering."},"ICON-2184":{"nm":"Relaxation Breathing Hourglass","on":"hourglass","de":"A quiet promise to draw out a long breath until the very last grain of sand falls. The slender stream of sand quietly counts the rhythm of inhale and exhale. A busy mind, too, settles for a while in the meantime."},"ICON-2185":{"nm":"Sole Acupressure Ball Support","on":"support","de":"Prop a ball at the center of your sole and press down steadily. To feet that propped up the whole body all day, the little support quietly yields its spot, saying it's their turn to be held now. Even what holds things up has times to rest."},"ICON-2186":{"nm":"Shoulder-Release Loop Cord","on":"cord","de":"A loop cord you hook over the shoulder and pull. Stretch the line toward a stiff spot and a knotted joint loosens free, one notch at a time. It shows that even becoming free needs something to take your hand."},"ICON-2187":{"nm":"Lane-Rope Disk","on":"lane-rope disk","de":"A single round bead of the lane line that divides the water. A kind boundary drawn over the water so you won't bump the swimmer beside you. Small partitions that guard each one's path carry everyone forward, side by side, to the end."},"ICON-2188":{"nm":"Lane-Rope Tension Hook","on":"hook","de":"A hook that pulls the lane rope taut and holds it. Too loose and it bends with the waves, too tight and it snaps. Finding the right tension is like steadying your heart—you always grope for somewhere in between."},"ICON-2189":{"nm":"Lane Color Cap","on":"cap","de":"A small cap painted a different color for each lane. A marker colored so you can spot your own path at a glance, even from afar. To keep someone from getting lost with one color—guidance, at heart, begins with such small kindness."},"ICON-2190":{"nm":"Lane-Rope Hanging Board","on":"board","de":"A board for hanging the lane ropes neatly when not in use. In the hand that tidily arranges the ropes for the next start, a calm resolve to wrap up the day well is quietly held."},"ICON-2191":{"nm":"Lane-Rope Reel Handle","on":"handle","de":"Crank the handle round and round to reel in the long-unrolled rope. Gathering up what's been scattered always takes patience. One turn, then another—a finish is completed slowly like this, without rushing."},"ICON-2192":{"nm":"Lane-End Knot Clamp","on":"clamp","de":"A clamp that bites firmly so the knot at the rope's end won't come undone. It won't let even a stray bit slip away. There must be a hand minding things to the end for a long rope to keep its tidy shape without unraveling."},"ICON-2193":{"nm":"Lane-Rope Float Bead","on":"lane-rope float bead","de":"The lane rope's float bead that bobs up on the water. To keep from sinking, it has taken a lungful of air inside. Some lightness comes from an emptiness filled with effort, the rippling water keeps floating up to show."},"ICON-2194":{"nm":"Lane Number Flag","on":"flag","de":"A small flag that announces the lane number. One scrap of cloth fluttering in the wind tells you clearly, \"this is your spot.\" A small but unmistakable signpost that sends you straight onto your path without getting lost."},"ICON-2195":{"nm":"Lane-Rope Connector Hook","on":"lane-rope connector hook","de":"A hook that joins one lane rope to the next. With a single hook that links a broken path back together, the waterway is finally complete. To connect is, in the end, the work of a small piece of metal quietly reaching a hand between things that have come apart."},"ICON-2196":{"nm":"Starting-Block Footplate","on":"plate","de":"The footplate on the start line takes the full weight of the first leap. That 0.1 second of kicking off hard—the firmness your toes press against shoves a whole race into motion. Every soaring flight starts from a place to plant firmly."},"ICON-2197":{"nm":"Start Grab Bar","on":"start grab bar","de":"The bar your hands grip tight just before the start signal. You have to anchor your trembling heart somewhere or the start will waver. Just having something to hold makes the next single move that much clearer and steadier."},"ICON-2198":{"nm":"Backstroke Flag Line","on":"line","de":"A flag line that tells the one swimming face-up to the ceiling that the wall is near. A kindness that warns you in advance of what you can't see. With one signal looking out for your back, the final stroke turns safe."},"ICON-2199":{"nm":"Turn-Wall Pad","on":"pad","de":"A soft pad layered onto the wall where you change direction. So it won't hurt even if you hit it hard, it cushions the turning spot. On the path back, someone's quiet consideration is always laid down first."},"ICON-2200":{"nm":"Finish Touchpad","on":"pad","de":"The moment your fingertips touch, it's all over. The end of a long, breathless course comes down to this one light tap. Arrival isn't anything grand—it's reaching the exact right spot, the pad quietly answers."},"ICON-2201":{"nm":"Starting-Platform Slide Strip","on":"strip","de":"Anyone, standing at the top of the slope, holds their breath at least once. Get past that brief fear and slide down, and—splash—laughter bursts out with the spray. A start always begins one small notch of fear beyond."},"ICON-2202":{"nm":"Turn-Distance Marker Cone","on":"turn-distance marker cone","de":"When you hesitate at a fork, this little point speaks up first. Turn back here, it says, don't lose your way. Someone sees this one hue and finds their direction again, and walks on."},"ICON-2203":{"nm":"Starting-Block Angle Wedge","on":"wedge","de":"That half-beat where the body crouches lowest, just before the leap. A small foothold is there, propping the angle so your toes won't slip. Every moment of soaring high is born from this slant."},"ICON-2204":{"nm":"Wall-Corner Bumper Cap","on":"cap","de":"So it won't hurt even if you bump it while romping, the corner has rounded away its sharpness. The wish that you not get hurt is whittled and whittled and stuck to the wall. The kindest protection is mostly this quiet."},"ICON-2205":{"nm":"Lifebuoy Hanging Hook","on":"hook","de":"Most of the time it's just a spot where something hangs. But the moment someone falls into the water, this is the first place a hand reaches for. There's a kind of reliability in this world that's better off never being used."},"ICON-2206":{"nm":"Rescue Hook Pole","on":"rescue hook pole","de":"A long arm that closes an unreachable distance in one stroke. When your hand falls short, this hook becomes a hand in its stead. Rescue is, in the end, the act of offering your fingertips to someone far away."},"ICON-2207":{"nm":"Poolside Showerhead","on":"poolside showerhead","de":"\"Be sure to rinse off before you go in.\" Like the lifeguard's go-to line, a stream of water pours over your head. With one cold burst, the day's dust trickles right off."},"ICON-2208":{"nm":"Anti-Slip Floor Tile","on":"anti-slip floor tile","de":"Finely raised grooves so bare feet won't slip. From an unseen spot, they quietly hold the soles of your feet. The firmest safety is always hidden in the unshowy places."},"ICON-2209":{"nm":"Water-Depth Sign","on":"sign","de":"Before you set foot in, the number tells you the depth first. A spot that would frighten you if you entered unknowing settles the mind once you've read it. What this sign does is help with a small bit of preparation."},"ICON-2210":{"nm":"Safety-Line Float Rope","on":"rope","de":"Colorful ropes bobbing on the water, dividing the zones. This far is safe, the floats promise, joining hands. Because there's a boundary, you can finally swim freely with an easy mind."},"ICON-2211":{"nm":"Footbath Disinfecting Basin","on":"basin","de":"A small basin where bare feet linger a moment before entering the water. A short ritual of growing clean from the feet up is held there. Cleanliness always begins with this one step's worth of care."},"ICON-2212":{"nm":"Wet-Floor Caution Cone","on":"wet-floor caution cone","de":"One yellow cone quietly slows your steps. \"It's wet here, careful.\" A consideration offered in color instead of words. This little warning quietly guards the day of someone who nearly slipped."},"ICON-2213":{"nm":"First-Aid Wall Cabinet","on":"first-aid wall cabinet","de":"The white cabinet on the wall rarely ever opens. But in the moment it does open, it becomes someone's relief. An emergency always waits quietly in the very nearest place."},"ICON-2214":{"nm":"Surface Skimmer Net","on":"surface skimmer net","de":"It quietly lifts up the leaves and dust drifting on the surface. Clarity doesn't come on its own, so someone's hand must scoop it out once each day. Behind still water, there's a diligent net."},"ICON-2215":{"nm":"Floor-Cleaning Robot Hose","on":"floor-cleaning robot hose","de":"Even on a night when everyone's asleep, it roams slowly, feeling along the floor. The most faithful worker in the hours no one's watching. That morning clarity is the trail this hose drew all night."},"ICON-2216":{"nm":"Chlorine Dosing Canister","on":"canister","de":"Even keeping the water clear has its just-right amount. Too much and it turns harsh, too little and it clouds—the balance between. An unseen hand quietly sets that measure each day."},"ICON-2217":{"nm":"Water-Test Bottle","on":"bottle","de":"You gather a mouthful of water in a little bottle and ask after today's state. To the eye it looks the same, but numbers don't lie. Peace of mind is something confirmed once each day like this."},"ICON-2218":{"nm":"Floatboard Skimming Rake","on":"floatboard skimming rake","de":"A long rake that gathers together the boards and floating debris drifting on the water. A hand that rakes up what's scattered somehow resembles the heart. Even disarray, swept once, falls neatly into line."},"ICON-2219":{"nm":"Drain Cover Mesh","on":"drain cover mesh","de":"A fine mesh guarding the passage where water flows out. It quietly sorts what to let go and what to hold back. Even letting things go needs a filter, this little mesh silently tells you."},"ICON-2220":{"nm":"Water-Temperature Float","on":"marker","de":"A small scout that bobs on the water and reads the temperature. Whether it's cold or just right, a kindness that tells you before your body touches it. The first reassurance of entering always begins with this float."},"ICON-2221":{"nm":"Pool-Cover Reel Rod","on":"rod","de":"A handle that rolls up a wide cover and stows it to one side. A tool that knows when to spread out and when to gather in is somehow dependable. At rest, it's like tucking the water in under a quilt too."},"ICON-2222":{"nm":"Skimmer Basket Bin","on":"bin","de":"The basket where debris drifting on the surface finally collects. Because there's a vessel taking in the dregs in an unseen spot, the top water is always clear. Behind cleanliness, toil piles up."},"ICON-2223":{"nm":"Swim-Cap Drying Rack","on":"swim-cap drying rack","de":"You hang a water-laden swim cap upside down. As it drips one drop at a time, the cap slowly catches its breath. Drying is, in the end, just another name for waiting."},"ICON-2224":{"nm":"Swimsuit Shoulder-Strap Loop","on":"loop","de":"A small loop that holds the strap so it won't slip off the shoulder. From an unseen spot, it quietly keeps your appearance in order. Neatness is always completed atop little supports like this."},"ICON-2225":{"nm":"Swim-Cap Organizer Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A pouch where wet swim caps find their places one by one. A small dwelling that gathers easily scattered things into one embrace. Tidying is a tender habit of trying not to lose things."},"ICON-2226":{"nm":"Swimsuit Chest Pad","on":"pad","de":"A single pad set quietly inside the garment. Unseen from the outside, it gently straightens the wearer's shoulders. Some reassurance is filled in quietly from within, not from without."},"ICON-2227":{"nm":"Swim-Cap Name-Tag Clip","on":"clip","de":"A little clip that pinches a name tag onto the edge of a swim cap. Among look-alike things, it says clearly, \"this one's mine.\" One mark and the mix-ups end at once."},"ICON-2228":{"nm":"Swimsuit Zipper Loop","on":"loop","de":"\"Could you zip up my back?\" That spot you couldn't reach alone, this little loop pulls up in place of a hand. A tender reach that lends a hand with the final notch."},"ICON-2229":{"nm":"Swim-Cap Anti-Curl Board","on":"board","de":"You straighten and prop a swim cap that's curled into a habit. A support that quietly helps the warped thing recover its shape. There has to be a hand to straighten it for anything to turn flat and proper again."},"ICON-2230":{"nm":"Swimsuit Waist-Drawstring Cinch","on":"swimsuit waist-drawstring cinch","de":"A cinch that wraps the waist just right and holds it so it won't slide down. Neither too tight nor too loose—just that much rightness. Comfort always lives somewhere in between."},"ICON-2231":{"nm":"Swim-Cap Reversing Clamp","on":"clamp","de":"A clamp that grabs an inside-out swim cap and sets it right in one go. The knack of turning the flipped thing back the proper way is rather satisfying. The small thrill of tidying comes from trifling things like this."},"ICON-2232":{"nm":"Kickboard Handle Strap","on":"strap","de":"A strap that winds around your hand so you won't lose the kickboard. Even shoved by the current, having something to hold is a great comfort. The thrill of the day you first learned to kick still lingers in this strap."},"ICON-2233":{"nm":"Pull-Buoy Tightening Strap","on":"strap","de":"A strap that firmly holds the buoy tucked between your two legs. Only when it won't come loose can you finally focus on form alone. Atop something well-held, that day's practice deepens a hand's-breadth at a time."},"ICON-2234":{"nm":"Fin Wall Hanger","on":"fin wall hanger","de":"When the fins hang side by side on the wall, they look just like a flock of ducks resting by the water. Feet that finished their swim flick off the water and wait for tomorrow. Even the pause is somehow round and adorable."},"ICON-2235":{"nm":"Kickboard Corner Cap","on":"cap","de":"One small cap slipped over the kickboard's corner. So it won't hurt when bumped, won't spoil when worn, it wraps the tip. The secret to keeping it by your side long lies in cherishing it from the corners first."},"ICON-2236":{"nm":"Fin Storage Net","on":"fin storage net","de":"Fins resembling webbed feet bask in the sun inside the net. Like ducks just out of the water drying their feathers, they dry slowly within the mesh. A leisurely nap for the next swim."},"ICON-2237":{"nm":"Pull-Buoy Organizing Tag","on":"tag","de":"You attach a name tag to each buoy to mark its owner clearly. The more a place is shared among many, the easier the mind rests when \"whose it is\" is plain. One small tag sets order."},"ICON-2238":{"nm":"Kickboard Drainage Rest","on":"rest","de":"A spot propped at a slant so water pooled in the kickboard trickles down. You have to empty what you've taken in to grow light, the rest silently tells you. The first step of drying is propping things up well."},"ICON-2239":{"nm":"Fin Strap Cinch","on":"fin strap cinch","de":"A small part that cinches the fin strap to fit your foot snugly. Too loose and it slips off, too tight and it hurts—that delicate one notch. To glide on lightly like a webbed-footed duck, you need this fine margin."},"ICON-2240":{"nm":"Kick Rhythm Chip","on":"chip","de":"A little chip that tells the beat each time you kick. One, two, three—once the rhythm settles into your body, the water turns into song before you know it. This chip gently teaches that swimming, too, has a beat."},"ICON-2241":{"nm":"Wet-Swimsuit Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Inside the bag leaving the pool, the first to claim a spot is always me. Let the other belongings give me looks—what can I do, the wet must be held apart so we all stay dry. The quarantine room for dampness, that's the tender post I hold."},"ICON-2242":{"nm":"Water-Wringing Press Board","on":"board","de":"Water has a way of slipping off the moment you press it. One firm push, then a second—it surrenders only once you lay weight on it over the board. For someone who never had use for their wrist strength, there's hardly a better stage than this."},"ICON-2243":{"nm":"Swim-Bag Divider Board","on":"board","de":"Pack it all in one compartment and wet and dry rub off on each other. The work of slipping quietly in between and drawing a line. If one divider brings peace, then reconciliation may be a surprisingly simple thing."},"ICON-2244":{"nm":"Waterproof Shoe Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"It swallows sand-covered shoes whole without changing its expression in the least. Whatever goes on inside, the outside stays dry—that's the courtesy waterproofing keeps. A tight-lipped pouch is welcome anywhere."},"ICON-2245":{"nm":"Swim-Bag Drain Cap","on":"cap","de":"Twist the cap and the day pooled at the bag's bottom drains right out. Cleaning up after a good time of play always comes down to this one little hole. Even knowing how to let things flow away takes design."},"ICON-2246":{"nm":"Water-Absorbing Mat","on":"mat","de":"It lies quietly before the entrance, taking in the water from every foot coming in. Even if no one acknowledges it, the floorboards know—no one slipped today either. In a silent spot dwells a silent reward."},"ICON-2247":{"nm":"Wet-Cap Saucer","on":"saucer","de":"When a tossed-off swim cap loses its place to go, I hold it up. Called a saucer though I cradle droplets instead of food, if it's the work of making a place for someone, even a stand can hold its head up proudly."},"ICON-2248":{"nm":"Towel-Drying Clip","on":"clip","de":"The job of biting down hard on one towel atop the clothesline. My pride is a stubbornness that won't let go no matter how the wind teases. Until it's dried soft in the sun, a hand once gripped never lets go first."},"ICON-2249":{"nm":"Waterproof Pouch Hanger","on":"waterproof pouch hanger","de":"The moment it hangs on the hook, the drifting pouch finally gets an address. Even if it's just dangling, borrowing one square of wall, is there anything as reassuring as a spot where you needn't fear getting lost?"},"ICON-2250":{"nm":"Slide Entry Wristband","on":"band","de":"The excitement of quietly waiting your turn is all bound up in this one little band. Only once it's fastened to your wrist does the slide line start to surge, so entry may just be the act of strapping a promise around your wrist."},"ICON-2251":{"nm":"Water Slide Mat Piece","on":"water slide mat piece","de":"People dash across it gleefully, never noticing the gap underfoot. Laid down so no one would slip, it only reveals its presence once that single piece goes missing. There are quite a few things in this world remembered only by the empty space they leave."},"ICON-2252":{"nm":"Locker-Key Waterproof Band","on":"band","de":"Guarding a locker key from the water is my lifelong job. Wrapped around a wrist, I splash along too, yet keep that one key bone-dry. Lose me and you can't even find your clothes, so really I'm a weighty officer of duty."},"ICON-2253":{"nm":"Slide Start Signal Light Panel","on":"panel","de":"In that brief instant when red switches to green, every heart atop the slide leaps as one. The authority to grant a start, and to think such a tiny signal panel could hold so much thrill."},"ICON-2254":{"nm":"Lazy-River Life Vest Buckle","on":"lazy-river life vest buckle","de":"The buckle that holds tight to a body drifting down the lazy river. Only after that click do you finally relax and surrender to the current. Sometimes reassurance begins with a small latch like this."},"ICON-2255":{"nm":"Wave Pool Guide Flag","on":"flag","de":"It tells everyone in advance when the waves are coming. Flag up means cheers, flag down means a moment to catch your breath. Funny that the thing keeping the beat by the churning pool is a single scrap of cloth."},"ICON-2256":{"nm":"Slide Number Necklace","on":"slide number necklace","de":"Wear which line you're in around your neck and there's no mix-up. A single number tag settles whose turn it is, and order, it seems, often begins with a small necklace like this."},"ICON-2257":{"nm":"Wristband Recharge Token","on":"token","de":"Tap it lightly to your wristband and the recharge is done. In an age of roaming the water with no cash or card, this little token plays the part of a whole wallet. The lighter your wrist, the lighter your heart."},"ICON-2258":{"nm":"Water Cannon Grip Cap","on":"cap","de":"A water cannon grip is best when held tight. Lose one cap and forget aiming, it just spins in your hand, and the outcome of a midsummer water fight hangs on this one little finishing piece."},"ICON-2259":{"nm":"Sandcastle Tower Mold Cup","on":"cup","de":"Pack in wet sand, press firmly, flip it over, and up rises a little tower. No one understands better than I do the heart that keeps building even knowing it will crumble. To a sand architect, the mold is the blueprint."},"ICON-2260":{"nm":"Sand Rake Tines","on":"sand rake tines","de":"Drag it like combing the sand and neat furrows remain. Knowing the waves will soon erase the pattern, the tines still busily lay down their lines. There's a certain charm in lovingly crafting things destined to vanish."},"ICON-2261":{"nm":"Parasol Pole Anchor Weight","on":"parasol pole anchor weight","de":"It stands silently at the base so the parasol won't blow away in the wind. Keeping the shade is the job not of the showy canopy but of the hefty, planted weight. The unseen heft is the most dependable of all."},"ICON-2262":{"nm":"Sand Sieve Handle","on":"handle","de":"Shake to sift the sand and only shells and small treasures stay in your hand. Grab the handle and jiggle away, half of seaside treasure-hunting is decided by this one sieve."},"ICON-2263":{"nm":"Shell-Shaped Sand Mold","on":"shell-shaped sand mold","de":"Fill it with wet sand, tap-tap, and palm-sized shells bloom in a row along the beach. You may not be able to eat a real shell, but anyone can make this shape. A humble bit of summer magic."},"ICON-2264":{"nm":"Parasol Angle Adjustment Pin","on":"pin","de":"Each time the sun shifts, the parasol must turn its head to follow. Pull the pin and reset it, and the shade quietly moves over. The heart of dodging the light lies in this tiny angle."},"ICON-2265":{"nm":"Sand Shovel Blade Tip Cap","on":"cap","de":"Slip it over the sharp blade tip and your bag stays safe. Set aside the bravado of digging sand for a moment, and with one cap it becomes a gentle toy. Knowing how to hide your edge is a kindness too."},"ICON-2266":{"nm":"Beach Mat Corner Clip","on":"clip","de":"When the wind tries to lift the mat's corner, I bite down hard. Holding a single spot on the sand comes down to the stubbornness of all four corners. A flutter-free afternoon is the work of small clips."},"ICON-2267":{"nm":"Parasol-Shade Clothes Hook","on":"hook","de":"Hang it casually on the parasol pole and wet clothes dry in the shade. Out of the sun, into the breeze, a makeshift clothesline set up by a single hook. Even at the beach, the wisdom of housekeeping abides."},"ICON-2268":{"nm":"Waterproof Phone Neck Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Cradle a phone and hang it round your neck, and you find the courage to take photos even underwater. Keeping that wish to capture one more shot safe and dry. As a bodyguard of memories, it's quite the sturdy one."},"ICON-2269":{"nm":"Wet Clothes Waterproof Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"It takes in your changed-out wet clothes whole, without complaint. Letting not a single drop touch the rest of your gear is its pride, so it keeps its mouth shut tight and guards a corner of the bag. A clean finish starts with me."},"ICON-2270":{"nm":"Water Sandal Instep Strap","on":"strap","de":"It gently wraps the instep so the barefoot sandal won't slip off. Scamper across the sand all you like, one strap and you're at ease. A reliable companion to your steps, unnoticed yet always by your side."},"ICON-2271":{"nm":"Waterproof Card Neck Case","on":"case","de":"Holding tickets and cards, it hangs round your neck and joins the water play. Splash to your heart's content with no fear of dropping anything, for it shields the cards with its own body. The posture of a trusty bodyguard."},"ICON-2272":{"nm":"Goggle Anti-Fog Cloth Pouch","on":"goggle anti-fog cloth pouch","de":"Wipe the misted inside of your goggles once with the cloth, and the underwater world turns crisp again. A single little cloth pouch is the key that clears a clouded view."},"ICON-2273":{"nm":"Wet-Sand Brush","on":"brush","de":"It gently sweeps away even the sand between your toes. The last hand that tidies up the traces of a joyful romp through the sea, right at your doorstep. One pass of the brush, and a day's worth of sand finally bids farewell."},"ICON-2274":{"nm":"Waterproof Coin Zip Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"It locks a few coins snugly behind a zipper. Soaked or not, the jingle stays the same, so the emergency snack-stand money is guarded to the end. A small pouch, but a thrifty, capable one."},"ICON-2275":{"nm":"Towel Roll Tie","on":"strap","de":"Roll up a towel, bind it with one tie, and it clips right onto your bag strap. Hands free, towel on your shoulder. The secret to packing light for water play hides in this little bundle."},"ICON-2276":{"nm":"Waterproof Band Key-Ring Cap","on":"cap","de":"The finishing button on the band that guards a key from the water. Only when the cap clicks shut do you finally dive into the pool at ease. A small but flawless period that takes charge of sealing the lock."},"ICON-2277":{"nm":"Snorkel Mouthpiece Plug","on":"snorkel mouthpiece plug","de":"Bite it and your airway opens, and the seascape draws right up to your eyes. A little plug that lets you breathe even beneath the water. Who knew lending a breath could be this thrilling."},"ICON-2278":{"nm":"Mask Anti-Fog Pad","on":"pad","de":"When the inside of the mask clouds up, the underwater sightseeing goes flat too. A single pad holds off that haze, so a crisp view is the work of this one unseen layer."},"ICON-2279":{"nm":"Fin Toe Tightening Clip","on":"clip","de":"It cinches the fin tip to fit your foot just right, so you kick the water with no slack. So that the force in a single kick doesn't leak away, the clip quietly ties a snug little knot at the toe."},"ICON-2280":{"nm":"Mask Strap Cover","on":"cover","de":"It softly wraps the mask strap so it won't tug at your hair. A single layer of thoughtfulness that erases that stinging moment every time you take it off. What a small cover looks after is, surprisingly, tenderness."},"ICON-2281":{"nm":"Snorkel Purge Valve Cap","on":"cap","de":"Even in the act of holding a breath, there's a gap where water quietly leaks. One small valve gently steers that trickle back out and guards your room to inhale to the very end. The sea remembers this small bit of diligence most gratefully."},"ICON-2282":{"nm":"Fin Storage Hook","on":"hook","de":"When fins hang neatly on a single hook driven into the wall, a settled calm descends even on the cluttered gear room. Putting things in their place is the quietest promise toward the next dive."},"ICON-2283":{"nm":"Mask Nose-Pocket Pad","on":"pad","de":"A single pad that gently presses the nose. Thanks to this small tenderness that blocks the water from rushing in, the face keeps its expression even in the cold sea."},"ICON-2284":{"nm":"Snorkel Top Guard","on":"snorkel top guard","de":"The guard wrapped round the snorkel's tip quietly pushes back the water when waves wash over. The more unseen a part's work, the more deeply it upholds the safety of a single breath."},"ICON-2285":{"nm":"Fin Sole Anti-Slip Strip","on":"strip","de":"A slender strip stuck to the fin's sole. It's the one line of friction your toes cling to so you won't slip on a wet deck. Safety always begins quietly in small textures like this."},"ICON-2286":{"nm":"Air Tank Valve Cap","on":"air tank valve cap","de":"A cap that covers the valve of a tank brimming with air. So dust can't settle, so the airway stays unsoiled. Covering it is caring in advance, all the way down to the next person's first breath."},"ICON-2287":{"nm":"Regulator Mouthpiece Cap","on":"cap","de":"The spot that touches your lips must always be the cleanest. This single cap over the mouthpiece silently guards the gateway of breath from salt wind and sand."},"ICON-2288":{"nm":"Wetsuit Zipper Pull Loop","on":"loop","de":"A short pull loop fastened to the wetsuit zipper. It's a thoughtful touch added so even hands numbed by cold water can yank it up in one go. Even fastening clothes carries someone's careful thought."},"ICON-2289":{"nm":"Air Gauge Protective Cap","on":"protective cap","de":"The protective cap wrapping the glass of the gauge that tells you the air remaining. Because those numbers must never blur. The more a dial reads life itself, the more carefully it's wiped clean and covered."},"ICON-2290":{"nm":"Weight Belt Buckle","on":"weight belt buckle","de":"People wrap weight round their waists to descend into the depths. In the instant a single buckle unlocks and locks, the choice between rising and sinking gathers quietly at the fingertips."},"ICON-2291":{"nm":"Dive Lantern Wrist Strap","on":"strap","de":"In the pitch-dark water, one strap tied round the wrist holds the lantern fast. Let go and the light still follows. Not losing a small glow amid the darkness is, for that reason, reassuring."},"ICON-2292":{"nm":"Breathing Hose Tidy Clip","on":"clip","de":"A small clip that gathers scattered hoses into one. Prevent tangles in advance and your hands won't fumble even in an urgent moment. Tidying up is a quiet kindness to your future self."},"ICON-2293":{"nm":"Dive Glove Fingertip Reinforcement","on":"dive glove fingertip reinforcement","de":"Reinforcing fabric layered over each fingertip. The spots that pull ropes and grip rocks are bound to wear first, so an extra layer was laid down to embrace that wear ahead of time."},"ICON-2294":{"nm":"Air Tank Base Ring","on":"ring","de":"A single base ring that holds a heavy tank upright. It cradles a weight that might otherwise topple, offering balance with its round embrace. To support is to lend your side so something won't fall."},"ICON-2295":{"nm":"Surfboard Fin Cap","on":"cap","de":"A cap that wraps the sharp tip of the fin beneath the board. So you won't get hurt walking the sand, it puts the wave-slicing blade-tip to rest for a while. While resting, anyone is allowed to go dull."},"ICON-2296":{"nm":"Paddle Blade Tip Guard Cap","on":"protective cap","de":"A protective cap guarding the tip of the paddle blade. It blocks scrapes from rocks from disturbing the flow of water. Cherish the tip, and a single stroke carries you farther."},"ICON-2297":{"nm":"Kayak Paddle Grip","on":"kayak paddle grip","de":"A grip wound where palm meets paddle. It softly cushions the spot where blisters used to form, so your hands won't come to resent the paddle even while pushing upriver."},"ICON-2298":{"nm":"Surf Wax Storage Tin","on":"surf wax storage tin","de":"A small tin can that holds a lump of wax. That magic which fastens your feet to the board is always drawn from this palm-sized case. Today's preparation begins with one tidy little tin."},"ICON-2299":{"nm":"Leash Ankle Tightening Loop","on":"loop","de":"The loop that cinches the leash linking ankle to board. A single knot vowing it won't let go of you even when swept up by a big wave. Connection is a promise to hold on so you won't drift too far away."},"ICON-2300":{"nm":"Paddleboard Air Plug","on":"paddleboard air plug","de":"A board that firms up when filled with air, and the plug that seals that breath. Open it and it folds flat, close it and it stands upon the water. A single small plug holds a day that swells and deflates."},"ICON-2301":{"nm":"Kayak Seat Cushion Strap","on":"strap","de":"A strap that binds the cushion to the seat. For the back and waist that paddle while seated long, it holds the softness in place so it won't slide away. Even comfort needs a firm knot."},"ICON-2302":{"nm":"Surfboard Nose Bumper","on":"surfboard nose bumper","de":"A bumper wrapping the board's prow. It's padding added to the nose, where collisions are frequent, so it would go dull first. To place softness at the spot that leads is a vow to use it long."},"ICON-2303":{"nm":"Waterproof Bag Closure Buckle","on":"waterproof bag closure buckle","de":"A buckle you fold and fasten two, three times over to let not a single drop in. Keeping precious things dry always takes one more touch of the hand. That one firm cinch becomes peace of mind."},"ICON-2304":{"nm":"Futsal Goal Net Piece","on":"futsal goal net piece","de":"A single piece of the net that once shook the goalmouth. It remembers, thread by thread, the cheers of the moment a ball filled it. A goal lived in every knot, and in every frayed spot that day's match still lives on."},"ICON-2305":{"nm":"Soccer Ball Pump Nozzle","on":"nozzle","de":"A pump nozzle that breathes air into a deflated ball. The leather that rolled about, all flat and dispirited, springs and bounces once more. To fill it up is to raise a halted game back onto its feet."},"ICON-2306":{"nm":"Corner Flag Base","on":"base","de":"A base that stands a flag upright at the corner of the field. It's a small marker of the boundary, but with that one point, the dirt ground finally takes on the shape of a stadium."},"ICON-2307":{"nm":"Shin Guard Strap","on":"strap","de":"A strap that binds the shin guard to the calf. It holds fast the spot that takes frequent knocks, so each step stays unafraid even amid rough tussles."},"ICON-2308":{"nm":"Stud Replacement Pin","on":"pin","de":"A pin for swapping a worn-out stud for a new one. The little teeth at the toe that grip the turf. To keep from slipping, sometimes you must rebuild from the ground up."},"ICON-2309":{"nm":"Soccer Ball Valve Cap","on":"cap","de":"A small valve cap that seals the ball's breathing hole. It guards the entrance so the air you filled in won't leak out. Keeping it taut is much like not losing your edge until the next match."},"ICON-2310":{"nm":"Line Marker Cone","on":"line marker cone","de":"A cone that draws lines on the ground to divide the way. This far is our side, from there is theirs. One small cone turns a messy empty lot into a playground with rules."},"ICON-2311":{"nm":"Futsal Shoe Dust Brush","on":"brush","de":"A brush that sweeps the dirt and dust caught in the grooves of futsal shoes. When the match ends, a day's worth of dirt piles onto the shoes too. The brushing hand is a quiet thank-you to feet that ran so well."},"ICON-2312":{"nm":"Goalkeeper Glove Hanger","on":"goalkeeper glove hanger","de":"A hanger that dries and holds the goalkeeper's gloves. It's where the sweat-soaked hands rest a while, as many as the shots they stopped. For the next match, the wet dries and the hardened heart slowly loosens."},"ICON-2313":{"nm":"Basketball Rim Net Loops","on":"loop","de":"The small loops that hang the net from the rim. Because of these, the ball makes that soft swish as it passes through. That crisp sound of a score actually begins at these little hooks."},"ICON-2314":{"nm":"Basketball Air Release Tool","on":"basketball air release tool","de":"A tool that lets a little air out of an overly firm ball. Too much tautness makes the bounce wild. Easing it just right. A ball with a good feel is always born from that proper balance."},"ICON-2315":{"nm":"Backboard Sensor Pad","on":"pad","de":"A sensor pad stuck behind the backboard. It reads the instant the ball touches, clearly, in numbers. Even the moment the eye missed, this small sense remembers, so the call grows that much fairer."},"ICON-2316":{"nm":"Dribble Obstacle Cones","on":"dribble obstacle cones","de":"Obstacle cones lined up along the dribbling path. Weaving this way and that between them, footwork grows. To stand in the way is also a kindness, teaching how to slip through even better."},"ICON-2317":{"nm":"Basketball Valve Brush","on":"brush","de":"A small brush that cleans out the ball's valve hole. If dust clogs it, the needle won't go in, so you clean from the unseen entrance first. Before filling, you always empty and wipe."},"ICON-2318":{"nm":"Finger Taping Roll","on":"finger taping roll","de":"A roll of tape wound round the fingers. It holds a sprained joint firmly, lending the courage to grip the ball again. Wrapping a wound is a small declaration that you won't stop."},"ICON-2319":{"nm":"Jersey Number Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clip that fastens the back number to the jersey. In place of your name, a number roams the court. In that one firm pinch so it won't fall off, who is playing today is clearly written down."},"ICON-2320":{"nm":"Shooting Practice Target Ring","on":"ring","de":"A target ring fitted inside the rim to narrow the aim. It shrinks the spot the ball must enter, training you to endure misses. Throw toward that narrow gate long enough and your fingertips quietly learn precision."},"ICON-2321":{"nm":"Basketball Shoe Sole Wiper","on":"basketball shoe sole wiper","de":"Before stepping onto the court, you crouch and wipe your soles first. Because you don't want to leave a single slip on the hardwood. Plant that first step with clean toes, and today's you is a little sturdier than yesterday's."},"ICON-2322":{"nm":"Volleyball Net Tension Loop","on":"loop","de":"Tautness can't be seen. Only in the moment the loop pulls the cord to its end and stops does the net divide the court in two with a hand's-breadth of tension. A balance held by an unseen hand awakens the game."},"ICON-2323":{"nm":"Antenna Fixing Clip","on":"clip","de":"The antenna that kept swaying in the wind stands straight with one clip. A small thing holding back a great wobble. The hand that quietly secures a single cable backstage moves with just this much heart."},"ICON-2324":{"nm":"Libero Vest Hanger","on":"libero vest hanger","de":"The defense specialist's different-colored vest hangs on the wall, awaiting the next match. Not flashy, yet a name that upholds the whole court: the libero. There, in the lowest spot, are the eyes that see the farthest."},"ICON-2325":{"nm":"Knee Pad Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"The more you roll across the floor, the more often your knees take a hit. This little pouch that neatly stows the pads knows: only those who first learn how to fall well, in the end, soar the farthest."},"ICON-2326":{"nm":"Volleyball Pressure Gauge","on":"volleyball pressure gauge","de":"You can't tell by a flick of the fingertip. The gauge needle trembles faintly and points to a single mark. Measuring the breath of one ball is the first button of the match. From honest pressure, an honest arc is born."},"ICON-2327":{"nm":"Dodgeball Line Tape","on":"dodgeball line tape","de":"A single circle drawn on the field's dirt with tape. Its inside and outside divide a half-day's universe of tag. The hand that drew the line knows: rules are the very start of play."},"ICON-2328":{"nm":"Referee Whistle Rest","on":"rest","de":"When the sharp whistle falls silent, it's set quietly back in its place on the rest. The spot that hears the referee's breath closest. Fairness always begins with the small task of keeping one's place."},"ICON-2329":{"nm":"Toss Practice Wall Target","on":"toss practice wall target","de":"In the dawn with no one to receive, you loft your fingertips thousands of times toward the target on the wall. The wall is the most forgiving teammate. The ball it returns lifts a weary you back up again."},"ICON-2330":{"nm":"Net Height Measuring Rod","on":"rod","de":"If the net is even a finger lower, the game goes astray. In the moment you raise the measuring rod, fairness becomes not a number but a daily habit. Unseen precision guards the court."},"ICON-2331":{"nm":"Starting Block Angle Pin","on":"pin","de":"From the crouched stance, the angle where toes meet the block, that one degree decides the start. With a single pin you fix the block and steady your breath. The posture of the start follows you quietly all the way to the finish."},"ICON-2332":{"nm":"Track Lane Number Flag","on":"track lane number flag","de":"A small flag planted in each lane waves its number in the wind. Run all in the same direction, yet each has a separate path. The track embraces side-by-side sameness and difference all at once."},"ICON-2333":{"nm":"Relay Baton End Cap","on":"relay baton end cap","de":"For the moment it will meet the last runner's hand, the end cap rounds off the corners. In a relay, the most precious thing is not speed but the hand you pass to the next person."},"ICON-2334":{"nm":"Record Measuring Tape Hanger","on":"record measuring tape hanger","de":"You hang the tape measure that recorded the marks on the wall so it won't tangle. The spot where yesterday's distance and today's hang side by side. Growth always arrives first as a small difference in numbers."},"ICON-2335":{"nm":"Track Curve Marker Cone","on":"track curve marker cone","de":"A small cone set on the inside of the curve tells you the way's intent. Don't cut too far in, don't scatter too far out. The one who rounds it well, in the end, leads at the front."},"ICON-2336":{"nm":"Finish Line Ribbon Clip","on":"clip","de":"That ribbon which will first touch a chest, the clip holds taut and waits. A line that exists to be broken. It endures the wind all day for someone's single second."},"ICON-2337":{"nm":"Starting Gun Cover","on":"starting gun cover","de":"Until the bang of the signal rings out, the muzzle sleeps beneath its cover. A vessel of sound holding the start within. The deeper the silence, the farther the echo of the first shot carries."},"ICON-2338":{"nm":"Hurdle Height Adjustment Pin","on":"pin","de":"Each time you raise the height a notch, the pin's place shifts to follow. And fear grows by just that much too. Even so, the feet gauge a slightly higher spot each time and run on."},"ICON-2339":{"nm":"Lap Counter Dial","on":"dial","de":"When you lose track of how many laps remain, you turn the dial a notch. The small click of a shrinking number puts strength back into your legs. The hand that counts the distance left keeps your pace."},"ICON-2340":{"nm":"Pole Storage Stand","on":"pole storage stand","de":"A long, swaying pole needs a place of its own to lean. Because it's a tool that must bend to leap, you stand it with extra care. Well-kept flexibility holds the highest of leaps."},"ICON-2341":{"nm":"Sand Pit Leveling Rake","on":"sand pit leveling rake","de":"Slowly you rake even the footprints the previous athlete left. The sand pit grows flat again, like the first time, every round. The hand that erases traces for someone's leap is there, steadfast and silent."},"ICON-2342":{"nm":"Approach Run Distance Marker Strip","on":"strip","de":"A step short won't do, and a step too many won't either. The distance marker strip on the ground honestly tells you where to plant your foot. A good approach run isn't reckless greed but calm calculation."},"ICON-2343":{"nm":"Discus Grip","on":"discus grip","de":"If the fingers slip, the throw is thrown before you ever throw it. The rough texture of the grip wrapping the discus holds the spin in check. The timing of release always begins in the sense of the hold."},"ICON-2344":{"nm":"Shot Put Cradle Ring","on":"ring","de":"A cradle ring quietly holds the heavy iron ball so it won't roll away. A small nest that keeps the stillness just before the throw. The more explosive the force, the firmer its resting place must be."},"ICON-2345":{"nm":"Javelin Tip Guard Cap","on":"protective cap","de":"A cap slipped over the sharp javelin tip covers it in soft silence. When a tool meant to fly far lies quietly still, danger is tamed by thoughtfulness. Safety lives even in storage."},"ICON-2346":{"nm":"High Jump Bar Support Catch","on":"high jump bar support catch","de":"So the crossbar won't fall even at a slight touch, the catch holds it with exquisite balance. The spot in charge of that trembling line between clearing and not. Fairness dwells in the small details."},"ICON-2347":{"nm":"Landing Mat Corner Anchor","on":"landing mat corner anchor","de":"If the corner of the landing mat lifts, someone gets hurt. The anchor presses all four corners down firmly. So the body that flew highest lands most safely, it props it up, unseen."},"ICON-2348":{"nm":"Throwing Circle Boundary Tape","on":"throwing circle boundary tape","de":"The boundary of the throwing spot is drawn with a single line of tape. Whether you step on that line or not, a record lives or dies. The slender single line where freedom and rules meet, a promise."},"ICON-2349":{"nm":"Balance Beam Rubber Foot","on":"foot","de":"So the narrow balance beam won't wobble, the rubber foot grips the floor tight. The tremble-free balance unfolded atop it is, in truth, made by the unseen firmness below."},"ICON-2350":{"nm":"Horizontal Bar Grip Wrap","on":"horizontal bar grip wrap","de":"So the palm won't slip, you wind a wrap onto the horizontal bar's grip. The secret of the whirling rotation lies not in flair but in a tightly clenched hand. The sweat dropped onto the mat knows it."},"ICON-2351":{"nm":"Ring Strap Height Catch","on":"ring strap height catch","de":"If the two straps differ in height by even a palm's width, the routine collapses. The catch silently holds that balance. Only atop a precisely matched height does free flight finally begin."},"ICON-2352":{"nm":"Pommel Horse Handle Cover","on":"cover","de":"The cover wrapping the handle wards off blisters on the palm. Beneath the whirling, spinning routine is a hand that has scraped and healed countless times. Protection is a gentle promise toward the next practice."},"ICON-2353":{"nm":"Uneven Bars Spacing Pin","on":"pin","de":"You set the gap between the two bars precisely with a pin. That empty space the body will cross becomes the stage. The fingertips know first: atop a precise distance, the boldest leap is born."},"ICON-2354":{"nm":"Vault Springboard Spring Cap","on":"cap","de":"The instant you kick off the board, the spring thrusts the body skyward. The cap snugly wraps the force of that bounce. The shortest approach run makes the longest flight through the air."},"ICON-2355":{"nm":"Magnesium Chalk Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"The white powder you rub on your hands is a small charm that erases slipping. The brief ritual of dipping a hand into the pouch and out settles your fear. Even nerves, in the end, are tamed at the fingertips."},"ICON-2356":{"nm":"Gymnastics Band Wrist Wrap","on":"gymnastics band wrist wrap","de":"Winding the band round the wrist cinches the strings of the heart along with it. Holding a joint that would waver in advance. One well-bound wrist quietly permits a bolder rotation."},"ICON-2357":{"nm":"Trapeze Safety Loop","on":"loop","de":"Just before flinging the body into the air, the safety loop becomes an unseen hand. Only when the fear of falling vanishes can you fly the farthest. Trust completes the flight."},"ICON-2358":{"nm":"Tennis Ball Can Storage Cap","on":"cap","de":"Beneath the cap that seals the can's mouth, new balls sleep, holding their pressure. The small pop of opening a can awakens the thrill of the match. A seal is a promise that keeps freshness."},"ICON-2359":{"nm":"Racket String Tension Clamp","on":"clamp","de":"The clamp bites the string's tautness firmly and won't let go to the very end. Because one string's tension decides the ball's rebound. That unseen feel begins at this small clamp."},"ICON-2360":{"nm":"Tennis Court Line Sweeper","on":"tennis court line sweeper","de":"When the match ends, you slowly sweep along the court's white lines. Clear away the dust and the lines turn crisp again. Paving the path for the next match, that final care revives the court."},"ICON-2361":{"nm":"Racket Head Guard Tape","on":"racket head guard tape","de":"Wrap once round the racket's rim and even rough collisions are taken in roundly. I know the edge is the spot that wears first. Because taking on that wearing in your stead is my part, today too I stand at the very outside."},"ICON-2362":{"nm":"Indoor Air Temperature Chip","on":"chip","de":"The cold dawn wind that rushes in when the door opens, a palm-sized chip reads it before any person does. To sense it before your nose even chills, it's the quietest greeting that opens the day in an empty gym."},"ICON-2363":{"nm":"Baseline Foot Plate","on":"plate","de":"For the athlete unsure where to set a toe, a single line drawn on the ground is enough. The line not to be crossed becomes the very start line for the farthest leap, the foot plate silently tells you."},"ICON-2364":{"nm":"Tennis Ball Basket Hanger","on":"tennis ball basket hanger","de":"It holds dozens of balls in one mouthful and never drops a single one. Gathering what's scattered across the court and handing it to the next practice, a hand quietly busy in the corner hangs here today too."},"ICON-2365":{"nm":"Racket Handle End Cap","on":"racket handle end cap","de":"The moment you pop it onto the handle's end, the racket finally nestles into your palm. One small cap divides slipping from assurance. Cap the end snugly, and the first swing turns firm."},"ICON-2366":{"nm":"Courtside Towel Clip","on":"clip","de":"Even when the wind blows fierce, it keeps its mouth shut and holds on courtside so the carefully wrung towel won't fly off. Even guarding a brief breather to catch your breath, someone's deft fingertips have been at work."},"ICON-2367":{"nm":"Shuttlecock Feather Straightening Clip","on":"clip","de":"One ruffled feather and the flight wavers. Gently straighten the crumpled wing and the shuttlecock readies to fly true again. Going far always begins with small grooming like this."},"ICON-2368":{"nm":"Shuttlecock Tube Cap","on":"shuttlecock tube cap","de":"So the shuttlecocks lined up inside won't go soft, you plug the tube's end firmly. I've watched long enough to know a single touch of damp slumps a feather. Keeping things well-stored is already part of the match."},"ICON-2369":{"nm":"Ping-Pong Ball Roll Rest","on":"rest","de":"The little ball that came rolling along catches its breath a while atop me. Quietly propping it up so it won't tumble off, it's the roundest-shaped kindness offered beside the table."},"ICON-2370":{"nm":"Table Tennis Rubber Roller","on":"table tennis rubber roller","de":"Roll the roller gently over the rubber face and old dust lifts away while the tackiness revives. The spin must live for the ball to curve. The racket's condition today awakens with this one tender bit of care."},"ICON-2371":{"nm":"Net Height Measuring Stick","on":"stick","de":"If the net is even a hand's-breadth higher, the texture of the game changes. People who refuse, in the end, to trust the eye bring me up against it. Fairness, it seems, comes only from a height measured exactly by the rule."},"ICON-2372":{"nm":"Shuttlecock Speed Sensor Chip","on":"chip","de":"The speed of a shuttlecock slicing the air, I quietly reckon. When the once-invisible speed settles into a clear number, the coach's next word grows that much clearer. It's the work of turning a hunch into fact."},"ICON-2373":{"nm":"Ping-Pong Ball Storage Capsule","on":"ping-pong ball storage capsule","de":"Lay a round ball softly into the capsule and scratches and dust retreat far away. Wishing it safe until the next match, it's the heart that gives over a whole little room."},"ICON-2374":{"nm":"Badminton Racket String Hanger","on":"badminton racket string hanger","de":"Hang the loosened strings neatly and the next hand in line won't fumble. Tidying up is, after all, like a kind note written in advance to tomorrow's you. Today eases tomorrow."},"ICON-2375":{"nm":"Table Tennis Racket Edge Guard Tape","on":"table tennis racket edge guard tape","de":"The edge where the rubber easily lifts, I quietly hug in a single line. If the rim splits, even the ball's texture goes astray. Guarding the edge becomes, in the end, guarding a single point."},"ICON-2376":{"nm":"Squash Ball Warming Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A cold ball hardly bounces at all. Before the match, a pouch that warms and cradles it like a palm. That small warmth passed to the hand sets the breath and rhythm of a round in advance."},"ICON-2377":{"nm":"Lacrosse Mesh Net Clip","on":"clip","de":"When a mesh knot starts quietly to loosen, I bite down on that one stitch without a word. The mesh must be taut for the ball to stay. Here is the hand that holds the whole game together from an unseen spot."},"ICON-2378":{"nm":"Squash Racket Tip Guard Tape","on":"squash racket tip guard tape","de":"The harder you swing at the wall, the more the racket weeps first from its tip. Gently wrap that weeping tip and it plays alongside you one more season. The one who knows to spare the tip, in the end, holds the racket long."},"ICON-2379":{"nm":"Hockey Stick Blade Cover","on":"hockey stick blade cover","de":"Slip the cover over the sharp blade and finally both your bag and your fingertips rest at ease. Quietly putting a dangerous thing to sleep, it's the old courtesy you observe first when packing up a stick."},"ICON-2380":{"nm":"Cricket Ball Polishing Cloth","on":"cricket ball polishing cloth","de":"Rub the red ball with the cloth and one side holds the light like a mirror. The bowler knows by the sense in the fingertips that the ball curves when the shine lives. A quiet strategy dwells even in careful polishing."},"ICON-2381":{"nm":"Lacrosse Ball Storage Tube Cap","on":"cap","de":"So the hard balls won't roll off as they please, you plug the tube's mouth snugly. Coaxing things prone to scattering into one place, the basics of running things are always this small."},"ICON-2382":{"nm":"Squash Wall Target Piece","on":"squash wall target piece","de":"A small target set in the wall draws the athlete's wavering eyes to a single point. The one point that tells you where to aim, even that broad wall narrows into a clear bullseye before this little piece."},"ICON-2383":{"nm":"Hockey Stick Grip Sleeve","on":"hockey stick grip sleeve","de":"Transfer the grip your hand knows onto an unfamiliar new stick, and in that moment the tool becomes yours at once. A small sleeve that lets you slip familiarity right on, this is the shortcut to settling in."},"ICON-2384":{"nm":"Field Goal Net Hanger","on":"field goal net hanger","de":"Hang the net on the goal and a goal finally becomes goal-like. It was always the net that held to the very end that brief moment a ball filled it. At the spot that catches the shape of bursting cheers, I am there."},"ICON-2385":{"nm":"Skate Blade Cover","on":"skate blade cover","de":"With the blade bared, you can't trust a single step off the ice. Once you leave the ice, please slip me on. Putting sharpness gently to sleep is an etiquette skaters have long upheld."},"ICON-2386":{"nm":"Skate Lace Hanger","on":"skate lace hanger","de":"The long laces of the boots you took off, you hang neatly, one by one. Laces loosened so they won't tangle smoothly open the next time on the ice. Today's finish becomes, just so, the preparation for tomorrow."},"ICON-2387":{"nm":"Skate Blade Towel","on":"skate blade towel","de":"On a blade just off the ice, tiny droplets gather and bead. Wipe that moisture away gently and rust passes it by. Quietly collecting the traces the cold left behind, that is my day."},"ICON-2388":{"nm":"Skate Boot Ankle Pad","on":"pad","de":"Let the ankle waver once and the whole glide collapses. A pad that wraps it firmly and holds the footing fast. That graceful balance on the ice always begins first, unseen."},"ICON-2389":{"nm":"Skate Blade Guard Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"There's a small pouch in a corner of the bag to tuck the blade guard away neatly. The habit of packing what's needed, leaving nothing out, keeps gear alive long. A tidy bag is the first scene of a good glide."},"ICON-2390":{"nm":"Skate Boot Insole Clip","on":"clip","de":"So the insole inside the boot won't quietly slide out, it holds fast underfoot. If the spot you plant on slips, the jump goes astray too. The hand that grips the lowest place, in the end, aids the highest leap."},"ICON-2391":{"nm":"Skate Blade Cover Loop","on":"loop","de":"So the cover won't slip off, you fasten it tight with a loop. I know a loose protection is, in the end, no protection at all. One well-fastened loop guards that blade to the very end."},"ICON-2392":{"nm":"Skate Lace Tightening Cap","on":"cap","de":"Pull the laces tight and lock them with the cap, and now they'll never come undone. Cinching it up snugly with no gap from the very toe, it's the sturdiest knot tied before that first step onto the ice."},"ICON-2393":{"nm":"Skate Blade Drying Cloth","on":"skate blade drying cloth","de":"From a blade that's just finished a glide, you gently gather the gathered moisture. I know a blade left wet weeps. Only a blade dried soft draws the next curve clearly upon the ice."},"ICON-2394":{"nm":"Ski Pole Grip Cap","on":"cap","de":"Softly wrap the end of the pole grip and the gripping palm grows that much easier. The force that slices the snowfield comes, in the end, from that firmly held spot. One small cap upholds a long descent to the end."},"ICON-2395":{"nm":"Snowboard Binding Pin","on":"pin","de":"The instant the small pin linking board to foot slips out, the mountain before you halts. A piece you must check first though it's hard to spot, this firm connection becomes freedom upon the snow."},"ICON-2396":{"nm":"Ski Edge Tip Guard Clip","on":"clip","de":"So the sharp edge won't scratch the inside of your bag, you bite down gently on the tip. Soothing the sharpness to sleep, it's the kind finish you offer after a good run down the mountain."},"ICON-2397":{"nm":"Snowboard Nose Guard","on":"snowboard nose guard","de":"Wrap the board's nose snugly and even a head-on collision scatters softly. Silently guarding the spot that strikes first, the courage to face a steep descent begins right here."},"ICON-2398":{"nm":"Ski Boot Buckle Cover","on":"cover","de":"So the buckle won't be damaged knocking against the cold snow, you cover it gently. One more lock that guards the locking mechanism, this small cover quietly stretches the boot's season a little longer."},"ICON-2399":{"nm":"Snowboard Leash Loop","on":"loop","de":"So the board can't run far even if it leaves your hand, I link ankle and board in a single line. So that even if you lose your grip, you won't lose it for good, it's a quiet loop of reassurance hung at the end of a long cord."},"ICON-2400":{"nm":"Ski Base Scraper Tip","on":"ski base scraper tip","de":"The old wax caked onto the base, you scrape smoothly away. Only by clearing off the old does new glide come alive. A base tended with care opens the next snowfield that much faster."},"ICON-2401":{"nm":"Snowboard Deck Bumper","on":"snowboard deck bumper","de":"Before the board slices through the snow, the nose tip touches the world first. Every impact is taken by this little piece of rubber. Out front, wearing down without ever making a show of it—someone's downhill run glides over this blunt devotion."},"ICON-2402":{"nm":"Ski Pole Basket Ring","on":"ring","de":"Just as the pole is about to plunge deep into the snow, this round rim feels for the ground in its place. A circle that quietly steadies a step that nearly slipped. Unseen, it stays close like a hand keeping you from sliding."},"ICON-2403":{"nm":"Edge-Waxing Brush Cap","on":"cap","de":"When the grooming is done, it gently covers the bristles before the powder dries. Sealing today's softness so not a single fiber goes astray. So that when you open it next, yesterday's care is waiting just as it was."},"ICON-2404":{"nm":"Earmuff Hanger","on":"earmuff hanger","de":"Remember? The earmuffs briefly forgotten beside the bag once spring arrived. Yet on the night the first snowfall is announced, they're the first to be called. There's a special place to hang the season, and this hook never forgets that promise."},"ICON-2405":{"nm":"Sharpening Stone Case","on":"sharpening stone case","de":"To sharpen a blade, you must first wet the stone—a sequence steeped in like grandmother's touch. Even a tool that tames dullness needs a place to rest, so this little house cradles the stone and waits for the next grooming."},"ICON-2406":{"nm":"Wax Block Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"The very stuff that makes a brilliant glide lies packed tight and sleeping within. A solid heft, holding a hardened block. The glide always unwinds from this quiet weight and spreads across the snowfield."},"ICON-2407":{"nm":"Hand-Warmer Pouch Loop","on":"loop","de":"On a winter walk, the spot your fingers fumble for first inside your pocket. It gives a fixed home to the little warmth that thaws frozen hands. The colder the day, the kinder this little loop becomes."},"ICON-2408":{"nm":"Edge-Grinding Stone Rest","on":"rest","de":"If it wobbles, the blade goes crooked, so it fixes itself firmly first. A rest that never stirs, all to be responsible for another's precision. Someone's straight blade edge stands upon this quiet steadiness."},"ICON-2409":{"nm":"Neck Warmer Clip","on":"clip","de":"On a cold, windy walk to school, the moment the neck warmer starts to slip—click, onto the collar. Even warmth must hold its place before it can truly warm. One small sound holds fast to the morning's heat."},"ICON-2410":{"nm":"Waxing Iron Cover","on":"cover","de":"While the surface that worked so hot cools down, a single cloth quietly shields it from dust. One tool looking after another that prepared the glide. Care carries on this quietly."},"ICON-2411":{"nm":"Edge-Oil Pen Cap","on":"cap","de":"Once it's opened and dries out, you can't draw the next line. So closing it is the same as opening the next—this little cap seals the moisture at the tip, promising tomorrow's stroke in advance."},"ICON-2412":{"nm":"Cheer Pom Top","on":"cheer pom top","de":"Hundreds of strands set off from this single point, scattering in unison to the beat. The splendor of the swaying always begins from a firmly fastened spot. Beneath the stage, the first knot that sends the crowd rippling."},"ICON-2413":{"nm":"Light Stick Hand Strap","on":"strap","de":"After two hours of cheering, the instant you nearly drop your light stick, this strap brings it back into your hand. The wish not to lose it even when it falls. That tender worry made a loop upon your wrist."},"ICON-2414":{"nm":"Stadium Cushion Folding Clasp","on":"stadium cushion folding clasp","de":"Springing up and sitting down dozens of times while cheering. In between, this little clasp neatly folds the cushion and keeps your spot. Even in a giddy crowd, there's a touch tucked in that minds someone's seat."},"ICON-2415":{"nm":"Cheer Bandana Loop","on":"loop","de":"On the day the same pattern spreads across every seat, a single cloth binds tens of thousands of hearts into one color. The first point where that wave begins is this little loop—the place where a cheer that was alone becomes us."},"ICON-2416":{"nm":"Clapper Paddle Half","on":"clapper paddle half","de":"Clap alone and it's a small sound; gathered across the stands, it becomes a wave. The one half that knows most honestly the truth that it only rings when it meets another. The moment your clap meets mine, the cheer grows."},"ICON-2417":{"nm":"Cheer Picket Corner Cap","on":"cap","de":"It wraps the sharp corner round, so the person beside you won't get hurt. Even in fervent waving, there's consideration tucked in for one another. A cheer grows warmer where it's this rounded."},"ICON-2418":{"nm":"Cheer Ribbon Pole Holder","on":"cheer ribbon pole holder","de":"Even when the fluttering stops, the pole stands straight, waiting for the next roar. A spot resting still for a moment so it can sway again. Between one cheer and the next, a brief silence where the ribbon catches its breath."},"ICON-2419":{"nm":"Cheer Megaphone Fan","on":"fan","de":"So one person's shout can reach all the way to the stage, the fan shape narrows the path of sound. A mouth that always ponders how to deliver, more than the size of the heart. A shape made by the longing to reach a little farther."},"ICON-2420":{"nm":"Badge Pin-Back Case","on":"badge pin-back case","de":"Before it's pinned to the chest and after it's taken off, the badge's rest begins and ends here. A little house that safely beds down the sharp back pin. Even a sparkling point needs a place to lie down and rest a while."},"ICON-2421":{"nm":"Scoreboard Number Plate","on":"scoreboard number plate","de":"It carries the care of an era when each goal was swapped in by hand. Before the digital age, the outcome was carved one slot at a time by human fingertips. A plate where even a single number held someone's thrill."},"ICON-2422":{"nm":"Tactic Board Magnet Piece","on":"tactic board magnet piece","de":"Following the coach's fingertips, defense and offense trade places. Every picture in the mind before the match is first drawn in the shifting of these little dots. The outcome is played out once, in advance, upon the board."},"ICON-2423":{"nm":"Scoreboard Glare Visor","on":"scoreboard glare visor","de":"So the dazzling numbers won't blur a player's sight, the visor cuts away the light. Even brightness must sometimes be shaded just right to do its job. In the brightest place, a shadow that works most quietly."},"ICON-2424":{"nm":"Score Flip Ring","on":"ring","de":"Each time a page flips over, the number changes and the cheers rise to follow. A trace of the analog era, when records were renewed by the feel of a hand. A time when, at the sound of the score turning over, the heart turned over too."},"ICON-2425":{"nm":"Tactic-Line Marker Pen Case","on":"tactic-line marker pen case","de":"Every route drawn on the locker room whiteboard comes from this pen. A small, sturdy holder cradling the blueprint of the match. In the silence before the showdown, the spot holding the most words."},"ICON-2426":{"nm":"Score Counter Clicker","on":"score counter clicker","de":"Each press adds one slot, the count rising with a clear click. Leave the numbers to your fingers, and your heart can turn wholly to the game. A little rhythm that lightens the burden of counting."},"ICON-2427":{"nm":"Scoreboard Cable Cover","on":"scoreboard cable cover","de":"Behind the brilliant light, there are always tangled, untidy wires. The work of neatly covering that mess. Only when the unseen places are kept tidy can the seen places finally shine."},"ICON-2428":{"nm":"Tactic Board Eraser Brush","on":"brush","de":"When one round ends, it clears the surface for the next picture. A new strategy can only ever begin upon an empty space. The erasing brush is, in truth, the first stroke of the next play."},"ICON-2429":{"nm":"Score Flag Clip","on":"clip","de":"It grips a flag about to fly off in the wind and won't let go. So the fluttering cloth keeps its place. Even the work of announcing records to the world needs first a hand to hold it steady."},"ICON-2430":{"nm":"Referee Whistle Cord Clip","on":"clip","de":"At a single whistle, the game stops and flows again. A little knot that fastens that authority firmly to the neck. Until the whistle sounds, keeping the silence neatly bound is also this clip's duty."},"ICON-2431":{"nm":"Tape Measure Reel","on":"tape measure reel","de":"It gathers the measured length back into itself. Measuring is, in the end, the repetition of unrolling and rolling up. A handle that aids that simple round trip without complaint, turning each time behind the precision."},"ICON-2432":{"nm":"Call Flag Folding Case","on":"call flag folding case","de":"The flag that firmly divided in from out, once the match ends, folds neatly and rests. Even that clear signal catches its breath a while for what comes next. Even decisiveness has its quiet rest."},"ICON-2433":{"nm":"Stopwatch Hanging Loop","on":"loop","de":"It hangs flowing time in one place, not on the wrist. Still before the measuring, then dashing off the moment it's called—a station for time. A little home for seconds, holding its breath, waiting for the start signal."},"ICON-2434":{"nm":"Field Line-Marker Wheel","on":"field line-marker wheel","de":"Wherever it rolls, a clear white path remains. The boundaries of the rules are carved onto the ground like this, one neat turn at a time. Before the game begins, the wheel that leaves the first footprint on the field."},"ICON-2435":{"nm":"Referee Card Pocket","on":"pocket","de":"At the moment of decision, the card drawn from the chest sleeps here. The waiting room of a ruling that stays silent to the very end until it's shown. A pocket always ready and waiting, hoping never to be drawn from."},"ICON-2436":{"nm":"Scale Weight Rest","on":"rest","de":"The work of weighing is honest only upon an unshaking floor. A rest that bears the weight while offering its own body up flat. The first step of accurate measurement always begins from a quiet place."},"ICON-2437":{"nm":"Starter Clicker","on":"starter clicker","de":"At a single sound, every foot pushes off the ground at once. The start is ever so brief, but the hand that makes that brevity is calmer than anyone. A hand that releases the trembling of the starting line with just one click."},"ICON-2438":{"nm":"Field Cone Base","on":"base","de":"The name may be unfamiliar, but its job is clear—it weightily holds up the center of a field like a stage. At the center where everyone shines, there's always one unseen leg quietly enduring."},"ICON-2439":{"nm":"Diaphragm Breathing Belt Buckle","on":"diaphragm breathing belt buckle","de":"Good sound comes not from the throat but from a deep breath, and the waist knows it first. A buckle that lets your palm feel the belly swell and fall. The starting point of a song is always beneath this one breath."},"ICON-2440":{"nm":"Breath-Practice Feather Plate","on":"plate","de":"When the feather sways at your breath, it's a sign your breathing is steady. Gently giving shape to the unseen breath, it teaches the foundation of song. A practice that learns, with the eyes, the breath before the first note."},"ICON-2441":{"nm":"Inhale Sand Timer","on":"inhale sand timer","de":"Inside the glass, sand flows down like a breath. Breathe in, pause a moment, breathe slowly out—the grains count the rhythm for you. Watch the soundless falling sand a while, and somehow your scattered breathing falls neatly into line."},"ICON-2442":{"nm":"Candle-Practice Stand","on":"stand","de":"Light the wick, and your voice trembles along with the flickering flame. Someone carved this spot with care, to hold that small tremor for a while. As thick as the wax that hardened and built up, here pool the nights spent singing alone."},"ICON-2443":{"nm":"Belly-Press Cushion Strap","on":"strap","de":"Instead of laying a hand on the belly, a single strap quietly presses that spot. It pulls taut when the breath swells and loosens softly when it's all emptied out. A silent little companion at your side, helping the body remember the rhythm first."},"ICON-2444":{"nm":"Breath-Hold Balloon Cap","on":"cap","de":"Don't blow the balloon out all at once. Long, slow, push it all the way to the end. As you bite the cap and let the air out, the air reaches the deepest part of your lungs. A song, in the end, flies as far as the length of breath you held."},"ICON-2445":{"nm":"Breath-Steadying Grip","on":"grip","de":"The more the heart wavers, the more the hand wants to clutch something. Grasp this grip and your shoulders slide down, your inhale grows a hand's-width longer. Learning how to grip is learning how to compose yourself, your palm knows it first."},"ICON-2446":{"nm":"Ab-Vibration Band Loop","on":"loop","de":"Hook the band to the loop and a gentle vibration spreads to the center of your belly. Strength gathers quietly in the very spot that quivers when you laugh hard. A firm center always grows slowly like this, in a place no one sees."},"ICON-2447":{"nm":"Inhale-Count Dial","on":"plate","de":"One, two, three—each time the dial clicks over a notch, the depth of the breath you drew is carved in. Add one notch and the song holds one phrase longer. On this little dial, the lung capacity you built today is quietly recorded."},"ICON-2448":{"nm":"Tongue-Exercise Spoon Plate","on":"plate","de":"The spots where your tongue tip should land are clearly marked on the plate. How to roll, flick, and pause for a moment. Behind smoothly flowing pronunciation lie countless dawns where the tongue memorized its path like this."},"ICON-2449":{"nm":"Mouth-Shape Mirror Clip","on":"clip","de":"The clip gently holds the mouth shape reflected in the mirror. 'Ah' is round, 'ee' stretches wide to the sides. A quiet lesson of just you and the mirror, refining the shape of sound while facing your own face head-on."},"ICON-2450":{"nm":"Diction Cork Seal","on":"diction cork seal","de":"A little seal carved from cork sits on the corner of the desk, listening to pronunciation. On nights when the 'r' keeps slipping and your spirits sink, the seal's round eyes quietly say: It's okay, let's try just once more."},"ICON-2451":{"nm":"Lyric Breath-Mark Pin","on":"pin","de":"Where in the lyrics to breathe—this pin tells you first. Poke it at the end of a line, and that spot becomes the song's gentle rest. To sing freely, even a sentence needs one space to catch its breath."},"ICON-2452":{"nm":"Diction-Practice Chin Rest","on":"rest","de":"Just propping the chin up a little, and the pronunciation about to scatter finds its place. Clear speech isn't the mouth's work alone—it's built by chin, throat, and breath together. This little rest quietly aids that tricky balance."},"ICON-2453":{"nm":"Vowel Mouth-Shape Stand","on":"vowel mouth-shape stand","de":"Ah, eh, ee, oh, oo—a frame that sets up, just as they are, the paths these five vowels take out of the mouth. Set it quietly beside the mirror and shape the skeleton of sound each day. Any song's frame begins, in the end, from these five vowels."},"ICON-2454":{"nm":"Tongue-Twister Card","on":"card","de":"A card so tangling that, reading it, your tongue trips and laughter finally bursts out. It's truly okay to get it wrong—getting it wrong is the practice itself. Each time you get past this mischievous sentence, one more sound wakes up crisp and clear."},"ICON-2455":{"nm":"Lip-Loosening Plug","on":"lip-loosening plug","de":"A warm-up that flutters the lips to wake a stiff mouth. Bite the plug and let the air out long, and the sleeping lips loosen up soft. The smallest, kindest warm-up to open the first phrase gently."},"ICON-2456":{"nm":"Lyric-Section Rubber Band","on":"band","de":"Wrap a rubber band to mark the section that keeps tripping you up. Each time you see that spot on your wrist, today's mountain to climb comes to mind. The harder the measure, the more often you look at it, the longer you hold it in your heart."},"ICON-2457":{"nm":"Neck-Warming Scarf Loop","on":"loop","de":"So the throat won't go hoarse in the dawn air of changing seasons, the scarf is hung firmly on the loop. Only from a warmly wrapped throat does a clear sound finally unwind. Protecting the voice always starts with caring for the throat first."},"ICON-2458":{"nm":"Vocal-Cord Vibration Roller Tip","on":"vocal-cord vibration roller tip","de":"When the roller tip slowly rolls along the side of the neck, the vocal cords sleeping all night quietly awaken. A light vibration loosens the stiff tension, and the hesitant first note softens. A touch that warms the body before singing."},"ICON-2459":{"nm":"Humming Warm-Up Cup Coaster","on":"coaster","de":"Lips closed, humming softly, cradle a steaming warm cup in both hands and the throat warms too. A low hum spreads in rounds across the coaster. A song begins like this, from one sip of lukewarm warmth."},"ICON-2460":{"nm":"Throat-Candy Storage Capsule","on":"throat-candy storage capsule","de":"For days when the throat sinks scratchy and rough, candies are quietly gathered inside the capsule. Roll one in your mouth right before going on stage, and cooling mint clears the blocked throat. A bit of comfort for emergencies, kept in a little case all your own."},"ICON-2461":{"nm":"Steam Throat-Compress Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Wrap the pouch, finely soaked with warm steam, around your neck, and the spots gone stiff from long practice melt away softly. With the cozy warmth of a freshly heated towel, it gently offers a beat of rest to tired, sunken vocal cords."},"ICON-2462":{"nm":"Vocal-Rest Hourglass","on":"hourglass","de":"The quiet promise to not speak today is counted out softly by slender grains. Closing the mouth a while and sparing the voice. That quiet time, which is also the best care of all, flows slowly here."},"ICON-2463":{"nm":"Warm-Up Lip-Trill Plug","on":"warm-up lip-trill plug","de":"A lip trill that rides up and down the notes while the lips flutter lightly. Bite the plug gently and the unruly trembling settles into something far more even. A palm-sized little tool that gently fastens the first button of vocalizing."},"ICON-2464":{"nm":"Throat-Moisture Spray Cap","on":"cap","de":"So the throat won't dry out on a parched stage, press the cap and spray a fine mist. Take one deep breath of the moistened air, and the parched voice regains its clear sheen once more."},"ICON-2465":{"nm":"Vocal-Loosening Vibration Ball","on":"vocal-loosening vibration ball","de":"Hold the finely trembling ball still in your palm, and that vibration rises gently up the arm to the throat. A round, kind warm-up friend that softly shakes awake the vocal organs gone hard with tension."},"ICON-2466":{"nm":"Formation Spot Marker","on":"formation spot marker","de":"One little marker stuck into the stage floor. Here is your spot, over there is mine. When many gather to draw a single picture, it quietly holds everyone in place—an unseen promise that no one scatters."},"ICON-2467":{"nm":"Path Arrowhead Chip","on":"chip","de":"An arrowhead-shaped chip points clearly to the direction of the next step. Where to turn, where to stop—the floor tells you first so you don't lose your way. A path is a map the toes have memorized by treading it countless times."},"ICON-2468":{"nm":"Formation Center Pin","on":"pin","de":"The single point that quietly becomes the reference when many gather. Around this pin a circle is drawn round, and the formation opens wide. Even scattered movements find their order with just one center point."},"ICON-2469":{"nm":"Crossing-Point Wedge","on":"wedge","de":"Where two paths meet at one spot, a wedge is driven in firmly. So they won't collide, so they won't cross paths and clash. Even in that breathless, fleeting instant of passing by, no one loses their way."},"ICON-2470":{"nm":"Exit-Direction Flag","on":"flag","de":"When the lingering echo of the last note fades, you slip out quietly toward where the flag points. Leaving mustn't be any more ragged than entering. Even the stage's ending has a direction promised in advance."},"ICON-2471":{"nm":"Spacing Tape-Measure Clip","on":"clip","de":"Grip the end of the tape measure firmly with the clip, and one span, then another, comes out unfailingly exact. Even the spacing between person and person is aligned neatly, as if measured by a ruler. A scene that looks just right is always born from such careful fingertips."},"ICON-2472":{"nm":"Alignment Reference Cord Loop","on":"loop","de":"Hook the cord on the loop and pull it taut in a single line, and that slender line becomes the standard for everyone to stand abreast. A row looks so tidy thanks to this one straight, unseen line."},"ICON-2473":{"nm":"Movement-Path Dotted Piece","on":"movement-path dotted piece","de":"Pieces that quietly draw a path on the floor in a dotted line. Walk along these faint marks and you won't lose your way even in the dark. As you connect dot to dot, scattered footsteps merge into a single flow."},"ICON-2474":{"nm":"Position Floor Tack","on":"position floor tack","de":"A tack pressed into the floor so you won't forget your spot. Even in pitch darkness, the toes feel out that little bump and find it without fail. Only when you stop at exactly that one point does the light finally pour down overhead."},"ICON-2475":{"nm":"Neck-Isolation Focus Band","on":"band","de":"If the chin sways along, the voice trembles and scatters too. To master moving only the neck while the head stays still, you wrap on the band. Behind a movement that looked so free lies this quiet practice of isolation."},"ICON-2476":{"nm":"Shoulder-Fixing Cushion Clip","on":"clip","de":"So the shoulders won't jut up on their own, the cushion is held still with a clip. So the body clearly tells apart where it should sway and where it should stay. A restrained line is always born from such small acts of holding steady."},"ICON-2477":{"nm":"Rib-Sensing Belt Buckle","on":"rib-sensing belt buckle","de":"The belt quietly reads the fine grain of the ribs spreading and drawing back in. Fasten the buckle and the motion of the breath travels clearly to your fingertips. Deep, solid vocalizing comes from this unseen motion of the bones."},"ICON-2478":{"nm":"Hip-Sway Pendulum","on":"hip-sway pendulum","de":"The pendulum swings slowly side to side, quietly telling the rhythm the hips draw out. A palm-sized little weight teaches without words how the body's center shifts its load. That even swaying has a grain to it."},"ICON-2479":{"nm":"Wrist-Rotation Loop","on":"loop","de":"Hook the loop on your wrist and turn slowly inward, then outward, and the joints stiff all night loosen softly. For movement that reaches alive to the fingertips, the wrist must first grow supple. This little rotation opens up a greater expression."},"ICON-2480":{"nm":"Ankle-Resistance Ring Cord","on":"cord","de":"Slip the ring on your ankle and pull the cord, and with each step you take, a gentle resistance catches at your toes. As heavily as you tread, strength quietly builds in the legs. A feather-light jump always stands upon such heavy practice."},"ICON-2481":{"nm":"Core-Focus Sandbag","on":"sandbag","de":"Only after wrapping it around the belly do you finally know where the very center of your body was. While the weight tugs at the shoulders, the wavering center slowly finds its place, and where it's unwrapped, one upright posture remains."},"ICON-2482":{"nm":"Spine-Alignment Bar Cap","on":"cap","de":"When a little cap touches a back that's lived bent all day, it feels like someone is quietly straightening your shoulders. You can get by hunched, but standing straight is a tender skill you have to slowly learn again."},"ICON-2483":{"nm":"Muscle-Relaxing Acupressure Ball","on":"muscle-relaxing acupressure ball","de":"Press hard on a knotted spot and at first it stings, then soon it soothes. Like the warmth of grandmother's hand rubbing your back as a child, to loosen is to ache a little more for a while while staying by your side."},"ICON-2484":{"nm":"Mirror-Angle Adjusting Screw","on":"mirror-angle adjusting screw","de":"Tilt it just a palm's width and the mirror reflects an entirely different face. With one turn of the screw the world leans and rights itself, so it seems even facing yourself needs a quiet act of aiming."},"ICON-2485":{"nm":"Mirror-Fog Wiping Pad","on":"pad","de":"Before a mirror clouded by hot steam, a person briefly loses their own face. One swipe and the face returns. Thanks to this touch that clears the haze, I meet myself again each morning."},"ICON-2486":{"nm":"Camera Tripod Foot Rubber","on":"camera tripod foot rubber","de":"At the tripod's foot tip, one fingernail-sized piece of rubber decides the fate of the shot. Its grip biting hard into the floor stills the shaking, so a steady picture always begins quietly from unseen friction."},"ICON-2487":{"nm":"Angle-Reference Grid Film","on":"angle-reference grid film","de":"The fine grid lines on the film are like training wheels for the eyes. The more composition settles into your hands, the more the lines quietly vanish, leaving only instinct. Traces of learning grow invisible the riper they become."},"ICON-2488":{"nm":"Recording-Start Foot Pedal","on":"pedal","de":"For a person with both hands full of stuff, the last finger was always the toe. Tap it lightly and recording begins—behind the scenes, the housekeeping is handled deftly, right down to the toe."},"ICON-2489":{"nm":"Lighting-Direction Clip","on":"clip","de":"Where the light falls rests in the fingertips of this fingernail-sized clip. The work of shifting a shadow a span and bringing out a contour—over that tiny difference, someone deliberates long and hard."},"ICON-2490":{"nm":"Footage-Comparison Screen","on":"footage-comparison screen","de":"Set yesterday and today side by side, and only then does change speak up. The moment the screen slides down, the distance of time crossed in between is laid out honestly on the display."},"ICON-2491":{"nm":"Remote Wrist Strap","on":"strap","de":"Wind one cord around the wrist and the heart fretting over dropping it eases. A small safety device sets the hand freer instead—a tender paradox where being bound puts the mind at ease."},"ICON-2492":{"nm":"Lens Cap","on":"lens cap","de":"While the camera rests, the lens quietly closes its eye too. In a world where a single speck of dust leaves a scar on the screen, gently covering it is the wish to cherish it for a long time."},"ICON-2493":{"nm":"Lip-Corner Lift Band","on":"band","de":"Lift the corners of the mouth a little and a stiff expression slowly loosens. A smile, in the end, is muscle too—at first you borrow the tool's strength, and one morning you smile bright by your own."},"ICON-2494":{"nm":"Cheek-Muscle Massage Roll","on":"cheek-muscle massage roll","de":"Slowly roll out the inside of the cheek and words flow far more smoothly. A quiet preparation that gently wakes the face before singing. Warm up the expression too, and it grows warmer."},"ICON-2495":{"nm":"Smile-Angle Gauge","on":"gauge","de":"The camera knows that even a smile has its right angle. Measuring this way and that with the gauge, you finally realize—the prettiest smile blooms from a sincerity that can't be measured at all."},"ICON-2496":{"nm":"Eyebrow-Movement Clip","on":"clip","de":"Move an eyebrow by even 1 millimeter and the whole grain of the heart changes. A clip that quietly holds the smallest part of an expression—acting is the work of fingertips taming such fine detail."},"ICON-2497":{"nm":"Cheekbone-Lift Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"Lift the cheekbones a little and stick it on, and a spot where light lingers appears on the face. The dimension made by one fingernail-sized sticker—stage makeup hides unseen secrets like this."},"ICON-2498":{"nm":"Wink-Cover Eye Patch","on":"wink-cover eye patch","de":"Cover one eye and the heart gathers wholly into the one that remains. Wink practice is, in the end, learning how to gracefully hide half. There are expressions that grow clearer for what's been covered."},"ICON-2499":{"nm":"Mouth-Shape Mold Clip","on":"clip","de":"Ga, gya, geo... fit your mouth shape to the mold and the blurry pronunciation grows crisp. That each vowel is a posture of the face, you slowly carve into your body before the mirror."},"ICON-2500":{"nm":"Expression Warm-Up Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"Right before going on stage, a warm pouch that gently heats the face. Just as cold hands stiffen a performance, so does the expression. A little truth from backstage: even a smile needs preheating."},"ICON-2501":{"nm":"Forehead-Smoothing Band","on":"band","de":"Wrap the band around the forehead and the deeply set furrows quietly smooth out. An object that rests, for a while, the wrinkles carved by worry. Beneath a smoothed forehead, a person looks a little younger."},"ICON-2502":{"nm":"Script-Turning Thimble","on":"thimble","de":"A little thimble worn on the fingertip that turns the pages. The rhythm of turning a thick script page by page becomes, before you know it, the beat of the story. Even reading carries a fond little habit of the hand."},"ICON-2503":{"nm":"Emotion-Coloring Flag","on":"flag","de":"Joy is yellow, sorrow is blue. Color in your heart and raise a flag, and the unseen emotion takes shape, fluttering in the wind. Feelings, too, can be drawn out by hand like this."},"ICON-2504":{"nm":"Line-Stress Clip","on":"clip","de":"'Put the weight on this word,' the clip quietly tells you. The same line changes its whole meaning with a single stress, so it's a little marker that holds the center of gravity of speech."},"ICON-2505":{"nm":"Reading Comma Block","on":"reading comma block","de":"A block set down to say, 'rest one beat here.' A comma in the lines isn't a halt but a breath drawn in for the next words. The one who rests well, in the end, speaks well."},"ICON-2506":{"nm":"Breath-Mark Clip Band","on":"band","de":"The band rises and falls along the clip, drawing the length of the breath before your eyes. Watching and following the rhythm of breathing in and out—the opening of a song always begins with mastering the breath."},"ICON-2507":{"nm":"Emotion-Dice Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"A die rolls tumbling out of the pouch and decides today's emotion. If joy comes up, try being joyful; if anger, try being angry. Acting practice becomes a game of entrusting the heart to chance."},"ICON-2508":{"nm":"Script-Holder Incline Stand","on":"script-holder incline stand","de":"Set the script on the slanted stand and you needn't bow your head. This little slope, keeping you at eye level, quietly tends to a neck gone stiff from long practice."},"ICON-2509":{"nm":"Whisper Screen","on":"screen","de":"A mark to whisper from here on. Lower your voice behind the screen and the audience, on the contrary, holds its breath and leans in to listen. The stage's tender paradox: the softer you speak, the larger it lands."},"ICON-2510":{"nm":"Role-Swap Token Box","on":"role-swap token box","de":"Flip a token over and the role you play changes. Today the lead, tomorrow a friend who stays by your side. On an island where they grow together, everyone gets their turn to stand center stage."},"ICON-2511":{"nm":"Gaze-Fixing Point Sticker","on":"sticker","de":"Rest your eyes quietly on one little dot beside the camera. The moment a wavering gaze lands in one place, the eyes on screen come clearly alive. A steady gaze begins, in the end, from staying still."},"ICON-2512":{"nm":"Angle-Gauging Triangle Ruler","on":"ruler","de":"When a corner of the screen somehow looks tilted, hold the triangle ruler up and the answer appears. The work of righting what's crooked. Before you trust your eyes, try trusting the ruler for a moment."},"ICON-2513":{"nm":"Lens Eye-Level Rest","on":"rest","de":"Set the lens at a person's eye level and the screen tells fewer lies. Not from above, not from below—only when you face them with the same eyes is an unadorned, true expression captured."},"ICON-2514":{"nm":"Gaze-Guiding Arrow Vane","on":"gaze-guiding arrow vane","de":"The gaze slides along to where the vane points. A little arrow that gently leads the viewer's eyes. A good shot kindly gestures toward where you should look."},"ICON-2515":{"nm":"Filming-Path Floor Chip","on":"chip","de":"Step on one point of a path memorized until it's worn in, and the next spot is right there in hand. The footsteps roaming the stage are an unseen path made by connecting little markers like these, dotted across the floor."},"ICON-2516":{"nm":"Camera-Distance Tape Band","on":"band","de":"Measure the distance between subject and camera with the band. In a world where a hand's span divides far from near, the tape becomes a quiet sentinel guarding the line between blur and clarity."},"ICON-2517":{"nm":"Head-Tilt Guide","on":"head-tilt guide","de":"How far should you tilt your head to look most tender? Follow the guide and you quietly come to know—the angle of a tilt closely resembles, in the end, how far you open your heart."},"ICON-2518":{"nm":"Eye-Contact Hand-Mirror Clip","on":"clip","de":"Set a hand mirror beside the camera with the clip, and you look at your own eyes while meeting yours. A little device that gently lays a bridge of gaze between the me in the mirror and the you on the screen."},"ICON-2519":{"nm":"Filming-Indicator Light","on":"filming-indicator light","de":"When the light comes on, it's the signal that filming is underway. One little lamp gathers the giddy set's tension into one. From the moment the light is on, everyone's breath falls neatly into a single beat."},"ICON-2520":{"nm":"Reaction Bell Button","on":"button","de":"Press the button and a clear bell rings crisp and bright. Like applause bursting out after a good scene, someone's warm word of 'well done' is held inside this little bell."},"ICON-2521":{"nm":"Quick-Reflex Lot Tube","on":"tube","de":"Shake it and the wooden sticks rattle, stirring the mood first. Who opens the stage is decided by one snap of the wrist—the one drawn smiles sheepishly, the rest breathe a sigh of relief. Even sharing luck has its kindly rules."},"ICON-2522":{"nm":"Sound-Effect Shake Bell","on":"bell","de":"Flick your wrist just a little and—jingle—an interjection cuts in. This little bell fills the gap before silence can grow awkward. Counting the beat of laughter, this one's always a step ahead."},"ICON-2523":{"nm":"Surprise-Box Lid","on":"lid","de":"Until it opens, no one can guess what's inside. That's the one and only job this lid takes on. So that screams and laughter burst out together in the instant it jolts ajar, it hangs the thrill on a single hinge."},"ICON-2524":{"nm":"Reaction Folding Fan","on":"reaction folding fan","de":"The snap of opening becomes a reply in itself. The fan ribs fan out the admiration left unsaid. Between the gestures of folding and opening, excitement passes back and forth, and a strand of feeling sways on the breeze."},"ICON-2525":{"nm":"Penalty Roulette Wheel","on":"wheel","de":"No one knows in advance which slot the needle will stop on. The slower the wheel turns, the faster the heart races the other way—click, and today's silly fate is written where it stops. A few seconds where even the trembling is fun."},"ICON-2526":{"nm":"Exclamation Speech-Bubble Board","on":"board","de":"Hold it up high overhead and 'Wow' rises as letters. A single sheet of paper outruns the heart, shouting what the mouth couldn't keep up with. Because even a reaction needs a bit of stage direction."},"ICON-2527":{"nm":"Freeze Hand Flag","on":"flag","de":"The moment the flag goes up, everyone freezes right where they are. A signal that locks even the sound of breathing into a still frame. When it lowers again, the frozen laughter all comes pouring out at once."},"ICON-2528":{"nm":"Silly-Answer Clip Tub","on":"tub","de":"The sillier the answer, the more firmly it's clipped up and hung. When the wrong answers strung on the line sway in the wind, it becomes a stage where the misses are loved more than the right ones. A scene of a day where getting it wrong is just fine."},"ICON-2529":{"nm":"Posture-Correction Backrest Wedge","on":"wedge","de":"The moment you lean your back against it, the hunched spine quietly feels out its own path. One little wedge that holds you up without a word. Good posture, it tells you softly from behind, becomes easy only when someone is there to support it."},"ICON-2530":{"nm":"Pelvis-Alignment Support Block","on":"pelvis-alignment support block","de":"A small firmness propped under the feet when the center of gravity wavers. The body's balance rises, in the end, slowly from the floor. A nameless supporting player that holds up posture from an unseen place."},"ICON-2531":{"nm":"Ab-Tightening Balance Ball","on":"ab-tightening balance ball","de":"Tuck it at the belly and tighten gently, and the scattered center gathers into a single point. The deeper you steady your breath, the firmer the ball grows, and the body reclaims, one breath at a time, the axis it had forgotten."},"ICON-2532":{"nm":"Spine-Curve Check Ruler","on":"ruler","de":"Lay the ruler along the back and the unseen curve shows up on the scale. Standing straight isn't erasing the curve—it's reading even that small bend with tenderness."},"ICON-2533":{"nm":"Shoulder-Stretch Elastic Loop","on":"loop","de":"Hook it over the shoulders and pull slowly, and the cowering chest opens wide. The elastic always whispers, come back to your place, and the back, hunched a day's worth, straightens little by little at that gentle call."},"ICON-2534":{"nm":"Core-Stimulation Sandbag","on":"sandbag","de":"Wrap it around the waist and the heavy grains of sand wake the sleeping core. Even a light movement turns earnest in an instant before this weight. As much as you endure, you grow firmer—each grain quietly tells you so."},"ICON-2535":{"nm":"Tailbone-Support Cushion Tag","on":"tag","de":"A cushion that gently props beneath the tailbone, with a little tag hanging from its end. A device like a tender note, written and stuck on for a day worn out from long sitting: 'You can lean here a while.'"},"ICON-2536":{"nm":"Lumbar-Support Angle Tripod","on":"lumbar-support angle tripod","de":"Bracing on three legs, it quietly holds the angle for the lower back to lean on. A support that slips in to a posture about to collapse. To hold up what's wavering, three points are, surprisingly, enough."},"ICON-2537":{"nm":"Chin-Tuck Posture Clip","on":"clip","de":"Tuck the chin and prop it a little, and the neckline gone awry finds its place. The nagging of a finger-sized clip is somehow tender. How to hold your head straight, this little tool teaches."},"ICON-2538":{"nm":"Footstep Ladder Band","on":"band","de":"The band spread on the floor draws out, in turn, the squares for the feet to step in. Tread honestly square by square and, before you know it, the steps are carved into the body. A path grows clearer the more it's trodden."},"ICON-2539":{"nm":"Direction-Change Cone Chip","on":"chip","de":"Stand it up and it's a little marker that tells you 'turn here.' It gifts a corner to feet that only ever ran straight. Even the path of turning in has a rhythm of its own hidden within."},"ICON-2540":{"nm":"One-Foot-Stand Wobble Board","on":"board","de":"The moment you step up on one foot, the board tilts slightly. Those few seconds straining to overcome the wobble are balance's most honest lesson. The toes fighting not to fall tell the whole story."},"ICON-2541":{"nm":"Reaction-Speed Flash Light","on":"reaction-speed flash light","de":"The instant the signal lights up, hand and eye race to be first. The flashing light gives no room to hesitate. A quick hand always moves half a beat ahead of thought."},"ICON-2542":{"nm":"Zigzag Footstep Marker","on":"zigzag footstep marker","de":"Little dots stuck diagonally on the floor that lead the feet to dance in a zigzag. What's harder than a straight line is always the staggering. Wander along the dots and the quick footwork ripens deftly."},"ICON-2543":{"nm":"Balance Tightrope Flat Bar","on":"bar","de":"Set your feet on the slender bar and the world narrows to a single rope. Like a tightrope walker treading on air, you load your whole focus onto a hand's-width span. Balance, the narrower it gets, grows clearer instead."},"ICON-2544":{"nm":"Agility Rebound-Ball Bracelet","on":"agility rebound-ball bracelet","de":"Wear it on your wrist and a little ball springs back with a rebound. In the instant of throwing and catching, the speed of reaction is carved into the fingertips. Quickness is, in the end, not missing what comes back."},"ICON-2545":{"nm":"Nimble-Foot Hula Ring","on":"nimble-foot hula ring","de":"Hook it on your foot and spin, and the hula ring keeps egging the calf on. The moment you stop it drops, so the foot bobs without rest. While moving as if at play, the footwork ripens nimble and quick."},"ICON-2546":{"nm":"Toe-Center Wooden Top","on":"toe-center wooden top","de":"A top spinning on the palm stops dead the instant it loses its center. Like the childhood days of whipping a top in the yard, balance is something that can only stand by spinning endlessly."},"ICON-2547":{"nm":"Ankle-Protection Cinch Cord","on":"cord","de":"Wrap and cinch the ankle and the wavering footing grows far more sure. The more injury-prone a spot, the more tenderly it must be held. One strand of cord becomes the reassurance of a single step."},"ICON-2548":{"nm":"Knee-Warming Wrap Band","on":"band","de":"Wind it around a cold knee and warmth seeps between the joints. A stiff joint only goes supple once it's warmed. Before moving, the warmest morning greeting you offer your own body."},"ICON-2549":{"nm":"Muscle-Loosening Acupressure Ball","on":"muscle-loosening acupressure ball","de":"Press firmly on a knotted spot and the grains gently soothe the knot. The strange comfort that it loosens as much as it aches. Even the stiffness a hand couldn't reach, this little ball pats down in its place."},"ICON-2550":{"nm":"Warm-Up Order Wheel","on":"wheel","de":"Wake the body from whatever slot the wheel stops on. Neck, shoulders, ankles—leave the order to luck and keep the heart light. When play slips into the warm-up, the stiff body smiles softly first."},"ICON-2551":{"nm":"Joint-Warming Heat Pack","on":"heat pack","de":"Lay a steaming heat pack over your joints and a relief like a warm winter floor spreads through you. It's the time when stiff joints loosen into a drowsy ease. Only once it's warmed does the body slowly ready itself to move."},"ICON-2552":{"nm":"Stretch-Pull Handle Loop","on":"loop","de":"Grip the loop and pull, and stiff muscles lengthen out long. A taut conversation passes between the bracing hand and the unfolding body. The more it stretches, the lighter tomorrow's movements will feel."},"ICON-2553":{"nm":"Sole-Stimulating Nub Board","on":"board","de":"Stand barefoot on the nubs and your sleeping soles wake with a start. Like the bracing prickle of walking a gravel path barefoot, the feel of the ground rises up from your toes."},"ICON-2554":{"nm":"Injury-Note Magnet Pin","on":"pin","de":"Write 'Don't overdo it' and tap it onto the metal sheet. Painful memories fade easily, so you hang it before your eyes with a magnet. Caring for your body, too, begins with a single line of a note."},"ICON-2555":{"nm":"Fascia-Release Knobbed Roller","on":"roller","de":"Roll the knobbed bar slowly and the clinging fascia releases one section at a time. A touch that gently pushes the knots away. A bunched-up day, smoothed out node by node like this, grows much lighter too."},"ICON-2556":{"nm":"Walking-Line Floor Strip","on":"strip","de":"Laid straight on the floor, it gives your feet a single line to follow. Even a scattered gait, set upon this line, soon straightens itself. Draw the path, and feet no longer wander."},"ICON-2557":{"nm":"Shoulder-Level Bar","on":"bar","de":"Laid crosswise on the shoulders, it quietly reveals a balance tilted to one side. Being level always means lowering one side and raising the other. A single bar gently points out a crooked habit."},"ICON-2558":{"nm":"Crown Balance Weight","on":"crown balance weight","de":"To keep the weight on your crown from falling, your whole body must stand straight as a single line. Like the old sight of walking with a water jar balanced on the head, the center is set from the highest point on down."},"ICON-2559":{"nm":"Chin-Angle Rest","on":"rest","de":"Prop your chin gently and the head that keeps dropping recovers its proper angle. A brief rest leaned upon a single support. A straight line is only complete when someone holds it up from below."},"ICON-2560":{"nm":"Stride-Spacing Stake","on":"stride-spacing stake","de":"The stake driven into the floor measures out in advance where your feet should land. One stride, neither too wide nor too narrow—that honest distance. The balance of a walk begins quietly at this small marker."},"ICON-2561":{"nm":"Toe-Direction Wedge","on":"wedge","de":"A hesitant first step—the toes falter first over where to go. When this little wedge sets the direction, the heart leans gently that way too. Choosing your path isn't some grand resolve, but the handspan your toes point toward."},"ICON-2562":{"nm":"Back-Straightening Belt","on":"back-straightening belt","de":"That voice forever saying 'straighten up, straighten up' seems to live on inside this belt. Gently straighten a stooped day, and the weight resting on your shoulders grows oddly a little lighter. One good posture lifts even the heart upright."},"ICON-2563":{"nm":"Weight-Distribution Footplate","on":"plate","de":"Seven on the left foot, three on the right. Where you load the weight decides the balance. The footplate quietly asks—which way are you leaning right now? Standing straight, it turns out, is endless adjustment."},"ICON-2564":{"nm":"Eye-Level Target Pole","on":"pole","de":"The eyes keep dropping to the toes. At those times, a single pole set far off slowly lifts your gaze. Practicing looking far is practicing going far, so the moment you raise your head, even a place that seemed out of reach draws near."},"ICON-2565":{"nm":"Bow-Angle Card Clip","on":"clip","de":"Fifteen degrees, thirty degrees, forty-five degrees. The heart bows as deep as the waist folds. The angle on the card is not just a number, but a small gauge measuring the sincerity offered to another."},"ICON-2566":{"nm":"Hands-Folded Manner Loop","on":"loop","de":"Fold your two hands neatly together and a fluttering heart settles calmly into one place. This little loop kindly catches restless, unsure fingertips and quietly sets the first posture of a greeting."},"ICON-2567":{"nm":"Path-Arrow Magnet","on":"magnet","de":"What lost feet look for first, glancing around, is an arrow. A single direction snapped on by a magnet cuts off the hesitation and gently draws your steps toward where you must go. Even a wandering heart finally finds one direction."},"ICON-2568":{"nm":"Exit-Direction Marker Pin","on":"pin","de":"The way out is harder than the way in. Even in lights-out darkness, this clearly glowing pin quietly points out the final path. That leaving well is also part of the stage—you learn it only at the end."},"ICON-2569":{"nm":"Formal-Bow Order Strip","on":"strip","de":"There was a time when the order of who bowed first and who bowed after was clear. Lower yourself in the sequence written on the strip, and even courtesy gains a grain, and manners gain a flow. It is keeping the order of the heart."},"ICON-2570":{"nm":"Footstep-Align Magnet Chip","on":"chip","de":"If one person falls out of step, the whole line wavers. Like a chip that clicks on when toes are aligned, standing together means gently yielding your stride to the one beside you. Footsteps falling on the same beat are the most reassuring."},"ICON-2571":{"nm":"Stage-Bow Position Horseshoe","on":"stage-bow position horseshoe","de":"Even a single stage bow has a place to stand. Set your feet on the marks spread round like a horseshoe, and a first greeting that kept going wrong from nerves finally finds its shape. Knowing your spot, the trembling settles a little too."},"ICON-2572":{"nm":"Thank-You Gesture Card","on":"card","de":"Gratitude that words couldn't fully hold flows out through the fingertips. Drawing a heart, laying a hand on the chest—each gesture written on the card becomes a translation of the heart set down in motion. Sincerity that longs to reach always has a shape."},"ICON-2573":{"nm":"Queue-Spacing Card Stake","on":"queue-spacing card stake","de":"Even standing in line has a kind courtesy. Like a stake that keeps exactly a handspan from the person ahead, waiting begins with a small consideration not to push one another. Standing a little apart is caring too."},"ICON-2574":{"nm":"Cue-Card Flip Ring","on":"ring","de":"When the next line keeps hovering at your lips, a finger quietly flips a page. The little papers threaded on the ring gently press down the pounding heart and calmly open the box for what to say next. Nervous as you are, the flow doesn't break."},"ICON-2575":{"nm":"Program-Order Hourglass","on":"hourglass","de":"Watch the grains trickling down and the next sequence settles calmly in your mind. Until the last grain falls, this little glass teaches you to read time with your eyes, unhurried."},"ICON-2576":{"nm":"Mic-Hold Practice Rod","on":"rod","de":"Before it's second nature, an empty rod weighs a thousand pounds. The grip angle, the distance from your mouth, the force in your wrist—practice, gripping and releasing countless times, one day suddenly blooms into a single natural motion."},"ICON-2577":{"nm":"Crisp-Diction Tongue Stick","on":"stick","de":"Ga, na, da, ra. Hold the stick in your mouth and roll the sounds until your tongue grows clear. A word that crosses over crisp and clear is like a flower quietly blooming atop hundreds of slurred, mumbled hours."},"ICON-2578":{"nm":"Cue-Sign Hand Flag","on":"flag","de":"Start, stop, rest one beat. A single wordless flag conducts the breath of the stage. From a spot unseen by the audience, a quietly waving hand holds every beat without a gap."},"ICON-2579":{"nm":"Corner-Change Bell","on":"bell","de":"A clear little jingle, and the scene changes. Like the bell-sound that spread through a marketplace at dusk, this small ring lightly carries a hesitant heart over to the next segment. A transition always begins with a sound."},"ICON-2580":{"nm":"Speech-Breath Pendulum","on":"speech-breath pendulum","de":"Breathe in—one, two—and slowly out. Steady your breath with the pendulum swinging left and right, and words that came pouring out too fast soon find their beat again. The pace of speech, it turns out, was the pace of breath."},"ICON-2581":{"nm":"Script Folding Board","on":"board","de":"In a single fold-and-open, the whole day's order is held intact. The moment you spread the well-worn board, a mind muddled over what to bring up first calmly lines itself up. One unfolding sets the day in order."},"ICON-2582":{"nm":"Breath-Rhythm Hourglass","on":"hourglass","de":"Inhale three, hold four, exhale six. As the sand flows, your breath quietly flows along with it. Counting each breath one by one is the oldest, kindest way of slowly tending to a busy you."},"ICON-2583":{"nm":"Meditation Cushion Tassel","on":"meditation cushion tassel","de":"The tassel hung from the cushion's edge sways gently with no wind at all. Sit cross-legged, and the stillness of an old soul calming the heart on a wooden porch comes softly to your side, lingers a while, and goes."},"ICON-2584":{"nm":"Breath-Steadying Hand Chime","on":"breath-steadying hand chime","de":"When a single breeze passes, a clear sound quietly sings. Hung like a wind chime at the eaves, it drops one cool, refreshing drop over a heart roiling in confusion. Even sound has the power to cool you down."},"ICON-2585":{"nm":"Incense-Smoke Catch Plate","on":"plate","de":"The smoke left from burning incense settles slowly onto the plate. Like the scent that rose before the table on a holiday morning, a single wisp of smoke gently calms the unsettled air and fills the room with quiet."},"ICON-2586":{"nm":"Inhale-Exhale Swing Weight","on":"inhale-exhale swing weight","de":"My breath rides on a single weight that rises slowly and sinks again. Floating up as I inhale, settling down as I exhale—on a day the body forgets how to breathe, this little clock teaches it all over from the start."},"ICON-2587":{"nm":"Meditation Bell Striker","on":"meditation bell striker","de":"Strike the bell once, gently, and the resonance spreads out long. Like the wind-chime sound ringing through a mountain temple, simply listening in stillness until that ring vanishes entirely into the air rinses one corner of the heart clean."},"ICON-2588":{"nm":"Breath-Path Guide Feather","on":"breath-path guide feather","de":"Hold the feather still before your nose and the breath-path you couldn't see finally becomes visible. A faint sway means you're breathing well; stillness means you've held it too long. The lightest thing is sometimes the most honest guide."},"ICON-2589":{"nm":"Mind-Settling Pebble","on":"mind-settling pebble","de":"The pebble cupped in your palm is cool and smooth. Like a stone long rolled by a riverbank until it surrendered all its edges, keep fiddling with it at your fingertips and the sharp parts of a roiling heart wear gradually round."},"ICON-2590":{"nm":"Nose-Breath Temperature Clip","on":"clip","de":"The temperature at your nose tip quietly tells the depth of your breath. The clip silently reads the air coming in cool and going out warm, showing you clearly the breathing you usually never even feel. Breath, too, has an expression."},"ICON-2591":{"nm":"Mood-Weather Sticker Board","on":"board","de":"Is my heart clear today, or cloudy? The moment you pick a small sticker and tap it onto the board, a mood hard to put into words becomes a kind of weather and takes on a clear shape. The heart needs a forecast too."},"ICON-2592":{"nm":"Emotion-Color Hand Stamp","on":"emotion-color hand stamp","de":"Joy is yellow, sorrow is blue. Pick a color and press it firmly onto paper, and the heart's hue is left as a mark. Even a feeling too vague to name, the color comes first and gently recognizes it for you."},"ICON-2593":{"nm":"Today's-Heart Petal Chip","on":"chip","de":"Lay today's whole heart gently upon a single petal. Like azaleas drifting on a spring day, one chip light and tender asks softly, at the end of a fading day, how you've been."},"ICON-2594":{"nm":"Cheer Speech-Bubble Magnet","on":"magnet","de":"The words you want to say keep hovering at your lips. The moment you tap on the speech-bubble magnet, a word of encouragement you couldn't voice aloud quietly reaches someone's weary day. That is how the heart is conveyed."},"ICON-2595":{"nm":"Inner-Heart Envelope Seal","on":"inner-heart envelope seal","de":"Words you couldn't bring out are tucked neatly into an envelope and sealed. Like an old soul sealing a letter with paste at the fingertips, a single seal keeps the inner heart safe. Quietly awaiting the day to take it out and unfold it."},"ICON-2596":{"nm":"Emotion-Temperature Flower Bud","on":"emotion-temperature flower bud","de":"A closed bud, meeting warmth, opens one careful layer at a time. Blooming as the heart's temperature rises—how warmed I've been today, this flower knows before words do. Spring comes to the heart too."},"ICON-2597":{"nm":"Self-Praise Hand Mirror Strap","on":"strap","de":"Lift the mirror and meet your own eyes reflected there. What the little face hung on the strap shows is not your face, but yesterday's you, who deserves a word for enduring well. Comfort was never far away."},"ICON-2598":{"nm":"Mood-Face Stamp Set","on":"mood-face stamp set","de":"A bright smile, brimming tears, a pouting sulk. Press the expression stamps firmly to write the heart's diary. On a day too overwhelming to put into words, a little face speaks the day's mood quietly in my place."},"ICON-2599":{"nm":"Emotion-Tangle Sorting Loop","on":"loop","de":"However tangled the skein, unravel it carefully strand by strand and it returns to a single thread in the end. Hang muddled, stifling emotions on the loop one by one, and even a heart you couldn't make sense of finds a slender thread to follow."},"ICON-2600":{"nm":"Sleep Sachet Cord","on":"cord","de":"From the sachet hung at the pillowside, a faint scent of herbs gently spreads. Like the smell of grandmother tucking fragrance deep in the wardrobe, as you finger the cord, the tension strung tight all day slips off to sleep."},"ICON-2601":{"nm":"Sleep-Order Flip Board","on":"board","de":"A night when you tossed and only fell asleep at dawn. Gently flip the lying posture, and yesterday's tossing slips over into this morning's freshness. Resting is practice too, this little board says without a word."},"ICON-2602":{"nm":"Pillowside Moonlight Hanger","on":"pillowside moonlight hanger","de":"Hang a sliver of light that came through the curtain gap at the pillowside. A faint river flows over the sleeping face, and even a trainee's nights, when darkness frightened her, softened at last. It was the first small comfort she ever knew."},"ICON-2603":{"nm":"Condition Flower-Bud Chip","on":"chip","de":"Today's condition is closed like a flower bud. Tap the chip and it slowly opens—whether you slept well or not, the body knows first. Even that hesitation before it fully blooms is quietly lovely."},"ICON-2604":{"nm":"Bedtime-Lamp Wick Cap","on":"bedtime-lamp wick cap","de":"\"Don't turn off the light.\" For the youngest, afraid of the dark, someone gently set a cap over the wick. Not too bright, not too dim, a small and tender promise to keep watch only until sleep comes."},"ICON-2605":{"nm":"Morning-Wake Sunflower Pin","on":"pin","de":"Pin it at your bedside and it turns its head gently, like a sunflower, toward the first ray of sun. Even on days you don't want to rise, there's a reason the light is calling, and it carries the morning off in one direction."},"ICON-2606":{"nm":"Sleep-Herb Pillow Brush","on":"brush","de":"Dab lavender and chamomile on the brush tip and sweep it once over the pillow. As the scent seeps into the pillowcase, a day's worth of tension slowly unwinds down from your shoulders. Good sleep begins with this small fragrance."},"ICON-2607":{"nm":"Bedding-Corner Clip","on":"clip","de":"By dawn, your toes keep escaping out from under the blanket. Pin the corner snugly with the clip, and the warmth can't run away all night. It's a small fastening tucked in place of a 'sleep tight.'"},"ICON-2608":{"nm":"Condition-Pebble Basket","on":"basket","de":"One good thing a day, one palm-sized pebble. The heavier the stones gather in the basket, the more reassured the heart grows. Gathering ordinary moments into your hand—this is how happiness has always been counted."},"ICON-2609":{"nm":"Resolve-Star Gathering Jar","on":"resolve-star gathering jar","de":"Every night, shape today's resolve into a star and drop it into the jar. When it brims full, the jar becomes a little night sky. The once-empty mouth knows: promises shine only when you gather them up."},"ICON-2610":{"nm":"Small-Reward Candy Hanger","on":"small-reward candy hanger","de":"One candy you offer yourself at the end of a weary day. The moment you pull one from the hanger and pop it in your mouth, it's all right even if no one notices. A small reward is the most honest cheer."},"ICON-2611":{"nm":"Done-Today Stamp Mold","on":"done-today stamp mold","de":"Ink it and press firmly into the notebook. \"Done today.\" A day done well and a day merely endured fill one box just the same. Every day need not be perfect; you only must not stop pressing the stamp."},"ICON-2612":{"nm":"Cheer-Flag Holder Base","on":"base","de":"Plant it firmly in the ground, and the harder the wind blows, the more powerfully the flag flutters. Even what sways needs a hand to hold it up. The heart that cheers for someone braces from below like this."},"ICON-2613":{"nm":"Goal-Seed Planting Pot","on":"goal-seed planting pot","de":"A goal isn't recited in words but buried in soil. As you plant a seed, water it, and wait, impatience slowly turns into roots. What grows inside the pot is not only the sprout."},"ICON-2614":{"nm":"Praise-Sticker Board","on":"board","de":"A sticker for each thing done well. The more colorfully the board fills, the more the days carelessly let slip come back to life in color. As children, we knew: praise grows more vivid the more you stick it up."},"ICON-2615":{"nm":"Resolve-Ribbon Tying Loop","on":"loop","de":"A hand threading the ribbon through the loop and knotting it. Firm so it won't come undone, but not too tight. A resolve is just like this knot—pull it too tight and it snaps, leave it too loose and it slips quietly away."},"ICON-2616":{"nm":"Small-Achievement Seashell Chip","on":"chip","de":"Write a small achievement on a seashell picked up at the shore. Like a fragment that came this far, shaved and smoothed by waves, your day too has rolled long and now gleams glossy. All that endures time comes to shine."},"ICON-2617":{"nm":"Reward-Medal Hanging Hook","on":"hook","de":"A medal hard-won is hung not in a drawer but at eye level. The weight on the hook squares your shoulders each morning. A reward isn't meant to be hidden but hung there to be looked upon."},"ICON-2618":{"nm":"Monsoon-Umbrella Drip Cup","on":"cup","de":"Monsoon rain trickles down the umbrella's tip. Set a cup beneath it and the entryway stays dry. You can't stop what pours down, but you can decide where it lands."},"ICON-2619":{"nm":"Heat-Cooling Cold Pack","on":"pack","de":"Backstage in midsummer, a cold pack pressed lightly to the nape. The flushed, rising heat settles a beat. \"Take a breather.\" A hand that looks after me before the heat does is reassuring."},"ICON-2620":{"nm":"Fan-Blade Fixing Clip","on":"clip","de":"Even fiercely spinning blades come to a quiet stop with a single clip. The stronger the wind, the more you need something to hold it firmly. Fast-spinning things become safe by who holds them still."},"ICON-2621":{"nm":"Wet-Shoe Drying Rod","on":"rod","de":"Rain-soaked shoes leave even the heart damp by morning. Slip the rod inside and by morning they're dry enough to wear again. What's wet isn't to be thrown away but carefully dried."},"ICON-2622":{"nm":"Boot Mud-Scraper Plate","on":"plate","de":"Boots caked with paddy-field mud. Only after scrubbing them clean on the plate do you step up onto the floor. Leaving the outside mire at the door before coming in—an old courtesy that keeps a home tidy."},"ICON-2623":{"nm":"Summer Cool-Tile Footplate","on":"summer cool-tile footplate","de":"Bare feet know first. Press your soles to the tile laid on the summer floor and the midday heat fades in a handful of cool. Even one small chill makes a long season bearable."},"ICON-2624":{"nm":"Rain-Block Threshold Strip","on":"strip","de":"Just a strip set on the threshold, and the rain can't spill in any longer. A slender line dividing inside from out. A place worth protecting suits a snug boundary better than some grand wall."},"ICON-2625":{"nm":"Mosquito-Coil Holder Plate","on":"plate","de":"On a summer night, set the mosquito coil on its holder and an acrid yet familiar smoke rises. Like the incense circling smaller and smaller, the night, too, slowly deepens. It's the scent of those days counting stars on the wooden bench."},"ICON-2626":{"nm":"Heat Cool-Sleeve Loop","on":"loop","de":"Cover your arms, stung by sun, with a sleeve. Fasten it snugly to your shirt cuff with the loop and even midday work grows bearable. Coolness is the small kindness of shading a handspan where it touches."},"ICON-2627":{"nm":"Leaf-Sweeping Hand Broom","on":"leaf-sweeping hand broom","de":"Sweep the fallen leaves filling the yard into a pile with the hand broom. A whole season rustles underfoot. Tidying something is also seeing off, with care, what must be let go."},"ICON-2628":{"nm":"Ventilation-Window Prop Rod","on":"rod","de":"Wedge a rod into a stuffy room and hold the window cracked. The autumn breeze slips in and carries off the stale air. Ventilation is the small breathing-hole that gently trades what's pooled inside for the outside."},"ICON-2629":{"nm":"Acorn-Pouch Stopper","on":"acorn-pouch stopper","de":"Like a squirrel, fill the pouch with acorns and plug the mouth with the stopper. Tight, so none roll out. The wish to guard what's been gathered is the old instinct of small things wintering through."},"ICON-2630":{"nm":"Autumn-Bedding Dust Beater","on":"autumn-bedding dust beater","de":"Hang out the bedding used all summer in the yard and beat it briskly with the swatter. The smell of sunshine spreads through the dust. You must beat out the old season to lay the new one over you—the wrist remembers it first."},"ICON-2631":{"nm":"Window-Gap Draft Cord","on":"cord","de":"Block the cold draft seeping through the window gap snugly with a single cord. One slender line guards the room's warmth to the last. A great cold always begins at a small gap—winter preparation knows it."},"ICON-2632":{"nm":"Leaf-Strainer Cover","on":"leaf-strainer cover","de":"A strainer laid over the gutter. It filters the leaves out cleanly and lets only the water flow. To flow unblocked, you must decide what to pass and what to hold back, say the autumn eaves."},"ICON-2633":{"nm":"Dried-Grass Bundle Clip","on":"clip","de":"Fasten a bundle of bone-dry grass snugly with the clip. A hand binding scattering things into one. Even where summer's green has all drained away, gather it up and its usefulness remains intact."},"ICON-2634":{"nm":"Autumn-Wind Temperature Swayer","on":"autumn-wind temperature swayer","de":"When the wind blows, the swayer sways. By the width of its sway you gauge how deep autumn has grown today. Temperature isn't a number; it reaches your hand first as something gently swaying."},"ICON-2635":{"nm":"Coat-Pocket Hand-Warmer Holder","on":"coat-pocket hand-warmer holder","de":"\"Cold hands.\" The hand-warmer holder tucked in your coat pocket gently warms chilled fingers. The heart that reckons with someone's cold first is always sitting quietly inside a pocket."},"ICON-2636":{"nm":"Window-Condensation Drip Ledge","on":"window-condensation drip ledge","de":"The ledge quietly catches the tears the winter window shed all night. A small waterway made by the temperature gap between inside and out. Where the difference is great, much flows—the dawn window shows it every day."},"ICON-2637":{"nm":"Stove-Fire Guard Screen","on":"stove-fire guard screen","de":"Set a guard screen before the blazing stove. Warmth up close, danger just a handspan away. Keeping the fire near without getting burned is the most basic distance of caring for someone."},"ICON-2638":{"nm":"Winter-Bedding Hold-Down Clip","on":"clip","de":"When the thick winter quilt keeps sliding off, the clip presses it down and holds its place. Heavy warmth has to be held firmly to earn its keep. The snugness of a winter night is guarded this neatly."},"ICON-2639":{"nm":"Frost-Scraping Spatula","on":"frost-scraping spatula","de":"Scrape away the frost blooming white on the dawn windshield with the spatula. The blurred view clears line by line. Even what's frozen can be scraped off in the end, the fingertips of a winter morning tell you."},"ICON-2640":{"nm":"Hot-Water Bottle Cap Cozy","on":"hot-water bottle cap cozy","de":"Slip a cozy over the bottle filled with hot water. So it won't cool overnight, wrapping the warmth in one more layer. The way to hold warmth long is, in the end, to embrace it carefully with something."},"ICON-2641":{"nm":"Draft-Paper Press Rod","on":"rod","de":"The knife-edge wind that burrowed through the door gap falters the moment it meets you. A single rod pressing down the hem of the paper screen. The room's warmth finally guards its own kin—winter is warmed by such a small stubbornness."},"ICON-2642":{"nm":"Foot-Warmer Holder Plate","on":"plate","de":"The round plate set under the foot-warmer. It takes all the heat alone and leaves not a single scorch on the floor. When someone's toes are warmed drowsy, my own share of the day quietly ends."},"ICON-2643":{"nm":"Condensation-Wipe Cloth Loop","on":"loop","de":"So the cloth that wiped the droplets on the dawn window won't lose its place, a single loop hangs on the wall and waits. More than soaking through, waiting dry again for tomorrow morning is the true heart of absorption."},"ICON-2644":{"nm":"Winter-Glove Drying Hanger","on":"winter-glove drying hanger","de":"Gloves done with a snowball fight spread their fingers wide beside the radiator. The sight of them hung on the hanger, steaming faintly. At the end of an afternoon with a red nose, it's winter's most peaceful laundry."},"ICON-2645":{"nm":"Duster Feather Refill","on":"duster feather refill","de":"When the feathers wear out, swap in fresh ones. The moment the dust-chasing tip turns downy again. That cleaning tools have their changing seasons too—this little refill gently lets you know in your palm."},"ICON-2646":{"nm":"Rag-Wringing Handle","on":"handle","de":"A handle fitted on to spare your wrists. One twist and the rag spits out the water on its own. Goodbye to the days of straining over the washboard. In housekeeping, a handful of know-how becomes kindness itself."},"ICON-2647":{"nm":"Floor-Brush Replacement Head","on":"head","de":"When the floor brush wears out, swap in just the head. The handle stays, and so does the weight your hand knows. In things used long dwells a small, firm tenderness that won't throw the whole away."},"ICON-2648":{"nm":"Lint-Roller Refill Core","on":"lint-roller refill core","de":"After tearing off the roller's last sheet, something feels oddly empty. That's when you fit in a fresh core. It's the dogged, kind promise of a refill to see even a single sweater pill through to the end."},"ICON-2649":{"nm":"Corner-Dust Scraper","on":"corner-dust scraper","de":"Even in corners the broom can't reach, dust quietly sets up house. Poking the corner clean with a slender tip. The heart that tends even to the unseen is the very pride of housekeeping."},"ICON-2650":{"nm":"Broom-Cleaning Comb","on":"comb","de":"Even a sweeping broom needs a resting touch. Comb out the hair tangled among the bristles with this comb, and the broom, its bout of work done, readies itself at last for the next sweep."},"ICON-2651":{"nm":"Floor-Grain Wax Pad","on":"pad","de":"Lay a coat of wax along the grain of the floor and the wood slowly recalls a sheen it long forgot. Soles almost slipping, almost not—an afternoon when the whole house smiles, glossy and content."},"ICON-2652":{"nm":"Door-Gap Dust Sweeper","on":"door-gap dust sweeper","de":"I hunt the dust that lives in door gaps. Whatever slips in and piles up each time the door swings, I sweep it up with my thin body. The narrower and deeper the gap, the surer my turn comes round."},"ICON-2653":{"nm":"Doormat Dust-Mesh Cap","on":"cap","de":"So the dust the entry mat swallowed won't leak back out, a mesh cap stands as the last gatekeeper. The dust that muddy shoes brought in from the outside world is let only this far and no further."},"ICON-2654":{"nm":"Faucet Limescale Brush","on":"brush","de":"The little brush circles round and strips the limescale settled quietly on the faucet's neck. The more a spot is touched by hands each day, the more it must shine. That's the bathroom courtesy this little brush keeps."},"ICON-2655":{"nm":"Drain Hair-Mesh Cap","on":"cap","de":"I quietly catch the hair drifting down toward the drain. Heading off the small disaster of a clog with a single cap. The day of a round, sturdy little hero flows by quietly, always underfoot."},"ICON-2656":{"nm":"Tile-Grout Scraper","on":"tile-grout scraper","de":"The grout smeared dark between the white tiles—scrape that aged time gently away with the tip. When the narrow seams come clean, the whole bathroom catches its breath light, like new."},"ICON-2657":{"nm":"Showerhead Cleaning Pin","on":"pin","de":"Poke open the clogged showerhead holes with the pin tip, and water that had only dribbled forever pours out fresh again. The triumphant sound of morning water, as one small clog comes undone."},"ICON-2658":{"nm":"Toilet-Brush Storage Cup","on":"cup","de":"A toilet brush, too, is only hygienic once it rests in a dry spot. Set neatly in a little cup that catches the drips, it waits its next turn. A tool's dignity shows not in its use but in its keeping."},"ICON-2659":{"nm":"Mold-Wiping Sponge","on":"mold-wiping sponge","de":"The mold spreading black on the tile corners—to that stubborn guest, the sponge politely suggests an exit. Once wiped clean in a single pass, the bathroom returns bright to its original white."},"ICON-2660":{"nm":"Mirror Fog Squeegee","on":"mirror fog squeegee","de":"Before a mirror gone hazy after a shower, the squeegee draws one line and your clear face returns. The moment you meet again the day's expression that hid a while behind the fog."},"ICON-2661":{"nm":"Bathroom-Slipper Hanger","on":"bathroom-slipper hanger","de":"Hang wet slippers upside down and the water trickles off, the insides drying snug. So the next person's feet won't be cold. A little hanger's care is always a step ahead, gone out to meet you."},"ICON-2662":{"nm":"Nail-Brush Case","on":"case","de":"Even the small brush that scrubs under the nails has a home of its own. Tucked snugly into the case, it dries dry and free of moisture, awaiting the next washbasin. Tidiness always begins quietly with putting things away."},"ICON-2663":{"nm":"Toothbrush Sanitizer-Cup Lid","on":"lid","de":"Even a toothbrush, meeting your mouth twice a day, needs a small sanctuary. The moment the sanitizer-cup lid clicks shut, one measure of cleanliness is quietly guarded from the damp drifting through the bathroom."},"ICON-2664":{"nm":"Cotton-Swab Travel Capsule","on":"cotton-swab travel capsule","de":"So the cotton swabs in your travel bag won't snap or scatter, a capsule holds them snugly in its embrace. The smaller a thing, the more you must pack it ahead—so you won't be caught off guard on an unfamiliar road."},"ICON-2665":{"nm":"Breath-Check Mini Board","on":"board","de":"Breathe 'haa' onto your palm and hold it to the mini board, and your breath touches it and fogs it milky white. The cutest proof that I'm alive here on a cold day, this little board records without a word."},"ICON-2666":{"nm":"Ear-Pick Storage Home","on":"ear-pick storage home","de":"When an ear-pick travels in a bag, its tip dulls easily. So a tiny home was made for it. Inside, where the tip won't be hurt even carried about, the delicate tool sleeps soundly."},"ICON-2667":{"nm":"Handkerchief Folding Clip","on":"clip","de":"The clip softly bites a handkerchief folded neatly at its four corners, keeping it from coming undone in the bag. A single sheet folded tidy offers quiet grace whenever you draw it out."},"ICON-2668":{"nm":"Bandage Case","on":"case","de":"On a day you scrape your knee, open the case and bandages of every kind line up waiting for you. The tenderness of making a fuss even over a small wound. A first-aid kit should always be kept close at hand."},"ICON-2669":{"nm":"Palm Fingerprint Wiper","on":"palm fingerprint wiper","de":"Wipe the fingerprints left on glass and the traces of hesitant hands vanish. A palm-sized little magic, where the world beyond the window, blurred at every touch, turns clear again."},"ICON-2670":{"nm":"Recycling-Sort Divider","on":"recycling-sort divider","de":"Paper this side, cans that side. A single divider splits a fate that nearly got jumbled. Recycling is, in the end, the heart of sorting with care, and this snug compartment draws that first line clearly."},"ICON-2671":{"nm":"Sticker-Peeling Spade","on":"sticker-peeling spade","de":"Even a stickily clinging sticker quietly surrenders before me. Slip the flat spade-edge gently under a corner and it peels off clean without a single mark—a triumphant farewell."},"ICON-2672":{"nm":"Masking-Tape Cutting Teeth","on":"masking-tape cutting teeth","de":"No need to hunt for scissors just to use masking tape. Hold it to the teeth and pull, and it snaps off clean along the grain. The little, nimble best friend most dear to a deco-loving fingertip."},"ICON-2673":{"nm":"Corner-Bonding Edge Bracket","on":"corner-bonding edge bracket","de":"A small bracket that holds a lifting corner firmly from the inside. From an unseen spot, it silently keeps the angle true. Behind things straight on the surface, there is usually a hidden brace like this."},"ICON-2674":{"nm":"Seal-Sheet Protector Tube","on":"tube","de":"So precious seal-sheets won't crease or grow damp, they sleep in the tube alongside protective film. Beside the joy of collecting, there always follows the care of guarding it gently."},"ICON-2675":{"nm":"Ink-Stamp Cleaning Brush","on":"brush","de":"The brush sweeps gently along the grain through the ink-soaked stamp, stripping off the old color. A small, diligent touch that cleans ahead so the next impression you press comes out crisp."},"ICON-2676":{"nm":"Clear-Refill Holder Wing","on":"clear-refill holder wing","de":"So binder refills won't slip and slide out, the wings grip both sides tight. Thanks to each sheet staying in its place, the fingertip turning pages is never thrown into disorder."},"ICON-2677":{"nm":"Deco-Piece Storage Scoop","on":"deco-piece storage scoop","de":"Scoop up the tiny scattered deco pieces in a single sweep with the little scoop. When the bother of picking them up one by one is gone, the time spent crafting something with care grows all the more joyful."},"ICON-2678":{"nm":"Bookmark-Tassel Fastener","on":"bookmark-tassel fastener","de":"So the tassel at the bookmark's end won't come loose, the fastener binds it snugly. Even a guide back to a half-read page rests easier when its own trim is kept neat."},"ICON-2679":{"nm":"Deco-Pen Cap Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clip that pinches the cap tight so the deco-pen tip won't dry out. It prevents the mishap of a pen left open going stiff, so the color always flows out moist as the first time."},"ICON-2680":{"nm":"Screwdriver Bit Insert Tip","on":"screwdriver bit insert tip","de":"Leave the screwdriver handle as is and just swap in the tip at the end. Phillips or flathead, no trouble. The cleverness of handling many jobs with one is packed snugly into this little bit tip."},"ICON-2681":{"nm":"Sandpaper Corner Wrap","on":"sandpaper corner wrap","de":"Wrap the rough surface round to grip and your palm becomes a tool. Swish, swish—with each push along the grain, the prickly corner rounds, and the final smoothness is always recognized by a person's fingertips."},"ICON-2682":{"nm":"Screw-Sorting Funnel","on":"screw-sorting funnel","de":"Scattered screws pass through the narrow neck and gather, rolling, into one place. The sound of little things that rolled about the desk finding their place—it feels as if even a cluttered heart is set neatly in order."},"ICON-2683":{"nm":"Tape-Measure End Hook","on":"tape-measure end hook","de":"The hook at the tape measure's end is the second hand of one who works alone. Catch it on a corner and the tape won't waver, and your hand—and heart—grow as honest as the length you've measured."},"ICON-2684":{"nm":"Spanner Handle Cover","on":"spanner handle cover","de":"A layer wrapped over the cold metal handle. The moment you grip it, soft warmth meets your hand instead of a chill. A tool stays by you longer when it considers the one who holds it first."},"ICON-2685":{"nm":"Awl-Tip Protective Cone","on":"awl-tip protective cone","de":"A small cone is fitted over each sharp tip. The relief of fishing through a drawer without being pricked—the sharper the thing, the more carefully you wrap it, and no one gets hurt."},"ICON-2686":{"nm":"Wire-Insulation Stripping Blade","on":"wire-insulation stripping blade","de":"Strip only the insulation thin and leave the inner wire unharmed. The moment you gently unwind one layer and a copper strand glints into view, a good blade knows exactly where to stop."},"ICON-2687":{"nm":"Level Bubble-Window Wiper","on":"level bubble-window wiper","de":"Only when the single bubble stops dead center is it truly level. Wiping the little window clear resembles the quiet preparation of steadying your breath before drawing a line."},"ICON-2688":{"nm":"Nailing Finger-Guard Sleeve","on":"nailing finger-guard sleeve","de":"A small sleeve that wraps snug around the finger holding the nail. Strike without fear, it says, for even if the hammer slips it's all right—it's snugly ready to take the blow in your finger's place."},"ICON-2689":{"nm":"Feeding-Bowl Anti-Slip Mat","on":"mat","de":"A layer of rubber bracing the bowl so it won't skid on the floor. With no bowl running off mid-feast, the calm of a meal begins from a spot that doesn't waver."},"ICON-2690":{"nm":"Feed-Scoop Hanger","on":"feed-scoop hanger","de":"Hang the feed-scooping ladle on the wall to dry lightly. A small order that greets your hand from the same spot each mealtime—having a mouth to look after is a tender thing like this."},"ICON-2691":{"nm":"Water-Bowl Overflow Plate","on":"plate","de":"It quietly catches the mouthful that sloshed over the rim of the water bowl. Thanks to the wide plate that holds it ahead of time lest the floor get wet, the ground underfoot always stays dry and snug."},"ICON-2692":{"nm":"Treat-Dispensing Tongs","on":"tongs","de":"Tongs that pick up exactly one treat and offer it. Even before a little mouth waiting with its nose pushed forward, there's a tender fingertip to sharing that never falls into disorder."},"ICON-2693":{"nm":"Feed-Bag Roll Clip","on":"clip","de":"A small clamp that rolls up and bites the mouth of an opened feed bag. With one click shut, the damp is blocked, and tomorrow morning's crisp handful is kept perfectly intact."},"ICON-2694":{"nm":"Water-Bottle Spout Stopper","on":"water-bottle spout stopper","de":"A stopper that fits snug onto the water-bottle spout. Drip—the dripping water stops and the rim dries. What's well stopped won't leak, and stays pooled clear for a long time."},"ICON-2695":{"nm":"Feed-Measure Marked Cup","on":"cup","de":"Measure out exactly one cup along the marking. Neither too much nor too little—in the hand that gauges today's meal fairly, a little family member's day is portioned just right."},"ICON-2696":{"nm":"Spill-Feed Mat Rim","on":"spill-feed mat rim","de":"An edge that keeps spilled feed from crossing off the mat. A single rim raised just slightly gathers up, snug, the crumbs that nearly scattered."},"ICON-2697":{"nm":"Stacked-Bowl Separator Ring","on":"ring","de":"A small ring that gently parts two nested bowls. The hand that strained over them stuck fast grows light. Separating well, it turns out, is a tender care too."},"ICON-2698":{"nm":"Yard-Ball Rolling Funnel","on":"yard-ball rolling funnel","de":"A funnel that gathers into one place the balls that rolled off across the yard. After an evening of romping, the hand that draws in what's scattered here and there comes naturally to mind."},"ICON-2699":{"nm":"Fence-Post Cap","on":"cap","de":"Fit a round cap over each fence post. So the tips won't split in wind and rain, a heart that tends and covers even the smallest thing has soaked through the whole yard."},"ICON-2700":{"nm":"Play-Tunnel Folding Hook","on":"hook","de":"A hook to fold the well-played tunnel up neatly and hang it. Tuck away a day caked in dirt and hang it well, and play well put away never fails to promise tomorrow."},"ICON-2701":{"nm":"Pull-Cord Grip Cushion","on":"grip cushion","de":"A cushion that softly wraps the pull-cord handle. No matter how hard you yank, your palm never gets scraped. The longer you hold on, the easier it feels on the hand, all thanks to someone's small thoughtfulness."},"ICON-2702":{"nm":"Yard Shade-Cloth Clasp","on":"clasp","de":"A clasp that holds the shade cloth firmly over the yard. Even midday coolness must be pinned down to stay. Beneath the shade the clasp holds steady, a lazy afternoon stretches out and rests at length."},"ICON-2703":{"nm":"Digging Spade Blade Cover","on":"spade blade cover","de":"A cover gently slipped over the blade of a digging spade. Let it rest after a full day's work, and it stays sharp, ready to meet next spring's soil again."},"ICON-2704":{"nm":"Ball-Rolling Ramp","on":"board","de":"A single sloped board down which a ball rolls with a merry whirr. Following the slight incline, the ball dashes off in delight. One small tilt makes for a whole day of fun."},"ICON-2705":{"nm":"Fence-Gate Latch Ring","on":"ring","de":"A latch ring that locks the fence gate. The little click of it shutting sets the heart at ease. One snugly closed gate keeps a small yard safe as a world all its own."},"ICON-2706":{"nm":"Play-Bell Hanging Cord","on":"cord","de":"Sway the bell-hung cord and a clear sound spreads. Jingle, jingle, a once-quiet room wakes up, and at one small ring every heart pricks up its ears."},"ICON-2707":{"nm":"Flowerpot Saucer Drip Tray","on":"flowerpot saucer drip tray","de":"A dish that quietly catches the water seeping from beneath a flowerpot. It holds the overflow so the windowsill stays dry. Even when care brims over, there must be a place to catch it."},"ICON-2708":{"nm":"Seedling Transplant Trowel","on":"seedling transplant trowel","de":"A small trowel for gently tucking tender seedlings into the soil. Settling each sprout into place, careful fingertip by careful fingertip, even a palm-sized garden lifts its head into green spring."},"ICON-2709":{"nm":"Garden Row Marker Pin","on":"pin","de":"A marker pin you write on and plant in each row to note what's sown. On soil where not a sprout has shown yet, one little name tag quietly remembers what will grow."},"ICON-2710":{"nm":"Watering Can Spout Mesh","on":"watering can spout mesh","de":"A fine mesh fitted over a watering can's spout. Water that once poured in a single stream scatters into many strands like a gentle drizzle. Only a soft flow keeps tender leaves from harm."},"ICON-2711":{"nm":"Plant-Stake Fastening Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clip that gently binds a wobbling stem to its stake. A borrowed support, just until the still-tender thing can stand on its own. Growing needs a prop like this."},"ICON-2712":{"nm":"Seed Packet Seal Clip","on":"clip","de":"A clip that firmly bites a leftover seed packet shut. Snap it closed and not a single grain escapes. A small promise to next spring rests in this one little pinch."},"ICON-2713":{"nm":"Soil & Fertilizer Measuring Scoop","on":"soil and fertilizer measuring scoop","de":"A small scoop for portioning out just the right amount of soil and fertilizer. One measure, neither too much nor too little, and on that precisely gauged dose, the soil finally does its work."},"ICON-2714":{"nm":"Flowerpot Hanger Hook","on":"hook","de":"A hanger hook that lightly suspends a flowerpot in midair. Lifted up, the greenery sits a hand's breadth closer to sun and wind. A little garden floats up by the window."},"ICON-2715":{"nm":"Sprout-Shielding Cover Mesh","on":"sprout-shielding cover mesh","de":"A cover mesh that gently shields freshly sprouted shoots. Until the still-soft leaves can weather the first chill and the harsh sun, the most tender thing receives care first."},"ICON-2716":{"nm":"Grooming Comb Lint Holder","on":"grooming comb lint holder","de":"A spot to tap loose hair off a comb and hang it tidily. The fluffed-out, emptied comb waits for the next touch. Neatness always begins with the small habit of caring for one's tools."},"ICON-2717":{"nm":"Foot-Wash Basin Anti-Slip Ring","on":"ring","de":"A ring that props up a foot-washing basin so it won't slip. With the basin holding still beneath splashing little paws, neither the washing hands nor the washed heart ever wobble."},"ICON-2718":{"nm":"Walk-Leash Hanging Hook","on":"walk-leash hanging hook","de":"A single hook to hang the walking leash by the entryway. In its spot beside the door, the readiness to set out always waits. The moment you take down the leash, an eager set of footsteps comes along too."},"ICON-2719":{"nm":"Nail-Trim Guard Cap","on":"cap","de":"A guard cap that protects the tender quick while trimming nails. With a safe boundary drawn at just this far, even the hand holding the clippers stays calm and steady."},"ICON-2720":{"nm":"Bathwater Temperature Strip","on":"strip","de":"A strip that floats in the bathwater to show its temperature. The old habit of dipping the back of a hand to gauge the right warmth is now translated clearly into a single line of color, bobbing on the surface."},"ICON-2721":{"nm":"Shed-Hair Lint Roller","on":"shed-hair lint roller","de":"A single white hair on black clothes looms largest right before going onstage. Following the rolling sound, a day's worth of fuzz transfers neatly onto the sticky paper. Tidiness is completed like this, one strip at a time, as much as you peel away."},"ICON-2722":{"nm":"Walk Poop-Bag Clip","on":"clip","de":"At the end of a walk comes a tender moment of bending down. With a bag clipped to the tongs, your hands stay clean and your heart stays light. Walking together includes the small courtesy of cleaning up behind, and this clip knows it first."},"ICON-2723":{"nm":"Doormat Edge Trim","on":"doormat edge trim","de":"The edge of the mat by the door is the first welcome a foot ever touches. When damp toes pause here once, the floor inside stays dry. The lowest of places, silently wiping and welcoming everyone who enters."},"ICON-2724":{"nm":"Grooming Bell Knot Cord","on":"cord","de":"Even hanging a single bell has its order. Wrap the cord twice and pass it through once, and a clear sound trickles along with every step. Grooming, in the end, is the heart that never skips this little finishing touch."},"ICON-2725":{"nm":"Folding Umbrella Drip Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"In a lobby after the rain, droplets dot the floor from the tip of a folded umbrella. When one pouch quietly catches them, no one's footing turns slippery. Consideration usually stands by like this, without a sound."},"ICON-2726":{"nm":"Outing Bag Hook Clip","on":"clip","de":"A bag hung on a chair keeps sliding off. Clip it once with a hook clip and both hands go free, with no worry of it dropping. The ease of an outing begins the moment you can forget your load for a while."},"ICON-2727":{"nm":"Hand-Warmer Cloth Pouch","on":"pouch","de":"In a windswept alley, the cloth sack in your pocket gently passes warmth into your palm. A soft single layer wrapping the hot thing, warming it just right. Winter's tenderness is always passed along through a single sheet of cloth."},"ICON-2728":{"nm":"Pocket Mirror Folding Stand","on":"stand","de":"Unfold it and the little mirror tilts itself to just the right angle. So you can face yourself without holding it, the stand stands in your place. Even in the brief moment of fixing your look, a dependable supporting player is at your side."},"ICON-2729":{"nm":"Travel Wet-Wipe Lid Cap","on":"cap","de":"The first wet wipe was always halfway to drying out. Click the cap shut and moisture stays right down to the last sheet. Keeping it usable to the very end, the secret to long-lasting housekeeping hides in little things like this."},"ICON-2730":{"nm":"Travel Comb Tooth Cover","on":"cover","de":"Comb teeth in a bag would often scratch the other belongings. Slip on the tooth cover and the comb is safe and the things packed with it unharmed. Anyone who's looked after their things knows one small layer of protection keeps both sides safe."},"ICON-2731":{"nm":"Drawer Divider Clip","on":"clip","de":"Every time you opened the drawer, the jumbled contents spilled out like a sigh. Divide the space with a single clip and the little things finally found their own zones. A tidy drawer quietly changes the mood of every morning."},"ICON-2732":{"nm":"Coin Display Stand","on":"stand","de":"Stand a single old coin upright and it becomes a tiny exhibition all on its own. The stand props it at a slant, showing the face's design clearly. Lifting time worn by many hands to eye level, here the joy of collecting deepens."},"ICON-2733":{"nm":"Earphone Winding Loop","on":"loop","de":"There were mornings half lost to untangling earphone cords. Wind them neatly around the loop and next time they come out smooth. A small bit of tidying becomes a quiet gift slipped to tomorrow's self."},"ICON-2734":{"nm":"Charging-Cable Wall Hook","on":"charging-cable wall hook","de":"A charging cable trailing on the floor kept getting stepped on. Stick one hook to the wall to hang it, and the desk feels far roomier. Taming clutter isn't some grand thing, just a little spot the size of a single nail."},"ICON-2735":{"nm":"Remote-Control Upright Holder","on":"remote-control upright holder","de":"The remote that kept vanishing into the couch cushions finally has a home to return to. Stand it in the holder and there's no more hunting for it, no more sitting on it. Having a place of its own is a small comfort, even for an object."},"ICON-2736":{"nm":"Eyeglass Temple Hook Clip","on":"clip","de":"Glasses set down always slid off somewhere on their own. Hook the temple lightly onto the clip and the lenses never touch the floor. The wish to greet tomorrow scratch-free is held in this little hook."},"ICON-2737":{"nm":"Key-Ring Sorting Clip","on":"clip","de":"The heavier the bunch of keys grows, the blurrier which one opens which door. Bind them with a sorting clip and your fingertips alone know their match. A silent guide that quietly brings order to the doors you open and close each day."},"ICON-2738":{"nm":"Memo-Paper Upright Clip","on":"clip","de":"A jotted memo would often topple over on the desk. When the clip holds the paper upright, the words meet your eye head-on. A way to let the one line you mustn't forget live where you'll always see it."},"ICON-2739":{"nm":"Pen-Tip Upright Stand","on":"stand","de":"How many times did you bend down to pick up a pen that rolled off? Stand it tip-down in the stand and the distance to the next line shrinks by a hand's breadth. A little waiting post, always awake beside the one who writes."},"ICON-2740":{"nm":"Hourglass Flip Stand","on":"stand","de":"Once an hourglass has run out, someone must flip it for it to live again. The stand catches that last grain's moment and turns it smoothly upright. The touch that turns time back to the start rests here, on a little piece of wood."},"ICON-2741":{"nm":"Buttered Baked Potato","on":"buttered baked potato","de":"Butter melts slowly over a potato baked in its skin. As the golden streaks seep in with the steam, the fluffy flesh quietly takes in the savory richness. The very moment an earthy root vegetable grows warmest."},"ICON-2742":{"nm":"Buttered Grilled Corn","on":"buttered grilled corn","de":"Rows of yellow kernels pop and crackle on the grill. A pat of butter glides over them and a sweet aroma rises in a rush. The sweetness of a summer field is carried whole into a single bite."},"ICON-2743":{"nm":"Waffle","on":"waffle","de":"It waits quietly for syrup to pool in each little grid square. Crisp outside, fluffy within, bite in and warm steam slips out. The square pockets seem like little dishes that portion out small joys."},"ICON-2744":{"nm":"Pancakes","on":"pancakes","de":"You remember the smell of batter puffing golden on the pan. Butter slides and melts away over a stack of round, layered cakes. A soft plateful, quietly granted only on an unhurried morning."},"ICON-2745":{"nm":"Chocolate","on":"chocolate","de":"Hold a piece in your mouth and it slowly unravels at the touch of your warmth. The sweetness blooming after the bitterness gently loosens the heart's tension. A small brown piece of comfort, pulled from a pocket on a weary day."},"ICON-2746":{"nm":"Strawberry Cake","on":"strawberry cake","de":"Red strawberries perch atop white whipped cream, announcing spring first. As the fork cuts through the soft layer, a tart-sweet scent gently rises. The kind protagonist set at the center of the table on a day worth celebrating."},"ICON-2747":{"nm":"Cheesecake","on":"cheesecake","de":"A weighty slice crumbles richly on the tongue. The salty finish takes the hand of the sweetness, calling for just one more bite again and again. A dessert quietly savored by those who love a dense, deep richness."},"ICON-2748":{"nm":"Banana Cookies","on":"banana cookies","de":"The scent of mashed banana bakes to gold inside the oven. Bite into one and a soft sweetness spreads through your whole mouth. The warm moment a ripe fruit is reborn as a cookie."},"ICON-2749":{"nm":"Chocolate Chip Cookies","on":"chocolate chip cookies","de":"The chocolate chips in the dough melt richly as they bake. Break one open while warm and a deep brown smudges your fingertips. The kind of piece that makes an afternoon a little kinder, with a glass of milk."},"ICON-2750":{"nm":"Cacao Nib Cookies","on":"cacao nib cookies","de":"Finely crushed cacao bits crunch here and there in the dough. An unsweet, deep bitterness quietly soothes a grown-up's palate. A slightly serious cookie that holds the raw aroma just as it was before processing."},"ICON-2751":{"nm":"Cheese Toast","on":"cheese toast","de":"Cheese stretches in long threads over golden-toasted bread. The crisp outside and the savory inside fold together in one bite. The simplest and most tender of meals, filling a late morning with heartiness."},"ICON-2752":{"nm":"Sandwich","on":"sandwich","de":"Between two slices of bread, a day's worth of care is packed layer by layer. Bite in and the stacked flavors all greet you at once. A little table on your palm, ready to carry off anywhere."},"ICON-2753":{"nm":"French Toast","on":"french toast","de":"Bread soaked through in egg batter cooks to gold on the pan. The corners, puffing up with the scent of butter, crisp up first. Drizzle a line of syrup and even plain bread becomes a holiday luxury."},"ICON-2754":{"nm":"Mushroom Ramen","on":"mushroom ramen","de":"The deep aroma of mushrooms rises with the steam over the boiling broth. Lift out a chewy cap and an earthy sweetness spreads through your mouth. A slightly special bowl that fills you with fragrance before the noodles."},"ICON-2755":{"nm":"Stir-Fried Ramen","on":"stir-fried ramen","de":"Spicy seasoning glazes the broth-free noodles with a glossy sheen. Lift them with chopsticks and a savory smoky aroma drifts through the steam. The most dependable friend when you crave a quick, bold meal."},"ICON-2756":{"nm":"Cheese Ramen","on":"cheese ramen","de":"Lay a slice of cheese on the hot noodles and it slowly collapses and melts in. Spicy broth meets soft savoriness and the sharp edges round out. A bowl that fits perfectly on a night you want to gently soothe the spice."},"ICON-2757":{"nm":"Curry Ramen","on":"curry ramen","de":"A rich curry aroma winds around the noodles, sending up yellow steam. Slurp in a mouthful and a warm spiciness heats you from within. A playful variation on familiar broth, with a touch of the unfamiliar."},"ICON-2758":{"nm":"Seafood Ramen","on":"seafood ramen","de":"Shrimp and clams bob plump over a broth full of the sea. A clean yet deep savoriness seeps in between every strand of noodle. A small bit of magic that brings a whiff of the shore into one bowl without going far."},"ICON-2759":{"nm":"Pickled-Radish Gimbap","on":"pickled-radish gimbap","de":"With yellow pickled radish at the center, rice grains gather round in a circle, and a single sheet of seaweed binds them all warmly into one roll. The most honest of meals, born on the cutting board at dawn on a picnic day."},"ICON-2760":{"nm":"Tuna Gimbap","on":"tuna gimbap","de":"The moment a spoonful of mayo-tossed tuna seeps among the rice, a meal turns plenty warm even beneath the late-night convenience-store lights. The comfort busy hands reach for most often."},"ICON-2761":{"nm":"Fruit Salad","on":"fruit salad","de":"Colors gathered from the season meet for the first time in one bowl. Only after being cut and placed together does fruit reveal how red and green and yellow can blend without quarrel."},"ICON-2762":{"nm":"Chicken Salad","on":"chicken salad","de":"Lightly grilled chicken breast laid neatly over green leafy vegetables. On the table of someone preparing for tomorrow's stage, there is always a tidy plate like this."},"ICON-2763":{"nm":"Tomato Cucumber Salad","on":"tomato cucumber salad","de":"Ripe tomatoes and crisp cucumber tossed up tart and fresh. At a midday thick with cicada song, one chopstickful cools summer down a beat."},"ICON-2764":{"nm":"Lettuce Salad","on":"lettuce salad","de":"Rinse leaves just picked from the garden in cold water and your fingertips wake with a chill. The moment the most ordinary vegetable takes the greenest, freshest seat at the table."},"ICON-2765":{"nm":"Corn Salad","on":"corn salad","de":"Each time a sweet kernel bursts with a pop, a sun-drenched midsummer field unfurls before your eyes. Even in a salad bowl, yellow corn never forgets its own sunshine."},"ICON-2766":{"nm":"Coleslaw","on":"coleslaw","de":"When shredded cabbage takes in the sweet-and-sour dressing, its crispness softens into something gentler. The virtue of a side dish, doing its part without vying for the spotlight beside any main."},"ICON-2767":{"nm":"Lime Shrimp Salad","on":"lime shrimp salad","de":"Squeeze in a little lime and the sweetness of the shrimp wakes all the more clearly. One sour drop breathes life into the whole plate, a small but decisive final touch."},"ICON-2768":{"nm":"Hamburg Steak","on":"hamburg steak","de":"A thickly shaped patty of seasoned meat cooks to gold on a heated iron plate. Juices well up the moment the knife touches, the most enduringly loved meal somewhere between home cooking and Western fare."},"ICON-2769":{"nm":"Pizza","on":"pizza","de":"Gathered round in a group, you pass that one cheese-stretching bite from hand to hand. Only when a round pie is shared into slices together does a gathering truly become a gathering."},"ICON-2770":{"nm":"Mushroom Cream Pasta","on":"mushroom cream pasta","de":"The deep earthiness of mushrooms and the softness of cream embrace every single strand of noodle. On an evening of gentle rainfall, the rich aroma slowly spreads to the very bottom of the plate."},"ICON-2771":{"nm":"Shrimp Pasta","on":"shrimp pasta","de":"Plump shrimp, lightly sautéed in olive oil, tossed together with the noodles. When the sea's saltiness meets the noodles' mildness, an uneventful evening turns a little special."},"ICON-2772":{"nm":"Oil Pasta","on":"oil pasta","de":"Garlic, oil, and noodles, just three things and no more. Aglio e olio quietly proves, without a hint of excess, that some flavors grow clearer the more you take away."},"ICON-2773":{"nm":"Clam Pasta","on":"clam pasta","de":"The broth the clams release as they open their shells seeps deep into every strand. The scent of a sip of white wine lingers over the plate, long as a spring day."},"ICON-2774":{"nm":"Cream Pasta","on":"cream pasta","de":"When rich cream gently embraces the noodles, a corner of your heart goes cozy from the very first bite. The comfort that softness offers, growing deeper the colder and windier the day."},"ICON-2775":{"nm":"Tomato Pasta","on":"tomato pasta","de":"Long-simmered tomato sauce spreads red over the noodles. When sweetness and sourness reduce slowly to find their balance at last, the most basic plate is the most reassuring."},"ICON-2776":{"nm":"Omurice","on":"omurice","de":"A soft layer of egg gently blankets warm rice like a quilt. Write even a word of a name in ketchup, and that day's table becomes a little letter handed to you by someone."},"ICON-2777":{"nm":"Grilled Salmon","on":"grilled salmon","de":"Cook it slowly before the flame until the skin turns crisp. A wisp of steam rises as the pink flesh flakes apart along its grain, the wait is always repaid honestly by salmon."},"ICON-2778":{"nm":"Bruschetta","on":"bruschetta","de":"Heap diced tomato and basil onto crisply toasted bread. The lightness of picking one up and biting in opens a gathering's first greeting warmly."},"ICON-2779":{"nm":"Mango Smoothie","on":"mango smoothie","de":"Ripe mango finely blended and chilled together with ice. As beads of condensation form on the yellow glass, a languid midsummer afternoon rises right up to the tip of the straw."},"ICON-2780":{"nm":"Lemonade","on":"lemonade","de":"Fresh-squeezed lemon, sugar, and cold water, shaken together right in the cup. As the yellow tartness slides coolly down your throat, even the rampaging heat surrenders for a moment."},"ICON-2781":{"nm":"Strawberry Milk","on":"strawberry milk","de":"Stir mashed strawberries into milk and a pink cloud slowly settles within the cup. The flutter at the fingertips of flinging open the fridge as a child is held whole in one cup."},"ICON-2782":{"nm":"Banana Milk","on":"banana milk","de":"A drink that is already a whole bygone era just in the round shape of its little jug. The yellow memory of poking in a straw on a bathhouse bench comes warmly back to life with every sip."},"ICON-2783":{"nm":"Blueberry Milk","on":"blueberry milk","de":"Crush in the purple berries and the white milk tints to a faint sky blue. That small handful of fruit turns a whole cup over to an entirely new color."},"ICON-2784":{"nm":"Fruit Juice","on":"fruit juice","de":"Squeeze several fruits in together and it becomes a flavor no single name can call. A little chorus of sweetnesses, blending and swelling all the more lush."},"ICON-2785":{"nm":"Cocoa","on":"cocoa","de":"By a window where snow falls, you cup a warm mug gently in both hands. A brown cup with steam curling up warms you slowly, from fingertips to heart."},"ICON-2786":{"nm":"Coffee","on":"coffee","de":"It's always this one cup that turns on the lights of the dawn practice room. As the bitter aroma quietly pushes back the drowsiness, another day's stage begins, softly, just like that."},"ICON-2787":{"nm":"Salmon Sushi","on":"salmon sushi","de":"Press the rice in your hand, gauging that subtle line between firm and soft. The moment a thin slice of salmon lies gently atop it, a single bite becomes a small completion of care."},"ICON-2788":{"nm":"Sweet Pumpkin Porridge","on":"sweet pumpkin porridge","de":"Boil yellow pumpkin until tender and mash it down smooth. With every spoonful, autumn sunlight melts warmly in your mouth. The porridge that comes to mind first whenever you're ill."},"ICON-2789":{"nm":"Fish Curry","on":"fish curry","de":"Fish flesh, lightly simmered in spices, breaks apart softly within the curry. Add the sea's texture to a familiar bowl and an ordinary evening sets off on a journey a hand's breadth farther."},"ICON-2790":{"nm":"Fried Shrimp","on":"fried shrimp","de":"The brief instant of gripping the tail, coating it in batter, and dropping it into boiling oil is where it's won or lost. Shrimp robed in gold shine brightest eaten before the crispness has cooled."},"ICON-2791":{"nm":"Fried Squid","on":"fried squid","de":"Round rings puff up plump in the hot oil. That bite, chewiness wrapped in crisp, suits the yellow lights of a street-food stall best of all."},"ICON-2792":{"nm":"Grilled Chicken","on":"grilled chicken","de":"Brush on the seasoning and grill it slowly before the flame, and the skin gleams with a glossy sheen. A dish whose flavor turns on a single matter of heat control, the most honest precisely because it's the simplest."},"ICON-2793":{"nm":"Pork Kimchi Stir-Fry","on":"pork kimchi stir-fry","de":"Stir-fry well-fermented kimchi together with pork and the sourness ripens into sweetness. The most dependable partner at a Korean table, calling forth a bowl of white rice all on its own."},"ICON-2794":{"nm":"Stir-Fried Pork","on":"stir-fried pork","de":"Stir-fry it fast over high heat to sear the outside crisp. When the savory smell of the oil fills the kitchen, tonight's menu is already settled without another word."},"ICON-2795":{"nm":"Beef Mushroom Stir-Fry","on":"beef mushroom stir-fry","de":"Stir-fry fragrant mushrooms together with beef and each one's flavor grows deeper. A tidy autumn meal where earth and field gently clasp hands on a single plate."},"ICON-2796":{"nm":"Cheese Dak-galbi","on":"cheese dak-galbi","de":"Melt plenty of cheese over spicy dak-galbi and stretch it out in a long pull. Gather a group round a hot iron plate at the center and even the fierce spice unravels into laughter."},"ICON-2797":{"nm":"Kimchi Stew","on":"kimchi stew","de":"The longer kimchi has aged, the deeper and richer the broth it gives. Sit face to face before a bubbling earthenware pot and the word \"family\" warms up all over again."},"ICON-2798":{"nm":"Soybean Paste Stew","on":"soybean paste stew","de":"Stir in savory soybean paste, add tofu and zucchini, and simmer it low and slow. That sound of it bubbling to the very last in the earthenware pot is the surest sign that you've come home."},"ICON-2799":{"nm":"Beef Radish Soup","on":"beef radish soup","de":"A whole half-day spent waiting quietly before a low flame until the radish turns clear. One spoonful of the clear broth touches your lips and recalls the unadorned tables of those years. The plainest things linger longest."},"ICON-2800":{"nm":"Clam Soup","on":"clam soup","de":"The moment the clams open their shells, spring deepens inside the pot. As a handful of sea scent rides up on the steam, a seaside village's dawn kitchen comes into view. The briny sea pools in every parted shell."},"ICON-2801":{"nm":"Candied Sweet Potato","on":"candied sweet potato","de":"Yellow chunks held like a hand-warmer in a paper cup on the way home from school. Bite the golden coating and steam huffs out from within. The sweet-glazed outside and the hot inside, winter at its most tender."},"ICON-2802":{"nm":"Stir-Fried Eggplant","on":"stir-fried eggplant","de":"The instant the purple meets oil and softens loose. The vegetable scolded for being mushy is in truth better than any at taking in seasoning. Bite in and the soft-soaked touch of a cook's hand reaches you first."},"ICON-2803":{"nm":"Braised Potatoes","on":"braised potatoes","de":"An evening when the smell of sweetness spread through the kitchen as the soy sauce reduced. The hand that filled a lunchbox compartment with glossy brown pieces. A care unwritten in any recipe is steeped in each little chunk."},"ICON-2804":{"nm":"Pickled Perilla Leaves","on":"pickled perilla leaves","de":"The act of pickling a whole summer's scent to carry it to a winter table. Peel off one leaf, lay it on rice, and the past season blooms again in your mouth. That year's sunlight sleeps among the layered leaves."},"ICON-2805":{"nm":"Fresh Napa Kimchi","on":"fresh napa kimchi","de":"Hands that couldn't wait for kimjang toss it up by hand that very day. A freshness you can only enjoy the instant the seasoning has just begun soaking into crisp leaves. The green of pre-fermentation is a luxury only for today."},"ICON-2806":{"nm":"Stir-Fried Mushrooms","on":"stir-fried mushrooms","de":"The things that rose quietly in the shade of the woods after the rain cleared. As they fry in perilla oil, the earthy smell turns savory. The more silently a thing grew in the dark, the deeper and richer its aroma."},"ICON-2807":{"nm":"Seasoned Spinach","on":"seasoned spinach","de":"A leafy green that shrinks to a single handful when blanched, tossed and seasoned with your fingertips. That humble little volume is the virtue of a spring herb. One green plate and the table holds a hand's breadth more spring sun."},"ICON-2808":{"nm":"Seasoned Seaweed","on":"seasoned seaweed","de":"Slippery strands fresh-pulled from the sea mingle with a tart chili-vinegar sauce. A briny tingle bursting with each chew. A plate that carries the rolling-wave texture straight into the bowl."},"ICON-2809":{"nm":"Stir-Fried Zucchini","on":"stir-fried zucchini","de":"There's a vegetable that fills with sweetness the older it grows. Slice it thin and stir-fry it with salted shrimp, and even bland zucchini quietly offers up its own sweetness. A yellow that unravels soft in your mouth right to the last."},"ICON-2810":{"nm":"Kimchi Fried Rice","on":"kimchi fried rice","de":"Around the time aged kimchi grows deep, it meets cold rice in one pan. A bowl made heartiest when leftover meets leftover. The most tender salvation under the lights of a late-night studio apartment."},"ICON-2811":{"nm":"Chicken Curry","on":"chicken curry","de":"When the yellow sauce covers white rice, the table brightens up. The first taste of the outside world you grew close to, back when spices felt strange. A Sunday lunch when the chicken came apart soft and fluffy."},"ICON-2812":{"nm":"Fried Rice","on":"fried rice","de":"The odds and ends left at the back of the fridge mingle happily in one pan. A generosity that takes in anything graciously. Gathering the scattered into one, that's where housekeeping begins."},"ICON-2813":{"nm":"Bulgogi Rice Bowl","on":"bulgogi rice bowl","de":"Meat marinated in sweet seasoning slides smoothly over steaming rice. When the star of the company table settles down into a weekday bowl, its specialness grows all the warmer."},"ICON-2814":{"nm":"Bibimbap","on":"bibimbap","de":"Atop fluffy rice, five colors of seasoned vegetables sit round in a circle. In the fingertips that arrange the colors flows an old aesthetic of careful attention. A harmony of flavor completed only once it's all mixed together."},"ICON-2815":{"nm":"Shrimp Fried Rice","on":"shrimp fried rice","de":"Plump shrimp stand out pink among the grains of rice. Fry in a handful of the sea and even an ordinary meal puts on the airs of a feast. The sweetness spreading at that crunchy bite is a welcome thing."},"ICON-2816":{"nm":"Spicy Pork Rice Bowl","on":"spicy pork rice bowl","de":"Pork steeped deep in spicy seasoning meets steaming rice. The bowl that hit the bottom first at lunchtime. A meal's comfort, patting a busy day on the back."},"ICON-2817":{"nm":"Tuna Mayo Rice","on":"tuna mayo rice","de":"One can, a line of mayonnaise, and a warm bowl of rice. The ingredients are spare, but the comfort is plenty. The taste of that night, mixed in secret at a classroom desk after evening study."},"ICON-2818":{"nm":"Curry Rice","on":"curry rice","de":"A thick golden hue fills the plate. The care of long stirring until the potatoes and carrots go fully tender. It calls to mind the closeness of that evening when the whole family peered into the same pot."},"ICON-2819":{"nm":"Seaweed Bibimbap","on":"seaweed bibimbap","de":"Sea-scented strands meet red pepper paste and get mixed round and round. As the slippery, tart texture wraps each grain, the sea a diver held her breath to gather unfurls within one bowl."},"ICON-2820":{"nm":"Grilled Mackerel","on":"grilled mackerel","de":"Its silver back cooks to golden brown on the grill. The hand that boned it and laid the flesh on your rice. In one piece of blue-backed fish is steeped the quiet love that fed and raised you."},"ICON-2821":{"nm":"Potato Pancake","on":"potato pancake","de":"On rainy days, this is what they ground and fried in mountain-village kitchens of Gangwon. Chewy edges and crisp rims live side by side in a single round. The batter that suits the sound of rain on the window best."},"ICON-2822":{"nm":"Kimchi Pancake","on":"kimchi pancake","de":"The moment sour kimchi touches the oiled pan, the whole house fills with a sizzling sound. A golden round that calls for a bowl of makgeolli all on its own. The go-to dish that pairs with the sound of rain off the eaves."},"ICON-2823":{"nm":"Scallion Pancake","on":"scallion pancake","de":"Lay the chives out neatly, pour the batter, and fry it slowly. A single round that wavers between crisp and soft. Just like that fond scene of it sending up steam at a market-day stall."},"ICON-2824":{"nm":"Zucchini Fritters","on":"zucchini fritters","de":"Thinly sliced zucchini coated in batter and fried to gold. The pale-green circles that neatly held one corner of the ancestral rite table. A meticulous formality that comes together only with a lot of careful work."},"ICON-2825":{"nm":"Stir-Fried Squid","on":"stir-fried squid","de":"Legs glazed in red seasoning gleam glossy and slick. Even with beads of sweat dotting your brow from the heat, your chopsticks can't stop. That one plate where sweat and delight tangle together."},"ICON-2826":{"nm":"Tteokbokki","on":"tteokbokki","de":"Rice cakes and fish cake sink deep into red-simmered chili-paste broth. A whole afternoon at the snack shop, where two of you pooled coins to share it, is held inside. A taste of memory that makes your mouth water at the mere name."},"ICON-2827":{"nm":"Fish Cake Soup","on":"fish cake soup","de":"At a street stall where fish cakes ripple in the broth, steam fogs the window milky white. Grip a skewer, catch some broth in a paper cup, and slurp it down, and a biting winter night turns far warmer."},"ICON-2828":{"nm":"Tofu Kimchi","on":"tofu kimchi","de":"Beside soft tofu sits spicily stir-fried kimchi, side by side. Cold and hot, mild and strong, blend together on one plate. A pairing that has long kept watch over grown-ups' nights."},"ICON-2829":{"nm":"Sausage Vegetable Stir-Fry","on":"sausage vegetable stir-fry","de":"Red sausages and vegetables sizzle together in a ketchup hue. The compartment emptied first when you opened a sports-day lunchbox lid. That day's color stays vivid no matter how much time passes."},"ICON-2830":{"nm":"Sweet Potato Latte","on":"sweet potato latte","de":"Finely mashed sweet potato dissolves softly into warm milk. A homegrown sweetness written in Korean on the menu board. A cup whose warmth spreads slowly when you cup it in both hands on a day your fingertips ache with cold."}};
